obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (90988)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90988&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Bharatiya Nagarik`
  line `Suraksha Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Sanhita, other than those relating to Chapters IX, XI and XII thereof, shall`
  line `not apply---`
  line
  line `(a) to the State of Nagaland;`
  line
  line `(b) to the tribal areas,`
  line
  line `but the concerned State Government may, by notification, apply such provisions or any of them`
  line `to the whole or part of the State of Nagaland or such tribal areas, as the case may be, with such`
  line `supplemental, incidental or consequential modifications, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---In this section, "tribal areas" means the territories which immediately before`
  line `the 21st day of January, 1972, were included in the tribal areas of Assam, as referred to in paragraph 20 of`
  line `the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution, other than those within the local limits of the municipality of`
  line Shillong.
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st July, 2024,[ except the provisions of the entry relation to Section 106(2) in the first Schedule], vide notification No.`
  line `S.O. 848(E), dated, 23rd day of February, 2024, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (90989)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90989&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Sanhita, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) “audio-video electronic” means shall include use of any communication device for the purposes`
  line `of video conferencing, recording of processes of identification, search and seizure or evidence,`
  line `transmission of electronic communication and for such other purposes and by such other means as the`
  line `State Government may, by rules provide;`
  line
  line `(b) “bail” means release of a person accused of or suspected of commission of an offence from the`
  line `custody of law upon certain conditions imposed by an officer or Court on execution by such person of`
  line `a bond or a bail bond;`
  line
  line `(c) “bailable offence” means an offence which is shown as bailable in the First Schedule, or which`
  line `is made bailable by any other law for the time being in force; and “non-bailable offence” means any`
  line `other offence;`
  line
  line `(d) “bail bond” means an undertaking for release with surety;`
  line
  line `(e) “bond” means a personal bond or an undertaking for release without surety;`
  line
  line `(f) “charge” includes any head of charge when the charge contains more heads than one;`
  line
  line `(g) “cognizable offence” means an offence for which, and "cognizable case" means a case in which,`
  line `a police officer may, in accordance with the First Schedule or under any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, arrest without warrant;`
  line
  line `(h) “complaint” means any allegation made orally or in writing to a Magistrate, with a view to his`
  line `taking action under this Sanhita, that some person, whether known or unknown, has committed an`
  line `offence, but does not include a police report.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A report made by a police officer in a case which discloses, after investigation, the`
  line `commission of a non-cognizable offence shall be deemed to be a complaint; and the police officermeans of an`
  line `electronic device including a telephone, mobile;`
  line
  line `(i) “electronic communication” means the communication of any written, verbal, pictorial`
  line `information or video content transmitted or transferred (whether from one person to another or from`
  line `one device to another or from a person to a device or from a device to a person) by means of an`
  line `electronic device including a telephone, mobile`
  line
  line `phone, or other wireless telecommunication device, or a computer, or audio-video player or camera`
  line `or any other electronic device or electronic form as may be specified by notification, by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(j) “High Court” means,—`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to any State, the High Court for that State;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a Union territory to which the jurisdiction of the High Court for a State has`
  line `been extended by law, that High Court;`
  line
  line `(iii) in relation to any other Union territory, the highest Court of criminal appeal for that`
  line `territory other than the Supreme Court of India;`
  line
  line `(k) “inquiry” means every inquiry, other than a trial, conducted under this Sanhita by a Magistrate`
  line `or Court;`
  line
  line `(l) “investigation” includes all the proceedings under this Sanhita for the collection of evidence`
  line `conducted by a police officer or by any person (other than a Magistrate) who is authorised by a`
  line `Magistrate in this behalf.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Where any of the provisions of a special Act are inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Sanhita, the provisions of the special Act shall prevail;`
  line
  line `(m) “judicial proceeding” includes any proceeding in the course of which evidence is or may be`
  line `legally taken on oath;`
  line
  line `(n) “local jurisdiction”, in relation to a Court or Magistrate, means the local area within which the`
  line `Court or Magistrate may exercise all or any of its or his powers under this Sanhita and such local area`
  line `may comprise the whole of the State, or any part of the State, as the State Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify;`
  line
  line `(o) “non-cognizable offence” means an offence for which, and “non-cognizable case” means a case`
  line `in which, a police officer has no authority to arrest without warrant;`
  line
  line `(p) “notification” means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(q) “offence” means any act or omission made punishable by any law for the time being in force`
  line `and includes any act in respect of which a complaint may be made under section 20 of the Cattle`
  line `Trespass Act, 1871 (1 of 1871);`
  line
  line `(r) “officer in charge of a police station” includes, when the officer in charge of the police station`
  line `is absent from the station-house or unable from illness or other cause to perform his duties, the police`
  line
  line `officer present at the station-house who is next in rank to such officer and is above the rank of constable`
  line `or, when the State Government so directs, any other police officer so present;`
  line
  line `(s) “place” includes a house, building, tent, vehicle and vessel;`
  line
  line `(t) “police report” means a report forwarded by a police officer to a Magistrate under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 193;`
  line
  line `(u) “police station” means any post or place declared generally or specially by the State`
  line `Government, to be a police station, and includes any local area specified by the State Government in`
  line `this behalf;`
  line
  line `(v) “Public Prosecutor” means any person appointed under section 18, and includes any person`
  line `acting under the directions of a Public Prosecutor;`
  line
  line `(w) “sub-division” means a sub-division of a district;`
  line
  line `(x) “summons-case” means a case relating to an offence, and not being a warrant-case;`
  line
  line `(y) “victim” means a person who has suffered any loss or injury caused by reason of the act or`
  line `omission of the accused person and includes the guardian or legal heir of such victim;`
  line
  line `(z) “warrant-case” means a case relating to an offence punishable with death, imprisonment for life`
  line `or imprisonment for a term exceeding two years.`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Information`
  line `Technology Act, 2000 (2 of 2000) and the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 shall have the meanings`
  line `respectively assigned to them in that Act and Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (90990)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Construction of references.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90990&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless the context otherwise requires, any reference in any law,`
  line `to a Magistrate without any qualifying words, Magistrate of the first class or a Magistrate of the second`
  line `class shall, in relation to any area, be construed as a reference to a Judicial Magistrate of the first class or`
  line `Judicial Magistrate of the second class, as the case may be, exercising jurisdiction in such area.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, under any law, other than this Sanhita, the functions exercisable by a Magistrate relate to`
  line matters,—
  line
  line `(a) which involve the appreciation or shifting of evidence or the formulation of any decision which`
  line `exposes any person to any punishment or penalty or detention in custody pending investigation, inquiry`
  line `or trial or would have the effect of sending him for trial before any Court, they shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Sanhita, be exercisable by a Judicial Magistrate; or`
  line
  line `(b) which are administrative or executive in nature, such as, the granting of a licence, the suspension`
  line `or cancellation of a licence, sanctioning a prosecution or withdrawing from a prosecution, they shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of clause (a) be exercisable by an Executive Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (90991)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Trial of offences under Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 and other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90991&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) All offences under`
  line `the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 shall be investigated, inquired into, tried, and otherwise dealt with`
  line `according to the provisions hereinafter contained.`
  line
  line `(2) All offences under any other law shall be investigated, inquired into, tried, and otherwise dealt with`
  line `according to the same provisions, but subject to any enactment for the time being in force regulating the`
  line `manner or place of investigating, inquiring into, trying or otherwise dealing with such offences.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (90992)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90992&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Sanhita shall, in the absence of a specific provision to the`
  line `contrary, affect any special or local law for the time being in force, or any special jurisdiction or power`
  line `conferred, or any special form of procedure prescribed, by any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (90993)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Classes of Criminal Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90993&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Besides the High Courts and the Courts constituted under any law,`
  line `other than this Sanhita, there shall be, in every State, the following classes of Criminal Courts, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) Courts of Session;`
  line
  line `(ii) Judicial Magistrates of the first class;`
  line
  line `(iii) Judicial Magistrates of the second class; and`
  line
  line `(iv) Executive Magistrates.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (90994)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Territorial divisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90994&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State shall be a sessions division or shall consist of sessions`
  line `divisions; and every sessions divisions shall, for the purposes of this Sanhita, be a district or consist of`
  line districts.
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, after consultation with the High Court, alter the limits or the number`
  line `of such divisions and districts.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, after consultation with the High Court, divide any district into`
  line `sub-divisions and may alter the limits or the number of such sub-divisions.`
  line
  line `(4) The sessions divisions, districts and sub-divisions existing in a State at the commencement of this`
  line `Sanhita, shall be deemed to have been formed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (90995)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Court of Session.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90995&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall establish a Court of Session for every sessions`
  line division.
  line
  line `(2) Every Court of Session shall be presided over by a Judge, to be appointed by the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The High Court may also appoint Additional Sessions Judges to exercise jurisdiction in a Court of`
  line Session.
  line
  line `(4) The Sessions Judge of one sessions division may be appointed by the High Court to be also an`
  line `Additional Sessions Judge of another division, and in such case, he may sit for the disposal of cases at such`
  line `place or places in the other division as the High Court may direct.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the office of the Sessions Judge is vacant, the High Court may make arrangements for the`
  line `disposal of any urgent application which is, or may be, made or pending before such Court of Session by`
  line `an Additional Sessions Judge or if there be no Additional Sessions Judge, by a Chief Judicial Magistrate,`
  line `in the sessions division; and every such Judge or Magistrate shall have jurisdiction to deal with any such`
  line application.
  line
  line `(6) The Court of Session shall ordinarily hold its sitting at such place or places as the High Court may,`
  line `by notification, specify; but, if, in any particular case, the Court of Session is of opinion that it will tend to`
  line `the general convenience of the parties and witnesses to hold`
  line `its sittings at any other place in the sessions division, it may, with the consent of the prosecution and`
  line `the accused, sit at that place for the disposal of the case or the examination of any witness or witnesses`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(7) The Sessions Judge may, from time to time, make orders consistent with this Sanhita, as to the`
  line `distribution of business among such Additional Sessions Judges.`
  line
  line `(8) The Sessions Judge may also make provision for the disposal of any urgent application, in the event`
  line `of his absence or inability to act, by an Additional Sessions Judge or if there be no Additional Sessions`
  line `Judge, by the Chief Judicial Magistrate, and such Judge or Magistrate shall be deemed to have jurisdiction`
  line `to deal with any such application`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this Sanhita, appointment does not include the first appointment,`
  line `posting or promotion of a person by the Government to any Service, or post in connection with the affairs`
  line `of the Union or of a State, where under any law, such appointment, posting or promotion is required to be`
  line `made by the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (90996)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Courts of Judicial Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90996&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every district there shall be established as many Courts of`
  line `Judicial Magistrates of the first class and of the second class, and at such places, as the State Government`
  line `may, after consultation with the High Court, by notification, specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, after consultation with the High Court, establish, for any local`
  line `area, one or more Special Courts of Judicial Magistrates of the first class or of the second class to try any`
  line `particular case or particular class of cases, and where any such Special Court is established, no other Court`
  line `of Magistrate in the local area shall have jurisdiction to try any case or class of cases for the trial of which`
  line `such Special Court of Judicial Magistrate has been established.`
  line
  line `(2) The presiding officers of such Courts shall be appointed by the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The High Court may, whenever it appears to it to be expedient or necessary, confer the powers of a`
  line `Judicial Magistrate of the first class or of the second class on any member of the Judicial Service of the`
  line `State, functioning as a Judge in a Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (90997)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Chief Judicial Magistrate and Additional Chief Judicial Magistrate, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90997&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every district,`
  line `the High Court shall appoint a Judicial Magistrate of the first class to be the Chief Judicial Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) The High Court may appoint any Judicial Magistrate of the first class to be an Additional Chief`
  line `Judicial magistrate, and such Magistrate shall have all or any of the powers of a Chief Judicial Magistrate`
  line `under this Sanhita or under any other law for the time being in force as the High Court may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) The High Court may designate any Judicial Magistrate of the first class in any sub-division as the`
  line `Sub-divisional Judicial Magistrate and relieve him of the responsibilities specified in this section as`
  line `occasion requires.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the general control of the Chief Judicial Magistrate, every Sub-divisional Judicial`
  line `Magistrate shall also have and exercise, such powers of supervision and control over the work of the Judicial`
  line `Magistrates (other than Additional Chief Judicial Magistrates) in the sub-division as the High Court may,`
  line `by general or special order, specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (90998)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Special Judicial Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90998&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The High Court may, if requested by the Central or State`
  line `Government so to do, confer upon any person who holds or has held any post under the Government, all or any of the powers conferred or conferrable by or under this Sanhita on a Judicial Magistrate of the first class or of the second class, in respect to particular cases or to particular classes of cases, in any local area:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such power shall be conferred on a person unless he possesses such qualification or`
  line `experience in relation to legal affairs as the High Court may, by rules, specify.`
  line
  line `(2) Such Magistrates shall be called Special Judicial Magistrates and shall be appointed for such term,`
  line `not exceeding one year at a time, as the High Court may, by general or special order, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (90999)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Local Jurisdiction of Judicial Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=90999&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the control of the High Court, the`
  line `Chief udicial Magistrate may, from time to time, define the local limits of the areas within which the`
  line `Magistrates appointed under section 9 or under section 11 may exercise all or any of the powers with which`
  line `they may respectively be invested under this Sanhita:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court of Special Judicial Magistrate may hold its sitting at any place within the local`
  line `area for which it is established.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as otherwise provided by such definition, the jurisdiction and powers of every such`
  line `Magistrate shall extend throughout the district`
  line
  line `(3) Where the local jurisdiction of a Magistrate appointed under section 9 or section 11 extends to an`
  line `area beyond the district in which he ordinarily holds Court, any reference in this Sanhita to the Court of`
  line `Session or Chief Judicial Magistrate shall, in relation to such Magistrate, throughout the area within his`
  line `local jurisdiction, be construed, unless the context otherwise requires, as a reference to the Court of Session`
  line `or Chief Judicial Magistrate, as the case may be, exercising jurisdiction in relation to the said district.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (91000)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Subordination of Judicial Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91000&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Chief Judicial Magistrate shall be subordinate`
  line `to the Sessions Judge; and every other Judicial Magistrate shall, subject to the general control of the`
  line `Sessions Judge, be subordinate to the Chief Judicial Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Judicial Magistrate may, from time to time, make rules or give special orders, consistent`
  line `with this Sanhita, as to the distribution of business among the Judicial Magistrates subordinate to him`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (91001)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Executive Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91001&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every district, the State Government may appoint as many persons`
  line `as itthinks fit to be Executive Magistrates and shall appoint one of them to be the District Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may appoint any Executive Magistrate to be an Additional District`
  line `Magistrate, and such Magistrate shall have such of the powers of a District Magistrate under this Sanhita`
  line `or under any other law for the time being in force as may be directed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever, in consequence of the office of a District Magistrate becoming vacant, any officer`
  line `succeeds temporarily to the executive administration of the district, such officer shall, pending the orders`
  line `of the State Government, exercise all the powers and perform all the duties respectively conferred and`
  line `imposed by this Sanhita on the District Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may place an Executive Magistrate in charge of a sub-division and may`
  line `relieve him of the charge as occasion requires; and the Magistrate so placed in charge of a sub-division`
  line `shall be called the Sub-divisional Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Government may, by general or special order and subject to such control and directions`
  line `as it may deem fit to impose, delegate its powers under sub-section (4) to the District Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in this section shall preclude the State Government from conferring, under any law for the`
  line `time being in force, on a Commissioner of Police all or any of the powers of an Executive Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (91002)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Special Executive Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91002&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may appoint, for such term as it may`
  line `think fit, Executive Magistrates or any police officer not below the rank of Superintendent of Police or`
  line `equivalent, to be known as Special Executive Magistrates, for particular areas or for the performance of`
  line `particular functions and confer on such Special Executive Magistrates such of the powers as are conferrable`
  line `under this Sanhita on Executive Magistrates, as it may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (91003)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Local Jurisdiction of Executive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91003&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the control of the State Government,`
  line `the District Magistrate may, from time to time, define the local limits of the areas within which the`
  line `Executive Magistrates may exercise all or any of the powers with which they may be invested under`
  line `this Sanhita.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as otherwise provided by such definition, the jurisdiction and powers of every such`
  line `Magistrate shall extend throughout the district.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (91004)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Subordination of Executive Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91004&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) All Executive Magistrates shall be subordinate to`
  line `the District Magistrate, and every Executive Magistrate (other than the Sub-divisional Magistrate)`
  line `exercising powers in a sub-division shall also be subordinate to the Sub-divisional Magistrate, subject, to`
  line `the general control of the District Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Magistrate may, from time to time, make rules or give special orders, consistent with`
  line `this Sanhita, as to the distribution or allocation of business among the Executive Magistrates subordinate`
  line `to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (91005)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Public Prosecutors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91005&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) For every High Court, the Central Government or the State Government`
  line `shall, after consultation with the High Court, appoint a Public Prosecutor and may also appoint one or more`
  line `Additional Public Prosecutors, for conducting in such Court, any prosecution, appeal or other proceeding`
  line `on behalf of the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that for National Capital Territory of Delhi, the Central Government shall, after consultation`
  line `with the High Court of Delhi, appoint the Public Prosecutor or Additional Public Prosecutors for the`
  line `purposes of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint one or more Public Prosecutors for the purpose of conducting`
  line `any case in any district or local area.`
  line
  line `(3) For every district, the State Government shall appoint a Public Prosecutor and may also appoint one`
  line `or more Additional Public Prosecutors for the district:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Public Prosecutor or Additional Public Prosecutor appointed for one district may be`
  line `appointed also to be a Public Prosecutor or an Additional Public Prosecutor, as the case may be, for another`
  line district.
  line
  line `(4) The District Magistrate shall, in consultation with the Sessions Judge, prepare a panel of names of`
  line `persons, who are, in his opinion fit to be appointed as Public Prosecutors or Additional Public Prosecutors`
  line `for the district.`
  line
  line `(5) No person shall be appointed by the State Government as the Public Prosecutor or Additional Public`
  line `Prosecutor for the district unless his name appears in the panel of names prepared by the District Magistrate`
  line `under sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (5), where in a State there exists a regular Cadre of`
  line `Prosecuting Officers, the State Government shall appoint a Public Prosecutor or an Additional Public`
  line `Prosecutor only from among the persons constituting such Cadre:`
  line
  line `Provided that where, in the opinion of the State Government, no suitable person is available in such`
  line `Cadre for such appointment, that Government may appoint a person as Public Prosecutor or Additional`
  line `Public Prosecutor, as the case may be, from the panel of names prepared by the District Magistrate under`
  line `sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section,---`
  line
  line `(a) "regular Cadre of Prosecuting Officers" means a Cadre of Prosecuting Officers which includes`
  line `therein the post of Public Prosecutor, by whatever name called, and which provides for promotion of`
  line `Assistant Public Prosecutors, by whatever name called, to that post;`
  line
  line `(b) "Prosecuting Officer" means a person, by whatever name called, appointed to perform the`
  line `functions of a Public Prosecutor, Special Public Prosecutor, Additional Public Prosecutor or Assistant`
  line `Public Prosecutor under this Sanhita.`
  line
  line `(7) A person shall be eligible to be appointed as a Public Prosecutor or an Additional Public Prosecutor`
  line `under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (6), only if he has been in practice`
  line `as an advocate for not less than seven years.`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Government or the State Government may appoint, for the purposes of any case or class`
  line `of cases, a person who has been in practice as an advocate for not less than ten years as a Special Public`
  line `Prosecutor:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may permit the victim to engage an advocate of his choice to assist the`
  line `prosecution under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(9) For the purposes of sub-section (7) and sub-section (8), the period during which a person has been`
  line `in practice as an advocate, or has rendered (whether before or after the commencement of this Sanhita)`
  line `service as a Public Prosecutor or as an Additional Public Prosecutor or Assistant Public Prosecutor or other`
  line `Prosecuting Officer, by whatever name called, shall be deemed to be the period during which such person`
  line `has been in practice as an advocate`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (91006)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Assistant Public Prosecutors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91006&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall appoint in every district one or`
  line `more Assistant Public Prosecutors for conducting prosecutions in the Courts of Magistrates.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint one or more Assistant Public Prosecutors for the purpose of`
  line `conducting any case or class of cases in the Courts of Magistrates.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to provisions contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), where no Assistant Public`
  line `Prosecutor is available for the purposes of any particular case, the District Magistrate may appoint any other`
  line `person to be the Assistant Public Prosecutor in charge of that case after giving notice of fourteen days to`
  line `the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no police officer shall be eligible to be appointed as an Assistant Public`
  line `Prosecutor, if he—`
  line
  line `(a) has taken any part in the investigation into the offence with respect to which the accused is`
  line `being prosecuted; or`
  line
  line `(b) is below the rank of Inspector.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (91007)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Directorate of Prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91007&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may establish,—`
  line
  line `(a) a Directorate of Prosecution in the State consisting of a Director of Prosecution and as many`
  line `Deputy Directors of Prosecution as it thinks fit; and`
  line
  line `(b) a District Directorate of Prosecution in every district consisting of as many Deputy Directors`
  line `and Assistant Directors of Prosecution, as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall be eligible to be appointed,—`
  line
  line `(a) as a Director of Prosecution or a Deputy Director of Prosecution, if he has been in practice as`
  line `an advocate for not less than fifteen years or is or has been a Sessions Judge;`
  line
  line `(b) as an Assistant Director of Prosecution, if he has been in practice as an advocate for not less`
  line `than seven years or has been a Magistrate of the first class.`
  line
  line `(3) The Directorate of Prosecution shall be headed by the Director of Prosecution, who shall function`
  line `under the administrative control of the Home Department in the State.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Deputy Director of Prosecution or Assistant Director of Prosecution shall be subordinate to`
  line `the Director of Prosecution; and every Assistant Director of Prosecution shall be subordinate to the Deputy`
  line `Director of Prosecution.`
  line
  line `(5) Every Public Prosecutor, Additional Public Prosecutor and Special Public Prosecutor appointed by`
  line `the State Government under sub-section (1) or sub-section (8) of section 18 to conduct cases in the High`
  line `Court shall be subordinate to the Director of Prosecution.`
  line
  line `(6) Every Public Prosecutor, Additional Public Prosecutor and Special Public Prosecutor appointed by`
  line `the State Government under sub-section (3) or sub-section (8) of section 18 to conduct cases in District`
  line `Courts and every Assistant Public Prosecutor appointed under sub-section (1) of section 19 shall be`
  line `subordinate to the Deputy Director of Prosecution or the Assistant Director of Prosecution.`
  line
  line `(7) The powers and functions of the Director of Prosecution shall be to monitor cases in which offences`
  line `are punishable for ten years or more, or with life imprisonment, or with death; to expedite the proceedings`
  line `and to give opinion on filing of appeals.`
  line
  line `(8) The powers and functions of the Deputy Director of Prosecution shall be to examine and scrutinise`
  line `police report and monitor the cases in which offences are punishable for seven years or more, but less than`
  line `ten years, for ensuring their expeditious disposal.`
  line
  line `(9) The functions of the Assistant Director of Prosecution shall be to monitor cases in which offences`
  line `are punishable for less than seven years.`
  line
  line `(10) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (7), (8) and (9), the Director, Deputy Director`
  line `or Assistant Director of Prosecution shall have the power to deal with and be responsible for all proceedings`
  line `under this Sanhita.`
  line
  line `(11) The other powers and functions of the Director of Prosecution, Deputy Directors of Prosecution`
  line `and Assistant Directors of Prosecution and the areas for which each of the Deputy Directors of Prosecution`
  line `or Assistant Directors of Prosecution have been appointed shall be such as the State Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(12) The provisions of this section shall not apply to the Advocate General for the State while`
  line `performing the functions of a Public Prosecutor.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (91008)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Courts by which offences are triable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91008&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the other provisions of this Sanhita,—`
  line
  line `(a) any offence under the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 may be tried by—`
  line
  line `(i) the High Court; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the Court of Session; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any other Court by which such offence is shown in the First Schedule to be triable:`
  line
  line `Provided that any offence under section 64, section 65, section 66, section 67, section 68,`
  line `section 69, section 70 or section 71 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 shall be tried as far as`
  line `practicable by a Court presided over by a woman;`
  line
  line `(b) any offence under any other law shall, when any Court is mentioned in this behalf in such law, be`
  line `tried by such Court and when no Court is so mentioned, may be tried by—`
  line
  line `(i) the High Court; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any other Court by which such offence is shown in the First Schedule to be triable.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (91009)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Sentences which High Courts and Sessions Judges may pass.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91009&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) A High Court may pass any`
  line `sentence authorised by law.`
  line
  line `(2) A Sessions Judge or Additional Sessions Judge may pass any sentence authorised by law; but any`
  line `sentence of death passed by any such Judge shall be subject to confirmation by the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (91010)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Sentences which Magistrates may pass.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91010&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court of a Chief Judicial Magistrate may pass`
  line `any sentence authorised by law except a sentence of death or of imprisonment for life or of imprisonment for a term exceeding seven years.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court of a Magistrate of the first class may pass a sentence of imprisonment for a term not`
  line `exceeding three years, or of fine not exceeding fifty thousand rupees, or of both, or of community service.`
  line
  line `(3) The Court of Magistrate of the second class may pass a sentence of imprisonment for a term not`
  line `exceeding one year, or of fine not exceeding ten thousand rupees, or of both, or of community service.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---"Community service" shall mean the work which the Court may order a convict to`
  line `perform as a form of punishment that benefits the community, for which he shall not be entitled to any`
  line remuneration.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (91011)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Sentence of imprisonment in default of fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91011&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court of a Magistrate may award such`
  line `term of imprisonment in default of payment of fine as is authorised by law:`
  line
  line `Provided that the term---`
  line
  line `(a) is not in excess of the powers of the Magistrate under section 23;`
  line
  line `(b) shall not, where imprisonment has been awarded as part of the substantive sentence, exceed`
  line `one-fourth of the term of imprisonment which the Magistrate is competent to inflict as punishment for`
  line `the offence otherwise than as imprisonment in default of payment of the fine.`
  line
  line `(2) The imprisonment awarded under this section may be in addition to a substantive sentence of`
  line `imprisonment for the maximum term awardable by the Magistrate under section 23.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (91012)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Sentence in cases of conviction of several offences at one trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91012&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a person is convicted`
  line `at one trial of two or more offences, the Court may, subject to the provisions of section 9 of the Bharatiya`
  line `Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, sentence him for such offences, to the several punishments prescribed therefor which`
  line `such Court is competent to inflict and the Court shall, considering the gravity of offences, order such`
  line `punishments to run concurrently or consecutively.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of consecutive sentences, it shall not be necessary for the Court by reason only of the`
  line `aggregate punishment for the several offences being in excess of the punishment which it is competent to`
  line `inflict on conviction of a single offence, to send the offender for trial before a higher Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) in no case shall such person be sentenced to imprisonment for a longer period than twenty years;`
  line
  line `(b) the aggregate punishment shall not exceed twice the amount of punishment which the Court is`
  line `competent to inflict for a single offence.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of appeal by a convicted person, the aggregate of the consecutive sentences passed`
  line `against him under this section shall be deemed to be a single sentence.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (91013)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Mode of conferring powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91013&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) In conferring powers under this Sanhita, the High Court or the`
  line `State Government, as the case may be, may, by order, empower persons specially by name or in virtue of`
  line `their offices or classes of officials generally be their official titles.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such order shall take effect from the date on which it is communicated to the person so`
  line empowered.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (91014)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Powers of officers appointed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91014&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person holding an office in the service of`
  line `Government who has been invested by the High Court or the State Government with any powers under this`
  line `Sanhita throughout any local area is appointed to an equal or higher office of the samenature, within a like`
  line `local area under the same State Government, he shall, unless the High Court or the State Government, as`
  line `the case may be, otherwise directs, or has otherwise directed, exercise the same powers in the local area in`
  line `which he is so appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (91015)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Withdrawal of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91015&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The High Court or the State Government, as the case may be, may`
  line `withdraw all or any of the powers conferred by it under this Sanhita on any person or by any officer`
  line `subordinate to it.`
  line
  line `(2) Any powers conferred by the Chief Judicial Magistrate or by the District Magistrate may be`
  line `withdrawn by the respective Magistrate by whom such powers were conferred`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (91016)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Powers of Judges and Magistrates exercisable by their successors-in-office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91016&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `other provisions of this Sanhita, the powers and duties of a Judge or Magistrate may be exercised or`
  line `performed by his successor-in-office.`
  line
  line `(2) When there is any doubt as to who is the successor-in-office, the Sessions Judge shall determine by`
  line `order in writing the Judge who shall, for the purposes of this Sanhita or of any proceedings or order`
  line `thereunder, be deemed to be the successor-in-office.`
  line
  line `(3) When there is any doubt as to who is the successor-in-office of any Magistrate, the Chief Judicial`
  line `Magistrate, or the District Magistrate, as the case may be, shall determine by order in writing the Magistrate`
  line `who shall, for the purpose of this Sanhita or of any proceedings or order thereunder, be deemed to be the`
  line `successor-in-office of such Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (91017)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Powers of superior officers of police.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91017&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Police officers superior in rank to an officer in charge of`
  line `a police station may exercise the same powers, throughout the local area to which they are appointed, as`
  line `may be exercised by such officer within the limits of his station.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (91018)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Public when to assist Magistrates and police.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91018&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Every person is bound to assist a Magistrate or`
  line `police officer reasonably demanding his aid—`
  line
  line `(a) in the taking or preventing the escape of any other person whom such Magistrate or police`
  line `officer is authorised to arrest; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the prevention or suppression of a breach of the peace; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the prevention of any injury attempted to be committed to any public property.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (91019)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Aid to person, other than police officer, executing warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91019&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `When a warrant is directed to a`
  line `person other than a police officer, any other person may aid in the execution of such warrant, if the person`
  line `to whom the warrant is directed be near at hand and acting in the execution of the warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (91020)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Public to give information of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91020&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person, aware of the commission of,`
  line `or of the intention of any other person to commit, any offence punishable under any of the following`
  line `sections of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) sections 103 to 105 (both inclusive);`
  line
  line `(ii) sections 111 to 113 (both inclusive);`
  line
  line `(iii) sections 140 to 144 (both inclusive);`
  line
  line `(iv) sections 147 to 154 (both inclusive) and section 158;`
  line
  line `(v) sections 178 to 182 (both inclusive);`
  line
  line `(vi) sections 189 and 191;`
  line
  line `(vii) sections 274 to 280 (both inclusive);`
  line
  line `(viii) section 307;`
  line
  line `(ix) sections 309 to 312 (both inclusive);`
  line
  line `(x) sub-section (5) of section 316;`
  line
  line `(xi) sections 326 to 328 (both inclusive); and`
  line
  line `(xii) sections 331 and 332, upon the person so aware, forthwith give information to the nearest`
  line `Magistrate or police officer of such commission or intention.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, the term “offence” includes any act committed at any place out of`
  line `India which would constitute an offence if committed in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (91534)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Duty of officers employed in connection with affairs of a village to make certain report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91534&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every officer employed in connection with the affairs of a village and every person residing`
  line `in a village shall forthwith communicate to the nearest Magistrate or to the officer in charge of the nearest`
  line `police station, whichever is nearer, any information which he may possess respecting—`
  line
  line `(a) the permanent or temporary residence of any notorious receiver or vendor of stolen property in`
  line `or near such village;`
  line
  line `(b) the resort to any place within, or the passage through, such village of any person whom he`
  line `knows, or reasonably suspects, to be a robber, escaped convict or proclaimed offender;`
  line
  line `(c) the commission of, or intention to commit, in or near such village any non-bailable offence or`
  line `any offence punishable under section 189 and section 191 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023;`
  line
  line `(d) the occurrence in or near such village of any sudden or unnatural death or of any death under`
  line `suspicious circumstances or the discovery in or near such village of any corpse or part of a corpse, in`
  line `circumstances which lead to a reasonable suspicion that such a death has occurred or the disappearance`
  line `from such village of any person in circumstances which lead to a reasonable suspicion that a nonbailable offence has been committed in respect of such person;`
  line
  line `(e) the commission of, or intention to commit, at any place out of India nearsuch village any act`
  line `which, if committed in India, would be an offence punishable under any of the following sections of`
  line `the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, namely, 103, 105, 111, 112, 113, 178 to 181 (both inclusive), 305,`
  line `307, 309 to 312 (both inclusive), clauses (f) and (g) of section 326, 331or 332;`
  line
  line `(f) any matter likely to affect the maintenance of order or the prevention of crime or the safety of`
  line `person or property respecting which the District Magistrate, by general or special order made with the`
  line `previous sanction of the State Government, has directed him to communicate information.`
  line
  line `(2) In this section,—`
  line
  line `(i) “village” includes village lands;`
  line
  line `(ii) the expression “proclaimed offender” includes any person proclaimed as an offender by any`
  line `Court or authority in any territory in India to which this Sanhita does not extend, in respect of any act`
  line `which if committed in the territories to which this Sanhita extends, would be an offence punishable`
  line `under any of the offence punishable with imprisonment for ten years or more or with imprisonment for`
  line `life or with death under the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023;`
  line
  line `(iii) the words “officer employed in connection with the affairs of the village” means a member of`
  line `the panchayat of the village and includes the headman and every officer or other person appointed to`
  line `perform any function connected with the administration of the village.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (91022)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `When police may arrest without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91022&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any police officer may without an order from a`
  line `Magistrate and without a warrant, arrest any person—`
  line
  line `(a) who commits, in the presence of a police officer, a cognizable offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) against whom a reasonable complaint has been made, or credible information has been received,`
  line `or a reasonable suspicion exists that he has committed a cognizable offence punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may be less than seven years or which may extend to seven years`
  line `whether with or without fine, if the following conditions are satisfied, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the police officer has reason to believe on the basis of such complaint, information, or`
  line `suspicion that such person has committed the said offence;`
  line
  line `(ii) the police officer is satisfied that such arrest is necessary—`
  line
  line `(a) to prevent such person from committing any further offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) for proper investigation of the offence; or`
  line
  line `(c) to prevent such person from causing the evidence of the offence to disappear or`
  line `tampering with such evidence in any manner; or`
  line
  line `(d) to prevent such person from making any inducement, threat or promise to any person`
  line `acquainted with the facts of the case so as to dissuade him from disclosing such facts to the`
  line `Court or to the police officer; or`
  line
  line `(e) as unless such person is arrested, his presence in the Court whenever required cannot`
  line `be ensured, and the police officer shall record while making such arrest, his reasons in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that a police officer shall, in all cases where the arrest of a person is not required`
  line `under the provisions of this sub-section, record the reasons in writing for not making the`
  line `arrest; or`
  line
  line `(c) against whom credible information has been received that he has committed a cognizable`
  line `offence punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to more than seven years whether`
  line `with or without fine or with death sentence and the police officer has reason to believe on the basis of`
  line `that information that such person has committed the said offence; or`
  line
  line `(d) who has been proclaimed as an offender either under this Sanhita or by order of the State`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(e) in whose possession anything is found which may reasonably be suspected to be stolen property`
  line `and who may reasonably be suspected of having committed an offence with reference to such thing; or`
  line
  line `(f) who obstructs a police officer while in the execution of his duty, or who has escaped, or attempts`
  line `to escape, from lawful custody; or`
  line
  line `(g) who is reasonably suspected of being a deserter from any of the Armed Forces of the Union; or`
  line
  line `(h) who has been concerned in, or against whom a reasonable complaint has been made, or credible`
  line `information has been received, or a reasonable suspicion exists, of his having been concerned in, any`
  line `act committed at any place out of India which, if committed in India, would have been punishable as`
  line `an offence, and for which he is, under any law relating to extradition, or otherwise, liable to be`
  line `apprehended or detained in custody in India; or`
  line
  line `(i) who, being a released convict, commits a breach of any rule made under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 394; or`
  line
  line `(j) for whose arrest any requisition, whether written or oral, has been received from another police`
  line `officer, provided that the requisition specifies the person to be arrested and the offence or other cause`
  line `for which the arrest is to be made and it appears therefrom that the person might lawfully be arrested`
  line `without a warrant by the officer who issued the requisition`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 39, no pn.erson concerned in a non-cognizable offence or against`
  line `whom a complaint has been made or credible information has been received or reasonable suspicion exists`
  line `of his having so concerned, shall be arrested except under a warrant or order of a Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(3) The police officer shall, in all cases where the arrest of a person is not required under`
  line `sub-section (1) issue a notice directing the person against whom a reasonable complaint has been made, or`
  line `credible information has been received, or a reasonable suspicion exists that he has committed a cognizable`
  line `offence, to appear before him or at such other place as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(4) Where such a notice is issued to any person, it shall be the duty of that person to comply with the`
  line `terms of the notice.`
  line
  line `(5) Where such person complies and continues to comply with the notice, he shall not be arrested in`
  line `respect of the offence referred to in the notice unless, for reasons to be recorded, the police officer is of the`
  line `opinion that he ought to be arrested.`
  line
  line `(6) Where such person, at any time, fails to comply with the terms of the notice or is unwilling to`
  line `identify himself, the police officer may, subject to such orders as may have been passed by a competent`
  line `Court in this behalf, arrest him for the offence mentioned in the notice.`
  line
  line `(7) No arrest shall be made without prior permission of an officer not below the rank of`
  line `Deputy Superintendent of Police in case of an offence which is punishable for imprisonment of less than`
  line `three years and such person is infirm or is above sixty years of age`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (91023)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Procedure of arrest and duties of officer making arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91023&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Every police officer while making an`
  line `arrest shall—`
  line
  line `(a) bear an accurate, visible and clear identification of his name which will facilitate easy`
  line identification;
  line
  line `(b) prepare a memorandum of arrest which shall be—`
  line
  line `(i) attested by at least one witness, who is a member of the family of the person arrested or a`
  line `respectable member of the locality where the arrest is made;`
  line
  line `(ii) countersigned by the person arrested; and`
  line
  line `(c) inform the person arrested, unless the memorandum is attested by a member of his family, that`
  line `he has a right to have a relative or a friend or any other person named by him to be informed of his`
  line arrest.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (91024)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Designated police officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91024&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall—`
  line
  line `(a) establish a police control room in every district and at State level;`
  line
  line `(b) designate a police officer in every district and in every police station, not below the rank of Assistant Sub-Inspector of Police who shall be responsible for maintaining the information about the names and addresses of the persons arrested, nature of the offence with which charged, which shall be prominently displayed in any manner including in digital mode in every police station and at the district`
  line headquarters.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (91025)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Right of arrested person to meet an advocate of his choice during interrogation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91025&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `When any`
  line `person is arrested and interrogated by the police, he shall be entitled to meet an advocate of his choice`
  line `during interrogation, though not throughout interrogation.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (91026)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Arrest on refusal to give name and residence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91026&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person who, in the presence of a`
  line `police officer, has committed or has been accused of committing a non-cognizable offence refuses on`
  line `demand of such officer to give his name and residence or gives a name or residence which such officer hasreason to believe to be false, he may be arrested by such officer in order that his name or residence may be`
  line ascertained.
  line
  line `(2) When the true name and residence of such person have been ascertained, he shall be released on a`
  line `bond or bail bond, to appear before a Magistrate if so required:`
  line
  line `Provided that if such person is not resident in India, the bail bond shall be secured by a surety or sureties`
  line `resident in India.`
  line
  line `(3) If the true name and residence of such person is not ascertained within twenty-four hours from the`
  line `time of arrest or if he fails to execute the bond or bail bond, or, if so required, to furnish sufficient sureties,`
  line `he shall forthwith be forwarded to the nearest Magistrate having jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (91027)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Arrest by private person and procedure on such arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91027&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any private person may arrest or`
  line `cause to be arrested any person who in his presence commits a non-bailable and cognizable offence, or any`
  line `proclaimed offender, and, without unnecessary delay, but within six hours from such arrest, shall make over`
  line `or cause to be made over any person so arrested to a police officer, or, in the absence of a police officer,`
  line `take such person or cause him to be taken in custody to the nearest police station.`
  line
  line `(2) If there is reason to believe that such person comes under the provisions of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 35, a police officer shall take him in custody.`
  line
  line `(3) If there is reason to believe that he has committed a non-cognizable offence, and he refuses on the`
  line `demand of a police officer to give his name and residence, or gives a name or residence which such officer`
  line `has reason to believe to be false, he shall be dealt with under the provisions of section 39; but if there is no`
  line `sufficient reason to believe that he has committed any offence, he shall be at once released`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (91028)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Arrest by Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91028&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any offence is committed in the presence of a Magistrate,`
  line `whether Executive or Judicial, within his local jurisdiction, he may himself arrest or order any person to`
  line `arrest the offender, and may thereupon, subject to the provisions herein contained as to bail, commit the`
  line `offender to custody.`
  line
  line `(2) Any Magistrate, whether Executive or Judicial, may at any time arrest or direct the arrest, in his`
  line `presence, within his local jurisdiction, of any person for whose arrest he is competent at the time and in the`
  line `circumstances to issue a warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (91029)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Protection of members of Armed Forces from arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91029&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in section 35 and sections 39 to 41 (both inclusive), no member of the Armed Forces of the Union shall be`
  line `arrested for anything done or purported to be done by him in the discharge of his official duties except after`
  line `obtaining the consent of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification, direct that the provisions of sub-section (1) shall apply`
  line `to such class or category of the members of the Force charged with the maintenance of public order as may`
  line `be specified therein, wherever they may be serving, and thereupon the provisions of that sub-section shall`
  line `apply as if for the expression “Central Government” occurring therein, the expression “State Government”`
  line `were substituted`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (91030)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Arrest how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91030&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) In making an arrest the police officer or other person making the same`
  line `shall actually touch or confine the body of the person to be arrested, unless there be a submission to the`
  line `custody by word or action:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a woman is to be arrested, unless the circumstances indicate to the contrary, her`
  line `submission to custody on an oral intimation of arrest shall be presumed and, unless the circumstances`
  line `otherwise require or unless the police officer is a female, the police officer shall not touch the person of the`
  line `woman for making her arrest.`
  line
  line `(2) If such person forcibly resists the endeavour to arrest him, or attempts to evade the arrest, such`
  line `police officer or other person may use all means necessary to effect the arrest.`
  line
  line `(3) The police officer may, keeping in view the nature and gravity of the offence, use handcuff while`
  line `making the arrest of a person or while producing such person before the court who is a habitual or repeat`
  line `offender, or who escaped from custody, or who has committed offence of organised crime, terrorist act,`
  line `drug related crime, or illegal possession of arms and ammunition, murder, rape, acid attack, counterfeiting`
  line `of coins and currency-notes, human trafficking, sexual offence against children, or offence against the State.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section gives a right to cause the death of a person who is not accused of an offence`
  line `punishable with death or with imprisonment for life.`
  line
  line `(5) Save in exceptional circumstances, no woman shall be arrested after sunset and before sunrise, and`
  line `where such exceptional circumstances exist, the woman police officer shall, by making a written report,`
  line `obtain the prior permission of the Magistrate of the first class within whose local jurisdiction the offence is`
  line `committed or the arrest is to be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (91031)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Search of place entered by person sought to be arrested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91031&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person acting under a`
  line `warrant of arrest, or any police officer having authority to arrest, has reason to believe that the person to be`
  line `arrested has entered into, or is within, any place, any person residing in, or being in charge of, such place`
  line `shall, on demand of such person acting as aforesaid or such police officer, allow him free ingress thereto,`
  line `and afford all reasonable facilities for a search therein.`
  line
  line `(2) If ingress to such place cannot be obtained under sub-section (1), it shall be lawful in any case for`
  line `a person acting under a warrant and in any case in which a warrant may issue, but cannot be obtained`
  line `without affording the person to be arrested an opportunity of escape, for a police officer to enter such place`
  line `and search therein, and in order to effect an entrance into such place, to break open any outer or inner door`
  line `or window of any house or place, whether that of the person to be arrested or of any other person, if after`
  line `notification of his authority and purpose, and demand of admittance duly made, he cannot otherwise obtain`
  line `admittance:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any such place is an apartment in the actual occupancy of a female (not being the person`
  line `to be arrested) who, according to custom, does not appear in public, such person or police officer shall,`
  line `before entering such apartment, give notice to such female that she is at liberty to withdraw and shall afford`
  line `her every reasonable facility for withdrawing, and may then break open the apartment and enter it.`
  line
  line `(3) Any police officer or other person authorised to make an arrest may break open any outer or inner`
  line `door or window of any house or place in order to liberate himself or any other person who, having lawfully`
  line `entered for the purpose of making an arrest, is detained therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (91032)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Pursuit of offenders into other jurisdictions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91032&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `A police officer may, for the purpose of arresting`
  line `without warrant any person whom he is authorised to arrest, pursue such person into any place in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (91033)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `No unnecessary restraint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91033&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The person arrested shall not be subjected to more restraint than is`
  line `necessary to prevent his escape.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (91034)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Person arrested to be informed of grounds of arrest and of right to bail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91034&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every police`
  line `officer or other person arresting any person without warrant shall forthwith communicate to him full`
  line `particulars of the offence for which he is arrested or other grounds for such arrest.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a police officer arrests without warrant any person other than a person accused of a nonbailable offence, he shall inform the person arrested that he is entitled to be released on bail and that he`
  line `may arrange for sureties on his behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (91035)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Obligation of person making arrest to inform about arrest, etc., to relative or friend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91035&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every police officer or other person making any arrest under this Sanhita shall forthwith give the`
  line `information regarding such arrest and place where the arrested person is being held to any of his relatives,`
  line `friends or such other persons as may be disclosed or nominated by the arrested person for the purpose of`
  line `giving such information and also to the designated police officer in the district.`
  line
  line `(2) The police officer shall inform the arrested person of his rights under sub-section (1) as soon as he`
  line `is brought to the police station.`
  line
  line `(3) An entry of the fact as to who has been informed of the arrest of such person shall be made in a`
  line `book to be kept in the police station in such form as the State Government may, by rules, provide.`
  line
  line `(4) It shall be the duty of the Magistrate before whom such arrested person is produced, to satisfy`
  line `himself that the requirements of sub-section (2) and sub-section (3) have been complied with in respect of`
  line `such arrested person`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (91036)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Search of arrested person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91036&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever,—`
  line
  line `(i) a person is arrested by a police officer under a warrant which does not provide for the taking of`
  line `bail, or under a warrant which provides for the taking of bail but the person arrested cannot furnish bail;`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) a person is arrested without warrant, or by a private person under a warrant, and cannot legally`
  line `be admitted to bail, or is unable to furnish bail, the officer making the arrest or, when the arrest is made`
  line `by a private person, the police officer to whom he makes over the person arrested, may search such`
  line `person, and place in safe custody all articles, other than necessary wearing-apparel, found upon him`
  line `and where any article is seized from the arrested person, a receipt showing the articles taken in`
  line `possession by the police officer shall be given to such person.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever it is necessary to cause a female to be searched, the search shall be made by another`
  line `female with strict regard to decency.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (91037)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Power to seize offensive weapons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91037&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The police officer or other person making any arrest under`
  line `this Sanhita may, immediately after the arrest is made, take from the person arrested any offensive weapons`
  line `which he has about his person, and shall deliver all weapons so taken to the Court or officer before which`
  line `or whom the officer or person making the arrest is required by this Sanhita to produce the person arrested.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (91038)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Examination of accused by medical practitioner at request of police officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91038&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a`
  line `person is arrested on a charge of committing an offence of such a nature and alleged to have been committed`
  line `under such circumstances that there are reasonable grounds for believing that an examination of his person`
  line `will afford evidence as to the commission of an offence, it shall be lawful for a registered medical`
  line `practitioner, acting at the request of any police officer, and for any person acting in good faith in his aid`
  line `and under his direction, to make such an examination of the person arrested as is reasonably necessary in`
  line `order to ascertain the facts which may afford such evidence, and to use such force as is reasonably necessary`
  line `for that purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever the person of a female is to be examined under this section, the examination shall be`
  line `made only by, or under the supervision of, a female registered medical practitioner.`
  line
  line `(3) The registered medical practitioner shall, without any delay, forward the examination report to the`
  line `investigating officer.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---In this section and sections 52 and 53,---`
  line
  line `(a) "examination" shall include the examination of blood, blood stains, semen, swabs in case of sexual`
  line `offences, sputum and sweat, hair samples and finger nail clippings by the use of modern and scientific`
  line `techniques including DNA profiling and such other tests which the registered medical practitioner thinks`
  line `necessary in a particular case;`
  line
  line `(b) "registered medical practitioner" means a medical practitioner who possesses any medical`
  line `qualification recognised under the National Medical Commission Act, 2019 (30 of 2019) and whose name`
  line `has been entered in the National Medical Register or a State Medical Register under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (91039)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Examination of person accused of rape by medical practitioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91039&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a person is arrested`
  line `on a charge of committing an offence of rape or an attempt to commit rape and there are reasonable grounds`
  line `for believing that an examination of his person will afford evidence as to the commission of such offence,`
  line `it shall be lawful for a registered medical practitioner employed in a hospital run by the Government or by`
  line `a local authority and in the absence of such a practitioner within the radius of sixteen kilometres from the`
  line `place where the offence has been committed, by any other registered medical practitioner, acting at the`
  line `request of any police officer, and for any person acting in good faith in his aid and under his direction, to`
  line `make such an examination of the arrested person and to use such force as is reasonably necessary for that`
  line purpose.
  line
  line `(2) The registered medical practitioner conducting such examination shall, without any delay, examine`
  line `such person and prepare a report of his examination giving the following particulars, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the name and address of the accused and of the person by whom he was brought;`
  line
  line `(ii) the age of the accused;`
  line
  line `(iii) marks of injury, if any, on the person of the accused;`
  line
  line `(iv) the description of material taken from the person of the accused for DNA profiling; and`
  line
  line `(v) other material particulars in reasonable detail.`
  line
  line `(3) The report shall state precisely the reasons for each conclusion arrived at.`
  line
  line `(4) The exact time of commencement and completion of the examination shall also be noted in the`
  line report.
  line
  line `(5) The registered medical practitioner shall, without any delay, forward the report to the investigating`
  line `officer, who shall forward it to the Magistrate referred to in section 193 as part of the documents referred`
  line `to in clause (a) of sub-section (6) of that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (91040)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Examination of arrested person by medical officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91040&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person is arrested, he shall`
  line `be examined by a medical officer in the service of the Central Government or a State Government, and in`
  line `case the medical officer is not available, by a registered medical practitioner soon after the arrest is made:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the medical officer or the registered medical practitioner is of the opinion that one more`
  line `examination of such person is necessary, he may do so:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the arrested person is a female, the examination of the body shall be made`
  line `only by or under the supervision of a female medical officer, and in case the female medical officer is not`
  line `available, by a female registered medical practitioner.`
  line
  line `(2) The medical officer or a registered medical practitioner so examining the arrested person shall`
  line `prepare the record of such examination, mentioning therein any injuries or marks of violence upon the`
  line `person arrested, and the approximate time when such injuries or marks may have been inflicted.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an examination is made under sub-section (1), a copy of the report of such examination shall`
  line `be furnished by the medical officer or registered medical practitioner, as the case may be, to the arrested`
  line `person or the person nominated by such arrested person not available, by a registered medical practitioner`
  line `soon after the arrest is made:`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (91041)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Identification of person arrested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91041&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Where a person is arrested on a charge of committing an`
  line `offence and his identification by any other person or persons is considered necessary for the purpose of`
  line `investigation of such offence, the Court, having jurisdiction may, on the request of the officer in charge of`
  line `a police station, direct the person so arrested to subject himself to identification by any person or persons`
  line `in such manner as the Court may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the person identifying the person arrested is mentally or physically disabled, such`
  line `process of identification shall take place under the supervision of a Magistrate who shall take appropriate`
  line `steps to ensure that such person identifies the person arrested using methods that person is comfortable with`
  line `and the identification process shall be recorded by any audio-video electronic means.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (91042)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Procedure when police officer deputes subordinate to arrest without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91042&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any`
  line `officer in charge of a police station or any police officer making an investigation under Chapter XIII`
  line `requires any officer subordinate to him to arrest without a warrant (otherwise than in his presence) any`
  line `person who may lawfully be arrested without a warrant, he shall deliver to the officer required to make the`
  line `arrest an order in writing, specifying the person to be arrested and the offence or other cause for which the`
  line `arrest is to be made and the officer so required shall, before making the arrest, notify to the person to be`
  line `arrested the substance of the order and, if so required by such person,`
  line `shall show him the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall affect the power of a police officer to arrest a person under`
  line `section 35`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (91043)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Health and safety of arrested person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91043&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the person having the custody of an`
  line `accused to take reasonable care of the health and safety of the accused.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (91044)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Person arrested to be taken before Magistrate or officer in charge of police station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91044&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `A police`
  line `officer making an arrest without warrant shall, without unnecessary delay and subject to the provisions`
  line `herein contained as to bail, take or send the person arrested before a Magistrate having jurisdiction in the`
  line `case, or before the officer in charge of a police station.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (91045)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Person arrested not to be detained more than twenty-four hours.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91045&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Officers in charge of police`
  line `stations shall report to the District Magistrate, or, if he so directs, to the Sub-divisional Magistrate, the cases`
  line `of all persons arrested without warrant, within the limits of their respective stations, whether such persons`
  line `have been admitted to bail or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (91046)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Police to report apprehensions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91046&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Officers in charge of police stations shall report to the District`
  line `Magistrate, or, if he so directs, to the Sub-divisional Magistrate, the cases of all persons arrested without`
  line `warrant, within the limits of their respective stations, whether such persons have been admitted to bail or`
  line otherwise.
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (91047)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Discharge of person apprehended.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91047&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `No person who has been arrested by a police officer shall be`
  line `discharged except on his bond, or bail bond, or under the special order of a Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (91048)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Power, on escape, to pursue and retake.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91048&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person in lawful custody escapes or is rescued,`
  line `the person from whose custody he escaped or was rescued may immediately pursue and arrest him in any`
  line `place in India.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of section 44 shall apply to arrests under sub-section (1) although the person making`
  line `any such arrest is not acting under a warrant and is not a police officer having authority to arrest.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (91049)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Arrest to be made strictly according to Sanhita.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91049&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `No arrest shall be made except in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Sanhita or any other law for the time being in force providing for arrest.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (91535)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Form of summons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91535&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Every summons issued by a Court under this`
  line `Sanhita shall be,—`
  line
  line `(i) in writing, in duplicate, signed by the presiding officer of such Court or by such other officer as`
  line `the High Court may, from time to time, by rule direct, and shall`
  line `bear the seal of the Court; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in an encrypted or any other form of electronic communication and shall bear the image of the`
  line `seal of the Court or digital signature.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (91051)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Summons how served.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91051&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every summons shall be served by a police officer, or subject to such`
  line `rules as the State Government may make in this behalf, by an officer of the Court issuing it or other public`
  line `servant:`
  line
  line `Provided that the police station or the registrar in the Court shall maintain a register to enter the address,`
  line `email address, phone number and such other details as the State Government may, by rules, provide.`
  line
  line `(2) The summons shall, if practicable, be served personally on the person summoned, by delivering or`
  line `tendering to him one of the duplicates of the summons:`
  line
  line `Provided that summons bearing the image of Court's seal may also be served by electronic`
  line `communication in such form and in such manner, as the State Government may, by rules, provide.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person on whom a summons is so served personally shall, if so required by the serving officer,`
  line `sign a receipt therefor on the back of the other duplicate.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (91052)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Service of summons on corporate bodies, firms, and societies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91052&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) Service of a summons on a`
  line `company or corporation may be effected by serving it on the Director, Manager, Secretary or other officer`
  line `of the company or corporation, or by letter sent by registered post addressed to the Director, Manager,`
  line `Secretary or other officer of the company or corporation in India, in which case the service shall be deemed`
  line `to have been effected when the letter would arrive in ordinary course of post.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, “company” means a body corporate and “corporation” means an`
  line `incorporated company or other body corporate registered under the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) or`
  line `a society registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(2) Service of a summons on a firm or other association of individuals may be effected by serving it on`
  line `any partner of such firm or association, or by letter sent by registered post addressed to such partner, in`
  line `which case the service shall be deemed to have been effected when the letter would arrive in ordinary course`
  line `of post`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (91053)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Service when persons summoned cannot be found.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91053&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Where the person summoned cannot, by`
  line `the exercise of due diligence, be found, the summons may be served by leaving one of the duplicates for`
  line `him with some adult member of his family residing with him, and the person with whom the summons is`
  line `so left shall, if so required by the serving officer, sign a receipt therefor on the back of the other duplicate.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A servant is not a member of the family within the meaning of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (91054)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Procedure when service cannot be effected as before provided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91054&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `If service cannot by the`
  line `exercise of due diligence be effected as provided in section 64, section 65 or section 66, the serving officer`
  line `shall affix one of the duplicates of the summons to some conspicuous part of the house or homestead in`
  line `which the person summoned ordinarily resides; and thereupon the Court, after making such inquiries as it`
  line `thinks fit, may either declare that the summons has been duly served or order fresh service in such manner`
  line `as it considers proper.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (91055)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Service on Government servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91055&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the person summoned is in the active service of the`
  line `Government, the Court issuing the summons shall ordinarily send it in duplicate to the head of the office in`
  line `which such person is employed; and such head shall thereupon cause the summons to be served in the`
  line `manner provided by section 64, and shall return it to the Court under his signature with the endorsement`
  line `required by that section.`
  line
  line `(2) Such signature shall be evidence of due service.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (91056)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Service of summons outside local limits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91056&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `When a Court desires that a summons issued by it shall`
  line `be served at any place outside its local jurisdiction, it shall ordinarily send such summons in duplicate to a`
  line `Magistrate within whose local jurisdiction the person summoned resides, or is, to be there served.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (91057)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Proof of service in such cases and when serving officer not present.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91057&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a summons`
  line `issued by a Court is served outside its local jurisdiction, and in any case where the officer who has served`
  line `a summons is not present at the hearing of the case, an affidavit, purporting to be made before a Magistrate,`
  line `that such summons has been served, and a duplicate of the summons purporting to be endorsed (in the`
  line `manner provided by section 64 or section 66) by the person to whom it was delivered or tendered or with`
  line `whom it was left, shall be admissible in evidence, and the statements made therein shall be deemed to be`
  line `correct unless and until the contrary is proved.`
  line
  line `(2) The affidavit mentioned in this section may be attached to the duplicate of the summons and returned`
  line `to the Court.`
  line
  line `(3) All summons served through electronic communication under sections 64 to 71 (both inclusive)`
  line `shall be considered as duly served and a copy of such summons shall be attested and kept as a proof of`
  line `service of summons.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (91058)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Service of summons on witness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91058&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the preceding`
  line `sections of this Chapter, a Court issuing a summons to a witness may, in addition to and simultaneously`
  line `with the issue of such summons, direct a copy of the summons to be served by electronic communication`
  line `or by registered post addressed to the witness at the place where he ordinarily resides or carries on business`
  line `or personally works for gain.`
  line
  line `(2) When an acknowledgement purporting to be signed by the witness or an endorsement purporting to`
  line `be made by a postal employee that the witness refused to take delivery of the summons has been received`
  line `or on the proof of delivery of summons under sub-section (3) of section 70 by electronic communication to`
  line `the satisfaction of the Court, the Court issuing summons may deem that the summons has been duly served.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (91536)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Form of warrant of arrest and duration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91536&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every warrant of arrest issued by a Court under`
  line `this Sanhita shall be in writing, signed by the presiding officer of such Court and shall bear the seal of the`
  line Court.
  line
  line `(2) Every such warrant shall remain in force until it is cancelled by the Court which issued it, or until`
  line `it is executed.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (91060)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Power to direct security to be taken.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91060&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Court issuing a warrant for the arrest of any person`
  line `may in its discretion direct by endorsement on the warrant that, if such person executes a bail bond with`
  line `sufficient sureties for his attendance before the Court at a specified time and thereafter until otherwise`
  line `directed by the Court, the officer to whom the warrant is directed shall take such security and shall release`
  line `such person from custody.`
  line
  line `(2) The endorsement shall state—`
  line
  line `(a) the number of sureties;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount in which they and the person for whose arrest the warrant is issued, are to be`
  line `respectively bound;`
  line
  line `(c) the time at which he is to attend before the Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever security is taken under this section, the officer to whom the warrant is directed shall`
  line `forward the bond to the Court`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (91061)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Warrants to whom directed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91061&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) A warrant of arrest shall ordinarily be directed to one or more`
  line `police officers; but the Court issuing such a warrant may, if its immediate execution is necessary and no police officer is immediately available, direct it to any other person or persons, and such person or persons`
  line `shall execute the same.`
  line
  line `(2) When a warrant is directed to more officers or persons than one, it may be executed by all, or by`
  line `any one or more of them.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (91062)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Warrant may be directed to any person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91062&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Judicial Magistrate or a Magistrate of`
  line `the first class may direct a warrant to any person within his local jurisdiction for the arrest of any escaped`
  line `convict, proclaimed offender or of any person who is accused of a non-bailable offence and is evading`
  line arrest.
  line
  line `(2) Such person shall acknowledge in writing the receipt of the warrant, and shall execute it if the person`
  line `for whose arrest it was issued, is in, or enters on, any land or other property`
  line `under his charge.`
  line
  line `(3) When the person against whom such warrant is issued is arrested, he shall be made over with the`
  line `warrant to the nearest police officer, who shall cause him to be taken before a Magistrate having jurisdiction`
  line `in the case, unless security is taken under section 73.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (91063)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Warrant directed to police officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91063&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `A warrant directed to any police officer may also be executed`
  line `by any other police officer whose name is endorsed upon the warrant by the officer to whom it is directed`
  line `or endorsed.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (91064)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Notification of substance of warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91064&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `The police officer or other person executing a warrant of`
  line `arrest shall notify the substance thereof to the person to be arrested, and, if so required, shall show him`
  line `the warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (91065)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Person arrested to be brought before Court without delay.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91065&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `The police officer or other person`
  line `executing a warrant of arrest shall (subject to the provisions of section 73 as to security) without`
  line `unnecessary delay bring the person arrested before the Court before which he is required by law to produce`
  line `such person:`
  line
  line `Provided that such delay shall not, in any case, exceed twenty-four hours exclusive of the time`
  line `necessary for the journey from the place of arrest to the Magistrate's Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (91066)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Where warrant may be executed.`
  content `A warrant of arrest may be executed at any place in India.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91066&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (91067)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Warrant forwarded for execution outside jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91067&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a warrant is to be executed`
  line `outside the local jurisdiction of the Court issuing it, such Court may, instead of directing the warrant to a`
  line `police officer within its jurisdiction, forward it by post or otherwise to any Executive Magistrate or District`
  line `Superintendent of Police or Commissioner of Police within the local limits of whose jurisdiction it is to be`
  line `executed; and the Executive Magistrate or District Superintendent or Commissioner shall endorse his name`
  line `thereon, and if practicable, cause it to be executed in the manner`
  line `hereinbefore provided.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court issuing a warrant under sub-section (1) shall forward, along with thewarrant, the`
  line `substance of the information against the person to be arrested together with such documents, if any, as may`
  line `be sufficient to enable the Court acting under section 83 to decide whether bail should or should not be`
  line `granted to the person.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (91068)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Warrant directed to police officer for execution outside jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91068&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a warrant`
  line `directed to a police officer is to be executed beyond the local jurisdiction of the Court issuing the same, he`
  line `shall ordinarily take it for endorsement either to an Executive Magistrate or to a police officer not below`
  line `the rank of an officer in charge of a police station, within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the warrant`
  line `is to be executed.`
  line
  line `(2) Such Magistrate or police officer shall endorse his name thereon and such endorsement shall be`
  line `sufficient authority to the police officer to whom the warrant is directed to execute the same, and the local`
  line `police shall, if so required, assist such officer in executing such warrant.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever there is reason to believe that the delay occasioned by obtaining the endorsement of the`
  line `Magistrate or police officer within whose local jurisdiction the warrant is to be executed will prevent such`
  line `execution, the police officer to whom it is directed may execute the same without such endorsement in any`
  line `place beyond the local jurisdiction of the Court which issued it.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (91069)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Procedure on arrest of person against whom warrant issued.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91069&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a warrant of arrest is`
  line `executed outside the district in which it was issued, the person arrested shall, unless the Court which issued`
  line `the warrant is within thirty kilometres of the place of arrest or is nearer than the Executive Magistrate or`
  line `District Superintendent of Police or Commissioner of Police within the local limits of whose jurisdiction`
  line `the arrest was made, or unless security is taken under section 73, be taken before such Magistrate or District`
  line `Superintendent or Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) On the arrest of any person referred to in sub-section (1), the police officer shall forthwith give the`
  line `information regarding such arrest and the place where the arrested person is being held to the designated`
  line `police officer in the district and to such officer of another district where the arrested person normally resides.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (91070)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Procedure by Magistrate before whom such person arrested is brought.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91070&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Executive`
  line `Magistrate or District Superintendent of Police or Commissioner of Police shall, if the person arrested`
  line `appears to be the person intended by the Court which issued the warrant, direct his removal in custody to`
  line `such Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the offence is bailable, and such person is ready and willing to give bail bond to the`
  line `satisfaction of such Magistrate, District Superintendent or Commissioner, or a direction has been endorsed`
  line `under section 73 on the warrant and such person is ready and willing to give the security required by such`
  line `direction, the Magistrate, District Superintendent or Commissioner shall take such bail bond or security, as`
  line `the case may be, and forward the bond, to the Court which issued the warrant:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the offence is a non-bailable one, it shall be lawful for the Chief Judicial`
  line `Magistrate (subject to the provisions of section 480), or the Sessions Judge, of the district in which the`
  line `arrest is made on consideration of the information and the documents referred to in sub-section (2) of section`
  line `80, to release such person on bail.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent a police officer from taking security under`
  line `section 73.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (91537)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Proclamation for person absconding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91537&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any Court has reason to believe (whether after`
  line `taking evidence or not) that any person against whom a warrant has been issued by it has absconded or is`
  line `concealing himself so that such warrant cannot be executed, such Court may publish a written proclamation`
  line `requiring him to appear at a specified place and at a specified time not less than thirty days from the date`
  line `of publishing such proclamation.`
  line
  line `(2) The proclamation shall be published as follows:—`
  line
  line `(i) (a) it shall be publicly read in some conspicuous place of the town or village in which such`
  line `person ordinarily resides;`
  line
  line `(b) it shall be affixed to some conspicuous part of the house or homestead in which such person`
  line `ordinarily resides or to some conspicuous place of such town or village;`
  line
  line `(c) a copy thereof shall be affixed to some conspicuous part of the Court-house;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Court may also, if it thinks fit, direct a copy of the proclamation to be published in a daily`
  line `newspaper circulating in the place in which such person ordinarily resides.`
  line
  line `(3) A statement in writing by the Court issuing the proclamation to the effect that the proclamation was`
  line `duly published on a specified day, in the manner specified in clause (i) ofsub-section (2), shall be conclusive`
  line `evidence that the requirements of this section have been complied with, and that the proclamation was`
  line `published on such day.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a proclamation published under sub-section (1) is in respect of a person accused of an offence`
  line `which is made punishable with imprisonment of ten years or more, or imprisonment for life or with death`
  line `under the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 or under any other law for the time being in force, and such person`
  line `fails to appear at the specified place and time required by the proclamation, the Court may, after making`
  line `such inquiry as it thinks fit, pronounce him a proclaimed offender and make a declaration to that effect.`
  line
  line `(5) The provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) shall apply to a declaration made by the Court under`
  line `sub-section (4) as they apply to the proclamation published`
  line `under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (91072)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Attachment of property of person absconding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91072&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court issuing a proclamation under`
  line `section 84 may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, at any time after the issue of the proclamation, order`
  line `the attachment of any property, movable or immovable, or both, belonging to the proclaimed person:`
  line
  line `Provided that where at the time of the issue of the proclamation the Court is satisfied, by affidavit or`
  line `otherwise, that the person in relation to whom the proclamation is to be issued,—`
  line
  line `(a) is about to dispose of the whole or any part of his`
  line `property; or`
  line
  line `(b) is about to remove the whole or any part of his property from the local jurisdiction of the Court,`
  line `it may order the attachment of property simultaneously with`
  line `the issue of the proclamation.`
  line
  line `(2) Such order shall authorise the attachment of any property belonging to such person within the`
  line `district in which it is made; and it shall authorise the attachment of any property belonging to such person`
  line `without such district when endorsed by the District Magistrate within whose district such property is situate.`
  line
  line `(3) If the property ordered to be attached is a debt or other movable property, the attachment under this`
  line `section shall be made—`
  line
  line `(a) by seizure; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the appointment of a receiver; or`
  line
  line `(c) by an order in writing prohibiting the delivery of such property to the proclaimed person or to`
  line `any one on his behalf; or`
  line
  line `(d) by all or any two of such methods, as the Court thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) If the property ordered to be attached is immovable, the attachment under this section shall, in the`
  line `case of land paying revenue to the State Government, be made through the Collector of the district in which`
  line `the land is situate, and in all other cases—`
  line
  line `(a) by taking possession; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the appointment of a receiver; or`
  line
  line `(c) by an order in writing prohibiting the payment of rent on delivery of property to the proclaimed`
  line `person or to any one on his behalf; or`
  line
  line `(d) by all or any two of such methods, as the Court thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(5) If the property ordered to be attached consists of live-stock or is of a perishable nature, the Court`
  line `may, if it thinks it expedient, order immediate sale thereof, and in such case the proceeds of the sale shall`
  line `abide the order of the Court.`
  line
  line `(6) The powers, duties and liabilities of a receiver appointed under this section shall be the same as`
  line `those of a receiver appointed under the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (91073)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Identification and attachment of property of proclaimed person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91073&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `The Court may, on the`
  line `written request from a police officer not below the rank of the Superintendent of Police or Commissioner`
  line `of Police, initiate the process of requesting assistance from a Court or an authority in the contracting State`
  line `for identification, attachment and forfeiture of property belonging to a proclaimed person in accordance`
  line `with the procedure provided in Chapter VIII.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (91074)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Claims and objections to attachment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91074&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any claim is preferred to, or objection made to the`
  line `attachment of, any property attached under section 85, within six months from the date of such attachment,`
  line `by any person other than the proclaimed person, on the ground that the claimant or objector has an interest`
  line `in such property, and that such interest is not liable to attachment under section 85, the claim or objection`
  line `shall be inquired into, and may be allowed or disallowed in whole or`
  line `in part:`
  line
  line `Provided that any claim preferred or objection made within the period allowed by this sub-section may,`
  line `in the event of the death of the`
  line `claimant or objector, be continued by his legal representative.`
  line
  line `(2) Claims or objections under sub-section (1) may be preferred or made in the Court by which the`
  line `order of attachment is issued, or, if the claim or objection is in respect of property attached under an order`
  line `endorsed under sub-section (2) of section 85, in the Court of the Chief Judicial Magistrate of the district in`
  line `which the attachment is made.`
  line
  line `(3) Every such claim or objection shall be inquired into by the Court in which it is preferred or made:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if it is preferred or made in the Court of a Chief Judicial Magistrate, he may make it over`
  line `for disposal to any Magistrate subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person whose claim or objection has been disallowed in whole or in part by an order under`
  line `sub-section (1) may, within a period of one year from the date of such order, institute a suit to establish the`
  line `right which he claims in respect of the property in dispute; but subject to the result of such suit, if any, the`
  line `order shall be conclusive.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (91075)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Release, sale and restoration of attached property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91075&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the proclaimed person appears within`
  line `the time specified in the proclamation, the Court shall make an order releasing the property from the`
  line attachment.
  line
  line `(2) If the proclaimed person does not appear within the time specified in the proclamation, the property`
  line `under the attachment shall be at the disposal of the State Government; but it shall not be sold until the`
  line `expiration of six months from the date of the attachment and until any claim preferred or objection made`
  line `under section 87 has been disposed of under that section, unless it is subject to speedy and natural decay,`
  line `or the Court considers that the sale would be for the benefit of the owner; in either of which cases the Court`
  line `may cause it to be sold whenever it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) If, within two years from the date of the attachment, any person whose property is or has been at`
  line `the disposal of the State Government under sub-section (2), appears voluntarily or is apprehended and`
  line `brought before the Court by whose order the property was attached, or the Court to which such Court is`
  line `subordinate, and proves to the satisfaction of such Court that he did not abscond or conceal himself for the`
  line `purpose of avoiding execution of the warrant, and that he had not such notice of the proclamation as to`
  line `enable him to attend within the time specified therein, such property, or, if the same has been sold, the net`
  line `proceeds of the sale, or, if part only thereof has been sold, the net proceeds of the sale and the residue of`
  line `the property, shall, after satisfying therefrom all costs incurred in consequence of the attachment, be`
  line `delivered to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (91076)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Appeal from order rejecting application for restoration of attached property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91076&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `referred to in sub-section (3) of section 88, who is aggrieved by any refusal to deliver property or the`
  line `proceeds of the sale thereof may appeal to the Court to which appeals ordinarily lie from the sentences of`
  line `the first-mentioned Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (91538)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Issue of warrant in lieu of, or in addition to, summons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91538&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `A Court may, in any case in which it`
  line `is empowered by this Sanhita to issue a summons for the appearance of any person, issue, after recording`
  line `its reasons in writing, a warrant for his arrest—`
  line
  line `(a) if, either before the issue of such summons, or after the issue of the same but before the time`
  line `fixed for his appearance, the Court sees reason to believe that he has absconded or will not obey the`
  line `summons; or`
  line
  line `(b) if at such time he fails to appear and the summons is proved to have been duly served in time`
  line `to admit of his appearing in accordance therewith and no reasonable excuse is offered for such failure.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (91078)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Power to take bond or bail bond for appearance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91078&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `When any person for whose appearance or`
  line `arrest the officer presiding in any Court is empowered to issue a summons or warrant, is present in such`
  line `Court, such officer may require such person to execute a bond or bail bond for his appearance in such Court,`
  line `or any other Court to which the case may be transferred for trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (91079)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Arrest on breach of bond or bail bond for appearance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91079&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `When any person who is bound by any`
  line `bond or bail bond taken under this Sanhita to appear before a Court, does not appear, the officer presiding`
  line `in such Court may issue a warrant directing that such person be arrested and produced before him`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (91080)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Provisions of this Chapter generally applicable to summons and warrants of arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91080&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line The
  line `provisions contained in this Chapter relating to summons and warrant, and their issue, service and`
  line `execution, shall, so far as may be, apply to every summons and every warrant of arrest issued under this`
  line Sanhita.
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (91539)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Summons to produce document or other thing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91539&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any Court or any officer in`
  line `charge of a police station considers that the production of any document, electronic communication,`
  line `including communication devices, which is likely to contain digital evidence or other thing is necessary or`
  line `desirable for the purposes of any investigation, inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita by or`
  line `before such Court or officer, such Court may issue a summons or such officer may, by a written order,`
  line `either in physical form or in electronic form, require the person in whose possession or power such`
  line `document or thing is believed to be, to attend and produce it, or to produce it, at the time and place stated`
  line `in the summons or order.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person required under this section merely to produce a document, or other thing shall be`
  line `deemed to have complied with the requisition if he causes such document or thing to be produced instead`
  line `of attending personally to produce the same.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be deemed—`
  line
  line `(a) to affect sections 129 and 130 of the Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam, 2023 or the Bankers’ Books`
  line `Evidence Act, 1891 (13 of 1891); or`
  line
  line `(b) to apply to a letter, postcard, or other document or any parcel or thing in the custody of the`
  line `postal authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (91082)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Procedure as to letters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91082&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any document, parcel or thing in the custody of a postal authority`
  line `is, in the opinion of the District Magistrate, Chief Judicial Magistrate, Court of Session or High Court`
  line `wanted for the purpose of any investigation, inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita, such`
  line `Magistrate or Court may require the postal authority to deliver the document, parcel or thing to such person`
  line `as the Magistrate or Court directs.`
  line
  line `(2) If any such document, parcel or thing is, in the opinion of any other Magistrate, whether Executive`
  line `or Judicial, or of any Commissioner of Police or District Superintendent of Police, wanted for any such`
  line `purpose, he may require the postal authority to cause search to be made for and to detain such document,`
  line `parcel or thing pending the order of a District Magistrate, Chief Judicial Magistrate or Court under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (91540)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `When search-warrant may be issued.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91540&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where---`
  line
  line `(a) any Court has reason to believe that a person to whom a summons order under section 94 or a`
  line `requisition under sub-section (1) of section 95 has been, or might be, addressed, will not or would not`
  line `produce the document or thing as required by such summons or`
  line `requisition; or`
  line
  line `(b) such document or thing is not known to the Court to be in the possession of any person; or`
  line
  line `(c) the Court considers that the purposes of any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita will`
  line `be served by a general search or inspection,`
  line
  line `it may issue a search-warrant; and the person to whom such warrant is directed, may search or inspect in`
  line `accordance therewith and the provisions hereinafter contained.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may, if it thinks fit, specify in the warrant the particular place or part thereof to which only`
  line `the search or inspection shall extend; and the person charged with the execution of such warrant shall then search`
  line `or inspect only the place or part so specified.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this section shall authorise any Magistrate other than a District Magistrate or Chief`
  line `Judicial Magistrate to grant a warrant to search for a document, parcel or other thing in the custody of the postal`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (91084)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Search of place suspected to contain stolen property, forged documents, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91084&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a District`
  line `Magistrate, Sub-divisional Magistrate or Magistrate of the first class, upon information and after such inquiry as`
  line `he thinks necessary, has reason to believe that any place is used for the deposit or sale of stolen property, or for`
  line `the deposit, sale or production of any objectionable article to which this section applies, or that any such`
  line `objectionable article is deposited in any place, he may by warrant authorise any police officer above the rank of`
  line `a constable---`
  line
  line `(a) to enter, with such assistance as may be required,`
  line `such place;`
  line
  line `(b) to search the same in the manner specified in the warrant;`
  line
  line `(c) to take possession of any property or article therein found which he reasonably suspects to be stolen`
  line `property or objectionable article to which this section applies;`
  line
  line `(d) to convey such property or article before a Magistrate, or to guard the same on the spot until the`
  line `offender is taken before a Magistrate, or otherwise to dispose of it in`
  line `some place of safety;`
  line
  line `(e) to take into custody and carry before a Magistrate every person found in such place who appears to`
  line `have been privy to the deposit, sale or production of any such property or article knowing or having`
  line `reasonable cause to suspect it to be stolen property or,`
  line `as the case may be, objectionable article to which`
  line `this section applies.`
  line
  line `(2) The objectionable articles to which this section applies are---`
  line
  line `(a) counterfeit coin;`
  line
  line `(b) pieces of metal made in contravention of the Coinage Act, 2011 (11 of 2011), or brought into India`
  line `in contravention of any notification for the time being in force issued under section 11 of the Customs`
  line `Act, 1962 (52 of 1962);`
  line
  line `(c) counterfeit currency note; counterfeit stamps;`
  line
  line `(d) forged documents;`
  line
  line `(e) false seals;`
  line
  line `(f) obscene objects referred to in section 294 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023);`
  line
  line `(g) instruments or materials used for the production of any of the articles mentioned in`
  line `clauses (a) to (f).`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (91085)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Power to declare certain publications forfeited and to issue search-warrants for same.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91085&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where—`
  line
  line `(a) any newspaper, or book; or`
  line
  line `(b) any document,`
  line
  line `wherever printed, appears to the State Government to contain any matter the publication of which is`
  line `punishable under section 152 or section 196 or section 197 or section 294 or section 295 or section 299 of`
  line `the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) , the State Government may, by notification, stating the`
  line `grounds of its opinion, declare every copy of the issue of the newspaper containing such matter, and every`
  line `copy of such book or other document to be forfeited to Government, and thereupon any police officer may`
  line `seize the same wherever found in India and any Magistrate may by warrant authorise any police officer not`
  line `below the rank of sub-inspector to enter upon and search for the same in any premises where any copy of`
  line `such issue, or any such book or other document may be or may be reasonably suspected to be.`
  line
  line `(2) In this section and in section 99,—`
  line
  line `(a) “newspaper” and “book” have the same meanings as in the Press and Registration of Books`
  line `Act, 1867 (25 of 1867);`
  line
  line `(b) “document” includes any painting, drawing or photograph, or other visible representation.`
  line
  line `(3) No order passed or action taken under this section shall be called in question in any Court otherwise`
  line `than in accordance with the provisions of section 99.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (91086)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Application to High Court to set aside declaration of forfeiture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91086&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person having any`
  line `interest in any newspaper, book or other document, in respect of which a declaration of forfeiture has been`
  line `made under section 98, may, within two months from the date of publication in the Official Gazette of such`
  line `declaration, apply to the High Court to set aside such declaration on the ground that the issue of the`
  line `newspaper, or the book or other document, in respect of which the declaration was made, did not contain`
  line `any such matter as is referred to in sub-section (1) of section 98.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such application shall, where the High Court consists of three or more Judges, be heard and`
  line `determined by a Special Bench of the High Court composed of three Judges and where the High Court`
  line `consists of less than three Judges, such Special Bench shall be composed of all the Judges of that High`
  line Court.
  line
  line `(3) On the hearing of any such application with reference to any newspaper, any copy of such`
  line `newspaper may be given in evidence in aid of the proof of the nature or tendency of the words, signs or`
  line `visible representations contained in such newspaper, in respect of which the declaration of forfeiture was`
  line made.
  line
  line `(4) The High Court shall, if it is not satisfied that the issue of the newspaper, or the book or other`
  line `document, in respect of which the application has been made, contained any such matter as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 98, set aside the declaration of forfeiture.`
  line
  line `(5) Where there is a difference of opinion among the Judges forming the Special Bench, the decision`
  line `shall be in accordance with the opinion of the majority of those Judges.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (91087)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Search for persons wrongfully confined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91087&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `If any District Magistrate, Sub-divisional Magistrate`
  line `or Magistrate of the first class has reason to believe that any person is confined under such circumstances`
  line `that the confinement amounts to an offence, he may issue a search-warrant, and the person to whom such`
  line `warrant is directed may search for the person so confined; and such search shall be made in accordance`
  line `therewith, and the person, if found, shall be immediately taken before a Magistrate, who shall make such`
  line `order as in the circumstances of the case seems proper.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (91088)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Power to compel restoration of abducted females.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91088&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `Upon complaint made on oath of the`
  line `abduction or unlawful detention of a woman, or a female child for any unlawful purpose, a District`
  line `Magistrate, Sub-divisional Magistrate or Magistrate of the first class may make an order for the immediate`
  line `restoration of such woman to her liberty, or of such female child to her parent, guardian or other person`
  line `having the lawful charge of such child, and may compel compliance with such order, using such force as`
  line `may be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (91541)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Direction, etc., of search-warrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91541&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 32, 72, 74, 76, 79, 80 and 81`
  line `shall, so far as may be, apply to all search-warrants issued under section 96, section 97, section 98 or`
  line `section 100.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (91090)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Persons in charge of closed place to allow search.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91090&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any place liable to search or`
  line `inspection under this Chapter is closed, any person residing in, or being in charge of, such place, shall, on`
  line `demand of the officer or other person executing the warrant, and on production of the warrant, allow him`
  line `free ingress thereto, and afford all reasonable facilities for a search therein.`
  line
  line `(2) If ingress into such place cannot be so obtained, the officer or other person executing the warrant`
  line `may proceed in the manner provided by sub-section (2) of section 44.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any person in or about such place is reasonably suspected of concealing about his person`
  line `any article for which search should be made, such person may be searched and if such person is a woman,`
  line `the search shall be made by another woman with strict regard to decency.`
  line
  line `(4) Before making a search under this Chapter, the officer or other person about to make it shall call`
  line `upon two or more independent and respectable inhabitants of the locality in which the place to be searched`
  line `is situate or of any other locality if no such inhabitant of the said locality is available or is willing to be a`
  line `witness to the search, to attend and witness the search and may issue an order in writing to them or any of`
  line `them so to do.`
  line
  line `(5) The search shall be made in their presence, and a list of all things seized in the course of such search`
  line `and of the places in which they are respectively found shall be prepared by such officer or other person and`
  line `signed by such witnesses; but no person witnessing a search under this section shall be required to attend`
  line `the Court as a witness of the search unless specially summoned by it.`
  line
  line `(6) The occupant of the place searched, or some person in his behalf, shall, in every instance, be`
  line `permitted to attend during the search, and a copy of the list prepared under this section, signed by the said`
  line `witnesses, shall be delivered to such occupant or person.`
  line
  line `(7) When any person is searched under sub-section (3), a list of all things taken possession of shall be`
  line `prepared, and a copy thereof shall be delivered to such person.`
  line
  line `(8) Any person who, without reasonable cause, refuses or neglects to attend and witness a search under`
  line `this section, when called upon to do so by an order in writing delivered or tendered to him, shall be deemed`
  line `to have committed an offence under section 222 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (91091)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Disposal of things found in search beyond jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91091&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `When, in the execution of a searchwarrant at any place beyond the local jurisdiction of the Court which issued the same, any of the things for`
  line `which search is made, are found, such things, together with the list of the same prepared under the provisions hereinafter contained, shall be immediately taken before the Court issuing the warrant, unless`
  line `such place is nearer to the Magistrate having jurisdiction therein than to such Court, in which case the list`
  line `and things shall be immediately taken before such Magistrate; and, unless there be good cause to the`
  line `contrary, such Magistrate shall make an order authorising them to be taken to such Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (91542)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Recording of search and seizure through audio video electronic means..`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91542&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `The process of`
  line `conducting search of a place or taking possession of any property, article or thing under this Chapter or`
  line `under section 185, including preparation of the list of all things seized in the course of such search and`
  line `seizure and signing of such list by witnesses, shall be recorded through any audio-video electronic means`
  line `preferably mobile phone and the police officer shall without delay forward such recording to the District`
  line `Magistrate, Sub-divisional Magistrate or Judicial Magistrate of the first class.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (91093)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Power of police officer to seize certain property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91093&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any police officer may seize any property`
  line `which may be alleged or suspected to have been stolen, or which may be found under circumstances which`
  line `create suspicion of the commission of any offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Such police officer, if subordinate to the officer in charge of a police station, shall forthwith report`
  line `the seizure to that officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Every police officer acting under sub-section (1) shall forthwith report the seizure to the Magistrate`
  line `having jurisdiction and where the property seized is such that it cannot be conveniently transported to the`
  line `Court, or where there is difficulty in securing proper accommodation for the custody of such property, or`
  line `where the continued retention of the property in police custody may not be considered necessary for the`
  line `purpose of investigation, he may give custody thereof to any person on his executing a bond undertaking`
  line `to produce the property before the Court as and when required and to give effect to the further orders of the`
  line `Court as to the disposal of the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the property seized under sub-section (1) is subject to speedy and natural decay`
  line `and if the person entitled to the possession of such property is unknown or absent and the value of such`
  line `property is less than five hundred rupees, it may forthwith be sold by auction under the orders of the`
  line `Superintendent of Police and the provisions of sections 503 and 504 shall, as nearly as may be practicable,`
  line `apply to the net proceeds of such sale`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (91094)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Attachment, forfeiture or restoration of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91094&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a police officer making an`
  line `investigation has reason to believe that any property is derived or obtained, directly or indirectly, as a result`
  line `of a criminal activity or from the commission of any offence, he may, with the approval of the`
  line `Superintendent of Police or Commissioner of Police, make an application to the Court or the Magistrate`
  line `exercising jurisdiction to take cognizance of the offence or commit for trial or try the case, for the`
  line `attachment of such property.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Court or the Magistrate has reasons to believe, whether before or after taking evidence, that`
  line `all or any of such properties are proceeds of crime, the Court or the Magistrate may issue a notice upon`
  line `such person calling upon him to show cause within a period of fourteen days as to why an order of`
  line `attachment shall not be made.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the notice issued to any person under sub-section (2) specifies any property as being held by`
  line `any other person on behalf of such person, a copy of the notice shall also be served upon such other person.`
  line
  line `(4) The Court or the Magistrate may, after considering the explanation, if any, to the show-cause notice`
  line `issued under sub-section (2) and the material fact available before such Court or Magistrate and after giving`
  line `a reasonable opportunity of being heard to such person or persons, may pass an order of attachment, in`
  line `respect of those properties which are found to be the proceeds of crime:`
  line
  line `Provided that if such person does not appear before the Court or the Magistrate or represent his case`
  line `before the Court or Magistrate within a period of fourteen days specified in the show-cause notice, the`
  line `Court or the Magistrate may proceed to pass the ex parte order.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), if the Court or the Magistrate is of the`
  line `opinion that issuance of notice under the said sub-section would defeat the object of attachment or seizure,`
  line `the Court or Magistrate may by an interim order passed ex parte direct attachment or seizure of such`
  line `property, and such order shall remain in force till an order under sub-section (6) is passed.`
  line
  line `(6) If the Court or the Magistrate finds the attached or seized properties to be the proceeds of crime, the`
  line `Court or the Magistrate shall by order direct the District Magistrate to rateably distribute such proceeds of`
  line `crime to the persons who are affected by such crime.`
  line
  line `(7) On receipt of an order passed under sub-section (6), the District Magistrate shall, within a period of`
  line `sixty days distribute the proceeds of crime either by himself or authorise any officer subordinate to him to`
  line `effect such distribution.`
  line
  line `(8) If there are no claimants to receive such proceeds or no claimant is ascertainable or there is any`
  line `surplus after satisfying the claimants, such proceeds of crime shall stand forfeited to the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (91095)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Magistrate may direct search in his presence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91095&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `Any Magistrate may direct a search to be made`
  line `in his presence of any place for the search of which he is competent to issue a search-warrant`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (91096)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Power to impound document, etc., produced.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91096&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `Any Court may, if it thinks fit, impound any`
  line `document or thing produced before it under this Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (91097)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Reciprocal arrangements regarding processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91097&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Court in the territories to which`
  line `this Sanhita extends (hereafter in this section referred to as the said territories)`
  line `desires that---`
  line
  line `(a) a summons to an accused person; or`
  line
  line `(b) a warrant for the arrest of an accused person; or`
  line
  line `(c) a summons to any person requiring him to attend and produce a document or other thing, or to`
  line `produce it; or`
  line
  line `(d) a search-warrant,`
  line
  line `issued by it shall be served or executed at any place,---`
  line
  line `(i) within the local jurisdiction of a Court in any State or area in India outside the said territories, it`
  line `may send such summons or warrant in duplicate by post or otherwise, to the presiding officer of that Court to be served or executed; and where any summons referred to in clause (a) or clause (c) has been so served, the provisions of section 70 shall apply in relation to such summons as if the presiding officer`
  line `of the Court to whom it is sent were a Magistrate in the said territories;`
  line
  line `(ii) in any country or place outside India in respect of which arrangements have been made by the`
  line `Central Government with the Government of such country or place for service or execution of summons`
  line `or warrant in relation to criminal matters (hereafter in this section referred to as the contracting State),`
  line `it may send such summons or warrant in duplicate in such form, directed to such Court, Judge or`
  line `Magistrate, and send to such authority for transmission, as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a Court in the said territories has received for service or execution---`
  line
  line `(a) a summons to an accused person; or`
  line
  line `(b) a warrant for the arrest of an accused person; or`
  line
  line `(c) a summons to any person requiring him to attend and produce a document or other thing, or to`
  line `produce it; or`
  line
  line `(d) a search-warrant,`
  line
  line `issued by---`
  line
  line `(I) a Court in any State or area in India outside the said territories;`
  line
  line `(II) a Court, Judge or Magistrate in a contracting State,`
  line
  line `it shall cause the same to be served or executed as if it were a summons or warrant received by it from`
  line `another Court in the said territories for service or execution within its local jurisdiction; and where`
  line
  line `(i) a warrant of arrest has been executed, the person arrested shall, so far as possible, be dealt with`
  line `in accordance with the procedure specified by sections 82 and 83;`
  line
  line `(ii) a search-warrant has been executed, the things found in the search shall, so far as possible, be`
  line `dealt with in accordance with the procedure specified by section 104:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a case where a summons or search-warrant received from a contracting State has been`
  line `executed, the documents or things produced or things found in the search shall be forwarded to the Court`
  line `issuing the summons or search-warrant through such authority as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify in this behalf`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (91098)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91098&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "contracting State" means any country or place outside India in respect of which arrangements`
  line `have been made by the Central Government with the Government of such country through a treaty or`
  line otherwise;
  line
  line `(b) "identifying" includes establishment of a proof that the property was derived from, or used in,`
  line `the commission of an offence;`
  line
  line `(c) "proceeds of crime" means any property derived or obtained directly or indirectly, by any person`
  line `as a result of criminal activity (including crime involving currency transfers) or the value of any such`
  line property;
  line
  line `(d) "property" means property and assets of every description whether corporeal or incorporeal,`
  line `movable or immovable, tangible or intangible and deeds and instruments evidencing title to, or interest`
  line `in, such property or assets derived or used in the commission of an offence and includes property`
  line `obtained through proceeds of crime;`
  line
  line `(e) "tracing" means determining the nature, source, disposition, movement, title or ownership of`
  line property.
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (91099)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Letter of request to competent authority for investigation in a country or place outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91099&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the course of an investigation into an offence, an application is made by the investigating`
  line `officer or any officer superior in rank to the investigating officer that evidence may be available in a country`
  line `or place outside India, any Criminal Court may issue a letter of request to a Court or an authority in that`
  line `country or place competent to deal with such request to examine orally any person supposed to be`
  line `acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case and to record his statement made in the course of`
  line `such examination and also to require such person or any other person to produce any document or thing`
  line `which may be in his possession pertaining to the case and to forward all the evidence so taken or collected`
  line `or the authenticated copies thereof or the thing so collected to the Court issuing such letter.`
  line
  line `(2) The letter of request shall be transmitted in such manner as the Central Government may specify in`
  line `this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Every statement recorded or document or thing received under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to`
  line `be the evidence collected during the course of investigation under this Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (91543)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Letter of request from a country or place outside India to a Court or an authority for investigation in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91543&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) Upon receipt of a letter of request from a Court or an authority in a country or`
  line `place outside India competent to issue such letter in that country or place for the examination of any person`
  line `or production of any document or thing in relation to an offence under investigation in that country or place,`
  line `the Central Government may, if it thinks fit---`
  line
  line `(i) forward the same to the Chief Judicial Magistrate or Judicial Magistrate as he may appoint in`
  line `this behalf, who shall thereupon summon the person before him and record his statement or cause the`
  line `document or thing to be produced; or`
  line
  line `(ii) send the letter to any police officer for investigation, who shall thereupon investigate into the`
  line `offence in the same manner,`
  line
  line `as if the offence had been committed within India.`
  line
  line `(2) All the evidence taken or collected under sub-section (1), or authenticated copies thereof or the`
  line `thing so collected, shall be forwarded by the Magistrate or police officer, as the case may be, to the Central`
  line `Government for transmission to the Court or the authority issuing the letter of request, in such manner as`
  line `the Central Government may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (91101)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Assistance in securing transfer of persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91101&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Court in India, in relation to a criminal`
  line `matter, desires that a warrant for arrest of any person to attend or produce a document or other thing issued`
  line `by it shall be executed in any place in a contracting State, it shall send such warrant in duplicate in such`
  line `form to such Court, Judge or Magistrate through such authority, as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify in this behalf and that Court, Judge or Magistrate, as the case may be, shall cause the`
  line `same to be executed.`
  line
  line `(2) If , in the course of an investigation or any inquiry into an offence, an application is made by the`
  line `investigating officer or any officer superior in rank to the investigating officer that the attendance of a`
  line `person who is in any place in a contracting State is required in connection with such investigation or inquiry`
  line `and the Court is satisfied that such attendance is so required, it shall issue a summons or warrant, in`
  line `duplicate, against the said person to such Court, Judge or Magistrate, in such form as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf, to cause the same to be served or executed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a Court in India, in relation to a criminal matter, has received a warrant for arrest of any`
  line `person requiring him to attend or attend and produce a document or other thing in that Court or before any`
  line `other investigating agency, issued by a Court, Judge or Magistrate in a contracting State, the same shall be`
  line `executed as if it is the warrant received by it from another Court in India for execution within its local`
  line limits.
  line
  line `(4) Where a person transferred to a contracting State pursuant to sub-section (3) is a prisoner in India,`
  line `the Court in India or the Central Government may impose such conditions as that Court or Government`
  line `deems fit.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the person transferred to India pursuant to sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) is a prisoner in`
  line `a contracting State, the Court in India shall ensure that the conditions subject to which the prisoner is`
  line `transferred to India are complied with and such prisoner shall be kept in such custody subject to such`
  line `conditions as the Central Government may direct in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (91102)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Assistance in relation to orders of attachment or forfeiture of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91102&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a Court`
  line `in India has reasonable grounds to believe that any property obtained by any person is derived or obtained,`
  line `directly or indirectly, by such person from the commission of an offence, it may make an order of`
  line `attachment or forfeiture of such property, as it may deem fit under the provisions of sections 116 to 122`
  line `(both inclusive).`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Court has made an order for attachment or forfeiture of any property under`
  line `sub-section (1), and such property is suspected to be in a contracting State, the Court may issue a letter of`
  line `request to a Court or an authority in the contracting State for execution of such order.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a letter of request is received by the Central Government from a Court or an authority in a`
  line `contracting State requesting attachment or forfeiture of the property in India, derived or obtained, directly`
  line `or indirectly, by any person from the commission of an offence committed in that contracting State, the`
  line `Central Government may forward such letter of request to the Court, as it thinks fit, for execution in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sections 116 to 122 (both inclusive) or, as the case may be, any other law`
  line `for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (91103)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Identifying unlawfully acquired property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91103&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court shall, under sub-section (1), or on`
  line `receipt of a letter of request under sub-section (3) of section 115, direct any police officer not below the`
  line `rank of Sub-Inspector of Police to take all steps necessary for tracing and identifying such property.`
  line
  line `(2) The steps referred to in sub-section (1) may include any inquiry, investigation or survey in respect`
  line `of any person, place, property, assets, documents, books of account in any bank or public financial`
  line `institutions or any other relevant matters.`
  line
  line `(3) Any inquiry, investigation or survey referred to in sub-section (2) shall be carried out by an officer`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (1) in accordance with such directions issued by the said Court in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (91104)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Seizure or attachment of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91104&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any officer conducting an inquiry or`
  line `investigation under section 116 has a reason to believe that any property in relation to which such inquiry`
  line `or investigation is being conducted is likely to be concealed, transferred or dealt with in any manner which`
  line `will result in disposal of such property, he may make an order for seizing such property and where it is not`
  line `practicable to seize such property, he may make an order of attachment directing that such property shall`
  line `not be transferred or otherwise dealt with, except with the prior permission of the officer making such order,`
  line `and a copy of such order shall be served on the person concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any order made under sub-section (1) shall have no effect unless the said order is confirmed by an`
  line `order of the said Court, within a period of thirty days of its being made.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (91105)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Management of properties seized or forfeited under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91105&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court may appoint`
  line `the District Magistrate of the area where the property is situated, or any other officer that may be nominated`
  line `by the District Magistrate, to perform the functions of an Administrator of such property.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator appointed under sub-section (1) shall receive and manage the property in relation`
  line `to which the order has been made under sub-section (1) of section 117 or under section 120 in such manner`
  line `and subject to such conditions as may be specified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Administrator shall also take such measures, as the Central Government may direct, to dispose`
  line `of the property which is forfeited to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (91106)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Notice of forfeiture of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91106&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `(1) If as a result of the inquiry, investigation or survey under`
  line `section 116, the Court has reason to believe that all or any of such properties are proceeds of crime, it may`
  line `serve a notice upon such person (hereinafter referred to as the person affected) calling upon him within a`
  line `period of thirty days specified in the notice to indicate the source of income, earnings or assets, out of which`
  line `or by means of which he has acquired such property, the evidence on which he relies and other relevant`
  line `information and particulars, and to show cause why all or any of such properties, as the case may be, should`
  line `not be declared to be proceeds of crime and forfeited to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a notice under sub-section (1) to any person specifies any property as being held on behalf`
  line `of such person by any other person, a copy of the notice shall also be served upon such other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (91107)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Forfeiture of property in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91107&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court may, after considering the explanation,`
  line `if any, to the show-cause notice issued under section 119 and the material available before it and after giving`
  line `to the person affected (and in a case where the person affected holds any property specified in the notice`
  line `through any other person, to such other person also) a reasonable opportunity of being heard, by order,`
  line `record a finding whether all or any of the properties in question are proceeds of crime:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the person affected (and in a case where the person affected holds any property specified`
  line `in the notice through any other person such other person also) does not appear before the Court or represent`
  line `his case before it within a period of thirty days specified in the show-cause notice, the Court may proceed`
  line `to record a finding under this sub-section ex parte on the basis of evidence available before it.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Court is satisfied that some of the properties referred to in the show-cause notice are`
  line `proceeds of crime but it is not possible to identify specifically such properties, then, it shall be lawful for`
  line `the Court to specify the properties which, to the best of its judgment, are proceeds of crime and record a`
  line `finding accordingly under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Court records a finding under this section to the effect that any property is proceeds of`
  line `crime, such property shall stand forfeited to the Central Government free from all encumbrances.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any shares in a company stand forfeited to the Central Government under this section, then,`
  line `the company shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) or the`
  line `Articles of Association of the company, forthwith register the Central Government as the transferee of such`
  line shares.
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (91108)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Fine in lieu of forfeiture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91108&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Court makes a declaration that any property stands`
  line `forfeited to the Central Government under section 120 and it is a case where the source of only a part of`
  line `such property has not been proved to the satisfaction of the Court, it shall make an order giving an option`
  line `to the person affected to pay, in lieu of forfeiture, a fine equal to the market value of such part.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making an order imposing a fine under sub-section (1), the person affected shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the person affected pays the fine due under sub-section (1), within such time as may be`
  line `allowed in that behalf, the Court may, by order, revoke the declaration of forfeiture under section 120 and`
  line `thereupon such property shall stand released.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (91109)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Certain transfers to be null and void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91109&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `Where after the making of an order under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 117 or the issue of a notice under section 119, any property referred to in the said`
  line `order or notice is transferred by any mode whatsoever such transfers shall, for the purposes of the`
  line `proceedings under this Chapter, be ignored and if such property is subsequently forfeited to the Central`
  line `Government under section 120, then, the transfer of such property shall be deemed to be null and void.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (91110)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Procedure in respect of letter of request.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91110&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `Every letter of request, summons or warrant, received`
  line `by the Central Government from, and every letter of request, summons or warrant, to be transmitted to a`
  line `contracting State under this Chapter shall be transmitted to a contracting State or, as the case may be, sent`
  line `to the concerned Court in India in such form and in such manner as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (91111)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Application of this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91111&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, direct that the application of this Chapter in relation to a contracting State with which reciprocal`
  line `arrangements have been made, shall be subject to such conditions, exceptions or qualifications as are`
  line `specified in the said notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (91112)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Security for keeping peace on conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91112&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a Court of Session or Court of a Magistrate`
  line `of the first class convicts a person of any of the offences specified in sub-section (2) or of abetting any such`
  line `offence and is of opinion that it is necessary to take security from such person for keeping the peace, the`
  line `Court may, at the time of passing sentence on such person, order him to execute a bond or bail bond, for`
  line `keeping the peace for such period, not exceeding three years, as it thinks fit..`
  line
  line `(2) The offences referred to in sub-section (1) are---`
  line
  line `(a) any offence punishable under Chapter XI of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023),`
  line `other than an offence punishable under sub-section (1) of section 193 or section 196 or section 197`
  line thereof;
  line
  line `(b) any offence which consists of, or includes, assault or using criminal force or committing`
  line mischief;
  line
  line `(c) any offence of criminal intimidation;`
  line
  line `(d) any other offence which caused, or was intended or known to be likely to cause, a breach of the`
  line peace.
  line
  line `(3) If the conviction is set aside on appeal or otherwise, the bond or bail bond so executed shall become`
  line void.
  line
  line `(4) An order under this section may also be made by an Appellate Court or by a Court when exercising`
  line `its powers of revision.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (91113)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Security for keeping peace in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91113&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an Executive Magistrate receives`
  line `information that any person is likely to commit a breach of the peace or disturb the public tranquillity or to`
  line `do any wrongful act that may probably occasion a breach of the peace or disturb the public tranquillity and`
  line `is of opinion that there is sufficient ground for proceeding, he may, in the manner hereinafter provided,`
  line `require such person to show cause why he should not be ordered to execute a bond or bail bond for keeping`
  line `the peace for such period, not exceeding one year, as the Magistrate thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Proceedings under this section may be taken before any Executive Magistrate when either the place`
  line `where the breach of the peace or disturbance is apprehended is within his local jurisdiction or there is within`
  line `such jurisdiction a person who is likely to commit a breach of the peace or disturb the public tranquillity or`
  line `to do any wrongful act as aforesaid beyond such jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (91114)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Security for good behaviour from persons disseminating certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91114&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an`
  line `Executive Magistrate receives information that there is within his local jurisdiction any person who, within`
  line `or without such jurisdiction,—`
  line
  line `(i) either orally or in writing or in any other manner, intentionally disseminates or attempts to`
  line `disseminate or abets the dissemination of,—`
  line
  line `(a) any matter the publication of which is punishable under section 152 or section 196 or`
  line `section 197 or section 299 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023); or`
  line
  line `(b) any matter concerning a Judge acting or purporting to act in the discharge of his official`
  line `duties which amounts to criminal intimidation or defamation under the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita,`
  line 2023;
  line
  line `(ii) makes, produces, publishes or keeps for sale, imports, exports, conveys, sells, lets to hire,`
  line `distributes, publicly exhibits or in any other manner puts into circulation any obscene matter such as is`
  line `referred to in section 294 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023,`
  line
  line `and the Magistrate is of opinion that there is sufficient ground for proceeding, the Magistrate may, in the`
  line `manner hereinafter provided, require such person to show cause why he should not be ordered to execute a`
  line `bond or bail bond, for his good behaviour for such period, not exceeding one year, as the Magistrate thinks`
  line fit.
  line
  line `(2) No proceedings shall be taken under this section against the editor, proprietor, printer or publisher`
  line `of any publication registered under, and edited, printed and published in conformity with, the rules laid`
  line `down in the Press and Registration of Books Act, 1867 (25 of 1867) with reference to any matter contained`
  line `in such publication except by the order or under the authority of the State Government or some officer`
  line `empowered by the State Government in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (91115)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Security for good behaviour from suspected persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91115&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `When an Executive Magistrate receives`
  line `information that there is within his local jurisdiction a person taking precautions to conceal his presence`
  line `and that there is reason to believe that he is doing so with a view to committing a cognizable offence, the`
  line `Magistrate may, in the manner hereinafter provided, require such person to show cause why he should not`
  line `be ordered to execute a bond or bail bond for his good behaviour for such period, not exceeding one year,`
  line `as the Magistrate thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (91116)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Security for good behaviour from habitual offenders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91116&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `When an Executive Magistrate`
  line `receives information that there is within his local jurisdiction a person who---`
  line
  line `(a) is by habit a robber, house-breaker, thief, or forger; or`
  line
  line `(b) is by habit a receiver of stolen property knowing the same to have been stolen; or`
  line
  line `(c) habitually protects or harbours thieves, or aids in the concealment or disposal of stolen property;`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) habitually commits, or attempts to commit, or abets the commission of, the offence of`
  line `kidnapping, abduction, extortion, cheating or mischief, or any offence punishable under Chapter X of`
  line `the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, or under section 178, section 179, section 180 or section 181 of`
  line `that Sanhita; or`
  line
  line `(e) habitually commits, or attempts to commit, or abets the commission of, offences, involving a`
  line `breach of the peace; or`
  line
  line `(f) habitually commits, or attempts to commit, or abets the commission of---`
  line
  line `(i) any offence under one or more of the following Acts, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the Drugs and Cosmetics Act, 1940 (23 of 1940.);`
  line
  line `(b) the Foreigners Act, 1946 (31 of 1946);`
  line
  line `(c) the Employees' Provident Fund and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952);`
  line
  line `(d) the Essential Commodities Act, 1955 (10 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(e) the Protection of Civil Rights Act, 1955 (22 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(f) the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962);`
  line
  line `(g) the Food Safety and Standards Act, 2006 (34 of 2006); or`
  line
  line `(ii) any offence punishable under any other law providing for the prevention of hoarding or profiteering or of adulteration of food or drugs or of corruption; or`
  line
  line `(g) is so desperate and dangerous as to render his being at large without security hazardous to the`
  line community,
  line
  line `such Magistrate may, in the manner hereinafter provided, require such person to show cause why he`
  line `should not be ordered to execute a bail bond, for his good behaviour for such period, not exceeding three`
  line `years, as the Magistrate thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (91117)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Order to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91117&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `When a Magistrate acting under section 126, section 127, section 128 or`
  line `section 129, deems it necessary to require any person to show cause under such section, he shall make an`
  line `order in writing, setting forth the substance of the information received, the amount of the bond to be`
  line `executed, the term for which it is to be in force and the number of sureties, after considering the sufficiency`
  line `and fitness of sureties.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (91118)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Procedure in respect of person present in Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91118&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `If the person in respect of whom such order`
  line `is made is present in Court, it shall be read over to him, or, if he so desires, the substance thereof shall be`
  line `explained to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (91119)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `Summons or warrant in case of person not so present.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91119&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `If such person is not present in Court,`
  line `the Magistrate shall issue a summons requiring him to appear, or, when such person is in custody, a warrant`
  line `directing the officer in whose custody he is to bring him before the Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that whenever it appears to such Magistrate, upon the report of a police officer or upon other`
  line `information (the substance of which report or information shall be recorded by the Magistrate), that there`
  line `is reason to fear the commission of a breach of the peace, and that such breach of the peace cannot be`
  line `prevented otherwise than by the immediate arrest of such person, the Magistrate may at any time issue a`
  line `warrant for his arrest.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (91120)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Copy of order to accompany summons or warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91120&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `Every summons or warrant issued under`
  line `section 132 shall be accompanied by a copy of the order made under section 130, and such copy shall be`
  line `delivered by the officer serving or executing such summons or warrant to the person served with, or arrested`
  line `under, the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (91121)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Power to dispense with personal attendance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91121&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `The Magistrate may, if he sees sufficient cause,`
  line `dispense with the personal attendance of any person called upon to show cause why he should not be ordered`
  line `to execute a bond for keeping the peace or for good behaviour and may permit him to appear by an advocate.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (91122)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Inquiry as to truth of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91122&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an order under section 130 has been read or`
  line `explained under section 131 to a person present in Court, or when any person appears or is brought before`
  line `a Magistrate in compliance with, or in execution of, a summons or warrant, issued under section 132, the`
  line `Magistrate shall proceed to inquire into the truth of the information upon which action has been taken, and`
  line `to take such further evidence as may appear necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) Such inquiry shall be made, as nearly as may be practicable, in the manner hereinafter prescribed`
  line `for conducting trial and recording evidence in summons-cases.`
  line
  line `(3) After the commencement, and before the completion, of the inquiry under sub-section (1), the`
  line `Magistrate, if he considers that immediate measures are necessary for the prevention of a breach of the`
  line `peace or disturbance of the public tranquillity or the commission of any offence or for the public safety,`
  line `may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, direct the person in respect of whom the order under section 130`
  line `has been made to execute a bond or bail bond, for keeping the peace or maintaining good behaviour until`
  line `the conclusion of the inquiry, and may detain him in custody until such bond or bail bond is executed or, in`
  line `default of execution, until the inquiry is concluded:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) no person against whom proceedings are not being taken under section 127, section 128, or`
  line `section 129 shall be directed to execute a bond or bail bond for maintaining good behaviour;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions of such bond, whether as to the amount thereof or as to the provision of sureties`
  line `or the number thereof or the pecuniary extent of their liability, shall not be more onerous than those`
  line `specified in the order under section 130.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this section the fact that a person is a habitual offender or is so desperate and`
  line `dangerous as to render his being at large without security hazardous to the community may be proved by`
  line `evidence of general repute or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(5) Where two or more persons have been associated together in the matter under inquiry, they may be`
  line `dealt with in the same or separate inquiries as the Magistrate shall think just.`
  line
  line `(6) The inquiry under this section shall be completed within a period of six months from the date of its`
  line `commencement, and if such inquiry is not so completed, the proceedings under this Chapter shall, on the`
  line `expiry of the said period, stand terminated unless, for special reasons to be recorded in writing, the`
  line `Magistrate otherwise directs:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any person has been kept in detention pending such inquiry, the proceeding against`
  line `that person, unless terminated earlier, shall stand terminated on the expiry of a period of six months of such`
  line detention.
  line
  line `(7) Where any direction is made under sub-section (6) permitting the continuance of proceedings, the`
  line `Sessions Judge may, on an application made to him by the aggrieved party, vacate such direction if he is`
  line `satisfied that it was not based on any special reason or was perverse.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (91123)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Order to give security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91123&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `If, upon such inquiry, it is proved that it is necessary for keeping the`
  line `peace or maintaining good behaviour, as the case may be, that the person in respect of whom the inquiry is`
  line `made should execute a bond or bail bond, the Magistrate shall make an order accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) no person shall be ordered to give security of a nature different from, or of an amount larger`
  line `than, or for a period longer than, that specified in the order made under section 130;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of every bond or bail bond shall be fixed with due regard to the circumstances of`
  line `the case and shall not be excessive;`
  line
  line `(c) when the person in respect of whom the inquiry is made is a child, the bond shall be executed`
  line `only by his sureties.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (91124)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Discharge of person informed against.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91124&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `If, on an inquiry under section 135, it is not proved that`
  line `it is necessary for keeping the peace or maintaining good behaviour, as the case may be, that the person in`
  line `respect of whom the inquiry is made, should execute a bond, the Magistrate shall make an entry on the`
  line `record to that effect, and if such person is in custody only for the purposes of the inquiry, shall release him,`
  line `or, if such person is not in custody, shall discharge him.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (91125)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Commencement of period for which security is required.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91125&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person, in respect of`
  line `whom an order requiring security is made under section 125 or section 136, is at the time such order is`
  line `made, sentenced to, or undergoing a sentence of, imprisonment, the period for which such security is`
  line `required shall commence on the expiration of such sentence.`
  line
  line `(2) In other cases such period shall commence on the date of such order unless the Magistrate, for`
  line `sufficient reason, fixes a later date.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (91126)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Contents of bond.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91126&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `The bond or bail bond to be executed by any such person shall bind him to`
  line `keep the peace or to be of good behaviour, as the case may be, and in the latter case the commission or`
  line `attempt to commit, or the abetment of, any offence punishable with imprisonment, wherever it may be`
  line `committed, is a breach of the bond or bail bond.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (91127)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Power to reject sureties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91127&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Magistrate may refuse to accept any surety offered, or may`
  line `reject any surety previously accepted by him or his predecessor under this Chapter on the ground that such`
  line `surety is an unfit person for the purposes of the bail bond:`
  line
  line `Provided that before so refusing to accept or rejecting any such surety, he shall either himself hold an`
  line `inquiry on oath into the fitness of the surety, or cause such inquiry to be held and a report to be made thereon`
  line `by a Magistrate subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(2) Such Magistrate shall, before holding the inquiry, give reasonable notice to the surety and to the`
  line `person by whom the surety was offered and shall, in making the inquiry, record the substance of the`
  line `evidence adduced before him.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Magistrate is satisfied, after considering the evidence so adduced either before him or before`
  line `a Magistrate deputed under sub-section (1), and the report of such Magistrate (if any), that the surety is an`
  line `unfit person for the purposes of the bail bond, he shall make an order refusing to accept or rejecting, as the`
  line `case may be, such surety and recording his reasons for so doing:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making an order rejecting any surety who has previously been accepted, the`
  line `Magistrate shall issue his summons or warrant, as he thinks fit, and cause the person for whom the surety`
  line `is bound to appear or to be brought before him.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (91128)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Imprisonment in default of security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91128&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `(1) (a) If any person ordered to give security under`
  line `section 125 or section 136 does not give such security on or before the date on which the period for which`
  line `such security is to be given commences, he shall, except in the case next hereinafter mentioned, be`
  line `committed to prison, or, if he is already in prison, be detained in prison until such period expires or until`
  line `within such period he gives the security to the Court or Magistrate who made the order requiring it;`
  line
  line `(b) if any person after having executed a bond or bail bond for keeping the peace in pursuance of an`
  line `order of a Magistrate under section 136, is proved, to the satisfaction of such Magistrate or his successorin-office, to have committed breach of the bond or bail bond, such Magistrate or successor-in-office may,`
  line `after recording the grounds of such proof, order that the person be arrested and detained in prison until the`
  line `expiry of the period of the bond or bail bond and such order shall be without prejudice to any other`
  line `punishment or forfeiture to which the said person may be liable in accordance with law.`
  line
  line `(2) When such person has been ordered by a Magistrate to give security for a period exceeding one`
  line `year, such Magistrate shall, if such person does not give such security as aforesaid, issue a warrant directing`
  line `him to be detained in prison pending the orders of the Sessions Judge and the proceedings shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as conveniently may be, before such Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Such Court, after examining such proceedings and requiring from the Magistrate any further`
  line `information or evidence which it thinks necessary, and after giving the concerned person a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard, may pass such order on the case as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period (if any) for which any person is imprisoned for failure to give security shall`
  line `not exceed three years.`
  line
  line `(4) If security has been required in the course of the same proceeding from two or more persons in`
  line `respect of any one of whom the proceedings are referred to the Sessions Judge under sub-section (2) such`
  line `reference shall also include the case of any other of such persons who has been ordered to give security,`
  line `and the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) shall, in that event, apply to the case of such other person`
  line `also, except that the period (if any) for which he may be imprisoned, shall not exceed the period for which`
  line `he was ordered to give security.`
  line
  line `(5) A Sessions Judge may in his discretion transfer any proceedings laid before him under`
  line `sub-section (2) or sub-section (4) to an Additional Sessions Judge and upon such transfer, such Additional`
  line `Sessions Judge may exercise the powers of a Sessions Judge under this section in respect of such`
  line proceedings.
  line
  line `(6) If the security is tendered to the officer in charge of the jail, he shall forthwith refer the matter to`
  line `the Court or Magistrate who made the order, and shall await the orders of such Court or Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(7) Imprisonment for failure to give security for keeping the peace shall be simple.`
  line
  line `(8) Imprisonment for failure to give security for good behaviour shall, where the proceedings have been`
  line `taken under section 127, be simple, and, where the proceedings have been taken under section 128 or`
  line `section 129, be rigorous or simple as the Court or Magistrate in each case directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (91129)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Power to release persons imprisoned for failing to give security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91129&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the District`
  line `Magistrate in the case of an order passed by an Executive Magistrate under section 136, or the Chief Judicial`
  line `Magistrate in any other case is of opinion that any person imprisoned for failing to give security under this`
  line `Chapter may be released without hazard to the community or to any other person, he may order such person`
  line `to be discharged.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any person has been imprisoned for failing to give security under this Chapter, the High`
  line `Court or Court of Session, or, where the order was made by any other Court, District Magistrate, in the case`
  line `of an order passed by an Executive Magistrate under section 136, or the Chief Judicial Magistrate in any`
  line `other case, may make an order reducing the amount of the security or the number of sureties or the time for`
  line `which security has been required.`
  line
  line `(3) An order under sub-section (1) may direct the discharge of such person either without conditions or`
  line `upon any conditions which such person accepts:`
  line
  line `Provided that any condition imposed shall cease to be operative when the period for which such person`
  line `was ordered to give security has expired.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may prescribe, by rules, the conditions upon which a conditional discharge`
  line `may be made.`
  line
  line `(5) If any condition upon which any person has been discharged is, in the opinion of District Magistrate,`
  line `in the case of an order passed by an Executive Magistrate under section 136, or the Chief Judicial Magistrate`
  line `in any other case by whom the order of discharge was made or of his successor, not fulfilled, he may cancel`
  line `the same.`
  line
  line `(6) When a conditional order of discharge has been cancelled under sub-section (5), such person may`
  line `be arrested by any police officer without warrant, and shall thereupon be produced before the District`
  line `Magistrate, in the case of an order passed by an Executive Magistrate under section 136, or the Chief`
  line `Judicial Magistrate in any other case.`
  line
  line `(7) Unless such person gives security in accordance with the terms of the original order for the`
  line `unexpired portion of the term for which he was in the first instance committed or ordered to be detained`
  line `(such portion being deemed to be a period equal to the period between the date of the breach of the`
  line `conditions of discharge and the date on which, except for such conditional discharge, he would have been`
  line `entitled to release), District Magistrate, in the case of an order passed by an Executive Magistrate under`
  line `section 136, or the Chief Judicial Magistrate in any other case may remand such person to prison to undergo`
  line `such unexpired portion.`
  line
  line `(8) A person remanded to prison under sub-section (7) shall, subject to the provisionsof section 141, be`
  line `released at any time on giving security in accordance with the terms of the original order for the unexpired`
  line `portion aforesaid to the Court or Magistrate by whom such order was made, or to its or his successor.`
  line
  line `(9) The High Court or Court of Session may at any time, for sufficient reasons to be recorded in writing,`
  line `cancel any bond for keeping the peace or for good behaviour executed under this Chapter by any order`
  line `made by it, and District Magistrate, in the case of an order passed by an Executive Magistrate under section`
  line `136, or the Chief Judicial Magistrate in any other case may make such cancellation where such bond was`
  line `executed under his order or under the order of any other Court in his district.`
  line
  line `(10) Any surety for the peaceable conduct or good behaviour of another person ordered to execute a`
  line `bond under this Chapter may at any time apply to the Court making such order to cancel the bond and on`
  line `such application being made, the Court shall issue a summons or warrant, as it thinks fit, requiring the`
  line `person for whom such surety is bound to appear or to be brought before it.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (91130)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Security for unexpired period of bond.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91130&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a person for whose appearance a summons`
  line `or warrant has been issued under the proviso to sub-section (3) of section 140 or under sub-section (10) of`
  line `section 142, appears or is brought before the Magistrate or Court, the Magistrate or Court shall cancel the`
  line `bond or bail bond executed by such person and shall order such person to give, for the unexpired portion`
  line `of the term of such bond, fresh security of the same description as the original security.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such order shall, for the purposes of sections 139 to 142 (both inclusive) be deemed to be an`
  line `order made under section 125 or section 136, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (91131)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Order for maintenance of wives, children and parents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91131&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person having sufficient`
  line `means neglects or refuses to maintain—`
  line
  line `(a) his wife, unable to maintain herself; or`
  line
  line `(b) his legitimate or illegitimate child, whether married or not, unable to maintain itself; or`
  line
  line `(c) his legitimate or illegitimate child (not being a married daughter) who has attained majority,`
  line `where such child is, by reason of any physical or mental abnormality or injury unable to maintain itself;`
  line or
  line
  line `(d) his father or mother, unable to maintain himself or herself,`
  line
  line `a Magistrate of the first class may, upon proof of such neglect or refusal, order such person to make a`
  line `monthly allowance for the maintenance of his wife or such child, father or mother, at such monthly rate as`
  line `such Magistrate thinks fit and to pay the same to such person as the Magistrate may from time to time`
  line `direct:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Magistrate may order the father of a female child referred to in clause (b) to make`
  line `such allowance, until she attains her majority, if the Magistrate is satisfied that the husband of such female`
  line `child, if married, is not possessed of sufficient means:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Magistrate may, during the pendency of the proceeding regarding monthly`
  line `allowance for the maintenance under this sub-section, order such person to make a monthly allowance for`
  line `the interim maintenance of his wife or such child, father or mother, and the expenses of such proceeding`
  line `which the Magistrate considers reasonable, and to pay the same to such person as the Magistrate may from`
  line `time to time direct:`
  line
  line `Provided also that an application for the monthly allowance for the interim maintenance and expenses`
  line `of proceeding under the second proviso shall, as far as possible, be disposed of within sixty days from the`
  line `date of the service of notice of the application to such person.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this Chapter, "wife" includes a woman who has been divorced by,`
  line `or has obtained a divorce from, her husband and has not remarried.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such allowance for the maintenance or interim maintenance and expenses of proceeding shall`
  line `be payable from the date of the order, or, if so ordered, from the date of the application for maintenance or`
  line `interim maintenance and expenses of proceeding, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person so ordered fails without sufficient cause to comply with the order, any such Magistrate`
  line `may, for every breach of the order, issue a warrant for levying the amount due in the manner provided for`
  line `levying fines, and may sentence such person, for the whole or any part of each month's allowance for the`
  line `maintenance or the interim maintenance and expenses of proceeding, as the case may be, remaining unpaid`
  line `after the execution of the warrant, to imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month or until`
  line `payment if sooner made:`
  line
  line `Provided that no warrant shall be issued for the recovery of any amount due under this section unless`
  line `application be made to the Court to levy such amount within a period of one year from the date on which it`
  line `became due:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if such person offers to maintain his wife on condition of her living with him, and`
  line `she refuses to live with him, such Magistrate may consider any grounds of refusal stated by her, and may`
  line `make an order under this section notwithstanding such offer, if he is satisfied that there is just ground for`
  line `so doing.`
  line
  line `Explanation—.If a husband has contracted marriage with another woman or keeps a mistress, it shall`
  line `be considered to be just ground for his wife's refusal to live with him.`
  line
  line `(4) No wife shall be entitled to receive an allowance for the maintenance or the interim maintenance`
  line `and expenses of proceeding, from her husband under this section if she is living in adultery, or if, without`
  line `any sufficient reason, she refuses to live with her husband, or if they are living separately by mutual consent.`
  line
  line `(5) On proof that any wife in whose favour an order has been made under this section is living in`
  line `adultery, or that without sufficient reason she refuses to live with her husband, or that they are living`
  line `separately by mutual consent, the Magistrate shall cancel the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (91132)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title Procedure.
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91132&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `(1) Proceedings under section 144 may be taken against any person in any district—`
  line
  line `(a) where he is; or`
  line
  line `(b) where he or his wife resides; or`
  line
  line `(c) where he last resided with his wife, or as the case may be, with the mother of the illegitimate`
  line `child; or`
  line
  line `(d) where his father or mother resides.`
  line
  line `(2) All evidence in such proceedings shall be taken in the presence of the person against whom an order`
  line `for payment of maintenance is proposed to be made, or, when his personal attendance is dispensed with, in`
  line `the presence of his advocate, and shall be recorded in the manner prescribed for summons-cases:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Magistrate is satisfied that the person against whom an order for payment of`
  line `maintenance is proposed to be made is wilfully avoiding service, or willfully neglecting to attend the Court,`
  line `the Magistrate may proceed to hear and determine the case ex parte and any order so made may be set aside`
  line `for good cause shown on an application made within three months from the date thereof subject to such`
  line `terms including terms as to payment of costs to the opposite party as the Magistrate may think just and`
  line proper.
  line
  line `(3) The Court in dealing with applications under section 144 shall have power to make such order as to`
  line `costs as may be just.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (91133)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Alteration in allowance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91133&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `(1) On proof of a change in the circumstances of any person, receiving,`
  line `under section 144 a monthly allowance for the maintenance or interim maintenance, or ordered under the`
  line `same section to pay a monthly allowance for the maintenance, or interim maintenance, to his wife, child,`
  line `father or mother, as the case may be, the Magistrate may make such alteration, as he thinks fit, in the`
  line `allowance for the maintenance or the interim maintenance, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Where it appears to the Magistrate that in consequence of any decision of a competent Civil Court,`
  line `any order made under section 144 should be cancelled or varied, he shall cancel the order or, as the case`
  line `may be, vary the same accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any order has been made under section 144 in favour of a woman who has been divorced`
  line `by, or has obtained a divorce from, her husband, the Magistrate shall, if he is satisfied that—`
  line
  line `(a) the woman has, after the date of such divorce, remarried, cancel such order as from the date of`
  line `her remarriage;`
  line
  line `(b) the woman has been divorced by her husband and that she has received, whether before or after`
  line `the date of the said order, the whole of the sum which, under any customary or personal law applicable`
  line `to the parties, was payable on such divorce, cancel such order,—`
  line
  line `(i) in the case where such sum was paid before such order, from the date on which such order`
  line `was made;`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, from the date of expiry of the period, if any, for which maintenance has`
  line `been actually paid by the husband to the woman;`
  line
  line `(c) the woman has obtained a divorce from her husband and that she had voluntarily surrendered`
  line `her rights to maintenance or interim maintenance, as the case may be, after her divorce, cancel the order`
  line `from the date thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) At the time of making any decree for the recovery of any maintenance or dowry by any person, to`
  line `whom a monthly allowance for the maintenance and interim maintenance or any of them has been ordered`
  line `to be paid under section 144, the Civil Court shall take into account the sum which has been paid to, or`
  line `recovered by, such person as monthly allowance for the maintenance and interim maintenance or any of`
  line `them, as the case may be, in pursuance of the said order.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (91134)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Enforcement of order of maintenance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91134&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `A copy of the order of maintenance or interim`
  line `maintenance and expenses of proceedings, as the case may be, shall be given without payment to the person`
  line `in whose favour it is made, or to his guardian, if any, or to the person to whom the allowance for the`
  line `maintenance or the allowance for the interim maintenance and expenses of proceeding, as the case may be,`
  line `is to be paid; and such order may be enforced by any Magistrate in any place where the person against`
  line `whom it is made may be, on such Magistrate being satisfied as to the identity of the parties and the`
  line `non-payment of the allowance, or as the case may be, expenses, due.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (91544)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Dispersal of assembly by use of civil force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91544&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Executive Magistrate or officer in charge`
  line `of a police station or, in the absence of such officer in charge, any police officer, not below the rank of a`
  line `sub-inspector, may command any unlawful assembly, or any assembly of five or more persons likely to`
  line `cause a disturbance of the public peace, to disperse; and it shall thereupon be the duty of the members of`
  line `such assembly to disperse accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) If, upon being so commanded, any such assembly does not disperse, or if, without being so`
  line `commanded, it conducts itself in such a manner as to show a determination not to disperse, any Executive`
  line `Magistrate or police officer referred to in sub-section (1), may proceed to disperse such assembly by force,`
  line `and may require the assistance of any person, not being an officer or member of the armed forces and acting`
  line `as such, for the purpose of dispersing such assembly, and, if necessary, arresting and confining the persons`
  line `who form part of it, in order to disperse such assembly or that they may be punished according to law.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (91136)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Use of armed forces to disperse assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91136&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any assembly referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 148 cannot otherwise be dispersed, and it is necessary for the public security that it should be`
  line `dispersed, the District Magistrate or any other Executive Magistrate authorised by him, who is present, may`
  line `cause it to be dispersed by the armed forces.`
  line
  line `(2) Such Magistrate may require any officer in command of any group of persons belonging to the`
  line `armed forces to disperse the assembly with the help of the armed forces under his command, and to arrest`
  line `and confine such persons forming part of it as the Executive Magistrate may direct, or as it may be necessary`
  line `to arrest and confine in order to disperse the assembly or to have them punished according to law.`
  line
  line `(3) Every such officer of the armed forces shall obey such requisition in such manner as he thinks fit,`
  line `but in so doing he shall use as little force, and do as little injury to person and property, as may be consistent`
  line `with dispersing the assembly and arresting and detaining such persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (91137)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Power of certain armed force officers to disperse assembly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91137&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `When the public security is`
  line `manifestly endangered by any such assembly and no Executive Magistrate can be communicated with, any`
  line `commissioned or gazetted officer of the armed forces may disperse such assembly with the help of the`
  line `armed forces under his command, and may arrest and confine any persons forming part of it, in order to`
  line `disperse such assembly or that they may be punished according to law; but if, while he is acting under this`
  line `section, it becomes practicable for him to communicate with an Executive Magistrate, he shall do so, and`
  line `shall thenceforward obey the instructions of the Magistrate, as to whether he shall or shall not continue such`
  line action.
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (91138)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Protection against prosecution for acts done under sections 148, 149 and 150.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91138&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `prosecution against any person for any act purporting to be done under section 148, section 149 or`
  line `section 150 shall be instituted in any Criminal Court except—`
  line
  line `(a) with the sanction of the Central Government where such person is an officer or member of the`
  line `armed forces;`
  line
  line `(b) with the sanction of the State Government in any other case.`
  line
  line `(2) (a) No Executive Magistrate or police officer acting under any of the said sections in good faith;`
  line
  line `(b) no person doing any act in good faith in compliance with a requisition under section 148 or`
  line `section 149;`
  line
  line `(c) no officer of the armed forces acting under section 150 in good faith;`
  line
  line `(d) no member of the armed forces doing any act in obedience to any order which he was bound to`
  line obey,
  line `shall be deemed to have thereby committed an offence.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section and in the preceding sections of this Chapter,—`
  line
  line `(a) the expression “armed forces” means the army, naval and air forces, operating as land forces`
  line `and includes any other armed forces of the Union so operating;`
  line
  line `(b) “officer”, in relation to the armed forces, means a person commissioned, gazetted or in pay as`
  line `an officer of the armed forces and includes a junior commissioned officer, a warrant officer, a petty`
  line `officer, a non-commissioned officer and a non-gazetted officer;`
  line
  line `(c) “member”, in relation to the armed forces, means a person in the armed forces other than an`
  line officer.
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (91545)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Conditional order for removal of nuisance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91545&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever a District Magistrate or a`
  line `Sub-divisional Magistrate or any other Executive Magistrate specially empowered in this behalf by the`
  line `State Government, on receiving the report of a police officer or other information and on taking such`
  line `evidence (if any) as he thinks fit, considers—`
  line
  line `(a) that any unlawful obstruction or nuisance should be removed from any public place or from any`
  line `way, river or channel which is or may be lawfully used by the public; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the conduct of any trade or occupation, or the keeping of any goods or merchandise, is`
  line `injurious to the health or physical comfort of the community, and that in consequence such trade or`
  line `occupation should be prohibited or regulated or such goods or merchandise should be removed or the`
  line `keeping thereof regulated; or`
  line
  line `(c) that the construction of any building, or, the disposal of any substance, as is likely to occasion`
  line `conflagration or explosion, should be prevented or stopped; or`
  line
  line `(d) that any building, tent or structure, or any tree is in such a condition that it is likely to fall and`
  line `thereby cause injury to persons living or carrying on business in the neighbourhood or passing by, and`
  line `that in consequence the removal, repair or support of such building, tent or structure, or the removal or`
  line `support of such tree, is necessary; or`
  line
  line `(e) that any tank, well or excavation adjacent to any such way or public place should be fenced in`
  line `such manner as to prevent danger arising to the public; or`
  line
  line `(f) that any dangerous animal should be destroyed, confined or otherwise disposed of,`
  line `such Magistrate may make a conditional order requiring the person causing such obstruction or nuisance,`
  line `or carrying on such trade or occupation, or keeping any such goods or merchandise, or owning, possessing`
  line `or controlling such building, tent, structure, substance, tank, well or excavation, or owning or possessing`
  line `such animal or tree, within a time to be fixed in the order—`
  line
  line `(i) to remove such obstruction or nuisance; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to desist from carrying on, or to remove or regulate in such manner as may be directed, such trade or occupation, or to remove such goods or merchandise, or to regulate the keeping thereof in such`
  line `manner as may be directed; or`
  line
  line `(iii) to prevent or stop the construction of such building, or to alter the disposal of such`
  line `substance; or`
  line
  line `(iv) to remove, repair or support such building, tent or structure, or to remove or support such`
  line `trees; or`
  line
  line `(v) to fence such tank, well or excavation; or`
  line
  line `(vi) to destroy, confine or dispose of such dangerous animal in the manner provided in the said`
  line `order, or, if he objects so to do, to appear before himself or some other Executive Magistrate subordinate`
  line `to him at a time and place to be fixed by the order, and show cause, in the manner hereinafter provided,`
  line `why the order should not be made absolute.`
  line
  line `(2) No order duly made by a Magistrate under this section shall be called in question in any Civil Court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A "public place" includes also property belonging to the State, camping grounds and`
  line `grounds left unoccupied for sanitary or recreative purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (91140)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `Service or notification of order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91140&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `(1) The order shall, if practicable, be served on the person`
  line `against whom it is made, in the manner herein provided for service of summons.`
  line
  line `(2) If such order cannot be so served, it shall be notified by proclamation published in such manner as`
  line `the State Government may, by rules, direct, and a copy thereof shall be stuck up at such place or places as`
  line `may be fittest for conveying the information to such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (91141)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Person to whom order is addressed to obey or show cause.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91141&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `The person against whom such`
  line `order is made shall—`
  line
  line `(a) perform, within the time and in the manner specified in the order, the act directed thereby; or`
  line
  line `(b) appear in accordance with such order and show cause against the same; and such appearance or`
  line `hearing may be permitted through audio-video conferencing.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (91142)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with section 154.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91142&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `If the person against whom an order is made`
  line `under section 154 does not perform such act or appear and show cause, he shall be liable to the penalty`
  line `specified in that behalf in section 223 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, and the order shall be made`
  line absolute.
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (91143)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Procedure where existence of public right is denied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91143&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an order is made under`
  line `section 152 for the purpose of preventing obstruction, nuisance or danger to the public in the use of any`
  line `way, river, channel or place, the Magistrate shall, on the appearance before him of the person against whom`
  line `the order was made, question him as to whether he denies the existence of any public right in respect of the`
  line `way, river, channel or place, and if he does so, the Magistrate shall, before proceeding under section 157,`
  line `inquire into the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) If in such inquiry the Magistrate finds that there is any reliable evidence in support of such denial,`
  line `he shall stay the proceedings until the matter of the existence of such right has been decided by a competent`
  line `Court; and, if he finds that there is no such evidence, he shall proceed as laid down in section 157.`
  line
  line `(3) A person who has, on being questioned by the Magistrate under sub-section (1), failed to deny the`
  line `existence of a public right of the nature therein referred to, or who, having made such denial, has failed to`
  line `adduce reliable evidence in support thereof, shall not in the subsequent proceedings be permitted to make`
  line `any such denial.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (91144)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Procedure where person against whom order is made under section 152 appears to show-cause.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91144&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person against whom an order under section 152 is made appears and shows cause against`
  line `the order, the Magistrate shall take evidence in the matter as in a summons-case.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Magistrate is satisfied that the order, either as originally made or subject to such modification`
  line `as he considers necessary, is reasonable and proper, the order shall be made absolute without modification`
  line `or, as the case may be, with such modification.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Magistrate is not so satisfied, no further proceedings shall be taken in the case:`
  line
  line `Provided that the proceedings under this section shall be completed, as soon as possible, within a period`
  line `of ninety days, which may be extended for the reasons to be recorded in writing, to one hundred and twenty`
  line days.
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (91145)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Power of Magistrate to direct local investigation and examination of an expert.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91145&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `The Magistrate may, for the purposes of an inquiry under section 156 or section 157—`
  line
  line `(a) direct a local investigation to be made by such person as he thinks fit; or`
  line
  line `(b) summon and examine an expert.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (91146)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title `Power of Magistrate to furnish written instructions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91146&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Magistrate directs a`
  line `local investigation by any person under section 158, the Magistrate may—`
  line
  line `(a) furnish such person with such written instructions as may seem necessary for his guidance;`
  line
  line `(b) declare by whom the whole or any part of the necessary expenses of the local investigation shall`
  line `be paid.`
  line
  line `(2) The report of such person may be read as evidence in the case.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Magistrate summons and examines an expert under section 158, the Magistrate may`
  line `direct by whom the costs of such summoning and examination shall be paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (91147)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Procedure on order being made absolute and consequences of disobedience.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91147&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an`
  line `order has been made absolute under section 155 or section 157, the Magistrate shall give notice of the same`
  line `to the person against whom the order was made, and shall further require him to perform the act directed`
  line `by the order within the time to be fixed in the notice, and inform him that, in case of disobedience, he shall`
  line `be liable to the penalty provided by section 223 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(2) If such act is not performed within the time fixed, the Magistrate may cause it to be performed, and`
  line `may recover the costs of performing it, either by the sale of any building, goods or other property removed`
  line `by his order, or by the distress and sale of any other movable property of such person within or without`
  line `such Magistrate's local jurisdiction, and if such other property is without such jurisdiction, the order shall`
  line `authorise its attachment and sale when endorsed by the Magistrate within whose local jurisdiction the`
  line `property to be attached is found.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit shall lie in respect of anything done in good faith under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (91148)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title `Injunction pending inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91148&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a Magistrate making an order under section 152 considers`
  line `that immediate measures should be taken to prevent imminent danger or injury of a serious kind to the`
  line `public, he may issue such an injunction to the person against whom the order was made, as is required to`
  line `obviate or prevent such danger or injury pending the determination of the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) In default of such person forthwith obeying such injunction, the Magistrate may himself use, or`
  line `cause to be used, such means as he thinks fit to obviate such danger or to prevent such injury.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit shall lie in respect of anything done in good faith by a Magistrate under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (91149)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title `Magistrate may prohibit repetition or Continuance of public nuisance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91149&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `A District Magistrate`
  line `or Sub-divisional Magistrate, or any other Executive Magistrate or Deputy Commissioner of Police`
  line `empowered by the State Government or the District Magistrate in this behalf, may order any person not to`
  line `repeat or continue a public nuisance, as defined in the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, or any special or`
  line `local law.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (91546)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 163
  title `Power to issue order in urgent cases of nuisance or apprehended danger.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91546&sectionno=163&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `(1) In cases where,`
  line `in the opinion of a District Magistrate, a Sub-divisional Magistrate or any other Executive Magistrate`
  line `specially empowered by the State Government in this behalf, there is sufficient ground for proceeding under`
  line `this section and immediate prevention or speedy remedy is desirable, such Magistrate may, by a written`
  line `order stating the material facts of the case and served in the manner provided by section 153, direct any`
  line `person to abstain from a certain act or to take certain order with respect to certain property in his possession`
  line `or under his management, if such Magistrate considers that such direction is likely to prevent, or tends to`
  line `prevent, obstruction, annoyance or injury to any person lawfully employed, or danger to human life, health`
  line `or safety or a disturbance of the public tranquillity, or a riot, or an affray.`
  line
  line `(2) An order under this section may, in cases of emergency or in cases where the circumstances do not`
  line `admit of the serving in due time of a notice upon the person against whom the order is directed, be passed`
  line `ex parte.`
  line
  line `(3) An order under this section may be directed to a particular individual, or to persons residing in a`
  line `particular place or area, or to the public generally when frequenting or visiting a particular place or area.`
  line
  line `(4) No order under this section shall remain in force for more than two months from the making thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the State Government considers it necessary so to do for preventing danger to human`
  line `life, health or safety or for preventing a riot or any affray, it may, by notification, direct that an order made`
  line `by a Magistrate under this section shall remain in force for such further period not exceeding six months`
  line `from the date on which the order made by the Magistrate would have, but for such order, expired, as it may`
  line `specify in the said notification.`
  line
  line `(5) Any Magistrate may, either on his own motion or on the application of any person aggrieved, rescind`
  line `or alter any order made under this section by himself or any Magistrate subordinate to him or by his`
  line predecessor-in-office.
  line
  line `(6) The State Government may, either on its own motion or on the application of any person aggrieved,`
  line `rescind or alter any order made by it under the proviso to sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(7) Where an application under sub-section (5) or sub-section (6) is received, the Magistrate, or the`
  line `State Government, as the case may be, shall afford to the applicant an early opportunity of appearing before`
  line `him or it, either in person or by an advocate and showing cause against the order; and if the Magistrate or`
  line `the State Government, as the case may be, rejects the application wholly or in part, he or it shall record in`
  line `writing the reasons for so doing.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (91547)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 164
  title `Procedure where dispute concerning land or water is likely to cause breach of peace.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91547&sectionno=164&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever an Executive Magistrate is satisfied from a report of a police officer or upon other`
  line `information that a dispute likely to cause a breach of the peace exists concerning any land or water or the`
  line `boundaries thereof, within his local jurisdiction, he shall make an order in writing, stating the grounds of`
  line `his being so satisfied, and requiring the parties concerned in such dispute to attend his Court in person or`
  line `by an advocate on aspecified date and time, and to put in written statements of their respective claims as`
  line `respects the fact of actual possession of the subject of dispute.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, the expression "land or water" includes buildings, markets,`
  line `fisheries, crops or other produce of land, and the rents or profits of any such property.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the order shall be served in the manner provided by this Sanhita for the service of`
  line `summons upon such person or persons as the Magistrate may direct, and at least one copy shall be published`
  line `by being affixed to some conspicuous place at or near the subject of dispute.`
  line
  line `(4) The Magistrate shall, without reference to the merits or the claims of any of the parties to a right to`
  line `possess the subject of dispute, peruse the statements so put in, hear the parties, receive all such evidence as`
  line `may be produced by them, take such further evidence, if any, as he thinks necessary, and, if possible, decide`
  line `whether any and which of the parties was, at the date of the order made by him under sub-section (1), in`
  line `possession of the subject of dispute:`
  line
  line `Provided that if it appears to the Magistrate that any party has been forcibly and wrongfully`
  line `dispossessed within two months next before the date on which the report of a police officer or other`
  line `information was received by the Magistrate, or after that date and before the date of his order under`
  line `sub-section (1), he may treat the party so dispossessed as if that party had been in possession on the date of`
  line `his order under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall preclude any party so required to attend, or any other person interested,`
  line `from showing that no such dispute as aforesaid exists or has existed; and in such case the Magistrate shall`
  line `cancel his said order, and all further proceedings thereon shall be stayed, but, subject to such cancellation,`
  line `the order of the Magistrate under sub-section (1) shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) (a) If the Magistrate decides that one of the parties was, or should under the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (4) be treated as being, in such possession of the said subject of dispute, he shall issue an order`
  line `declaring such party to be entitled to possession thereof until evicted therefrom in due course of law, and`
  line `forbidding all disturbance of such possession until such eviction; and when he proceeds under the proviso`
  line `to sub-section (4), may restore to possession the party forcibly and wrongfully dispossessed;`
  line
  line `(b) the order made under this sub-section shall be served and published in the manner laid down in subsection (3).`
  line
  line `(7) When any party to any such proceeding dies, the Magistrate may cause the legal representative of`
  line `the deceased party to be made a party to the proceeding and shall thereupon continue the inquiry, and if any`
  line `question arises as to who the legal representative of a deceased party for the purposes of such proceeding`
  line `is, all persons claiming to be representatives of the deceased party shall be made parties thereto.`
  line
  line `(8) If the Magistrate is of opinion that any crop or other produce of the property, the subject of dispute`
  line `in a proceeding under this section pending before him, is subject to speedy and natural decay, he may make`
  line `an order for the proper custody or sale of such property, and, upon the completion of the inquiry, shall make`
  line `such order for the disposal of such property, or the sale-proceeds thereof, as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(9) The Magistrate may, if he thinks fit, at any stage of the proceedings under this section, on the`
  line `application of either party, issue a summons to any witness directing him to attend or to produce any`
  line `document or thing.`
  line
  line `(10) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to be in derogation of powers of the Magistrate to proceed`
  line `under section 126.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (91152)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 165
  title `Power to attach subject of dispute and to appoint receiver.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91152&sectionno=165&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Magistrate at any time`
  line `after making the order under sub-section (1) of section 164 considers the case to be one of emergency, or`
  line `if he decides that none of the parties was then in such possession as is referred to in section 164, or if he is`
  line `unable to satisfy himself as to which of them was then in such possession of the subject of dispute, he may`
  line `attach the subject of dispute until a competent Court has determined the rights of the parties thereto with`
  line `regard to the person entitled to the possession thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that such Magistrate may withdraw the attachment at any time if he is satisfied that there is`
  line `no longer any likelihood of breach of the peace with regard to the subject of dispute.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Magistrate attaches the subject of dispute, he may, if no receiver in relation to such subject`
  line `of dispute has been appointed by any Civil Court, make such arrangements as he considers proper for`
  line `looking after the property or if he thinks fit, appoint a receiver thereof, who shall have, subject to the control`
  line `of the Magistrate, all the powers of a receiver appointed under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of`
  line `1908):`
  line
  line `Provided that in the event of a receiver being subsequently appointed in relation to the subject of dispute`
  line `by any Civil Court, the Magistrate—`
  line
  line `(a) shall order the receiver appointed by him to hand over the possession of the subject of dispute`
  line `to the receiver appointed by the Civil Court and shall thereafter discharge the receiver appointed by`
  line him;
  line
  line `(b) may make such other incidental or consequential orders as may be just.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (91153)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 166
  title `Dispute concerning right of use of land or water.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91153&sectionno=166&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever an Executive Magistrate is`
  line `satisfied from the report of a police officer or upon other information, that a dispute likely to cause a breach`
  line `of the peace exists regarding any alleged right of user of any land or water within his local jurisdiction,`
  line `whether such right be claimed as an easement or otherwise, he shall make an order in writing, stating the`
  line `grounds of his being so satisfied and requiring the parties concerned in such dispute to attend his Court in`
  line `person or by an advocate on a specified date and time and to put in written statements of their respective`
  line claims.
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "land or water" has the meaning`
  line `given to it in sub-section (2) of section 164.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate shall peruse the statements so put in, hear the parties, receive all such evidence as`
  line `may be produced by them respectively, consider the effect of such evidence, take such further evidence, if`
  line `any, as he thinks necessary and, if possible, decide whether such right exists; and the provisions of`
  line `section 164 shall, so far as may be, apply in the case of such inquiry.`
  line
  line `(3) If it appears to such Magistrate that such rights exist, he may make an order prohibiting any`
  line `interference with the exercise of such right, including, in a proper case, an order for the removal of any`
  line `obstruction in the exercise of any such right:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made where the right is exercisable at all times of the year, unless`
  line `such right has been exercised within three months next before the receipt under sub-section (1) of the report`
  line `of a police officer or other information leading to the institution of the inquiry, or where the right is`
  line `exercisable only at particular seasons or on particular occasions, unless the right has been exercised during`
  line `the last of such seasons or on the last of such occasions before such receipt.`
  line
  line `(4) When in any proceedings commenced under sub-section (1) of section 164 the Magistrate finds that`
  line `the dispute is as regards an alleged right of user of land or water, he may, after recording his reasons,`
  line `continue with the proceedings as if they had been commenced under sub-section (1), and when in any`
  line `proceedings commenced under sub-section (1) the Magistrate finds that the dispute should be dealt with`
  line `under section 164, he may, after recording his reasons, continue with the proceedings as if they had been`
  line `commenced under sub-section (1) of section 164.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (91154)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 167
  title `Local inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91154&sectionno=167&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever a local inquiry is necessary for the purposes of section 164, section`
  line `165 or section 166, a District Magistrate or Sub-divisional Magistrate may depute any Magistrate`
  line `subordinate to him to make the inquiry, and may furnish him with such written instructions as may seem`
  line `necessary for his guidance, and may declare by whom the whole or any part of the necessary expenses of`
  line `the inquiry shall be paid.`
  line
  line `(2) The report of the person so deputed may be read as evidence in the case.`
  line
  line `(3) When any costs have been incurred by any party to a proceeding under section 164, section 165 or`
  line `section 166, the Magistrate passing a decision may direct by whom such costs shall be paid, whether by`
  line `such party or by any other party to the proceeding, and whether in whole or in part or proportion and such`
  line `costs may include any expenses incurred in respect of witnesses and of advocates' fees, which the Court`
  line `may consider reasonable.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (91155)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 168
  title `Police to prevent cognizable offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91155&sectionno=168&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `Every police officer may interpose for the purpose of`
  line `preventing, and shall, to the best of his ability, prevent, the commission of any cognizable offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (91156)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 169
  title `Information of design to commit cognizable offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91156&sectionno=169&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `Every police officer receiving`
  line `information of a design to commit any cognizable offence shall communicate such information to the police`
  line `officer to whom he is subordinate, and to any other officer whose duty it is to prevent or take cognizance`
  line `of the commission of any such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (91157)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 170
  title `Arrest to prevent commission of cognizable offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91157&sectionno=170&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `(1) A police officer knowing of a design`
  line `to commit any cognizable offence may arrest, without orders from a Magistrate and without a warrant, the`
  line `person so designing, if it appears to such officer that the commission of the offence cannot be otherwise`
  line prevented.
  line
  line `(2) No person arrested under sub-section (1) shall be detained in custody for a period exceeding`
  line `twenty-four hours from the time of his arrest unless his further detention is required or authorised under`
  line `any other provisions of this Sanhita or of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (91158)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 171
  title `Prevention of injury to public property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91158&sectionno=171&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `A police officer may of his own authority interpose`
  line `to prevent any injury attempted to be committed in his view to any public property, movable or immovable,`
  line `or the removal or injury of any public landmark, buoy or other mark used for navigation.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (91548)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 172
  title `Persons bound to conform to lawful directions of police`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91548&sectionno=172&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `(1) All persons shall be bound to`
  line `conform to the lawful directions of a police officer given in fulfilment of any of his duty under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) A police officer may detain or remove any person resisting, refusing, ignoring or disregarding to`
  line `conform to any direction given by him under sub-section (1) and may either take such person before a`
  line `Magistrate or, in petty cases, release him as soon as possible within a period of twenty-four hours.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (91549)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 173
  title `Information in cognizable cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91549&sectionno=173&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every information relating to the commission of a`
  line `cognizable offence, irrespective of the area where the offence is committed, may be given orally or by`
  line `electronic communication to an officer in charge of a police station, and if given—`
  line
  line `(i) orally, it shall be reduced to writing by him or under his direction, and be read over to the`
  line `informant; and every such information, whether given in writing or reduced to writing as aforesaid,`
  line `shall be signed by the person giving it;`
  line
  line `(ii) by electronic communication, it shall be taken on record by him on being signed within three`
  line `days by the person giving it,`
  line
  line `and the substance thereof shall be entered in a book to be kept by such officer in such form as the State`
  line `Government may by rules prescribe in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the information is given by the woman against whom an offence under section 64,`
  line `section 65, section 66, section 67, section 68, section 69, section 70, section 71, section 74, section 75,`
  line `section 76, section 77, section 78, section 79 or section 124 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 is alleged`
  line `to have been committed or attempted, then such information shall be recorded, by a woman police officer`
  line `or any woman officer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that—`
  line
  line `(a) in the event that the person against whom an offence under section 64, section 65, section 66,`
  line `section 67, section 68, section 69, section 70, section 71, section 74, section 75, section 76, section 77,`
  line `section 78, section 79 or section 124 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 is alleged to have been`
  line `committed or attempted, is temporarily or permanently mentally or physically disabled, then such`
  line `information shall be recorded by a police officer, at the residence of the person seeking to report such`
  line `offence or at a convenient place of such person's choice, in the presence of an interpreter or a special`
  line `educator, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) the recording of such information shall be videographed;`
  line
  line `(c) the police officer shall get the statement of the person recorded by a Magistrate under clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (6) of section 183 as soon as possible.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the information as recorded under sub-section (1) shall be given forthwith, free of cost,`
  line `to the informant or the victim.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in section 175, on receipt of information relating to`
  line `the commission of any cognizable offence, which is made punishable for three years or more but less than`
  line `seven years, the officer in charge of the police station may with the prior permission from an officer not`
  line `below the rank of Deputy Superintendent of Police, considering the nature and gravity of the offence,`
  line
  line `(i) proceed to conduct preliminary enquiry to ascertain whether there exists a prima facie case for`
  line `proceeding in the matter within a period of fourteen days; or`
  line
  line `(ii) proceed with investigation when there exists a prima facie case.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by a refusal on the part of an officer in charge of a police station to record`
  line `the information referred to in sub-section (1), may send the substance of such information, in writing and`
  line `by post, to the Superintendent of Police concerned who, if satisfied that such information discloses the`
  line `commission of a cognizable offence, shall either investigate the case himself or direct an investigation to`
  line `be made by any police officer subordinate to him, in the manner provided by this Sanhita, and such officer`
  line `shall have all the powers of an officer in charge of the police station in relation to that offence failing which`
  line `such aggrieved person may make an application to the Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (91160)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 174
  title `Information as to non-cognizable cases and investigation of such cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91160&sectionno=174&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `(1) When`
  line `information is given to an officer in charge of a police station of the commission within the limits of such`
  line `station of a non-cognizable offence, he shall enter or cause to be entered the substance of the information`
  line `in a book to be kept by such officer in such form as the State Government may by rules prescribe in this`
  line `behalf, and,—`
  line
  line `(i) refer the informant to the Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(ii) forward the daily diary report of all such cases fortnightly to the Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) No police officer shall investigate a non-cognizable case without the order of a Magistrate having`
  line `power to try such case or commit the case for trial.`
  line
  line `(3) Any police officer receiving such order may exercise the same powers in respect of the investigation`
  line `(except the power to arrest without warrant) as an officer in charge of a police station may exercise in a`
  line `cognizable case.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a case relates to two or more offences of which at least one is cognizable, the case shall be`
  line `deemed to be a cognizable case, notwithstanding that the other offences are non-cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (91161)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 175
  title `Police officer’s power to investigate cognizable case.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91161&sectionno=175&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any officer in charge of a police`
  line `station may, without the order of a Magistrate, investigate any cognizable case which a Court having`
  line `jurisdiction over the local area within the limits of such station would have power to inquire into or try`
  line `under the provisions of Chapter XIV:`
  line
  line `Provided that considering the nature and gravity of the offence, the Superintendent of Police may`
  line `require the Deputy Superintendent of Police to investigate the case.`
  line
  line `(2) No proceeding of a police officer in any such case shall at any stage be called in question on the`
  line `ground that the case was one which such officer was not empowered under this section to investigate.`
  line
  line `(3) Any Magistrate empowered under section 210 may, after considering the application supported by`
  line `an affidavit made under sub-section (4) of section 173, and after making such inquiry as he thinks necessary`
  line `and submission made in this regard by the police officer, order such an investigation as above-mentioned.`
  line
  line `(4) Any Magistrate empowered under section 210, may, upon receiving a complaint against a public`
  line `servant arising in course of the discharge of his official duties, order investigation, subject to—`
  line
  line `(a) receiving a report containing facts and circumstances of the incident from the officer superior`
  line `to him; and`
  line
  line `(b) after consideration of the assertions made by the public servant as to the situation that led to the`
  line `incident so alleged.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (91162)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 176
  title `Procedure for investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91162&sectionno=176&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, from information received or otherwise, an officer in charge`
  line `of a police station has reason to suspect the commission of an offence which he is empowered under`
  line `section 175 to investigate, he shall forthwith send a report of the same to a Magistrate empowered to take`
  line `cognizance of such offence upon a police report and shall proceed in person, or shall depute one of his`
  line `subordinate officers not being below such rank as the State Government may, by general or special order,`
  line `prescribe in this behalf, to proceed, to the spot, to investigate the facts and circumstances of the case, and,`
  line `if necessary, to take measures for the discovery and arrest of the offender:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) when information as to the commission of any such offence is given against any person by name`
  line `and the case is not of a serious nature, the officer in charge of a police station need not proceed in`
  line `person or depute a subordinate officer to make an investigation on the spot;`
  line
  line `(b) if it appears to the officer in charge of a police station that there is no sufficient ground for`
  line `entering on an investigation, he shall not investigate the case:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in relation to an offence of rape, the recording of statement of the victim shall be`
  line `conducted at the residence of the victim or in the place of her choice and as far as practicable by a woman`
  line `police officer in the presence of her parents or guardian or near relatives or social worker of the locality and`
  line `such statement may also be recorded through any audio-video electronic means including mobile phone.`
  line
  line `(2) In each of the cases mentioned in clauses (a) and (b) of the first proviso to sub-section (1), the`
  line `officer in charge of the police station shall state in his report the reasons for not fully complying with the`
  line `requirements of that sub-section by him, and, forward the daily diary report fortnightly to the Magistrate`
  line `and in the case mentioned inclause (b) of the said proviso, the officer shall also forthwith notify to the`
  line `informant, if any, in such manner as may be prescribed by rules made by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of every information relating to the commission of an offence which is made punishable`
  line `for seven years or more, the officer in charge of a police station shall, from such date, as may be notified`
  line `within a period of five years by the State Government in this regard, cause the forensic expert to visit the`
  line `crime scene to collect forensic evidence in the offence and also cause videography of the process on mobile`
  line `phone or any other electronic device:`
  line
  line `Provided that where forensic facility is not available in respect of any such offence, the State`
  line `Government shall, until the facility in respect of that matter is developed or made in the State, notify the`
  line `utilisation of such facility of any other State.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (91163)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 177
  title `Report how submitted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91163&sectionno=177&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every report sent to a Magistrate under section 176 shall, if the State`
  line `Government so directs, be submitted through such superior officer of police as the State Government, by`
  line `general or special order, appoints in that behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Such superior officer may give such instructions to the officer in charge of the police station as he`
  line `thinks fit, and shall, after recording such instructions on such report, transmit the same without delay to the`
  line Magistrate.
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (91164)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 178
  title `Power to hold investigation or preliminary inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91164&sectionno=178&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `The Magistrate, on receiving a report`
  line `under section 176, may direct an investigation, or, if he thinks fit, at once proceed, or depute any Magistrate`
  line `subordinate to him to proceed, to hold a preliminary inquiry into, or otherwise to dispose of, the case in the`
  line `manner provided in this Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (91165)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 179
  title `Police officer's power to require attendance of witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91165&sectionno=179&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any police officer making an`
  line `investigation under this Chapter may, by order in writing, require the attendance before himself of any`
  line `person being within the limits of his own or any adjoining station who, from the information given or`
  line `otherwise, appears to be acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case; and such person shall`
  line `attend as so required:`
  line
  line `Provided that no male person under the age of fifteen years or above the age of sixty years or a woman`
  line `or a mentally or physically disabled person or a person with acute illness shall be required to attend at any`
  line `place other than the place in which such person resides:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if such person is willing to attend at the police station, such person may be`
  line `permitted so to do.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by rules made in this behalf, provide for the payment by the police`
  line `officer of the reasonable expenses of every person, attending under sub-section (1) at any place other than`
  line `his residence.`
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (91166)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 180
  title `Examination of witnesses by police.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91166&sectionno=180&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any police officer making an investigation under this`
  line `Chapter, or any police officer not below such rank as the State Government may, by general or special`
  line `order, prescribe in this behalf, acting on the requisition of such officer, may examine orally any person`
  line `supposed to be acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(2) Such person shall be bound to answer truly all questions relating to such case put to him by such`
  line `officer, other than questions the answers to which would have a tendency to expose him to a criminal charge`
  line `or to a penalty or forfeiture.`
  line
  line `(3) The police officer may reduce into writing any statement made to him in the course of an`
  line `examination under this section; and if he does so, he shall make a separate and true record of the statement`
  line `of each such person whose statement he records:`
  line
  line `Provided that statement made under this sub-section may also be recorded by audio-video electronic`
  line `means:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the statement of a woman against whom an offence under section 64, section 65,`
  line `section 66, section 67, section 68, section 69, section 70, section 71, section 74, section 75, section 76,`
  line `section 77, section 78, section 79 or section 124 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 is alleged to have`
  line `been committed or attempted, shall be recorded, by a woman police officer or any woman officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (91167)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 181
  title `Statements to police and use thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91167&sectionno=181&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `(1) No statement made by any person to a police officer`
  line `in the course of an investigation under this Chapter, shall, if reduced to writing, be signed by the person`
  line `making it; nor shall any such statement or any record thereof, whether in a police diary or otherwise, or any`
  line `part of such statement or record, be used for any purpose, save as hereinafter provided, at any inquiry or`
  line `trial in respect of any offence under investigation at the time when such statement was made:`
  line
  line `Provided that when any witness is called for the prosecution in such inquiry or trial whose statement`
  line `has been reduced into writing as aforesaid, any part of his statement, if duly proved, may be used by the`
  line `accused, and with the permission of the Court, by the prosecution, to contradict such witness in the manner`
  line `provided by section 148 of the Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam, 2023; and when any part of such statement`
  line `is so used, any part thereof may also be used in the re-examination of such witness, but for the purpose only`
  line `of explaining any matter referred to in his cross-examination.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to apply to any statement falling within the provisions of`
  line `clause (a) of section 26 of the Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam, 2023; or to affect the provisions of the proviso`
  line `to sub-section (2) of section 23 of that Adhiniyam.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—An omission to state a fact or circumstance in the statement referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) may amount to contradiction if the same appears to be significant and otherwise relevant`
  line `having regard to the context in which such omission occurs and whether any omission amounts to a`
  line `contradiction in the particular context shall be a question of fact.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (91168)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 182
  title `No inducement to be offered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91168&sectionno=182&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `(1) No police officer or other person in authority shall offer or`
  line `make, or cause to be offered or made, any such inducement, threat or promise as is mentioned in`
  line `section 22 of the Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam, 2023.`
  line
  line `(2) But no police officer or other person shall prevent, by any caution or otherwise, any person from`
  line `making in the course of any investigation under this Chapter any statement which he may be disposed to`
  line `make of his own free will:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall affect the provisions of sub-section (4) of section 183.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (91169)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 183
  title `Recording of confessions and statements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91169&sectionno=183&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Magistrate of the District in which the`
  line `information about commission of any offence has been registered, may, whether or not he has jurisdiction`
  line `in the case, record any confession or statement made to him in the course of an investigation under this`
  line `Chapter or under any other law for the time being in force, or at any time afterwards but before the`
  line `commencement of the inquiry or trial:`
  line
  line `Provided that any confession or statement made under this sub-section may also be recorded by audiovideo electronic means in the presence of the advocate of the person accused of an offence:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no confession shall be recorded by a police officer on whom any power of a`
  line `Magistrate has been conferred under any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate shall, before recording any such confession, explain to the person making it that he`
  line `is not bound to make a confession and that, if he does so, it may be used as evidence against him; and the`
  line `Magistrate shall not record any such confession unless, upon questioning the person making it, he has`
  line `reason to believe that it is being made voluntarily.`
  line
  line `(3) If at any time before the confession is recorded, the person appearing before the Magistrate states`
  line `that he is not willing to make the confession, the Magistrate shall not authorise the detention of such person`
  line `in police custody.`
  line
  line `(4) Any such confession shall be recorded in the manner provided in section 316 for recording the`
  line `examination of an accused person and shall be signed by the person making the confession; and the`
  line `Magistrate shall make a memorandum at the foot of such record to the following effect:—`
  line
  line `"I have explained to (name) that he is not bound to make a confession and that, if he does so, any`
  line `confession he may make may be used as evidence against him and I believe that this confession was`
  line `voluntarily made. It was taken in my presence and hearing, and was read over to the person making it`
  line `and admitted by him to be correct, and it contains a full and true account of the statement made by him.`
  line `(Signed) A. B.`
  line
  line `Magistrate.".`
  line
  line `(5) Any statement (other than a confession) made under sub-section (1) shall be recorded in such`
  line `manner hereinafter provided for the recording of evidence as is, in the opinion of the Magistrate, best fitted`
  line `to the circumstances of the case; and the Magistrate shall have power to administer oath to the person whose`
  line `statement is so recorded.`
  line
  line `(6) (a) In cases punishable under section 64, section 65, section 66, section 67, section 68, section 69,`
  line `section 70, section 71, section 74, section 75, section 76, section 77, section 78, section 79 or section 124`
  line `of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, the Magistrate shall record the statement of the person against whom`
  line `such offence has been committed in the manner specified in sub-section (5), as soon as the commission of`
  line `the offence is brought to the notice of the police:`
  line
  line `Provided that such statement shall, as far as practicable, be recorded by a woman Magistrate and in her`
  line `absence by a male Magistrate in the presence of a woman:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in cases relating to the offences punishable with imprisonment for ten years or`
  line `more or with imprisonment for life or with death, the Magistrate shall record the statement of the witness`
  line `brought before him by the police officer:`
  line
  line `Provided also that if the person making the statement is temporarily or permanently, mentally or`
  line `physically disabled, the Magistrate shall take the assistance of an interpreter or a special educator in`
  line `recording the statement:`
  line
  line `Provided also that if the person making the statement is temporarily or permanently, mentally or`
  line `physically disabled, the statement made by the person, with the assistance of an interpreter or a special`
  line `educator, shall be recorded through audio-video electronic means preferably by mobile phone;`
  line
  line `(b) a statement recorded under clause (a) of a person, who is temporarily or permanently, mentally or`
  line `physically disabled, shall be considered a statement in lieu of examination-in-chief, as specified in section`
  line `142 of the Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam, 2023 such that the maker of the statement can be cross-examined`
  line `on such statement, without the need for recording the same at the time of trial.`
  line
  line `(7) The Magistrate recording a confession or statement under this section shall forward it to the`
  line `Magistrate by whom the case is to be inquired into or tried.`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (91170)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 184
  title `Medical examination of victim of rape.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91170&sectionno=184&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, during the stage when an offence of`
  line `committing rape or attempt to commit rape is under investigation, it is proposed to get the person of the`
  line `woman with whom rape is alleged or attempted to have been committed or attempted, examined`
  line `by a medical expert, such examination shall be conducted by a registered medical practitioner employed in`
  line `a hospital run by the Government or a local authority and in the absence of such a practitioner, by any other`
  line `registered medical practitioner, with the consent of such woman or of a person competent to give such`
  line `consent on her behalf and such woman shall be sent to such registered medical practitioner within`
  line `twenty-four hours from the time of receiving the information relating to the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) The registered medical practitioner, to whom such woman is sent, shall, without delay, examine her`
  line `person and prepare a report of his examination giving the following particulars, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the name and address of the woman and of the person by whom she was brought;`
  line
  line `(ii) the age of the woman;`
  line
  line `(iii) the description of material taken from the person of the woman for DNA profiling;`
  line
  line `(iv) marks of injury, if any, on the person of the woman;`
  line
  line `(v) general mental condition of the woman; and`
  line
  line `(vi) other material particulars in reasonable detail.`
  line
  line `(3) The report shall state precisely the reasons for each conclusion arrived at.`
  line
  line `(4) The report shall specifically record that the consent of the woman or of the person competent to`
  line `give such consent on her behalf to such examination had been obtained.`
  line
  line `(5) The exact time of commencement and completion of the examination shall also be noted in the`
  line report.
  line
  line `(6) The registered medical practitioner shall, within a period of seven days forward the report to the`
  line `investigating officer who shall forward it to the Magistrate referred to in section 193 as part of the`
  line `documents referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (6) of that section.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing in this section shall be construed as rendering lawful any examination without the consent`
  line `of the woman or of any person competent to give such consent on her behalf.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, "examination" and "registered medical practitioner"`
  line `shall have the same meanings as respectively assigned to them in section 51.`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (91171)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 185
  title `Search by police officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91171&sectionno=185&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever an officer in charge of a police station or a police officer`
  line `making an investigation has reasonable grounds for believing that anything necessary for the purposes of`
  line `an investigation into any offence which he is authorised to investigate may be found in any place within the`
  line `limits of the police station of which he is in charge, or to which he is attached, and that such thing cannot`
  line `in his opinion be otherwise obtained without undue delay, such officer may, after recording in writing the`
  line `grounds of his belief in the case-diary and specifying in such writing, so far as possible, the thing for which`
  line `search is to be made, search, or cause search to be made, for such thing in any place within the limits of`
  line `such station.`
  line
  line `(2) A police officer proceeding under sub-section (1), shall, if practicable, conduct the search in person:`
  line
  line `Provided that the search conducted under this section shall be recorded through audio-video electronic`
  line `means preferably by mobile phone.`
  line
  line `(3) If he is unable to conduct the search in person, and there is no other person competent to make the`
  line `search present at the time, he may, after recording in writing his reasons for so doing, require any officer`
  line `subordinate to him to make the search, and he shall deliver to such subordinate officer an order in writing,`
  line `specifying the place to be searched, and so far as possible, the thing for which search is to be made; and`
  line `such subordinate officer may thereupon search for such thing in such place.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this Sanhita as to search-warrants and the general provisions as to searches`
  line `contained in section 103 shall, so far as may be, apply to a search made under this section.`
  line
  line `(5) Copies of any record made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) shall forthwith, but not later`
  line `than forty-eight hours, be sent to the nearest Magistrate empowered to take cognizance of the offence, and`
  line `the owner or occupier of the place searched shall, on application, be furnished, free of cost, with a copy of`
  line `the same by the Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (91172)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 186
  title `When officer in charge of police station may require another to issue search-warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91172&sectionno=186&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `An officer in charge of a police station or a police officer not being below the rank of sub-inspector making`
  line `an investigation may require an officer in charge of another police station, whether in the same or a different`
  line `district, to cause a search to be made in any place, in any case in which the former officer might cause such`
  line `search to be made, within the limits of his own station.`
  line
  line `(2) Such officer, on being so required, shall proceed according to the provisions of section 185, and`
  line `shall forward the thing found, if any, to the officer at whose request the search was made.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever there is reason to believe that the delay occasioned by requiring an officer in charge of`
  line `another police station to cause a search to be made under sub-section (1) might result in evidence of the`
  line `commission of an offence being concealed or destroyed, it shall be lawful for an officer in charge of a police`
  line `station or a police officer making any investigation under this Chapter to search, or cause to be searched,`
  line `any place in the limits of another police station in accordance with the provisions of section 185, as if such`
  line `place were within the limits of his own police station.`
  line
  line `(4) Any officer conducting a search under sub-section (3) shall forthwith send notice of the search to`
  line `the officer in charge of the police station within the limits of which such place is situate, and shall also`
  line `send with such notice a copy of the list (if any) prepared under section 103, and shall also send to the`
  line `nearest Magistrate empowered to take cognizance of the offence, copies of the records referred to in subsections (1) and (3) of section 185.`
  line
  line `(5) The owner or occupier of the place searched shall, on application, be furnished free of cost with a`
  line `copy of any record sent to the Magistrate under sub-section (4).`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (91173)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 187
  title `Procedure when investigation cannot be completed in twenty-four hours.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91173&sectionno=187&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any`
  line `person is arrested and detained in custody, and it appears that the investigation cannot be completed within`
  line `the period of twenty-four hours fixed by section 58, and there are grounds for believing that the accusation`
  line `or information is well-founded, the officer in charge of the police station or the police officer making the`
  line `investigation, if he is not below the rank of sub-inspector, shall forthwith transmit to the nearest Magistrate`
  line `a copy of the entries in the diary hereinafter specified relating to the case, and shall at the same time forward`
  line `the accused to such Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate to whom an accused person is forwarded under this section may, irrespective of`
  line `whether he has or has no jurisdiction to try the case, after taking into consideration whether such person`
  line `has not been released on bail or his bail has been cancelled, authorise, from time to time, the detention of`
  line `the accused in such custody as such Magistrate thinks fit, for a term not exceeding fifteen days in the whole,`
  line `or in parts, at any time during the initial forty days or sixty days out of detention period of sixty days or`
  line `ninety days, as the case may be, as provided in sub-section (3), and if he has no jurisdiction to try the case`
  line `or commit it for trial, and considers further detention unnecessary, he may order the accused to be forwarded`
  line `to a Magistrate having such jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) The Magistrate may authorise the detention of the accused person, beyond the period of fifteen days,`
  line `if he is satisfied that adequate grounds exist for doing so, but no Magistrate shall authorise the detention of`
  line `the accused person in custody under this sub-section for a total period exceeding—`
  line
  line `(i) ninety days, where the investigation relates to an offence punishable with death, imprisonment`
  line `for life or imprisonment for a term of ten years or more;`
  line
  line `(ii) sixty days, where the investigation relates to any other offence, and, on the expiry of the said`
  line `period of ninety days, or sixty days, as the case may be, the accused person shall be released on bail if`
  line `he is prepared to and does furnish bail, and every person released on bail under this sub-section shall`
  line `be deemed to be so released under the provisions of Chapter XXXV for the purposes of that Chapter.`
  line
  line `(4) No Magistrate shall authorise detention of the accused in custody of the police under this section`
  line `unless the accused is produced before him in person for the first time and subsequently every time till the`
  line `accused remains in the custody of the police, but the Magistrate may extend further detention in judicial`
  line `custody on production of the accused either in person or through the audio-video electronic means.`
  line
  line `(5) No Magistrate of the second class, not specially empowered in this behalf by the High Court, shall`
  line `authorise detention in the custody of the police.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.—For the avoidance of doubts, it is hereby declared that, notwithstanding the expiry of`
  line `the period specified in sub-section (3), the accused shall be detained in custody so long as he does not`
  line `furnish bail.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.—If any question arises whether an accused person was produced before the Magistrate`
  line `as required under sub-section (4), the production of the accused person may be proved by his signature on`
  line `the order authorising detention or by the order certified by the Magistrate as to production of the accused`
  line `person through the audio-video electronic means, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a woman under eighteen years of age, the detention shall be authorised to be`
  line `in the custody of a remand home or recognised social institution:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no person shall be detained otherwise than in police station under police custody`
  line `or in prison under judicial custody or a place declared as prison by the Central Government or the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) to sub-section (5), the officer in charge of`
  line `the police station or the police officer making the investigation, if he is not below the rank of a`
  line `sub-inspector, may, where a Magistrate is not available, transmit to the nearest Executive Magistrate, on`
  line `whom the powers of a Magistrate have been conferred, a copy of the entry in the diary hereinafter specified`
  line `relating to the case, and shall, at the same time, forward the accused to such Executive Magistrate, and`
  line `thereupon such Executive Magistrate, may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, authorise the detention of`
  line `the accused person in such custody as he may think fit for a term not exceeding seven days in the aggregate;`
  line `and, on the expiry of the period of detention so authorised, the accused person shall be released on bail`
  line `except where an order for further detention of the accused person has been made by a Magistrate competent`
  line `to make such order; and, where an order for such further detention is made, the period during which the`
  line `accused person was detained in custody under the orders made by an Executive Magistrate under this subsection, shall be taken into account in computing the period specified in sub-section (3):`
  line
  line `Provided that before the expiry of the period aforesaid, the Executive Magistrate shall transmit to the`
  line `nearest Judicial Magistrate the records of the case together with a copy of the entries in the diary relating`
  line `to the case which was transmitted to him by the officer in charge of the police station or the police officer`
  line `making the investigation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(7) A Magistrate authorising under this section detention in the custody of the police shall record his`
  line `reasons for so doing.`
  line
  line `(8) Any Magistrate other than the Chief Judicial Magistrate making such order shall forward a copy of`
  line `his order, with his reasons for making it, to the Chief Judicial Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(9) If in any case triable by a Magistrate as a summons-case, the investigation is not concluded within`
  line `a period of six months from the date on which the accused was arrested, the Magistrate shall make an order`
  line `stopping further investigation into the offence unless the officer making the investigation satisfies the`
  line `Magistrate that for special reasons and in the interests of justice the continuation of the investigation beyond`
  line `the period of six months is necessary.`
  line
  line `(10) Where any order stopping further investigation into an offence has been made under`
  line `sub-section (9), the Sessions Judge may, if he is satisfied, on an application made to him or otherwise, that`
  line `further investigation into the offence ought to be made, vacate the order made under sub-section (9) and`
  line `direct further investigation to be made into the offence subject to such directions with regard to bail and`
  line `other matters as he may specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (91174)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 188
  title `Report of investigation by subordinate police officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91174&sectionno=188&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `When any subordinate police officer`
  line `has made any investigation under this Chapter, he shall report the result of such investigation to the officer`
  line `in charge of the police station.`
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (91175)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 189
  title `Release of accused when evidence deficient.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91175&sectionno=189&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `If, upon an investigation under this Chapter, it`
  line `appears to the officer in charge of the police station that there is not sufficient evidence or reasonable round`
  line `of suspicion to justify the forwarding of the accused to a Magistrate, such officer shall, if such person is in`
  line `custody, release him on his executing a bond or bail bond, as such officer may direct, to appear, if and when`
  line `so required, before a Magistrate empowered to take cognizance of the offence on a police report, and to try`
  line `the accused or commit him for trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (91176)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 190
  title `Cases to be sent to Magistrate, when evidence is sufficient.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91176&sectionno=190&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, upon an investigation under`
  line `this Chapter, it appears to the officer in charge of the police station that there is sufficient evidence or`
  line `reasonable ground as aforesaid, such officer shall forward the accused under custody to a Magistrate`
  line `empowered to take cognizance of the offence upon a police report and to try the accused or commit him for`
  line `trial, or, if the offence is bailable and the accused is able to give security, shall take security from him for`
  line `his appearance before such Magistrate on a day fixed and for his attendance from day to day before such`
  line `Magistrate until otherwise directed:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the accused is not in custody, the police officer shall take security from such person for`
  line `his appearance before the Magistrate and the Magistrate to whom such report is forwarded shall not refuse`
  line `to accept the same on the ground that the accused is not taken in custody.`
  line
  line `(2) When the officer in charge of a police station forwards an accused person to a Magistrate or takes`
  line `security for his appearance before such Magistrate under this section, he shall send to such Magistrate any`
  line `weapon or other article which it may be necessary to produce before him, and shall require the complainant`
  line `(if any) and so many of the persons who appear to such officer to be acquainted with the facts and`
  line `circumstances of the case as he may think necessary, to execute a bond to appear before the Magistrate as`
  line `thereby directed and prosecute or give evidence (as the case may be) in the matter of the charge against the`
  line accused.
  line
  line `(3) If the Court of the Chief Judicial Magistrate is mentioned in the bond, such Court shall be held to`
  line `include any Court to which such Magistrate may refer the case for inquiry or trial, provided reasonable`
  line `notice of such reference is given to such complainant or persons.`
  line
  line `(4) The officer in whose presence the bond is executed shall deliver a copy thereof to one of the persons`
  line `who executed it, and shall then send to the Magistrate the original with his report.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (91550)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 191
  title `Complainant and witnesses not to be required to accompany police officer and not to be subject to restraint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91550&sectionno=191&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `No complainant or witness on his way to any Court shall be required to accompany`
  line `a police officer, or shall be subjected to unnecessary restraint or inconvenience, or required to give any`
  line `security for his appearance other than his own bond:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any complainant or witness refuses to attend or to execute a bond as directed in section`
  line `190, the officer in charge of the police station may forward him in custody to the Magistrate, who may`
  line `detain him in custody until he executes such bond, or until the hearing of the case is completed.`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (91178)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 192
  title `Diary of proceedings in investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91178&sectionno=192&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every police officer making an investigation under`
  line `this Chapter shall day by day enter his proceedings in the investigation in a diary, setting forth the time at`
  line `which the information reached him, the time at which he began and closed his investigation, the place or`
  line `places visited by him, and a statement of the circumstances ascertained through his investigation.`
  line
  line `(2) The statements of witnesses recorded during the course of investigation under section 180 shall be`
  line `inserted in the case diary.`
  line
  line `(3) The diary referred to in sub-section (1) shall be a volume and duly paginated.`
  line
  line `(4) Any Criminal Court may send for the police diaries of a case under inquiry or trial in such Court,`
  line `and may use such diaries, not as evidence in the case, but to aid it in such inquiry or trial.`
  line
  line `(5) Neither the accused nor his agents shall be entitled to call for such diaries, nor shall he or they be`
  line `entitled to see them merely because they are referred to by the Court; but, if they are used by the police`
  line `officer who made them to refresh his memory, or if the Court uses them for the purpose of contradicting`
  line `such police officer, the provisions of section 148 or section 164, as the case may be, of the Bharatiya`
  line `Sakshya Adhiniyam, 2023, shall apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (91179)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 193
  title `Report of police officer on completion of investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91179&sectionno=193&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every investigation under this`
  line `Chapter shall be completed without unnecessary delay.`
  line
  line `(2) The investigation in relation to an offence under sections 64, 65, 66, 67, 68, 70, 71 of the Bharatiya`
  line `Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 or under sections 4, 6, 8 or section 10 of the Protection of Children from Sexual`
  line `Offences Act, 2012 shall be completed within two months from the date on which the information was`
  line `recorded by the officer in charge of the police station.`
  line
  line `(3) (i) As soon as the investigation is completed, the officer in charge of the police station shall forward,`
  line `including through electronic communication to a Magistrate empowered to take cognizance of the offence`
  line `on a police report, a report in the form as the State Government may, by rules provide, stating—`
  line
  line `(a) the names of the parties;`
  line
  line `(b) the nature of the information;`
  line
  line `(c) the names of the persons who appear to be acquainted with the circumstances of the case;`
  line
  line `(d) whether any offence appears to have been committed and, if so, by whom;`
  line
  line `(e) whether the accused has been arrested;`
  line
  line `(f) whether the accused has been released on his bond or bail bond;`
  line
  line `(g) whether the accused has been forwarded in custody under section 190;`
  line
  line `(h) whether the report of medical examination of the woman has been attached where investigation`
  line `relates to an offence under sections 64, 65, 66, 67, 68, 70 or section 71 of the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023;`
  line
  line `(i) the sequence of custody in case of electronic device;`
  line
  line `(ii) the police officer shall, within a period of ninety days, inform the progress of the investigation`
  line `by any means including through electronic communication to the informant or the victim;`
  line
  line `(iii) the officer shall also communicate, in such manner as the State Government may, by rules,`
  line `provide, the action taken by him, to the person, if any, by whom the information relating to the`
  line `commission of the offence was first given.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a superior officer of police has been appointed under section 177, the report shall, in any`
  line `case in which the State Government by general or special order so directs, be submitted through that officer,`
  line `and he may, pending the orders of the Magistrate, direct the officer in charge of the police station to make`
  line `further investigation.`
  line
  line `(5) Whenever it appears from a report forwarded under this section that the accused has been released`
  line `on his bond or bail bond, the Magistrate shall make such order for the discharge of such bond or bail bond`
  line `or otherwise as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(6) When such report is in respect of a case to which section 190 applies, the police officer shall forward`
  line `to the Magistrate along with the report—`
  line
  line `(a) all documents or relevant extracts thereof on which the prosecution proposes to rely other than`
  line `those already sent to the Magistrate during investigation;`
  line
  line `(b) the statements recorded under section 180 of all the persons whom the prosecution proposes to`
  line `examine as its witnesses.`
  line
  line `(7) If the police officer is of opinion that any part of any such statement is not relevant to the subject`
  line `matter of the proceedings or that its disclosure to the accused is not essential in the interests of justice and`
  line `is inexpedient in the public interest, he shall indicate that part of the statement and append a note requesting`
  line `the Magistrate to exclude that part from the copies to be granted to the accused and stating his reasons for`
  line `making such request.`
  line
  line `(8) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (7), the police officer investigating the case shall`
  line `also submit such number of copies of the police report along with other documents duly indexed to the`
  line `Magistrate for supply to the accused as required under section 230:`
  line
  line `Provided that supply of report and other documents by electronic communication shall be considered`
  line `as duly served.`
  line
  line `(9) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to preclude further investigation in respect of an offence`
  line `after a report under sub-section (3) has been forwarded to the Magistrate and, where upon such`
  line `investigation, the officer in charge of the police station obtains further evidence, oral or documentary, he`
  line `shall forward to the Magistrate a further report or reports regarding such evidence in the form as the State`
  line `Government may, by rules, provide; and the provisions of sub-sections (3) to (8) shall, as far as may be,`
  line `apply in relation to such report or reports as they apply in relation to a report forwarded under`
  line `sub-section (3):`
  line
  line `Provided that further investigation during the trial may be conducted with the permission of the Court`
  line `trying the case and the same shall be completed within a period of ninety days which may be extended with`
  line `the permission of the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (91180)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 194
  title `Police to enquire and report on suicide, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91180&sectionno=194&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the officer in charge of a police station`
  line `or some other police officer specially empowered by the State Government in that behalf receives`
  line `information that a person has committed suicide, or has been killed by another or by an animal or by`
  line `machinery or by an accident, or has died under circumstances raising a reasonable suspicion that some other`
  line `person has committed an offence, he shall immediately give intimation thereof to the nearest Executive`
  line `Magistrate empowered to hold inquests, and, unless otherwise directed by any rule made by the State`
  line `Government, or by any general or special order of the District or Sub-divisional Magistrate, shall proceed`
  line `to the place where the body of such deceased person is, and there, in the presence of two or more respectable`
  line `inhabitants of the neighbourhood, shall make an investigation, and draw up a report of the apparent cause`
  line `of death, describing such wounds, fractures, bruises, and other marks of injury as may be found on the body,`
  line `and stating in what manner, or by what weapon or instrument (if any), such marks appear to have been`
  line inflicted.
  line
  line `(2) The report shall be signed by such police officer and other persons, or by so many of them as concur`
  line `therein, and shall be forwarded to the District Magistrate or the Sub-divisional Magistrate within twentyfour hours.`
  line
  line `(3) When—`
  line
  line `(i) the case involves suicide by a woman within seven years of her marriage; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the case relates to the death of a woman within seven years of her marriage in any circumstances`
  line `raising a reasonable suspicion that some other person committed an offence in relation to such`
  line `woman; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the case relates to the death of a woman within seven years of her marriage and any relative of`
  line `the woman has made a request in this behalf; or`
  line
  line `(iv) there is any doubt regarding the cause of death; or`
  line
  line `(v) the police officer for any other reason considers it expedient so to do,`
  line
  line `he shall, subject to such rules as the State Government may prescribe in this behalf, forward the body, with`
  line `a view to its being examined, to the nearest Civil Surgeon, or other qualified medical person appointed in`
  line `this behalf by the State Government, if the state of the weather and the distance admit of its being so`
  line `forwarded without risk of such putrefaction on the road as would render such examination useless.`
  line
  line `(4) The following Magistrates are empowered to hold inquests, namely, any District Magistrate or Subdivisional Magistrate and any other Executive Magistrate specially empowered in this behalf by the State`
  line `Government or the District Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (91181)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 195
  title `Power to summon persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91181&sectionno=195&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `(1) A police officer proceeding under section 194 may, by order in`
  line `writing, summon two or more persons as aforesaid for the purpose of the said investigation, and any other`
  line `person who appears to be acquainted with the facts of the case and every person so summoned shall be`
  line `bound to attend and to answer truly all questions other than questions the answers to which would have a`
  line `tendency to expose him to a criminal charge or to a penalty or forfeiture:`
  line
  line `Provided that no male person under the age of fifteen years or above the age of sixty years or a woman`
  line `or a mentally or physically disabled person or a person with acute illness shall be required to attend at any`
  line `place other than the place where such person resides:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if such person is willing to attend and answer at the police station, such person`
  line `may be permitted so to do.`
  line
  line `(2) If the facts do not disclose a cognizable offence to which section 190 applies, such persons shall not`
  line `be required by the police officer to attend a Magistrate's Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (91182)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 196
  title `Inquiry by Magistrate into cause of death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91182&sectionno=196&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the case is of the nature referred to in`
  line `clause (i) or clause (ii) of sub-section (3) of section 194, the nearest Magistrate empowered to hold inquests`
  line `shall, and in any other case mentioned in sub-section (1) of section 194, any Magistrate so empowered may`
  line `hold an inquiry into the cause of death either instead of, or in addition to, the investigation held by the`
  line `police officer; and if he does so, he shall have all the powers in conducting it which he would have in`
  line `holding an inquiry into an offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Where,—`
  line
  line `(a) any person dies or disappears; or`
  line
  line `(b) rape is alleged to have been committed on any woman, while such person or woman is in the`
  line `custody of the police or in any other custody authorisedby the Magistrate or the Court, under this`
  line `Sanhita in addition to the inquiry or investigation held by the police, an inquiry shall be held by the`
  line `Magistrate within whose local jurisdiction the offence has been committed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Magistrate holding such an inquiry shall record the evidence taken by him in connection`
  line `therewith in any manner hereinafter specified according to the circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(4) Whenever such Magistrate considers it expedient to make an examination of the dead body of any`
  line `person who has been already interred, in order to discover the cause of his death, the Magistrate may cause`
  line `the body to be disinterred and examined.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an inquiry is to be held under this section, the Magistrate shall, wherever practicable, inform`
  line `the relatives of the deceased whose names and addresses are known, and shall allow them to remain present`
  line `at the inquiry.`
  line
  line `(6) The Magistrate or the Executive Magistrate or the police officer holding an inquiry or investigation`
  line `under sub-section (2) shall, within twenty-four hours of the death of a person, forward the body with a view`
  line `to its being examined to the nearest Civil Surgeon or other qualified medical person appointed in this behalf`
  line `by the State Government, unless it is not possible to do so for reasons to be recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "relative" means parents, children, brothers, sisters and`
  line spouse.
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (91183)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 197
  title `Ordinary place of inquiry and trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91183&sectionno=197&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `Every offence shall ordinarily be inquired into and tried`
  line `by a Court within whose local jurisdiction it was committed.`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (91184)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 198
  title `Place of inquiry or trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91184&sectionno=198&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `(a) When it is uncertain in which of several local areas an offence was`
  line `committed; or`
  line
  line `(b) where an offence is committed partly in one local area and partly in another; or`
  line
  line `(c) where an offence is a continuing one, and continues to be committed in more local areas than`
  line `one; or`
  line
  line `(d) where it consists of several acts done in different local areas, it may be inquired into or tried by a`
  line `Court having jurisdiction over any of such local areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (91185)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 199
  title `Offence triable where act is done or consequence ensues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91185&sectionno=199&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `When an act is an offence by reason`
  line `of anything which has been done and of a consequence which has ensued, the offence may be inquired into`
  line `or tried by a Court within whose local jurisdiction such thing has been done or such consequence has`
  line ensued.
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (91186)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 200
  title `Place of trial where act is an offence by reason of relation to other offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91186&sectionno=200&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `When an act is`
  line `an offence by reason of its relation to any other act which is also an offence or which would be an offence`
  line `if the doer were capable of committing an offence, the first-mentioned offence may be inquired into or tried`
  line `by a Court within whose local jurisdiction either act was done.`
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_201:
  sectionId (91187)
  sectionNo (201)
  orderNo 201
  title `Place of trial in case of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_201_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91187&sectionno=201&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_201_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any offence of dacoity, or of dacoity with murder,`
  line `of belonging to a gang of dacoits, or of escaping from custody, may be inquired into or tried by a Court`
  line `within whose local jurisdiction the offence was committed or the accused person is found.`
  line
  line `(2) Any offence of kidnapping or abduction of a person may be inquired into or tried by a Court within`
  line `whose local jurisdiction the person was kidnapped or abducted or was conveyed or concealed or detained.`
  line
  line `(3) Any offence of theft, extortion or robbery may be inquired into or tried by a Court within whose`
  line `local jurisdiction the offence was committed or the stolen property which isthe subject of the offence was`
  line `possessed by any person committing it or by any person who received or retained such property knowing`
  line `or having reason to believe it to be stolen property.`
  line
  line `(4) Any offence of criminal misappropriation or of criminal breach of trust may be inquired into or tried`
  line `by a Court within whose local jurisdiction the offence was committed or any part of the property which is`
  line `the subject of the offence was received or retained, or was required to be returned or accounted for, by the`
  line `accused person.`
  line
  line `(5) Any offence which includes the possession of stolen property may be inquired into or tried by a`
  line `Court within whose local jurisdiction the offence was committed or the stolen property was possessed by`
  line `any person who received or retained it knowing or having reason to believe it to be stolen property.`
obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_202:
  sectionId (91188)
  sectionNo (202)
  orderNo 202
  title `Offences committed by means of electronic communications, letters, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_202_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91188&sectionno=202&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_202_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any offence`
  line `which includes cheating, may, if the deception is practised by means of electronic communications or letters`
  line `or telecommunication messages, be inquired into or tried by any Court within whose local jurisdiction such`
  line `electronic communications or letters or messages were sent or were received; and any offence of cheating`
  line `and dishonestly inducing delivery of property may be inquired into or tried by a Court within whose local`
  line `jurisdiction the property was delivered by the person deceived or was received by the accused person.`
  line
  line `(2) Any offence punishable under section 82 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 may be inquired`
  line `into or tried by a Court within whose local jurisdiction the offence was committed or the offender last`
  line `resided with his or her spouse by the first marriage, or the wife by the first marriage has taken up permanent`
  line `residence after the commission of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_203:
  sectionId (91189)
  sectionNo (203)
  orderNo 203
  title `Offence committed on journey or voyage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_203_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91189&sectionno=203&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_203_content:
  string
  line `When an offence is committed whilst the person by`
  line `or against whom, or the thing in respect of which, the offence is committed is in the course of performing`
  line `a journey or voyage, the offence may be inquired into or tried by a Court through or into whose local`
  line `jurisdiction that person or thing passed in the course of that journey or voyage.`
obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_204:
  sectionId (91190)
  sectionNo (204)
  orderNo 204
  title `Place of trial for offences triable together.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_204_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91190&sectionno=204&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line Where—
  line
  line `(a) the offences committed by any person are such that he may be charged with, and tried at one`
  line `trial for, each such offence by virtue of the provisions of section 242, section 243 or section 244; or`
  line
  line `(b) the offence or offences committed by several persons are such that they may be charged with`
  line `and tried together by virtue of the provisions of section 246, the offences may be inquired into or tried`
  line `by any Court competent to inquire into or try any of the offences.`
obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_205:
  sectionId (91191)
  sectionNo (205)
  orderNo 205
  title `Power to order cases to be tried in different sessions divisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_205_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91191&sectionno=205&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_205_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the preceding provisions of this Chapter, the State Government may direct that any case or`
  line `class of cases committed for trial in any district may be tried in any sessions division:`
  line
  line `Provided that such direction is not repugnant to any direction previously issued by the High Court or`
  line `the Supreme Court under the Constitution, or under this Sanhita or any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_206:
  sectionId (91192)
  sectionNo (206)
  orderNo 206
  title `High Court to decide, in case of doubt, district where inquiry or trial shall take place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_206_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91192&sectionno=206&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_206_content:
  string
  line `Where two or more Courts have taken cognizance of the same offence and a question arises as to which of`
  line `them ought to inquire into or try that offence, the question shall be decided—`
  line
  line `(a) if the Courts are subordinate to the same High Court, by that High Court;`
  line
  line `(b) if the Courts are not subordinate to the same High Court, by the High Court within the local`
  line `limits of whose appellate criminal jurisdiction the proceedings were first commenced, and thereupon`
  line `all other proceedings in respect of that offence shall be discontinued.`
obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_207:
  sectionId (91193)
  sectionNo (207)
  orderNo 207
  title `Power to issue summons or warrant for offence committed beyond local jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_207_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91193&sectionno=207&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_207_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `When a Magistrate of the first class sees reason to believe that any person within his local jurisdiction has`
  line `committed outside such jurisdiction (whether within or outside India) an offence which cannot, under the`
  line `provisions of sections 197 to 205 (both inclusive), or any other law for the time being in force, be inquired`
  line `into or tried within such jurisdiction but is under any law for the time being in force triable in India, such`
  line `Magistrate may inquire into the offence as if it had been committed within such local jurisdiction and`
  line `compel such person in the manner hereinbefore provided to appear before him, and send such person to the`
  line `Magistrate having jurisdiction to inquire into or try such offence, or, if such offence is not punishable with`
  line `death or imprisonment for life and such person is ready and willing to give bail to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Magistrate acting under this section, take a bond or bail bond for his appearance before the Magistrate`
  line `having such jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) When there are more Magistrates than one having such jurisdiction and the Magistrate acting under`
  line `this section cannot satisfy himself as to the Magistrate to or before whom such person should be sent or`
  line `bound to appear, the case shall be reported for the orders of the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_208:
  sectionId (91194)
  sectionNo (208)
  orderNo 208
  title `Offence committed outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_208_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91194&sectionno=208&orderno=208&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_208_content:
  string
  line `When an offence is committed outside India—`
  line
  line `(a) by a citizen of India, whether on the high seas or elsewhere; or`
  line
  line `(b) by a person, not being such citizen, on any ship or aircraft registered in India,`
  line
  line `he may be dealt with in respect of such offence as if it had been committed at any place within India at`
  line `which he may be found or where the offence is registered in India:`
  line
  line `Provided that notwithstanding anything in any of the preceding sections of this Chapter, no such offence`
  line `shall be inquired into or tried in India except with the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_209:
  sectionId (91195)
  sectionNo (209)
  orderNo 209
  title `Receipt of evidence relating to offences committed outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_209_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91195&sectionno=209&orderno=209&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_209_content:
  string
  line `When any offence alleged`
  line `to have been committed in a territory outside India is being inquired into or tried under the provisions of`
  line `section 208, the Central Government may, if it thinks fit, direct that copies of depositions made or exhibits`
  line `produced, either in physical form or in electronic form, before a judicial officer, in or for that territory or`
  line `before a diplomatic or consular representative of India in or for that territory shall be received as evidence`
  line `by the Court holding such inquiry or trial in any case in which such Court might issue a commission for`
  line `taking evidence as to the matters to which such depositions or exhibits relate.`
obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_210:
  sectionId (91196)
  sectionNo (210)
  orderNo 210
  title `Cognizance of offences by Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_210_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91196&sectionno=210&orderno=210&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_210_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Chapter, any`
  line `Magistrate of the first class, and any Magistrate of the second class specially empowered in this behalf`
  line `under sub-section (2), may take cognizance of any offence—`
  line
  line `(a) upon receiving a complaint of facts, including any complaint filed by a person authorised under`
  line `any special law, which constitutes such offence;`
  line
  line `(b) upon a police report (submitted in any mode including electronic mode) of such facts;`
  line
  line `(c) upon information received from any person other than a police officer, or upon his own`
  line `knowledge, that such offence has been committed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Judicial Magistrate may empower any Magistrate of the second class to take cognizance`
  line `under sub-section (1) of such offences as are within his competence to inquire into or try.`
obj_root_law_sections_210_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_211:
  sectionId (91197)
  sectionNo (211)
  orderNo 211
  title `Transfer on application of accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_211_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91197&sectionno=211&orderno=211&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_211_content:
  string
  line `When a Magistrate takes cognizance of an offence under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 210, the accused shall, before any evidence is taken, be informed`
  line `that he is entitled to have the case inquired into or tried by another Magistrate, and if the accused or any of`
  line `the accused, if there be more than one, objects to further proceedings before the Magistrate taking`
  line `cognizance, the case shall be transferred to such other Magistrate as may be specified by the Chief Judicial`
  line `Magistrate in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_211_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_212:
  sectionId (91198)
  sectionNo (212)
  orderNo 212
  title `Making over of cases to Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_212_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91198&sectionno=212&orderno=212&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_212_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Chief Judicial Magistrate may, after taking`
  line `cognizance of an offence, make over the case for inquiry or trial to any competent Magistrate subordinate`
  line `to him.`
  line
  line `(2) Any Magistrate of the first class empowered in this behalf by the Chief Judicial Magistrate may,`
  line `after taking cognizance of an offence, make over the case for inquiry or trial to such other competent`
  line `Magistrate as the Chief Judicial Magistrate may, by general or special order, specify, and thereupon such`
  line `Magistrate may hold the inquiry or trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_212_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_213:
  sectionId (91199)
  sectionNo (213)
  orderNo 213
  title `Cognizance of offences by Court of Session.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_213_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91199&sectionno=213&orderno=213&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_213_content:
  string
  line `Except as otherwise expressly provided by this`
  line `Sanhita or by any other law for the time being in force, no Court of Session shall take cognizance of any`
  line `offence as a Court of original jurisdiction unless the case has been committed to it by a Magistrate under`
  line `this Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_213_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_214:
  sectionId (91200)
  sectionNo (214)
  orderNo 214
  title `Additional Sessions Judges to try cases made over to them.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_214_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91200&sectionno=214&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_214_content:
  string
  line `An Additional Sessions Judge`
  line `shall try such cases as the Sessions Judge of the division may, by general or special order, make over to`
  line `him for trial or as the High Court may, by special order, direct him to try.`
obj_root_law_sections_214_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_215:
  sectionId (91551)
  sectionNo (215)
  orderNo 215
  title `. Prosecution for contempt of lawful authority of public servants, for offences against public justice and for offences relating to documents given in evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_215_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91551&sectionno=215&orderno=215&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_215_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Court shall take cognizance—`
  line
  line `(a) (i) of any offence punishable under sections 206 to 223 (both inclusive but excluding section`
  line `209) of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023; or`
  line
  line `(ii) of any abetment of, or attempt to commit, such offence; or`
  line
  line `(iii) of any criminal conspiracy to commit such offence,`
  line
  line `except on the complaint in writing of the public servant concerned or of some other public servant to`
  line `whom he is administratively subordinate or of some other public servant who is authorised by the`
  line `concerned public servant so to do;`
  line
  line `(b) (i) of any offence punishable under any of the following sections of the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023, namely, sections 229 to 233 (both inclusive), 236, 237, 242 to 248 (both inclusive) and`
  line `267, when such offence is alleged to have been committed in, or in relation to, any proceeding in any`
  line `Court; or`
  line
  line `(ii) of any offence described in sub-section (1) of section 336, or punishable under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 340 or section 342 of the said Sanhita, when such offence is alleged to have been committed`
  line `in respect of a document produced or given in evidence in a proceeding in any Court; or`
  line
  line `(iii) of any criminal conspiracy to commit, or attempt to commit, or the abetment of, any offence`
  line `specified in sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (ii),`
  line
  line `except on the complaint in writing of that Court or by such officer of the Court as that Court may authorise`
  line `in writing in this behalf, or of some other Court to which that Court is subordinate.`
obj_root_law_sections_215_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_216:
  sectionId (91202)
  sectionNo (216)
  orderNo 216
  title `Procedure for witnesses in case of threatening, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_216_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91202&sectionno=216&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_216_content:
  string
  line `A witness or any other person may file a`
  line `complaint in relation to an offence under section 232 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
obj_root_law_sections_216_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_217:
  sectionId (91203)
  sectionNo (217)
  orderNo 217
  title `Prosecution for offences against State and for criminal conspiracy to commit such offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_217_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91203&sectionno=217&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_217_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Court shall take cognizance of—`
  line
  line `(a) any offence punishable under Chapter VII or under section 196, section 299 or sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 353 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023; or`
  line
  line `(b) a criminal conspiracy to commit such offence; or`
  line
  line `(c) any such abetment, as is described in section 47 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, except`
  line `with the previous sanction of the Central Government or of the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) No Court shall take cognizance of—`
  line
  line `(a) any offence punishable under section 197 or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 353`
  line `of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023; or`
  line
  line `(b) a criminal conspiracy to commit such offence, except with the previous sanction of the Central`
  line `Government or of the State Government or of the District Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(3) No Court shall take cognizance of the offence of any criminal conspiracy punishable under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 61 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, other than a criminal conspiracy to`
  line `commit an offence punishable with death, imprisonment for life or rigorous imprisonment for a term of two`
  line `years or upwards, unless the State Government or the District Magistrate has consented in writing to the`
  line `initiation of the proceedings:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the criminal conspiracy is one to which the provisions of section 215 apply, no`
  line `such consent shall be necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government or the State Government may, before according sanction under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) and the District Magistrate may, before according sanction under`
  line `sub-section (2) and the State Government or the District Magistrate may, before giving consent under`
  line `sub-section (3), order a preliminary investigation by a police officer not being below the rank of Inspector,`
  line `in which case such police officer shall have the powers referred to in sub-section (3) of section 174.`
obj_root_law_sections_217_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_218:
  sectionId (91204)
  sectionNo (218)
  orderNo 218
  title `Prosecution of Judges and public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_218_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91204&sectionno=218&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_218_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person who is or was a Judge or`
  line `Magistrate or a public servant not removable from his office save by or with the sanction of the Government`
  line `is accused of any offence alleged to have been committed by him while acting or purporting to act in the`
  line `discharge of his official duty, no Court shall take cognizance of such offence except with the previous`
  line `sanction save as otherwise provided in the Lokpal and Lokayuktas Act, 2013 (1 of 2014)—`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a person who is employed or, as the case may be, was at the time of commission`
  line `of the alleged offence employed, in connection with the affairs of the Union, of the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a person who is employed or, as the case may be, was at the time of commission`
  line `of the alleged offence employed, in connection with the affairs of a State, of the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the alleged offence was committed by a person referred to in clause (b) during the`
  line `period while a Proclamation issued under clause (1) of article 356 of the Constitution was in force in a`
  line `State, clause (b) will apply as if for the expression "State Government" occurring therein, the expression`
  line `"Central Government" were substituted:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such Government shall take a decision within a period of one hundred and twenty`
  line `days from the date of the receipt of the request for sanction and in case it fails to do so, the sanction shall`
  line `be deemed to have been accorded by such Government:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no sanction shall be required in case of a public servant accused of any offence`
  line `alleged to have been committed under section 64, section 65, section 66, section 68, section 69, section 70,`
  line `section 71, section 74, section 75, section 76, section 77, section 78, section 79, section 143, section 199 or`
  line `section 200 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(2) No Court shall take cognizance of any offence alleged to have been committed by any member of`
  line `the Armed Forces of the Union while acting or purporting to act in the discharge of his official duty, except`
  line `with the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, by notification, direct that the provisions of sub-section (2) shall apply`
  line `to such class or category of the members of the Forces charged with the maintenance of public order as`
  line `may be specified therein, wherever they may be serving, and thereupon the provisions of that sub-section`
  line `will apply as if for the expression "Central Government" occurring therein, the expression "State`
  line `Government" were substituted.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), no Court shall take cognizance of any`
  line `offence, alleged to have been committed by any member of the Forces charged with the maintenance of`
  line `public order in a State while acting or purporting to act in the discharge of his official duty during the period`
  line `while a Proclamation issued under clause (1) of article 356 of the Constitution was in force therein, except`
  line `with the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government or the State Government, may determine the person by whom, the manner`
  line `in which, and the offence or offences for which, the prosecution of such Judge, Magistrate or public servant`
  line `is to be conducted, and may specify the Court before which the trial is to be held.`
obj_root_law_sections_218_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_219:
  sectionId (91205)
  sectionNo (219)
  orderNo 219
  title `Prosecution for offences against marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_219_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91205&sectionno=219&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_219_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Court shall take cognizance of an offence`
  line `punishable under sections 81 to 84 (both inclusive) of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 except upon a`
  line `complaint made by some person aggrieved by the offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) where such person is a child, or is of unsound mind or is having intellectual disability requiring`
  line `higher support needs, or is from sickness or infirmity unable to make a complaint, or is a woman who,`
  line `according to the local customs and manners, ought not to be compelled to appear in public, some other`
  line `person may, with the leave of the Court, make a complaint on his or her behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) where such person is the husband and he is serving in any of the Armed Forces of the Union`
  line `under conditions which are certified by his Commanding Officer as precluding him from obtaining`
  line `leave of absence to enable him to make a complaint in person, some other person authorised by the`
  line `husband in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (4) may make a complaint on his behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) where the person aggrieved by an offence punishable under section 82 of the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023 is the wife, complaint may be made on her behalf by her father, mother, brother, sister,`
  line `son or daughter or by her father's or mother's brother or sister, or, with the leave of the Court, by any`
  line `other person related to her by blood, marriage or adoption.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), no person other than the husband of the woman shall be deemed`
  line `to be aggrieved by any offence punishable under section 84 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(3) When in any case falling under clause (a) of the proviso to sub-section (1), the complaint is sought`
  line `to be made on behalf of a child or of a person of unsound mind by a person who has not been appointed or`
  line `declared by a competent authority to be the guardian of the child, or of the person of unsound mind, and`
  line `the Court is satisfied that there is a guardian so appointed or declared, the Court shall, before granting the`
  line `application for leave, cause notice to be given to such guardian and give him a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) The authorisation referred to in clause (b) of the proviso to sub-section (1), shall be in writing, shall`
  line `be signed or otherwise attested by the husband, shall contain a statement to the effect that he has been`
  line `informed of the allegations upon which the complaint is to be founded, shall be countersigned by his`
  line `Commanding Officer, and shall be accompanied by a certificate signed by that Officer to the effect that`
  line `leave of absence for the purpose of making a complaint in person cannot for the time being be granted to`
  line `the husband.`
  line
  line `(5) Any document purporting to be such an authorisation and complying with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (4), and any document purporting to be a certificate required by that sub-section shall, unless`
  line `the contrary is proved, be presumed to be genuine and shall be received in evidence.`
  line
  line `(6) No Court shall take cognizance of an offence under section 64 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita,`
  line `2023, where such offence consists of sexual intercourse by a man with his own wife, the wife being under`
  line `eighteen years of age, if more than one year has elapsed from the date of the commission of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_219_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_220:
  sectionId (91206)
  sectionNo (220)
  orderNo 220
  title `Prosecution of offences under section 85 of Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_220_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91206&sectionno=220&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_220_content:
  string
  line `No Court shall`
  line `take cognizance of an offence punishable under section 85 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 except`
  line `upon a police report of facts which constitute such offence or upon a complaint made by the person`
  line `aggrieved by the offence or by her father, mother, brother, sister or by her father’s or mother’s brother or`
  line `sister or, with the leave of the Court, by any other person related to her by blood, marriage or adoption.`
obj_root_law_sections_220_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_221:
  sectionId (91207)
  sectionNo (221)
  orderNo 221
  title `Cognizance of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_221_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91207&sectionno=221&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_221_content:
  string
  line `No Court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under`
  line `section 67 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 where the persons are in a marital relationship, except`
  line `upon prima facie satisfaction of the facts which constitute the offence upon a complaint having been filed`
  line `or made by the wife against the husband.`
obj_root_law_sections_221_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_222:
  sectionId (91208)
  sectionNo (222)
  orderNo 222
  title `Prosecution for defamation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_222_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91208&sectionno=222&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_222_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under`
  line `section 356 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 except upon a complaint made by some person aggrieved`
  line `by the offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person is a child, or is of unsound mind or is having intellectual disability or`
  line `is from sickness or infirmity unable to make a complaint, or is a woman who, according to the local customs`
  line `and manners, ought not to be compelled to appear in public, some other person may, with the leave of the`
  line `Court, make a complaint on his or her behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Sanhita, when any offence falling under section 356 of`
  line `the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 is alleged to have been committed against a person who, at the time of`
  line `such commission, is the President of India, the Vice-President of India, the Governor of a State, the`
  line `Administrator of a Union territory or a Minister of the Union or of a State or of a Union territory, or any`
  line `other public servant employed in connection with the affairs of the Union or of a State in respect of his`
  line `conduct in the discharge of his public functions, a Court of Session may take cognizance of such offence,`
  line `without the case being committed to it, upon a complaint in writing made by the Public Prosecutor.`
  line
  line `(3) Every complaint referred to in sub-section (2) shall set forth the facts which constitute the offence`
  line `alleged, the nature of such offence and such other particulars as are reasonably sufficient to give notice to`
  line `the accused of the offence alleged to have been committed by him.`
  line
  line `(4) No complaint under sub-section (2) shall be made by the Public Prosecutor except with the previous`
  line sanction—
  line
  line `(a) of the State Government,—`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a person who is or has been the Governor of that State or a Minister of that`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of any other public servant employed in connection with the affairs of the State;`
  line
  line `(b) of the Central Government, in any other case.`
  line
  line `(5) No Court of Session shall take cognizance of an offence under sub-section (2) unless the complaint`
  line `is made within six months from the date on which the offence is alleged to have been committed.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in this section shall affect the right of the person against whom the offence is alleged to`
  line `have been committed, to make a complaint in respect of that offence before a Magistrate having jurisdiction`
  line `or the power of such Magistrate to take cognizance of the offence upon such complaint.`
obj_root_law_sections_222_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_223:
  sectionId (91209)
  sectionNo (223)
  orderNo 223
  title `Examination of complainant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_223_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91209&sectionno=223&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_223_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Magistrate having jurisdiction while taking cognizance of`
  line `an offence on complaint shall examine upon oath the complainant and the witnesses present, if any, and the`
  line `substance of such examination shall be reduced to writing and shall be signed by the complainant and the`
  line `witnesses, and also by the Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that no cognizance of an offence shall be taken by the Magistrate without giving the accused`
  line `an opportunity of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided further that when the complaint is made in writing, the Magistrate need not examine the`
  line `complainant and the witnesses—`
  line
  line `(a) if a public servant acting or purporting to act in the discharge of his official duties or a Court`
  line `has made the complaint; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the Magistrate makes over the case for inquiry or trial to another Magistrate under`
  line `section 212:`
  line
  line `Provided also that if the Magistrate makes over the case to another Magistrate under section 212 after`
  line `examining the complainant and the witnesses, the latter Magistrate need not re-examine them.`
  line
  line `(2) A Magistrate shall not take cognizance on a complaint against a public servant for any offence`
  line `alleged to have been committed in course of the discharge of his official functions or duties unless—`
  line
  line `(a) such public servant is given an opportunity to make assertions as to the situation that led to the`
  line `incident so alleged; and`
  line
  line `(b) a report containing facts and circumstances of the incident from the officer superior to such`
  line `public servant is received.`
obj_root_law_sections_223_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_224:
  sectionId (91210)
  sectionNo (224)
  orderNo 224
  title `Procedure by Magistrate not competent to take cognizance of case.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_224_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91210&sectionno=224&orderno=224&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_224_content:
  string
  line `If the complaint is made`
  line `to a Magistrate who is not competent to take cognizance of the offence, he shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the complaint is in writing, return it for presentation to the proper Court with an endorsement`
  line `to that effect;`
  line
  line `(b) if the complaint is not in writing, direct the complainant to the proper Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_224_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_225:
  sectionId (91211)
  sectionNo (225)
  orderNo 225
  title `Postponement of issue of process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_225_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91211&sectionno=225&orderno=225&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_225_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Magistrate, on receipt of a complaint of an offence`
  line `of which he is authorised to take cognizance or which has been made over to him under section 212, may,`
  line `if he thinks fit, and shall, in a case where the accused is residing at a place beyond the area in which he`
  line `exercises his jurisdiction, postpone the issue of process against the accused, and either inquire into the case`
  line `himself or direct an investigation to be made by a police officer or by such other person as he thinks fit, for`
  line `the purpose of deciding whether or not there is sufficient ground for proceeding:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such direction for investigation shall be made,—`
  line
  line `(a) where it appears to the Magistrate that the offence complained of is triable exclusively by the`
  line `Court of Session; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the complaint has not been made by a Court, unless the complainant and the witnesses`
  line `present (if any) have been examined on oath under section 223.`
  line
  line `(2) In an inquiry under sub-section (1), the Magistrate may, if he thinks fit, take evidence of witnesses`
  line `on oath:`
  line
  line `Provided that if it appears to the Magistrate that the offence complained of is triable exclusively by the`
  line `Court of Session, he shall call upon the complainant to produce all his witnesses and examine them on oath.`
  line
  line `(3) If an investigation under sub-section (1) is made by a person not being a police officer, he shall`
  line `have for that investigation all the powers conferred by this Sanhita on an officer in charge of a police station`
  line `except the power to arrest without warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_225_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_226:
  sectionId (91212)
  sectionNo (226)
  orderNo 226
  title `Dismissal of complaint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_226_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91212&sectionno=226&orderno=226&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_226_content:
  string
  line `If, after considering the statements on oath (if any) of the complainant`
  line `and of the witnesses and the result of the inquiry or investigation (if any) under section 225, the Magistrate`
  line `is of opinion that there is no sufficient ground for proceeding, he shall dismiss the complaint, and in every`
  line `such case he shall briefly record his reasons for so doing.`
obj_root_law_sections_226_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_227:
  sectionId (91213)
  sectionNo (227)
  orderNo 227
  title `Issue of process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_227_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91213&sectionno=227&orderno=227&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_227_content:
  string
  line `(1) If in the opinion of a Magistrate taking cognizance of an offence there is`
  line `sufficient ground for proceeding, and the case appears to be—`
  line
  line `(a) a summons-case, he shall issue summons to the accused for his attendance; or`
  line
  line `(b) a warrant-case, he may issue a warrant, or, if he thinks fit, a summons, for causing the accused`
  line `to be brought or to appear at a certain time before such Magistrate or (if he has no jurisdiction himself)`
  line `some other Magistrate having jurisdiction:`
  line
  line `Provided that summons or warrants may also be issued through electronic means.`
  line
  line `(2) No summons or warrant shall be issued against the accused under sub-section (1) until a list of the`
  line `prosecution witnesses has been filed.`
  line
  line `(3) In a proceeding instituted upon a complaint made in writing, every summons or warrant issued`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by a copy of such complaint.`
  line
  line `(4) When by any law for the time being in force any process-fees or other fees are payable, no process`
  line `shall be issued until the fees are paid and, if such fees are not paid within a reasonable time, the Magistrate`
  line `may dismiss the complaint.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the provisions of section 90.`
obj_root_law_sections_227_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_228:
  sectionId (91214)
  sectionNo (228)
  orderNo 228
  title `Magistrate may dispense with personal attendance of accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_228_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91214&sectionno=228&orderno=228&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_228_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever a Magistrate`
  line `issues a summons, he may, if he sees reason so to do, dispense with the personal attendance of the accused`
  line `and permit him to appear by his advocate.`
  line
  line `(2) But the Magistrate inquiring into or trying the case may, in his discretion, at any stage of the`
  line `proceedings, direct the personal attendance of the accused, and, if necessary, enforce such attendance in the`
  line `manner hereinbefore provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_228_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_229:
  sectionId (91215)
  sectionNo (229)
  orderNo 229
  title `Special summons in cases of petty offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_229_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91215&sectionno=229&orderno=229&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_229_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the opinion of a Magistrate taking`
  line `cognizance of a petty offence, the case may be summarily disposed of under section 283 or section 284, the`
  line `Magistrate shall, except where he is, for reasons to be recorded in writing of a contrary opinion, issue`
  line `summons to the accused requiring him either to appear in person or by an advocate before the Magistrate`
  line `on a specified date, or if he desires to plead guilty to the charge without appearing before the Magistrate,`
  line `to transmit before the specified date, by post or by messenger to the Magistrate, the said plea in writing and`
  line `the amount of fine specified in the summons or if he desires to appear by an advocate and to plead guilty`
  line `to the charge through such advocate, to authorise, in writing, the advocate to plead guilty to the charge on`
  line `his behalf and to pay the fine through such advocate:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of the fine specified in such summons shall not exceed five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, “petty offence” means any offence punishable only with fine not`
  line `exceeding five thousand rupees, but does not include any offence so punishable under the Motor Vehicles`
  line `Act, 1988 (59 of 1988), or under any other law which provides for convicting the accused person in his`
  line `absence on a plea of guilty.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, by notification, specially empower any Magistrate to exercise the`
  line `powers conferred by sub-section (1) in relation to any offence which is compoundable under section 359`
  line `or any offence punishable with imprisonment for a term not exceeding three months, or with fine, or with`
  line `both where the Magistrate is of opinion that, having regard to the facts and circumstances of the case, the`
  line `imposition of fine only would meet the ends of justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_229_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_230:
  sectionId (91216)
  sectionNo (230)
  orderNo 230
  title `Supply to accused of copy of police report and other documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_230_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91216&sectionno=230&orderno=230&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_230_content:
  string
  line `In any case where the`
  line `proceeding has been instituted on a police report, the Magistrate shall without delay, and in no case beyond`
  line `fourteen days from the date of production or appearance of the accused, furnish to the accused and the`
  line `victim (if represented by an advocate) free of cost, a copy of each of the following:—`
  line
  line `(i) the police report;`
  line
  line `(ii) the first information report recorded under section 173;`
  line
  line `(iii) the statements recorded under sub-section (3) of section 180 of all persons whom the`
  line `prosecution proposes to examine as its witnesses, excluding therefrom any part in regard to which a`
  line `request for such exclusion has been made by the police officer under sub-section (7) of section 193;`
  line
  line `(iv) the confessions and statements, if any, recorded under section 183;`
  line
  line `(v) any other document or relevant extract thereof forwarded to the Magistrate with the police report`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 193:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Magistrate may, after perusing any such part of a statement as is referred to in`
  line `clause (iii) and considering the reasons given by the police officer for the request, direct that a copy of that`
  line `part of the statement or of such portion thereof as the Magistrate thinks proper, shall be furnished to the`
  line `accused:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the Magistrate is satisfied that any such document is voluminous, he shall,`
  line `instead of furnishing the accused and the victim (if represented by an advocate) with a copy thereof, may`
  line `furnish the copies through electronic means or direct that he will only be allowed to inspect it either`
  line `personally or through an advocate in Court:`
  line
  line `Provided also that supply of documents in electronic form shall be considered as duly furnished.`
obj_root_law_sections_230_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_231:
  sectionId (91217)
  sectionNo (231)
  orderNo 231
  title `Supply of copies of statements and documents to accused in other cases triable by Court of Session.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_231_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91217&sectionno=231&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_231_content:
  string
  line `Where, in a case instituted otherwise than on a police report, it appears to the Magistrate issuing`
  line `process under section 227 that the offence is triable exclusively by the Court of Session, the Magistrate`
  line `shall forthwith furnish to the accused, free of cost, a copy of each of the following:—`
  line
  line `(i) the statements recorded under section 223 or section 225, of all persons examined by the`
  line Magistrate;
  line
  line `(ii) the statements and confessions, if any, recorded under section 180 or section 183;`
  line
  line `(iii) any documents produced before the Magistrate on which the prosecution proposes to rely:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Magistrate is satisfied that any such document is voluminous, he shall, instead of`
  line `furnishing the accused with a copy thereof, direct that he will only be allowed to inspect it either personally`
  line `or through an advocate in Court:`
  line
  line `Provided further that supply of documents in electronic form shall be considered as duly furnished.`
obj_root_law_sections_231_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_232:
  sectionId (91218)
  sectionNo (232)
  orderNo 232
  title `Commitment of case to Court of Session when offence is triable exclusively by it.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_232_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91218&sectionno=232&orderno=232&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_232_content:
  string
  line `When in`
  line `a case instituted on a police report or otherwise, the accused appears or is brought before the Magistrate`
  line `and it appears to the Magistrate that the offence is triable exclusively by the Court of Session, he shall—`
  line
  line `(a) commit, after complying with the provisions of section 230 or section 231 the case to the Court`
  line `of Session, and subject to the provisions of this Sanhita relating to bail, remand the accused to custody`
  line `until such commitment has been made;`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the provisions of this Sanhita relating to bail, remand the accused to custody during,`
  line `and until the conclusion of, the trial;`
  line
  line `(c) send to that Court the record of the case and the documents and articles, if any, which are to be`
  line `produced in evidence;`
  line
  line `(d) notify the Public Prosecutor of the commitment of the case to the Court of Session:`
  line
  line `Provided that the proceedings under this section shall be completed within a period of ninety days from`
  line `the date of taking cognizance, and such period may be extended by the Magistrate for a period not exceeding`
  line `one hundred and eighty days for the reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any application filed before the Magistrate by the accused or the victim or any`
  line `person authorised by such person in a case triable by Court of Session, shall be forwarded to the Court of`
  line `Session with the committal of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_232_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_233:
  sectionId (91552)
  sectionNo (233)
  orderNo 233
  title `Procedure to be followed when there is a complaint case and police investigation in respect of same offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_233_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91552&sectionno=233&orderno=233&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_233_content:
  string
  line `(1) When in a case instituted otherwise than on a police report (hereinafter referred to`
  line `as a complaint case), it is made to appear to the Magistrate, during the course of the inquiry or trial held by`
  line `him, that an investigation by the police is in progress in relation to the offence which is the`
  line `subject-matter of the inquiry or trial held by him, the Magistrate shall stay the proceedings of such inquiry`
  line `or trial and call for a report on the matter from the police officer conducting the investigation.`
  line
  line `(2) If a report is made by the investigating police officer under section 193 and on such report`
  line `cognizance of any offence is taken by the Magistrate against any person who is an accused in the complaint`
  line `case, the Magistrate shall inquire into or try together the complaint case and the case arising out of the`
  line `police report as if both the cases were instituted on a police report.`
  line
  line `(3) If the police report does not relate to any accused in the complaint case or if the Magistrate does not`
  line `take cognizance of any offence on the police report, he shall proceed with the inquiry or trial, which was`
  line `stayed by him, in accordance with the provisions of this Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_233_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_234:
  sectionId (91553)
  sectionNo (234)
  orderNo 234
  title `Contents of charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_234_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91553&sectionno=234&orderno=234&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_234_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every charge under this Sanhita shall state the offence with which the`
  line `accused is charged.`
  line
  line `(2) If the law which creates the offence gives it any specific name, the offence may be described in the`
  line `charge by that name only.`
  line
  line `(3) If the law which creates the offence does not give it any specific name, so much of the definition of`
  line `the offence must be stated as to give the accused notice of the matter with which he is charged.`
  line
  line `(4) The law and section of the law against which the offence is said to have been committed shall be`
  line `mentioned in the charge.`
  line
  line `(5) The fact that the charge is made is equivalent to a statement that every legal condition required by`
  line `law to constitute the offence charged was fulfilled in the particular case.`
  line
  line `(6) The charge shall be written in the language of the Court.`
  line
  line `(7) If the accused, having been previously convicted of any offence, is liable, by reason of such previous`
  line `conviction, to enhanced punishment, or to punishment of a different kind, for a subsequent offence, and it`
  line `is intended to prove such previous conviction for the purpose of affecting the punishment which the Court`
  line `may think fit, to award for the subsequent offence, the fact, date and place of the previous conviction shall`
  line `be stated in the charge; and if such statement has been omitted, the Court may add it at any time before`
  line `sentence is passed.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A is charged with the murder of B. This is equivalent to a statement that A's act fell within the`
  line `definition of murder given in sections 100 and 101 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023; that it did not fall`
  line `within any of the general exceptions of the said Sanhita; and that it did not fall within any of the five`
  line `exceptions to section 101 thereof, or that, if it did fall within Exception 1, one or other of the three provisos`
  line `to that exception applied to it.`
  line
  line `(b) A is charged under sub-section (2) of section 118 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, with`
  line `voluntarily causing grievous hurt to B by means of an instrument for shooting. This is equivalent to a`
  line `statement that the case was not provided for by sub-section (2) of section 122 of the said Sanhita, and that`
  line `the general exceptions did not apply to it.`
  line
  line `(c) A is accused of murder, cheating, theft, extortion, or criminal intimidation, or using a false propertymark. The charge may state that A committed murder, or cheating, or theft, or extortion, or criminal`
  line `intimidation, or that he used a false propertymark, without reference to the definitions, of those crimes`
  line `contained in the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023; but the sections under which the offence is punishable`
  line `must, in each instance be referred to in the charge.`
  line
  line `(d) A is charged under section 219 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, with intentionally obstructing`
  line `a sale of property offered for sale by the lawful authority of a public servant. The charge should be in those`
  line words.
obj_root_law_sections_234_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_235:
  sectionId (91221)
  sectionNo (235)
  orderNo 235
  title `Particulars as to time, place and person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_235_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91221&sectionno=235&orderno=235&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_235_content:
  string
  line `(1) The charge shall contain such particulars as to`
  line `the time and place of the alleged offence, and the person (if any) against whom, or the thing (if any) in`
  line `respect of which, it was committed, as are reasonably sufficient to give the accused notice of the matter`
  line `with which he is charged.`
  line
  line `(2) When the accused is charged with criminal breach of trust or dishonest misappropriation of money`
  line `or other movable property, it shall be sufficient to specify the gross sum or, as the case may be, describe`
  line `the movable property in respect of which the offence is alleged to have been committed, and the dates`
  line `between which the offence is alleged to have been committed, without specifying particular items or exact`
  line `dates, and the charge so framed shall be deemed to be a charge of one offence within the meaning of`
  line `section 242:`
  line
  line `Provided that the time included between the first and last of such dates shall not exceed one year.`
obj_root_law_sections_235_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_236:
  sectionId (91222)
  sectionNo (236)
  orderNo 236
  title `When manner of committing offence must be stated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_236_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91222&sectionno=236&orderno=236&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_236_content:
  string
  line `When the nature of the case is such that`
  line `the particulars mentioned in sections 234 and 235 do not give the accused sufficient notice of the matter`
  line `with which he is charged, the charge shall also contain such particulars of the manner in which the alleged`
  line `offence was committed as will be sufficient for that purpose.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A is accused of the theft of a certain article at a certain time and place. The charge need not set out`
  line `the manner in which the theft was effected.`
  line
  line `(b) A is accused of cheating B at a given time and place. The charge must set out the manner in which`
  line `A cheated B.`
  line
  line `(c) A is accused of giving false evidence at a given time and place. The charge must set out that portion`
  line `of the evidence given by A which is alleged to be false.`
  line
  line `(d) A is accused of obstructing B, a public servant, in the discharge of his public functions at a given`
  line `time and place. The charge must set out the manner in which A obstructed B in the discharge of his`
  line functions.
  line
  line `(e) A is accused of the murder of B at a given time and place. The charge need not state the manner in`
  line `which A murdered B.`
  line
  line `(f) A is accused of disobeying a direction of the law with intent to save B from punishment. The charge`
  line `must set out the disobedience charged and the law infringed.`
obj_root_law_sections_236_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_237:
  sectionId (91223)
  sectionNo (237)
  orderNo 237
  title `Words in charge taken in sense of law under which offence is punishable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_237_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91223&sectionno=237&orderno=237&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_237_content:
  string
  line `In every charge`
  line `words used in describing an offence shall be deemed to have been used in the sense attached to them`
  line `respectively by the law under which such offence is punishable.`
obj_root_law_sections_237_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_238:
  sectionId (91224)
  sectionNo (238)
  orderNo 238
  title `Effect of errors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_238_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91224&sectionno=238&orderno=238&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_238_content:
  string
  line `No error in stating either the offence or the particulars required to be stated in`
  line `the charge, and no omission to state the offence or those particulars, shall be regarded at any stage of the`
  line `case as material, unless the accused was in fact misled by such error or omission, and it has occasioned a`
  line `failure of justice.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A is charged under section 180 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, with "having been in`
  line `possession of counterfeit coin, having known at the time when he became possessed thereof that such coin`
  line `was counterfeit," the word "fraudulently" being omitted in the charge. Unless it appears that A was in fact`
  line `misled by this omission, the error shall not be regarded as material.`
  line
  line `(b) A is charged with cheating B, and the manner in which he cheated B is not set out in the charge or`
  line `is set out incorrectly. A defends himself, calls witnesses and gives his own account of the transaction. The`
  line `Court may infer from this that the omission to set out the manner of the cheating is not material.`
  line
  line `(c) A is charged with cheating B, and the manner in which he cheated B is not set out in the charge.`
  line `There were many transactions between A and B, and A had no means of knowing to which of them the`
  line `charge referred, and offered no defence. The Court may infer from such facts that the omission to set out`
  line `the manner of the cheating was, in the case, a material error.`
  line
  line `(d) A is charged with the murder of Khoda Baksh on the 21st January, 2023. In fact, the murdered`
  line `person's name was Haidar Baksh, and the date of the murder was the 20th January, 2023. A was never`
  line `charged with any murder but one, and had heard the inquiry before the Magistrate, which referred`
  line `exclusively to the case of Haidar Baksh. The Court may infer from these facts that A was not misled, and`
  line `that the error in the charge was immaterial.`
  line
  line `(e) A was charged with murdering Haidar Baksh on the 20th January, 2023, and Khoda Baksh (who`
  line `tried to arrest him for that murder) on the 21st January, 2023. When charged for the murder of Haidar`
  line `Baksh, he was tried for the murder of Khoda Baksh. The witnesses present in his defence were witnesses`
  line `in the case of Haidar Baksh. The Court may infer from this that A was misled, and that the error was`
  line material.
obj_root_law_sections_238_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_239:
  sectionId (91225)
  sectionNo (239)
  orderNo 239
  title `Court may alter charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_239_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91225&sectionno=239&orderno=239&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_239_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Court may alter or add to any charge at any time before`
  line `judgment is pronounced.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such alteration or addition shall be read and explained to the accused.`
  line
  line `(3) If the alteration or addition to a charge is such that proceeding immediately with the trial is not`
  line `likely, in the opinion of the Court, to prejudice the accused in his defence or the prosecutor in the conduct`
  line `of the case, the Court may, in its discretion, after such alteration or addition has been made, proceed with`
  line `the trial as if the altered or added charge had been the original charge.`
  line
  line `(4) If the alteration or addition is such that proceeding immediately with the trial is likely, in the opinion`
  line `of the Court, to prejudice the accused or the prosecutor as aforesaid, the Court may either direct a new trial`
  line `or adjourn the trial for such period as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(5) If the offence stated in the altered or added charge is one for the prosecution of which previous`
  line `sanction is necessary, the case shall not be proceeded with until such sanction is obtained, unless sanction`
  line `has been already obtained for a prosecution on the same facts as those on which the altered or added charge`
  line `is founded.`
obj_root_law_sections_239_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_240:
  sectionId (91226)
  sectionNo (240)
  orderNo 240
  title `Recall of witnesses when charge altered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_240_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91226&sectionno=240&orderno=240&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_240_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a charge is altered or added to by the Court`
  line `after the commencement of the trial, the prosecutor and the accused shall be allowed—`
  line
  line `(a) to recall or re-summon, and examine with reference to such alteration or addition, any witness`
  line `who may have been examined, unless the Court, for reasons to be recorded in writing, considers that`
  line `the prosecutor or the accused, as the case may be, desires to recall or re-examine such witness for the`
  line `purpose of vexation or delay or for defeating the ends of justice;`
  line
  line `(b) also to call any further witness whom the Court may think to be material.`
obj_root_law_sections_240_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_241:
  sectionId (91227)
  sectionNo (241)
  orderNo 241
  title `Separate charges for distinct offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_241_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91227&sectionno=241&orderno=241&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_241_content:
  string
  line `(1) For every distinct offence of which any person is`
  line `accused there shall be a separate charge, and every such charge shall be tried separately:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the accused person, by an application in writing, so desires and the Magistrate is`
  line `of opinion that such person is not likely to be prejudiced thereby, the Magistrate may try together all or any`
  line `number of the charges framed against such person.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall affect the operation of the provisions of sections 242, 243, 244`
  line `and 246.`
  line
  line Illustration.
  line
  line `A is accused of a theft on one occasion, and of causing grievous hurt on another occasion. A must be`
  line `separately charged and separately tried for the theft and causing grievous hurt.`
obj_root_law_sections_241_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_242:
  sectionId (91228)
  sectionNo (242)
  orderNo 242
  title `Offences of same kind within year may be charged together.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_242_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91228&sectionno=242&orderno=242&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_242_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a person is accused`
  line `of more offences than one of the same kind committed within the space of twelve months from the first to`
  line `the last of such offences, whether in respect of the same person or not, he may be charged with, and tried`
  line `at one trial for, any number of them not exceeding five.`
  line
  line `(2) Offences are of the same kind when they are punishable with the same amount of punishment under`
  line `the same section of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 or of any special or local law:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of this section, an offence punishable under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 303 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 shall be deemed to be an offence of the same kind as an`
  line `offence punishable under section 305 of the said Sanhita, and that an offence punishable under any section`
  line `of the said Sanhita, or of any special or local law, shall be deemed to be an offence of the same kind as an`
  line `attempt to commit such offence, when such an attempt is an offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_242_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_243:
  sectionId (91229)
  sectionNo (243)
  orderNo 243
  title `Trial for more than one offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_243_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91229&sectionno=243&orderno=243&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_243_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in one series of acts so connected together as to form`
  line `the same transaction, more offences than one are committed by the same person, he may be charged with,`
  line `and tried at one trial for, every such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) When a person charged with one or more offences of criminal breach of trust or dishonest`
  line `misappropriation of property as provided in sub-section (2) of section 235 or in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 242, is accused of committing, for the purpose of facilitating or concealing the commission of that`
  line `offence or those offences, one or more offences of falsification of accounts, he may be charged with, and`
  line `tried at one trial for, every such offence.`
  line
  line `(3) If the acts alleged constitute an offence falling within two or more separate definitions of any law`
  line `in force for the time being by which offences are defined or punished, the person accused of them may be`
  line `charged with, and tried at one trial for, each of such offences.`
  line
  line `(4) If several acts, of which one or more than one would by itself or themselves constitute an offence,`
  line `constitute when combined a different offence, the person accused of them may be charged with, and tried`
  line `at one trial for the offence constituted by such acts when combined, and for any offence constituted by any`
  line `one, or more, of such acts.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing contained in this section shall affect section 9 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `Illustrations to sub-section (1)`
  line
  line `(a) A rescues B, a person in lawful custody, and in so doing causes grievous hurt to C, a constable in`
  line `whose custody B was. A may be charged with, and convicted of, offences under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 121 and section 263 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(b) A commits house-breaking by day with intent to commit rape, and commits, in the house so entered,`
  line `rape with B's wife. A may be separately charged with, and convicted of, offences under section 64 and subsection (3) of section 331 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(c) A has in his possession several seals, knowing them to be counterfeit and intending to use them for`
  line `the purpose of committing several forgeries punishable under section 337 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita,`
  line `2023. A may be separately charged with, and convicted of, the possession of each seal under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 341 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(d) With intent to cause injury to B, A institutes a criminal proceeding against him, knowing that there`
  line `is no just or lawful ground for such proceeding, and also falsely accuses B of having committed an offence,`
  line `knowing that there is no just or lawful ground for such charge. A may be separately charged with, and`
  line `convicted of, two offences under section 248 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(e) A, with intent to cause injury to B, falsely accuses him of having committed an offence, knowing`
  line `that there is no just or lawful ground for such charge. On the trial, A gives false evidence against B,`
  line `intending thereby to cause B to be convicted of a capital offence. A may be separately charged with, and`
  line `convicted of, offences under sections 230 and 248 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(f) A, with six others, commits the offences of rioting, grievous hurt and assaulting a public servant`
  line `endeavouring in the discharge of his duty as such to suppress the riot. A may be separately charged with,`
  line `and convicted of, offences under sub-section (2) of section 117, sub-section (2) of section 191 and section`
  line `195 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(g) A threatens B, C and D at the same time with injury to their persons with intent to cause alarm to`
  line `them. A may be separately charged with, and convicted of, each of the three offences under`
  line `sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 351 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `The separate charges referred to in illustrations (a) to (g), respectively, may be tried at the same time.`
  line
  line `Illustrations to sub-section (3)`
  line
  line `(h) A wrongfully strikes B with a cane. A may be separately charged with, and convicted of, offences`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 115 and section 131 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(i) Several stolen sacks of corn are made over to A and B, who knew they are stolen property, for the`
  line `purpose of concealing them. A and B thereupon voluntarily assist each other to conceal the sacks at the`
  line `bottom of a grain-pit. A and B may be separately charged with, and convicted of, offences under`
  line `sub-sections (2) and (5) of section 317 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(j) A exposes her child with the knowledge that she is thereby likely to cause its death. The child dies`
  line `in consequence of such exposure. A may be separately charged with, and convicted of, offences under`
  line `sections 93 and 105 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(k) A dishonestly uses a forged document as genuine evidence, in order to convict B, a public servant,`
  line `of an offence under section 201 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023. A may be separately charged with,`
  line `and convicted of, offences under section 233 and sub-section (2) of section 340 (read with section 337) of`
  line `that Sanhita.`
  line
  line `Illustration to sub-section (4)`
  line
  line `(l) A commits robbery on B, and in doing so voluntarily causes hurt to him. A may be separately charged`
  line `with, and convicted of, offences under sub-section (2) of section 115 and sub-sections (2) and (4) of section`
  line `309 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
obj_root_law_sections_243_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_244:
  sectionId (91230)
  sectionNo (244)
  orderNo 244
  title `Where it is doubtful what offence has been committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_244_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91230&sectionno=244&orderno=244&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_244_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a single act or series of acts is`
  line `of such a nature that it is doubtful which of several offences the facts which can be proved will constitute,`
  line `the accused may be charged with having committed all or any of such offences, and any number of such`
  line `charges may be tried at once; or he may be charged in the alternative with having committed someone of`
  line `the said offences.`
  line
  line `(2) If in such a case the accused is charged with one offence, and it appears in evidence that he`
  line `committed a different offence for which he might have been charged under the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1), he may be convicted of the offence which he is shown to have committed, although he was`
  line `not charged with it.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A is accused of an act which may amount to theft, or receiving stolen property, or criminal breach`
  line `of trust or cheating. He may be charged with theft, receiving stolen property, criminal breach of trust and`
  line `cheating, or he may be charged with having committed theft, or receiving stolen property, or criminal breach`
  line `of trust or cheating.`
  line
  line `(b) In the case mentioned, A is only charged with theft. It appears that he committed the offence of`
  line `criminal breach of trust, or that of receiving stolen goods. He may be convicted of criminal breach of trust`
  line `or of receiving stolen goods (as the case may be), though he was not charged with such offence.`
  line
  line `(c) A states on oath before the Magistrate that he saw B hit C with a club. Before the Sessions Court A`
  line `states on oath that B never hit C. A may be charged in the alternative and convicted of intentionally giving`
  line `false evidence, although it cannot be proved which of these contradictory statements was false.`
obj_root_law_sections_244_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_245:
  sectionId (91231)
  sectionNo (245)
  orderNo 245
  title `When offence proved included in offence charged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_245_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_245_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91231&sectionno=245&orderno=245&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_245_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a person is charged with an`
  line `offence consisting of several particulars, a combination of some only of which constitutes a complete minor`
  line `offence, and such combination is proved, but the remaining particulars are not proved, he may be convicted`
  line `of the minor offence, though he was not charged with it.`
  line
  line `(2) When a person is charged with an offence and facts are proved which reduce it to a minor offence,`
  line `he may be convicted of the minor offence, although he is not charged with it.`
  line
  line `(3) When a person is charged with an offence, he may be convicted of an attempt to commit such`
  line `offence although the attempt is not separately charged.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to authorise a conviction of any minor offence where the`
  line `conditions requisite for the initiation of proceedings in respect of that minor offence have not been satisfied.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A is charged, under sub-section (3) of section 316 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, with`
  line `criminal breach of trust in respect of property entrusted to him as a carrier. It appears, that he did commit`
  line `criminal breach of trust under sub-section (2) of section 316 of that Sanhita in respect of the property, but`
  line `that it was not entrusted to him as a carrier. He may be convicted of criminal breach of trust under the said`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 316.`
  line
  line `(b) A is charged, under sub-section (2) of section 117 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, with`
  line `causing grievous hurt. He proves that he acted on grave and sudden provocation. He may be convicted`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 122 of that Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_245_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_246:
  sectionId (91232)
  sectionNo (246)
  orderNo 246
  title `What persons may be charged jointly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_246_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_246_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91232&sectionno=246&orderno=246&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_246_content:
  string
  line `The following persons may be charged and tried`
  line `together, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) persons accused of the same offence committed in the course of the same transaction;`
  line
  line `(b) persons accused of an offence and persons accused of abetment of, or attempt to commit, such`
  line offence;
  line
  line `(c) persons accused of more than one offence of the same kind, within the meaning of section 242`
  line `committed by them jointly within the period of twelve months;`
  line
  line `(d) persons accused of different offences committed in the course of the same transaction;`
  line
  line `(e) persons accused of an offence which includes theft, extortion, cheating, or criminal`
  line `misappropriation, and persons accused of receiving or retaining, or assisting in the disposal or`
  line `concealment of, property possession of which is alleged to have been transferred by any such offence`
  line `committed by the first-named persons, or of abetment of or attempting to commit any such last-named`
  line offence;
  line
  line `(f) persons accused of offences under sub-sections (2) and (5) of section 317 of the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023 or either of those sections in respect of stolen property the possession of which has been`
  line `transferred by one offence;`
  line
  line `(g) persons accused of any offence under Chapter X of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 relating`
  line `to counterfeit coin and persons accused of any other offence under the said Chapter relating to the same`
  line `coin, or of abetment of or attempting to commit any such offence; and the provisions contained in the`
  line `former part of this Chapter shall, so far as may be, apply to all such charges:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a number of persons are charged with separate offences and such persons do not`
  line `fall within any of the categories specified in this section, the Magistrate or Court of Session may, if such`
  line `persons by an application in writing, so desire, and if he or it is satisfied that such persons would not be`
  line `prejudicially affected thereby, and it is expedient so to do, try all such persons together.`
obj_root_law_sections_246_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_247:
  sectionId (91233)
  sectionNo (247)
  orderNo 247
  title `Withdrawal of remaining charges on conviction on one of several charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_247_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_247_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91233&sectionno=247&orderno=247&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_247_content:
  string
  line `When a charge`
  line `containing more heads than one is framed against the same person, and when a conviction has been had on`
  line `one or more of them, the complainant, or the officer conducting the prosecution, may, with the consent of`
  line `the Court, withdraw the remaining charge or charges, or the Court of its own accord may stay the inquiry`
  line `into, or trial of, such charge or charges and such withdrawal shall have the effect of an acquittal on such`
  line `charge or charges, unless the conviction be set aside, in which case the said Court (subject to the order of`
  line `the Court setting aside the conviction) may proceed with the inquiry into, or trial of, the charge or charges`
  line `so withdrawn.`
obj_root_law_sections_247_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_248:
  sectionId (91234)
  sectionNo (248)
  orderNo 248
  title `Trial to be conducted by Public Prosecutor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_248_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_248_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91234&sectionno=248&orderno=248&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_248_content:
  string
  line `In every trial before a Court of Session, the`
  line `prosecution shall be conducted by a Public Prosecutor.`
obj_root_law_sections_248_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_249:
  sectionId (91235)
  sectionNo (249)
  orderNo 249
  title `Opening case for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_249_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_249_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91235&sectionno=249&orderno=249&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_249_content:
  string
  line `When the accused appears or is brought before the Court, in`
  line `pursuance of a commitment of the case under section 232, or under any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, the prosecutor shall open his case by describing the charge brought against the accused and stating`
  line `by what evidence he proposes to prove the guilt of the accused.`
obj_root_law_sections_249_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_250:
  sectionId (91236)
  sectionNo (250)
  orderNo 250
  title Discharge.
  content obj_root_law_sections_250_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_250_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91236&sectionno=250&orderno=250&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_250_content:
  string
  line `(1) The accused may prefer an application for discharge within a period of sixty days`
  line `from the date of commitment of the case under section 232.`
  line
  line `(2) If, upon consideration of the record of the case and the documents submitted therewith, and after`
  line `hearing the submissions of the accused and the prosecution in this behalf, the Judge considers that there is`
  line `not sufficient ground for proceeding against the accused, he shall discharge the accused and record his`
  line `reasons for so doing.`
obj_root_law_sections_250_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_251:
  sectionId (91237)
  sectionNo (251)
  orderNo 251
  title `Framing of charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_251_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_251_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91237&sectionno=251&orderno=251&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_251_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, after such consideration and hearing as aforesaid, the Judge is of`
  line `opinion that there is ground for presuming that the accused has committed an offence which—`
  line
  line `(a) is not exclusively triable by the Court of Session, he may, frame a charge against the accused`
  line `and, by order, transfer the case for trial to the Chief Judicial Magistrate, or any other Judicial Magistrate`
  line `of the first class and direct the accused to appear before the Chief Judicial Magistrate, or the Judicial`
  line `Magistrate of the first class, on such date as he deems fit, and thereupon such Magistrate shall try the`
  line `offence in accordance with the procedure for the trial of warrant-cases instituted on a police report;`
  line
  line `(b) is exclusively triable by the Court, he shall frame in writing a charge against the accused within`
  line `a period of sixty days from the date of first hearing on charge.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Judge frames any charge under clause (b) of sub-section (1), the charge shall be read and`
  line `explained to the accused present either physically or through audio-video electronic means and the accused`
  line `shall be asked whether he pleads guilty of the offence charged or claims to be tried.`
obj_root_law_sections_251_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_252:
  sectionId (91238)
  sectionNo (252)
  orderNo 252
  title `Conviction on plea of guilty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_252_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_252_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91238&sectionno=252&orderno=252&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_252_content:
  string
  line `If the accused pleads guilty, the Judge shall record the plea and`
  line `may, in his discretion, convict him thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_252_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_253:
  sectionId (91239)
  sectionNo (253)
  orderNo 253
  title `Date for prosecution evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_253_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_253_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91239&sectionno=253&orderno=253&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_253_content:
  string
  line `If the accused refuses to plead, or does not plead, or claims to`
  line `be tried or is not convicted under section 252, the Judge shall fix a date for the examination of witnesses,`
  line 97
  line `and may, on the application of the prosecution, issue any process for compelling the attendance of any`
  line `witness or the production of any document or other thing.`
obj_root_law_sections_253_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_254:
  sectionId (91240)
  sectionNo (254)
  orderNo 254
  title `Evidence for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_254_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_254_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91240&sectionno=254&orderno=254&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_254_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the date so fixed, the Judge shall proceed to take all such`
  line `evidence as may be produced in support of the prosecution:`
  line
  line `Provided that evidence of a witness under this sub-section may be recorded by audio-video electronic`
  line means.
  line
  line `(2) The deposition of evidence of any public servant may be taken through audio-video electronic`
  line means.
  line
  line `(3) The Judge may, in his discretion, permit the cross-examination of any witness to be deferred until`
  line `any other witness or witnesses have been examined or recall any witness for further cross-examination.`
obj_root_law_sections_254_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_255:
  sectionId (91241)
  sectionNo (255)
  orderNo 255
  title Acquittal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_255_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_255_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91241&sectionno=255&orderno=255&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_255_content:
  string
  line `If, after taking the evidence for the prosecution, examining the accused and hearing`
  line `the prosecution and the defence on the point, the Judge considers that there is no evidence that the accused`
  line `committed the offence, the Judge shall record an order of acquittal.`
obj_root_law_sections_255_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_256:
  sectionId (91242)
  sectionNo (256)
  orderNo 256
  title `Entering upon defence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_256_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_256_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91242&sectionno=256&orderno=256&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_256_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the accused is not acquitted under section 255, he shall be`
  line `called upon to enter on his defence and adduce any evidence he may have in support thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) If the accused puts in any written statement, the Judge shall file it with the record.`
  line
  line `(3) If the accused applies for the issue of any process for compelling the attendance of any witness or`
  line `the production of any document or thing, the Judge shall issue such process unless he considers, for reasons`
  line `to be recorded, that such application should be refused on the ground that it is made for the purpose of`
  line `vexation or delay or for defeating the ends of justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_256_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_257:
  sectionId (91243)
  sectionNo (257)
  orderNo 257
  title Arguments.
  content obj_root_law_sections_257_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_257_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91243&sectionno=257&orderno=257&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_257_content:
  string
  line `When the examination of the witnesses (if any) for the defence is complete, the`
  line `prosecutor shall sum up his case and the accused or his advocate shall be entitled to reply:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any point of law is raised by the accused or his advocate, the prosecution may,`
  line `with the permission of the Judge, make his submissions with regard to such point of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_257_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_258:
  sectionId (91244)
  sectionNo (258)
  orderNo 258
  title `Judgment of acquittal or conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_258_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_258_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91244&sectionno=258&orderno=258&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_258_content:
  string
  line `(1) After hearing arguments and points of law (if any),`
  line `the Judge shall give a judgment in the case, as soon as possible, within a period of thirty days from the date`
  line `of completion of arguments, which may be extended to a period of forty-five days for reasons to be recorded`
  line `in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) If the accused is convicted, the Judge shall, unless he proceeds in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 401, hear the accused on the questions of sentence, and then pass sentence on him according to law.`
obj_root_law_sections_258_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_259:
  sectionId (91245)
  sectionNo (259)
  orderNo 259
  title `Previous conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_259_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_259_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91245&sectionno=259&orderno=259&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_259_content:
  string
  line `In a case where a previous conviction is charged under the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (7) of section 234, and the accused does not admit that he has been previously convicted as`
  line `alleged in the charge, the Judge may, after he has convicted the said accused under section 252 or section`
  line `258, take evidence in respect of the alleged previous conviction, and shall record a finding thereon:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such charge shall be read out by the Judge nor shall the accused be asked to plead`
  line `thereto nor shall the previous conviction be referred to by the prosecution or in any evidence adduced by it,`
  line `unless and until the accused has been convicted under section 252 or section 258.`
obj_root_law_sections_259_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_260:
  sectionId (91246)
  sectionNo (260)
  orderNo 260
  title `Procedure in cases instituted under sub-section (2) of section 222.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_260_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_260_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91246&sectionno=260&orderno=260&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_260_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Court of Session`
  line `taking cognizance of an offence under sub-section (2) of section 222 shall try the case in accordance with`
  line `the procedure for the trial of warrant-cases instituted otherwise than on a police report before a Court of`
  line `Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person against whom the offence is alleged to have been committed shall, unless the`
  line `Court of Session, for reasons to be recorded, otherwise directs, be examined as a witness for the prosecution.`
  line
  line `(2) Every trial under this section shall be held in camera if either party thereto so desires or if the Court`
  line `thinks fit so to do.`
  line
  line `(3) If, in any such case, the Court discharges or acquits all or any of the accused and is of opinion that`
  line `there was no reasonable cause for making the accusation against them or any of them, it may, by its order`
  line `of discharge or acquittal, direct the person against whom the offence was alleged to have been committed`
  line `(other than the President, the Vice-President or the Governor of a State or the Administrator of a Union`
  line `territory) to show cause why he should not pay compensation to such accused or to each or any of such`
  line `accused, when there are more than one.`
  line
  line `(4) The Court shall record and consider any cause which may be shown by the person so directed, and`
  line `if it is satisfied that there was no reasonable cause for making the accusation, it may, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded, make an order that compensation to such amount not exceeding five thousand rupees, as it may`
  line `determine, be paid by such person to the accused or to each or any of them.`
  line
  line `(5) Compensation awarded under sub-section (4) shall be recovered as if it were a fine imposed by a`
  line Magistrate.
  line
  line `(6) No person who has been directed to pay compensation under sub-section (4) shall, by reason of`
  line `such order, be exempted from any civil or criminal liability in respect of the complaint made under this`
  line `section:`
  line
  line `Provided that any amount paid to an accused person under this section shall be taken into account in`
  line `awarding compensation to such person in any subsequent civil suit relating to the same matter.`
  line
  line `(7) The person who has been ordered under sub-section (4) to pay compensation may appeal from the`
  line `order, in so far as it relates to the payment of compensation, to the High Court.`
  line
  line `(8) When an order for payment of compensation to an accused person is made, the compensation shall`
  line `not be paid to him before the period allowed for the presentation of the appeal has elapsed, or, if an appeal`
  line `is presented, before the appeal has been decided.`
obj_root_law_sections_260_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_261:
  sectionId (91554)
  sectionNo (261)
  orderNo 261
  title `Compliance with section 230.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_261_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_261_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91554&sectionno=261&orderno=261&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_261_content:
  string
  line `When, in any warrant-case instituted on a police report, the`
  line `accused appears or is brought before a Magistrate at the commencement of the trial, the Magistrate shall`
  line `satisfy himself that he has complied with the provisions of section 230.`
obj_root_law_sections_261_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_262:
  sectionId (91248)
  sectionNo (262)
  orderNo 262
  title `When accused shall be discharged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_262_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_262_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91248&sectionno=262&orderno=262&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_262_content:
  string
  line `(1) The accused may prefer an application for discharge`
  line `within a period of sixty days from the date of supply of copies of documents under section 230.`
  line
  line `(2) If, upon considering the police report and the documents sent with it under section 193 and making`
  line `such examination, if any, of the accused, either physically or through audio-video electronic means, as the`
  line `Magistrate thinks necessary and after giving the prosecution and the accused an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `the Magistrate considers the charge against the accused to be groundless, he shall discharge the accused,`
  line `and record his reasons for so doing.`
obj_root_law_sections_262_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_263:
  sectionId (91249)
  sectionNo (263)
  orderNo 263
  title `Framing of charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_263_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_263_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91249&sectionno=263&orderno=263&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_263_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, upon such consideration, examination, if any, and hearing, the`
  line `Magistrate is of opinion that there is ground for presuming that the accused has committed an offence triable`
  line `under this Chapter, which such Magistrate is competent to try and which, in his opinion, could be adequately`
  line `punished by him, he shall frame in writing a charge against the accused within a period of sixty days from`
  line `the date of first hearing on charge.`
  line
  line `(2) The charge shall then be read and explained to the accused, and he shall be asked whether he pleads`
  line `guilty of the offence charged or claims to be tried.`
obj_root_law_sections_263_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_264:
  sectionId (91250)
  sectionNo (264)
  orderNo 264
  title `Conviction on plea of guilty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_264_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_264_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91250&sectionno=264&orderno=264&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_264_content:
  string
  line `If the accused pleads guilty, the Magistrate shall record the plea`
  line `and may, in his discretion, convict him thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_264_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_265:
  sectionId (91251)
  sectionNo (265)
  orderNo 265
  title `Evidence for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_265_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_265_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91251&sectionno=265&orderno=265&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_265_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the accused refuses to plead or does not plead, or claims to be`
  line `tried or the Magistrate does not convict the accused under section 264, the Magistrate shall fix a date for`
  line `the examination of witnesses:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Magistrate shall supply in advance to the accused, the statement of witnesses recorded`
  line `during investigation by the police.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate may, on the application of the prosecution, issue a summons to any of its witnesses`
  line `directing him to attend or to produce any document or other thing.`
  line
  line `(3) On the date so fixed, the Magistrate shall proceed to take all such evidence as may be produced in`
  line `support of the prosecution:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Magistrate may permit the cross-examination of any witness to be deferred until any`
  line `other witness or witnesses have been examined or recall any witness for further cross-examination:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the examination of a witness under this sub-section may be done by audio-video`
  line `electronic means at the designated place to be notified by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_265_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_266:
  sectionId (91252)
  sectionNo (266)
  orderNo 266
  title `Evidence for defence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_266_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_266_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91252&sectionno=266&orderno=266&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_266_content:
  string
  line `(1) The accused shall then be called upon to enter upon his defence and`
  line `produce his evidence; and if the accused puts in any written statement, the Magistrate shall file it with the`
  line record.
  line
  line `(2) If the accused, after he has entered upon his defence, applies to the Magistrate to issue any process`
  line `for compelling the attendance of any witness for the purpose of examination or cross-examination, or the`
  line `production of any document or other thing, the Magistrate shall issue such process unless he considers that`
  line `such application should be refused on the ground that it is made for the purpose of vexation or delay or for`
  line `defeating the ends of justice and such ground shall be recorded by him in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that when the accused has cross-examined or had the opportunity of cross-examining any`
  line `witness before entering on his defence, the attendance of such witness shall not be compelled under this`
  line `section, unless the Magistrate is satisfied that it is necessary for the ends of justice:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the examination of a witness under this sub-section may be done by audio-video`
  line `electronic means at the designated place to be notified by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Magistrate may, before summoning any witness on an application under sub-section (2), require`
  line `that the reasonable expenses incurred by the witness in attending for the purposes of the trial be deposited`
  line `in Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_266_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_267:
  sectionId (91555)
  sectionNo (267)
  orderNo 267
  title `Evidence for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_267_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_267_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91555&sectionno=267&orderno=267&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_267_content:
  string
  line `(1) When, in any warrant-case instituted otherwise than on a police`
  line `report, the accused appears or is brought before a Magistrate, the Magistrate shall proceed to hear the`
  line `prosecution and take all such evidence as may be produced in support of the prosecution.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate may, on the application of the prosecution, issue a summons to any of its witnesses`
  line `directing him to attend or to produce any document or other thing.`
obj_root_law_sections_267_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_268:
  sectionId (91254)
  sectionNo (268)
  orderNo 268
  title `When accused shall be discharged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_268_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_268_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91254&sectionno=268&orderno=268&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_268_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, upon taking all the evidence referred to in`
  line `section 267, the Magistrate considers, for reasons to be recorded, that no case against the accused has been`
  line `made out which, if unrebutted, would warrant his conviction, the Magistrate shall discharge him.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent a Magistrate from discharging the accused at any`
  line `previous stage of the case if, for reasons to be recorded by such Magistrate, he considers the charge to be`
  line groundless.
obj_root_law_sections_268_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_269:
  sectionId (91255)
  sectionNo (269)
  orderNo 269
  title `Procedure where accused is not discharged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_269_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_269_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91255&sectionno=269&orderno=269&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_269_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, when such evidence has been taken, or at`
  line `any previous stage of the case, the Magistrate is of opinion that there is ground for presuming that the`
  line `accused has committed an offence triable under this Chapter, which such Magistrate is competent to try and`
  line `which, in his opinion, could be adequately punished by him, he shall frame in writing a charge against the`
  line accused.
  line
  line `(2) The charge shall then be read and explained to the accused, and he shall be asked whether he pleads`
  line `guilty or has any defence to make.`
  line
  line `(3) If the accused pleads guilty, the Magistrate shall record the plea, and may, in his discretion, convict`
  line `him thereon.`
  line
  line `(4) If the accused refuses to plead, or does not plead or claims to be tried or if the accused is not`
  line `convicted under sub-section (3), he shall be required to state, at the commencement of the next hearing of`
  line `the case, or, if the Magistrate for reasons to be recorded in writing so thinks fit, forthwith, whether he wishes`
  line `to cross-examine any, and, if so, which, of the witnesses for the prosecution whose evidence has been taken.`
  line
  line `(5) If he says he does so wish, the witnesses named by him shall be recalled and, after cross-examination`
  line `and re-examination (if any), they shall be discharged.`
  line
  line `(6) The evidence of any remaining witnesses for the prosecution shall next be taken, and after crossexamination and re-examination (if any), they shall also be discharged.`
  line
  line `(7) Where, despite giving opportunity to the prosecution and after taking all reasonable measures under`
  line `this Sanhita, if the attendance of the prosecution witnesses under sub-sections (5) and (6) cannot be secured`
  line `for cross-examination, it shall be deemed that such witness has not been examined for not being available,`
  line `and the Magistrate may close the prosecution evidence for reasons to be recorded in writing and proceed`
  line `with the case on the basis of the materials on record.`
obj_root_law_sections_269_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_270:
  sectionId (91256)
  sectionNo (270)
  orderNo 270
  title `Evidence for defence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_270_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_270_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91256&sectionno=270&orderno=270&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_270_content:
  string
  line `The accused shall then be called upon to enter upon his defence and`
  line `produce his evidence; and the provisions of section 266 shall apply to the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_270_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_271:
  sectionId (91556)
  sectionNo (271)
  orderNo 271
  title `Acquittal or conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_271_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_271_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91556&sectionno=271&orderno=271&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_271_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in any case under this Chapter in which a charge has been`
  line `framed, the Magistrate finds the accused not guilty, he shall record an order of acquittal.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in any case under this Chapter, the Magistrate finds the accused guilty, but does not proceed`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of section 364 or section 401, he shall, after hearing the accused on the`
  line `question of sentence, pass sentence upon him according to law.`
  line
  line `(3) Where, in any case under this Chapter, a previous conviction is charged under the provisions of subsection (7) of section 234 and the accused does not admit that he has been previously convicted as alleged`
  line `in the charge, the Magistrate may, after he has convicted the said accused, take evidence in respect of the`
  line `alleged previous conviction, and shall record a finding thereon:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such charge shall be read out by the Magistrate nor shall the accused be asked to plead`
  line `thereto nor shall the previous conviction be referred to by the prosecution or in any evidence adduced by it,`
  line `unless and until the accused has been convicted under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_271_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_272:
  sectionId (91258)
  sectionNo (272)
  orderNo 272
  title `Absence of complainant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_272_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91258&sectionno=272&orderno=272&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_272_content:
  string
  line `When the proceedings have been instituted upon complaint, and on`
  line `any day fixed for the hearing of the case, the complainant is absent, and the offence may be lawfully`
  line `compounded or is not a cognizable offence, the Magistrate may after giving thirty days’ time to the`
  line `complainant to be present, in his discretion, notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained, at any time`
  line `before the charge has been framed, discharge the accused.`
obj_root_law_sections_272_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_273:
  sectionId (91259)
  sectionNo (273)
  orderNo 273
  title `Compensation for accusation without reasonable cause.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_273_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91259&sectionno=273&orderno=273&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_273_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in any case instituted upon`
  line `complaint or upon information given to a police officer or to a Magistrate, one or more persons is or are`
  line `accused before a Magistrate of any offence triable by a Magistrate, and the Magistrate by whom the case is`
  line `heard discharges or acquits all or any of the accused, and is of opinion that there was no reasonable ground`
  line `for making the accusation against them or any of them, the Magistrate may, by his order of discharge or`
  line `acquittal, if the person upon whose complaint or information the accusation was made is present, call upon`
  line `him forthwith to show cause why he should not pay compensation to such accused or to each or any of such`
  line `accused when there are more than one; or, if such person is not present, direct the issue of a summons to`
  line `him to appear and show cause as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate shall record and consider any cause which such complainant or informant may show,`
  line `and if he is satisfied that there was no reasonable ground for making the accusation, may, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded, make an order that compensation to such amount, not exceeding the amount of fine he is`
  line `empowered to impose, as he may determine, be paid by such complainant or informant to the accused or to`
  line `each or any of them.`
  line
  line `(3) The Magistrate may, by the order directing payment of the compensation under sub-section (2),`
  line `further order that, in default of payment, the person ordered to pay such compensation shall undergo simple`
  line `imprisonment for a period not exceeding thirty days.`
  line
  line `(4) When any person is imprisoned under sub-section (3), the provisions of sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 8 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 shall, so far as may be, apply.`
  line
  line `(5) No person who has been directed to pay compensation under this section shall, by reason of such`
  line `order, be exempted from any civil or criminal liability in respect of the complaint made or information`
  line `given by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that any amount paid to an accused person under this section shall be taken into account in`
  line `awarding compensation to such person in any subsequent civil suit relating to the same matter.`
  line
  line `(6) A complainant or informant who has been ordered under sub-section (2) by a Magistrate of the`
  line `second class to pay compensation exceeding two thousand rupees, may appeal from the order, as if such`
  line `complainant or informant had been convicted on a trial held by such Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(7) When an order for payment of compensation to an accused person is made in a case which is subject`
  line `to appeal under sub-section (6), the compensation shall not be paid to him before the period allowed for the`
  line `presentation of the appeal has elapsed, or, if an appeal is presented, before the appeal has been decided; and`
  line `where such order is made in a case which is not so subject to appeal the compensation shall not be paid`
  line `before the expiration of one month from the date of the order.`
  line
  line `(8) The provisions of this section apply to summons-cases as well as to warrant-cases.`
obj_root_law_sections_273_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_274:
  sectionId (91260)
  sectionNo (274)
  orderNo 274
  title `Substance of accusation to be stated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_274_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91260&sectionno=274&orderno=274&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_274_content:
  string
  line `When in a summons-case the accused appears or is`
  line `brought before the Magistrate, the particulars of the offence of which he is accused shall be stated to him,`
  line `and he shall be asked whether he pleads guilty or has any defence to make, but it shall not be necessary to`
  line `frame a formal charge:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Magistrate considers the accusation as groundless, he shall, after recording reasons`
  line `in writing, release the accused and such release shall have the effect of discharge.`
obj_root_law_sections_274_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_275:
  sectionId (91261)
  sectionNo (275)
  orderNo 275
  title `Conviction on plea of guilty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_275_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91261&sectionno=275&orderno=275&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_275_content:
  string
  line `If the accused pleads guilty, the Magistrate shall record the plea`
  line `as nearly as possible in the words used by the accused and may, in his discretion, convict him thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_275_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_276:
  sectionId (91262)
  sectionNo (276)
  orderNo 276
  title `Conviction on plea of guilty in absence of accused in petty cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_276_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91262&sectionno=276&orderno=276&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_276_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a summons has`
  line `been issued under section 229 and the accused desires to plead guilty to the charge without appearing before`
  line 102
  line `the Magistrate, he shall transmit to the Magistrate, by post or by messenger, a letter containing his plea and`
  line `also the amount of fine specified in the summons.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate may, in his discretion, convict the accused in his absence, on his plea of guilty and`
  line `sentence him to pay the fine specified in the summons, and the amount transmitted by the accused shall be`
  line `adjusted towards that fine, or where an advocate authorised by the accused in this behalf pleads guilty on`
  line `behalf of the accused, the Magistrate shall record the plea as nearly as possible in the words used by the`
  line `advocate and may, in his discretion, convict the accused on such plea and sentence him as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_276_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_277:
  sectionId (91263)
  sectionNo (277)
  orderNo 277
  title `Procedure when not convicted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_277_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91263&sectionno=277&orderno=277&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_277_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Magistrate does not convict the accused under section`
  line `275 or section 276, the Magistrate shall proceed to hear the prosecution and take all such evidence as may`
  line `be produced in support of the prosecution, and also to hear the accused and take all such evidence as he`
  line `produces in his defence.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate may, if he thinks fit, on the application of the prosecution or the accused, issue a`
  line `summons to any witness directing him to attend or to produce any document or other thing.`
  line
  line `(3) The Magistrate may, before summoning any witness on such application, require that the reasonable`
  line `expenses of the witness incurred in attending for the purposes of the trial be deposited in Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_277_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_278:
  sectionId (91264)
  sectionNo (278)
  orderNo 278
  title `Acquittal or conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_278_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91264&sectionno=278&orderno=278&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_278_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Magistrate, upon taking the evidence referred to in`
  line `section 277 and such further evidence, if any, as he may, of his own motion, cause to be produced, finds`
  line `the accused not guilty, he shall record an order of acquittal.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Magistrate does not proceed in accordance with the provisions of section 364 or`
  line `section 401, he shall, if he finds the accused guilty, pass sentence upon him according to law.`
  line
  line `(3) A Magistrate may, under section 275 or section 278, convict the accused of any offence triable`
  line `under this Chapter, which from the facts admitted or proved he appears to have committed, whatever may`
  line `be the nature of the complaint or summons, if the Magistrate is satisfied that the accused would not be`
  line `prejudiced thereby.`
obj_root_law_sections_278_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_279:
  sectionId (91265)
  sectionNo (279)
  orderNo 279
  title `Non-appearance or death of complainant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_279_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_279_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91265&sectionno=279&orderno=279&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_279_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the summons has been issued on complaint,`
  line `and on the day appointed for the appearance of the accused, or any day subsequent thereto to which the`
  line `hearing may be adjourned, the complainant does not appear, the Magistrate shall, after giving thirty days’`
  line `time to the complainant to be present, notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained, acquit the accused,`
  line `unless for some reason he thinks it proper to adjourn the hearing of the case to some other day:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the complainant is represented by an advocate or by the officer conducting the`
  line `prosecution or where the Magistrate is of opinion that the personal attendance of the complainant is not`
  line `necessary, the Magistrate may, dispense with his attendance and proceed with the case.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall, so far as may be, apply also to cases where the`
  line `non-appearance of the complainant is due to his death.`
obj_root_law_sections_279_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_280:
  sectionId (91266)
  sectionNo (280)
  orderNo 280
  title `Withdrawal of complaint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_280_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_280_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91266&sectionno=280&orderno=280&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_280_content:
  string
  line `If a complainant, at any time before a final order is passed in any`
  line `case under this Chapter, satisfies the Magistrate that there are sufficient grounds for permitting him to`
  line `withdraw his complaint against the accused, or if there be more than one accused, against all or any of them,`
  line `the Magistrate may permit him to withdraw the same, and shall thereupon acquit the accused against whom`
  line `the complaint is so withdrawn.`
obj_root_law_sections_280_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_281:
  sectionId (91267)
  sectionNo (281)
  orderNo 281
  title `Power to stop proceedings in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_281_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91267&sectionno=281&orderno=281&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_281_content:
  string
  line `In any summons-case instituted otherwise than`
  line `upon complaint, a Magistrate of the first class or, with the previous sanction of the Chief Judicial Magistrate,`
  line `any other Judicial Magistrate, may, for reasons to be recorded by him, stop the proceedings at any stage`
  line `without pronouncing any judgment and where such stoppage of proceedings is made after the evidence of`
  line `the principal witnesses has been recorded, pronounce a judgment of acquittal, and in any other case, release`
  line `the accused, and such release shall have the effect of discharge.`
obj_root_law_sections_281_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_282:
  sectionId (91268)
  sectionNo (282)
  orderNo 282
  title `Power of Court to convert summons-cases into warrant-cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_282_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91268&sectionno=282&orderno=282&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_282_content:
  string
  line `When in the course of the trial`
  line `of a summons-case relating to an offence punishable with imprisonment for a term exceeding six months,`
  line `it appears to the Magistrate that in the interests of justice, the offence should be tried in accordance with`
  line `the procedure for the trial of warrant-cases, such Magistrate may proceed to re-hear the case in the manner`
  line `provided by this Sanhita for the trial of warrant-cases and may recall any witness who may have been`
  line examined.
obj_root_law_sections_282_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_283:
  sectionId (91269)
  sectionNo (283)
  orderNo 283
  title `Power to try summarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_283_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91269&sectionno=283&orderno=283&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_283_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Sanhita—`
  line
  line `(a) any Chief Judicial Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(b) Magistrate of the first class,`
  line
  line `shall try in a summary way all or any of the following offences:—`
  line
  line `(i) theft, under sub-section (2) of section 303, section 305 or section 306 of the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023 where the value of the property stolen does not exceed twenty thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(ii) receiving or retaining stolen property, under sub-section (2) of section 317 of the Bharatiya`
  line `Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, where the value of the property does not exceed twenty thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(iii) assisting in the concealment or disposal of stolen property under sub-section (5) of section 317`
  line `of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, where the value of such property does not exceed twenty`
  line `thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(iv) offences under sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 331 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023;`
  line
  line `(v) insult with intent to provoke a breach of the peace, under section 352, and criminal intimidation,`
  line `under sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 351 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023;`
  line
  line `(vi) abetment of any of the foregoing offences;`
  line
  line `(vii) an attempt to commit any of the foregoing offences, when such attempt is an offence;`
  line
  line `(viii) any offence constituted by an act in respect of which a complaint may be made under`
  line `section 20 of the Cattle-trespass Act, 1871 (1 of 1871).`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate may, after giving the accused a reasonable opportunity of being heard, for reasons`
  line `to be recorded in writing, try in a summary way all or any of the offences not punishable with death or`
  line `imprisonment for life or imprisonment for a term exceeding three years:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appeal shall lie against the decision of a Magistrate to try a case in a summary way`
  line `under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) When, in the course of a summary trial it appears to the Magistrate that the nature of the case is`
  line `such that it is undesirable to try it summarily, the Magistrate shall recall any witnesses who may have been`
  line `examined and proceed to re-hear the case in the manner provided by this Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_283_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_284:
  sectionId (91270)
  sectionNo (284)
  orderNo 284
  title `Summary trial by Magistrate of second class.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_284_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_284_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91270&sectionno=284&orderno=284&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_284_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may confer on any Magistrate`
  line `invested with the powers of a Magistrate of the second class power to try summarily any offence which is`
  line `punishable only with fine or with imprisonment for a term not exceeding six months with or without fine,`
  line `and any abetment of or attempt to commit any such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_284_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_285:
  sectionId (91271)
  sectionNo (285)
  orderNo 285
  title `Procedure for summary trials.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_285_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91271&sectionno=285&orderno=285&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_285_content:
  string
  line `(1) In trials under this Chapter, the procedure specified in this`
  line `Sanhita for the trial of summons-case shall be followed except as hereinafter mentioned.`
  line
  line `(2) No sentence of imprisonment for a term exceeding three months shall be passed in the case of any`
  line `conviction under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_285_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_286:
  sectionId (91272)
  sectionNo (286)
  orderNo 286
  title `Record in summary trials.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_286_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91272&sectionno=286&orderno=286&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_286_content:
  string
  line `In every case tried summarily, the Magistrate shall enter, in such`
  line `form as the State Government may direct, the following particulars, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the serial number of the case;`
  line
  line `(b) the date of the commission of the offence;`
  line
  line `(c) the date of the report or complaint;`
  line
  line `(d) the name of the complainant (if any);`
  line
  line `(e) the name, parentage and residence of the accused;`
  line
  line `(f) the offence complained of and the offence (if any) proved, and in cases coming under clause (i),`
  line `clause (ii) or clause (iii) of sub-section (1) of section 283, the value of the property in respect of which`
  line `the offence has been committed;`
  line
  line `(g) the plea of the accused and his examination (if any);`
  line
  line `(h) the finding;`
  line
  line `(i) the sentence or other final order;`
  line
  line `(j) the date on which proceedings terminated.`
obj_root_law_sections_286_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_287:
  sectionId (91273)
  sectionNo (287)
  orderNo 287
  title `Judgment in cases tried summarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_287_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_287_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91273&sectionno=287&orderno=287&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_287_content:
  string
  line `In every case tried summarily in which the accused does`
  line `not plead guilty, the Magistrate shall record the substance of the evidence and a judgment containing a brief`
  line `statement of the reasons for the finding.`
obj_root_law_sections_287_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_288:
  sectionId (91274)
  sectionNo (288)
  orderNo 288
  title `Language of record and judgment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_288_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91274&sectionno=288&orderno=288&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_288_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every such record and judgment shall be written in the`
  line `language of the Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The High Court may authorise any Magistrate empowered to try offences summarily to prepare the`
  line `aforesaid record or judgment or both by means of an officer appointed in this behalf by the Chief Judicial`
  line `Magistrate, and the record or judgment so prepared shall be signed by such Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_288_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_289:
  sectionId (91275)
  sectionNo (289)
  orderNo 289
  title `Application of Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_289_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_289_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91275&sectionno=289&orderno=289&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_289_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Chapter shall apply in respect of an accused against whom—`
  line
  line `(a) the report has been forwarded by the officer in charge of the police station under section 193 alleging`
  line `therein that an offence appears to have been committed by him other than an offence for which the`
  line `punishment of death or of imprisonment for life or of imprisonment for a term exceeding seven years has`
  line `been provided under the law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) a Magistrate has taken cognizance of an offence on complaint, other than an offence for which the`
  line `punishment of death or of imprisonment for life or of imprisonment for a term exceeding seven years, has`
  line `been provided under the law for the time being in force, and after examining complainant and witnesses`
  line `under section 223, issued the process under section 227,`
  line
  line `but does not apply where such offence affects the socio-economic condition of the country or has been`
  line `committed against a woman, or a child.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the Central Government shall, by notification, determine the`
  line `offences under the law for the time being in force which shall be the offences affecting the socio-economic`
  line `condition of the country.`
obj_root_law_sections_289_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_290:
  sectionId (91276)
  sectionNo (290)
  orderNo 290
  title `Application for plea bargaining.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_290_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91276&sectionno=290&orderno=290&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_290_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person accused of an offence may file an application`
  line `for plea bargaining within a period of thirty days from the date of framing of charge in the Court in which`
  line `such offence is pending for trial.`
  line
  line `(2) The application under sub-section (1) shall contain a brief description of the case relating to which`
  line `the application is filed including the offence to which the case relates and shall be accompanied by an`
  line `affidavit sworn by the accused stating therein that he has voluntarily preferred, after understanding the`
  line `nature and extent of punishment provided under the law for the offence, the plea bargaining in his case and`
  line `that he has not previously been convicted by a Court in which he had been charged with the same offence.`
  line
  line `(3) After receiving the application under sub-section (1), the Court shall issue notice to the Public`
  line `Prosecutor or the complainant of the case and to the accused to appear on the date fixed for the case.`
  line
  line `(4) When the Public Prosecutor or the complainant of the case and the accused appear on the date fixed`
  line `under sub-section (3), the Court shall examine the accused in camera, where the other party in the case`
  line `shall not be present, to satisfy itself that the accused has filed the application voluntarily and where—`
  line
  line `(a) the Court is satisfied that the application has been filed by the accused voluntarily, it shall`
  line `provide time, not exceeding sixty days, to the Public Prosecutor or the complainant of the case and the`
  line `accused to work out a mutually satisfactory disposition of the case which may include giving to the`
  line `victim by the accused the compensation and other expenses during the case and thereafter fix the date`
  line `for further hearing of the case;`
  line
  line `(b) the Court finds that the application has been filed involuntarily by the accused or he has`
  line `previously been convicted by a Court in a case in which he had been charged with the same offence, it`
  line `shall proceed further in accordance with the provisions of this Sanhita from the stage such application`
  line `has been filed under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_290_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_291:
  sectionId (91277)
  sectionNo (291)
  orderNo 291
  title `Guidelines for mutually satisfactory disposition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_291_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91277&sectionno=291&orderno=291&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_291_content:
  string
  line `In working out a mutually satisfactory`
  line `disposition under clause (a) of sub-section (4) of section 290, the Court shall follow the following`
  line `procedure, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) in a case instituted on a police report, the Court shall issue notice to the Public Prosecutor, the`
  line `police officer who has investigated the case, the accused and the victim of the case to participate in the`
  line `meeting to work out a satisfactory disposition of the case:`
  line
  line `Provided that throughout such process of working out a satisfactory disposition of the case, it shall`
  line `be the duty of the Court to ensure that the entire process is completed voluntarily by the parties`
  line `participating in the meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the accused, if he so desires, may participate in such meeting with his`
  line `advocate, if any, engaged in the case;`
  line
  line `(b) in a case instituted otherwise than on police report, the Court shall issue notice to the accused`
  line `and the victim of the case to participate in a meeting to work out a satisfactory disposition of the case:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be the duty of the Court to ensure, throughout such process of working out a`
  line `satisfactory disposition of the case, that it is completed voluntarily by the parties participating in the`
  line `meeting:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the victim of the case or the accused so desires, he may participate in such`
  line `meeting with his advocate engaged in the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_291_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_292:
  sectionId (91278)
  sectionNo (292)
  orderNo 292
  title `Report of mutually satisfactory disposition to be submitted before Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_292_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91278&sectionno=292&orderno=292&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_292_content:
  string
  line `Where in a`
  line `meeting under section 291, a satisfactory disposition of the case has been worked out, the Court shall`
  line `prepare a report of such disposition which shall be signed by the presiding officer of the Court and all other`
  line `persons who participated in the meeting and if no such disposition has been worked out, the Court shall`
  line `record such observation and proceed further in accordance with the provisions of this Sanhita from the stage`
  line `the application under sub-section (1) of section 290 has been filed in such case.`
obj_root_law_sections_292_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_293:
  sectionId (91279)
  sectionNo (293)
  orderNo 293
  title `Disposal of case.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_293_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91279&sectionno=293&orderno=293&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_293_content:
  string
  line `Where a satisfactory disposition of the case has been worked out under`
  line `section 292, the Court shall dispose of the case in the following manner, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the Court shall award the compensation to the victim in accordance with the disposition under`
  line `section 292 and hear the parties on the quantum of the punishment, releasing of the accused on`
  line `probation of good conduct or after admonition under section 401 or for dealing with the accused under`
  line `the provisions of the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958) or any other law for the time being`
  line `in force and follow the procedure specified in the succeeding clauses for imposing the punishment on`
  line `the accused;`
  line
  line `(b) after hearing the parties under clause (a), if the Court is of the view that section 401 or the`
  line `provisions of the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958) or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force are attracted in the case of the accused, it may release the accused on probation or provide the`
  line `benefit of any such law;`
  line
  line `(c) after hearing the parties under clause (b), if the Court finds that minimum punishment has been`
  line `provided under the law for the offence committed by the accused, it may sentence the accused to half`
  line `of such minimum punishment, and where the accused is a first-time offender and has not been convicted`
  line `of any offence in the past, it may sentence the accused to one-fourth of such minimum punishment;`
  line
  line `(d) in case after hearing the parties under clause (b), the Court finds that the offence committed by`
  line `the accused is not covered under clause (b) or clause (c), then, it may sentence the accused to one-fourth`
  line `of the punishment provided or extendable for such offence and where the accused is a first-time`
  line `offender and has not been convicted of any offence in the past, it may sentence the accused to one-sixth`
  line `of the punishment provided or extendable, for such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_293_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_294:
  sectionId (91280)
  sectionNo (294)
  orderNo 294
  title `Judgment of Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_294_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91280&sectionno=294&orderno=294&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_294_content:
  string
  line `The Court shall deliver its judgment in terms of section 293 in the open`
  line `Court and the same shall be signed by the presiding officer of the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_294_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_295:
  sectionId (91281)
  sectionNo (295)
  orderNo 295
  title `Finality of judgment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_295_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91281&sectionno=295&orderno=295&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_295_content:
  string
  line `The judgment delivered by the Court under this section shall be final and`
  line `no appeal (except the special leave petition under article 136 and writ petition under articles 226 and 227`
  line `of the Constitution) shall lie in any Court against such judgment.`
obj_root_law_sections_295_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_296:
  sectionId (91282)
  sectionNo (296)
  orderNo 296
  title `Power of Court in plea bargaining.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_296_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91282&sectionno=296&orderno=296&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_296_content:
  string
  line `A Court shall have, for the purposes of discharging its`
  line `functions under this Chapter, all the powers vested in respect of bail, trial of offences and other matters`
  line `relating to the disposal of a case in such Court under this Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_296_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_297:
  sectionId (91283)
  sectionNo (297)
  orderNo 297
  title `Period of detention undergone by accused to be set off against sentence of imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_297_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91283&sectionno=297&orderno=297&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_297_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 468 shall apply, for setting off the period of detention undergone by the accused`
  line `against the sentence of imprisonment imposed under this Chapter, in the same manner as they apply in`
  line `respect of the imprisonment under other provisions of this Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_297_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_298:
  sectionId (91284)
  sectionNo (298)
  orderNo 298
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_298_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91284&sectionno=298&orderno=298&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_298_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Chapter shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent`
  line `therewith contained in any other provisions of this Sanhita and nothing in such other provisions shall be`
  line `construed to constrain the meaning of any provision of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this Chapter, the expression "Public Prosecutor" has the meaning`
  line `assigned to it under clause (v) of section 2 and includes an Assistant Public Prosecutor appointed under`
  line `section 19.`
obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_299:
  sectionId (91285)
  sectionNo (299)
  orderNo 299
  title `Statements of accused not to be used.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_299_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91285&sectionno=299&orderno=299&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_299_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the`
  line `time being in force, the statements or facts stated by an accused in an application for plea bargaining filed`
  line `under section 290 shall not be used for any other purpose except for the purpose of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_300:
  sectionId (91286)
  sectionNo (300)
  orderNo 300
  title `Non-application of Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_300_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91286&sectionno=300&orderno=300&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_300_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter shall apply to any juvenile or child as`
  line `defined in section 2 of the Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2015 (2 of 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_301:
  sectionId (91287)
  sectionNo (301)
  orderNo 301
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_301_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91287&sectionno=301&orderno=301&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_301_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter,---`
  line
  line `(a) "detained" includes detained under any law providing for preventive detention;`
  line
  line `(b) "prison" includes,---`
  line
  line `(i) any place which has been declared by the State Government, by general or special order, to`
  line `be a subsidiary jail;`
  line
  line `(ii) any reformatory, Borstal institution or other institution of a like nature.`
obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_302:
  sectionId (91288)
  sectionNo (302)
  orderNo 302
  title `Power to require attendance of prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_302_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91288&sectionno=302&orderno=302&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_302_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever, in the course of an inquiry, trial or`
  line `proceeding under this Sanhita, it appears to a Criminal Court,---`
  line
  line `(a) that a person confined or detained in a prison should be brought before the Court for answering`
  line `to a charge of an offence, or for the purpose of any proceedings against him; or`
  line
  line `(b) that it is necessary for the ends of justice to examine such person as a witness,`
  line
  line `the Court may make an order requiring the officer in charge of the prison to produce such person before the`
  line `Court answering to the charge or for the purpose of such proceeding or for giving evidence.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order under sub-section (1) is made by a Magistrate of the second class, it shall not be`
  line `forwarded to, or acted upon by, the officer in charge of the prison unless it is countersigned by the Chief`
  line `Judicial Magistrate, to whom such Magistrate is subordinate.`
  line
  line `(3) Every order submitted for countersigning under sub-section (2) shall be accompanied by a statement`
  line `of the facts which, in the opinion of the Magistrate, render the order necessary, and the Chief Judicial`
  line `Magistrate to whom it is submitted may, after considering such statement, decline to countersign the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_303:
  sectionId (91557)
  sectionNo (303)
  orderNo 303
  title `Power of State Government or Central Government to exclude certain persons from operation of section 302.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_303_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91557&sectionno=303&orderno=303&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_303_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government or the Central Government, as the case may be, may,`
  line `at any time, having regard to the matters specified in sub-section (2), by general or special order, direct that`
  line `any person or class of persons shall not be removed from the prison in which he or they may be confined`
  line `or detained, and thereupon, so long as the order remains in force, no order made under section 302, whether`
  line `before or after the order of the State Government or the Central Government, shall have effect in respect of`
  line `such person or class of persons.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making an order under sub-section (1), the State Government or the Central Government in`
  line `the cases instituted by its central agency, as the case may be, shall have regard to the following matters,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the nature of the offence for which, or the grounds on which, the person or class of persons has`
  line `been ordered to be confined or detained in prison;`
  line
  line `(b) the likelihood of the disturbance of public order if the person or class of persons is allowed to`
  line `be removed from the prison;`
  line
  line `(c) the public interest, generally.`
obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_304:
  sectionId (91290)
  sectionNo (304)
  orderNo 304
  title `Officer in charge of prison to abstain from carrying out order in certain contingencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_304_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91290&sectionno=304&orderno=304&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_304_content:
  string
  line `Where the person in respect of whom an order is made under section 302---`
  line
  line `(a) is by reason of sickness or infirmity unfit to be removed from the prison; or`
  line
  line `(b) is under committal for trial or under remand pending trial or pending a preliminary`
  line `investigation; or`
  line
  line `(c) is in custody for a period which would expire before the expiration of the time required for`
  line `complying with the order and for taking him back to the prison in which he is confined or detained; or`
  line
  line `(d) is a person to whom an order made by the State Government or the Central Government under`
  line `section 303 applies,`
  line
  line `the officer in charge of the prison shall abstain from carrying out the Court's order and shall send to the`
  line `Court a statement of reasons for so abstaining:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the attendance of such person is required for giving evidence at a place not more`
  line `than twenty-five kilometres distance from the prison, the officer in charge of the prison shall not so abstain`
  line `for the reason mentioned in clause (b).`
obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_305:
  sectionId (91291)
  sectionNo (305)
  orderNo 305
  title `Prisoner to be brought to Court in custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_305_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91291&sectionno=305&orderno=305&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_305_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 304, the`
  line `officer in charge of the prison shall, upon delivery of an order made under sub-section (1) of section 302`
  line `and duly countersigned, where necessary, under sub-section (2) thereof, cause the person named in the`
  line `order to be taken to the Court in which his attendance is required, so as to be present there at the time`
  line `mentioned in the order, and shall cause him to be kept in custody in or near the Court until he has been`
  line `examined or until the Court authorises him to be taken back to the prison in which he was confined or`
  line detained.
obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_306:
  sectionId (91292)
  sectionNo (306)
  orderNo 306
  title `Power to issue commission for examination of witness in prison.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_306_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91292&sectionno=306&orderno=306&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_306_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this`
  line `Chapter shall be without prejudice to the power of the Court to issue, under section 319, a commission for`
  line `the examination, as a witness, of any person confined or detained in a prison; and the provisions of Part B`
  line `of Chapter XXV shall apply in relation to the examination on commission of any such person in the prison`
  line `as they apply in relation to the examination on commission of any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_307:
  sectionId (91558)
  sectionNo (307)
  orderNo 307
  title `Language of Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_307_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91558&sectionno=307&orderno=307&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_307_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may determine what shall be, for purposes of this`
  line `Sanhita, the language of each Court within the State other than the High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_308:
  sectionId (91294)
  sectionNo (308)
  orderNo 308
  title `Evidence to be taken in presence of accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_308_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91294&sectionno=308&orderno=308&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_308_content:
  string
  line `Except as otherwise expressly provided, all`
  line `evidence taken in the course of the trial or other proceeding shall be taken in the presence of the accused,`
  line `or, when his personal attendance is dispensed with, in the presence of his advocate including through`
  line `audio-video electronic means at the designated place to be notified by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the evidence of a woman below the age of eighteen years who is alleged to have`
  line `been subjected to rape or any other sexual offence, is to be recorded, the Court may take appropriate`
  line `measures to ensure that such woman is not confronted by the accused while at the same time ensuring the`
  line `right of cross-examination of the accused.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section,"accused" includes a person in relation to whom any proceeding under`
  line `Chapter IX has been commenced under this Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_309:
  sectionId (91295)
  sectionNo (309)
  orderNo 309
  title `Record in summons-cases and inquiries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_309_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91295&sectionno=309&orderno=309&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_309_content:
  string
  line `(1) In all summons-cases tried before a Magistrate,`
  line `in all inquiries under sections 164 to 167 (both inclusive), and in all proceedings under section 491`
  line `otherwise than in the course of a trial, the Magistrate shall, as the examination of each witness proceeds,`
  line `make a memorandum of the substance of the evidence in the language of the Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Magistrate is unable to make such memorandum himself, he shall, after recording`
  line `the reason of his inability, cause such memorandum to be made in writing or from his dictation in open`
  line Court.
  line
  line `(2) Such memorandum shall be signed by the Magistrate and shall form part of the record.`
obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_310:
  sectionId (91296)
  sectionNo (310)
  orderNo 310
  title `Record in warrant-cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_310_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91296&sectionno=310&orderno=310&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_310_content:
  string
  line `(1) In all warrant-cases tried before a Magistrate, the evidence of`
  line `each witness shall, as his examination proceeds, be taken down in writing either by the Magistrate himself`
  line
  line `or by his dictation in open Court or, where he is unable to do so owing to a physical or other incapacity,`
  line `under his direction and superintendence, by an officer of the Court appointed by him in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that evidence of a witness under this sub-section may also be recorded by audio-video`
  line `electronic means in the presence of the advocate of the person accused of the offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Magistrate causes the evidence to be taken down, he shall record a certificate that the`
  line `evidence could not be taken down by himself for the reasons referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Such evidence shall ordinarily be taken down in the form of a narrative; but the Magistrate may, in`
  line `his discretion take down, or cause to be taken down, any part of such evidence in the form of question and`
  line answer.
  line
  line `(4) The evidence so taken down shall be signed by the Magistrate and shall form part of the record.`
obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_311:
  sectionId (91297)
  sectionNo (311)
  orderNo 311
  title `Record in trial before Court of Session.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_311_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91297&sectionno=311&orderno=311&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_311_content:
  string
  line `(1) In all trials before a Court of Session, the evidence`
  line `of each witness shall, as his examination proceeds, be taken down in writing either by the presiding Judge`
  line `himself or by his dictation in open Court, or under his direction and superintendence, by an officer of the`
  line `Court appointed by him in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Such evidence shall ordinarily be taken down in the form of a narrative, but the presiding Judge`
  line `may, in his discretion, take down, or cause to be taken down, any part of such evidence in the form of`
  line `question and answer.`
  line
  line `(3) The evidence so taken down shall be signed by the presiding Judge and shall form part of the record.`
obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_312:
  sectionId (91298)
  sectionNo (312)
  orderNo 312
  title `Language of record of evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_312_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91298&sectionno=312&orderno=312&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_312_content:
  string
  line `In every case where evidence is taken down under`
  line `section 310 or section 311,---`
  line
  line `(a) if the witness gives evidence in the language of the Court, it shall be taken down in that`
  line language;
  line
  line `(b) if he gives evidence in any other language, it may, if practicable, be taken down in that language,`
  line `and if it is not practicable to do so, a true translation of the evidence in the language of the Court shall`
  line `be prepared as the examination of the witness proceeds, signed by the Magistrate or presiding Judge,`
  line `and shall form part of the record;`
  line
  line `(c) where under clause (b) evidence is taken down in a language other than the language of the`
  line `Court, a true translation thereof in the language of the Court shall be prepared as soon as practicable,`
  line `signed by the Magistrate or presiding Judge, and shall form part of the record:`
  line
  line `Provided that when under clause (b) evidence is taken down in English and a translation thereof in`
  line `the language of the Court is not required by any of the parties, the Court may dispense with such`
  line translation.
obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_313:
  sectionId (91299)
  sectionNo (313)
  orderNo 313
  title `Procedure in regard to such evidence when completed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_313_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91299&sectionno=313&orderno=313&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_313_content:
  string
  line `(1) As the evidence of each witness`
  line `taken under section 310 or section 311 is completed, it shall be read over to him in the presence of the`
  line `accused, if in attendance, or of his advocate, if he appears by an advocate, and shall, if necessary, be`
  line corrected.
  line
  line `(2) If the witness denies the correctness of any part of the evidence when the same is read over to him,`
  line `the Magistrate or presiding Judge may, instead of correcting the evidence, make a memorandum thereon of`
  line `the objection made to it by the witness and shall add such remarks as he thinks necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) If the record of the evidence is in a language different from that in which it has been given and the`
  line `witness does not understand that language, the record shall be interpreted to him in the language in which`
  line `it was given, or in a language which he understands.`
obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_314:
  sectionId (91300)
  sectionNo (314)
  orderNo 314
  title `Interpretation of evidence to accused or his advocate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_314_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_314_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91300&sectionno=314&orderno=314&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_314_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any evidence is given in`
  line `a language not understood by the accused, and he is present in Court in person, it shall be interpreted to him`
  line `in open Court in a language understood by him.`
  line
  line `(2) If he appears by an advocate and the evidence is given in a language other than the language of the`
  line `Court, and not understood by the advocate, it shall be interpreted to such advocate in that language.`
  line
  line `(3) When documents are put for the purpose of formal proof, it shall be in the discretion of the Court`
  line `to interpret as much thereof as appears necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_314_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_315:
  sectionId (91301)
  sectionNo (315)
  orderNo 315
  title `Remarks respecting demeanour of witness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_315_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91301&sectionno=315&orderno=315&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_315_content:
  string
  line `When a presiding Judge or Magistrate has`
  line `recorded the evidence of a witness, he shall also record such remarks (if any) as he thinks material`
  line `respecting the demeanour of such witness whilst under examination.`
obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_316:
  sectionId (91302)
  sectionNo (316)
  orderNo 316
  title `Record of examination of accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_316_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91302&sectionno=316&orderno=316&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_316_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the accused is examined by any Magistrate,`
  line `or by a Court of Session, the whole of such examination, including every question put to him and every`
  line `answer given by him, shall be recorded in full by the presiding Judge or Magistrate himself or where he is`
  line `unable to do so owing to a physical or other incapacity, under his direction and superintendence by an`
  line `officer of the Court appointed by him in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The record shall, if practicable, be in the language in which the accused is examined or, if that is`
  line `not practicable, in the language of the Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The record shall be shown or read to the accused, or, if he does not understand the language in`
  line `which it is written, shall be interpreted to him in a language which he understands, and he shall be at liberty`
  line `to explain or add to his answers.`
  line
  line `(4) It shall thereafter be signed by the accused and by the Magistrate or presiding Judge, who shall`
  line `certify under his own hand that the examination was taken in his presence and hearing and that the record`
  line `contains a full and true account of the statement made by the accused:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the accused is in custody and is examined through electronic communication, his`
  line `signature shall be taken within seventy-two hours of such examination.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to apply to the examination of an accused person in the`
  line `course of a summary trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_317:
  sectionId (91559)
  sectionNo (317)
  orderNo 317
  title `Interpreter to be bound to interpret truthfully.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_317_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91559&sectionno=317&orderno=317&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_317_content:
  string
  line `When the services of an interpreter are`
  line `required by any Criminal Court for the interpretation of any evidence or statement, he shall be bound to`
  line `state the true interpretation of such evidence or statement.`
obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_318:
  sectionId (91560)
  sectionNo (318)
  orderNo 318
  title `Record in High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_318_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91560&sectionno=318&orderno=318&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_318_content:
  string
  line `Every High Court may, by general rule, prescribe the manner in which`
  line `the evidence of witnesses and the examination of the accused shall be taken down in cases coming before`
  line `it, and such evidence and examination shall be taken down in accordance with such rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_319:
  sectionId (91561)
  sectionNo (319)
  orderNo 319
  title `When attendance of witness may be dispensed with and commission issued.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_319_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91561&sectionno=319&orderno=319&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_319_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever,`
  line `in the course of any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita, it appears to a Court or Magistrate`
  line `that the examination of a witness is necessary for the ends of justice, and that the attendance of such witness`
  line `cannot be procured without an amount of delay, expense or inconvenience which, under the circumstances`
  line `of the case, would be unreasonable, the Court or Magistrate may dispense with such attendance and may`
  line `issue a commission for the examination of the witness in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the examination of the President or the Vice-President of India or the Governor of`
  line `a State or the Administrator of a Union territory as a witness is necessary for the ends of justice, a`
  line `commission shall be issued for the examination of such a witness.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may, when issuing a commission for the examination of a witness for the prosecution,`
  line `direct that such amount as the Court considers reasonable to meet the expenses of the accused, including`
  line `the advocate's fees, be paid by the prosecution.`
obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_320:
  sectionId (91305)
  sectionNo (320)
  orderNo 320
  title `Commission to whom to be issued.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_320_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91305&sectionno=320&orderno=320&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_320_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the witness is within the territories to which this`
  line `Sanhita extends, the commission shall be directed to the Chief Judicial Magistrate within whose local`
  line `jurisdiction the witness is to be found.`
  line
  line `(2) If the witness is in India, but in a State or an area to which this Sanhita does not extend, the`
  line `commission shall be directed to such Court or officer as the Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) If the witness is in a country or place outside India and arrangements have been made by the Central`
  line `Government with the Government of such country or place for taking the evidence of witnesses in relation`
  line `to criminal matters, the commission shall be issued in such form, directed to such Court or officer, and sent`
  line `to such authority for transmission as the Central Government may, by notification, prescribe in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_321:
  sectionId (91306)
  sectionNo (321)
  orderNo 321
  title `Execution of commissions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_321_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91306&sectionno=321&orderno=321&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_321_content:
  string
  line `Upon receipt of the commission, the Chief Judicial Magistrate or`
  line `such Magistrate as he may appoint in this behalf, shall summon the witness before him or proceed to the`
  line `place where the witness is, and shall take down his evidence in the same manner, and may for this purpose`
  line `exercise the same powers, as in trials of warrant-cases under this Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_322:
  sectionId (91307)
  sectionNo (322)
  orderNo 322
  title `Parties may examine witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_322_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91307&sectionno=322&orderno=322&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_322_content:
  string
  line `(1) The parties to any proceeding under this Sanhita in which`
  line `a commission is issued may respectively forward any interrogatories in writing which the Court or`
  line `Magistrate directing the commission may think relevant to the issue, and it shall be lawful for the`
  line `Magistrate, Court or officer to whom the commission, is directed, or to whom the duty of executing it is`
  line `delegated, to examine the witness upon such interrogatories.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such party may appear before such Magistrate, Court or Officer by an advocate, or if not in`
  line `custody, in person, and may examine, cross-examine and re-examine the said witness.`
obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_323:
  sectionId (91308)
  sectionNo (323)
  orderNo 323
  title `Return of commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_323_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91308&sectionno=323&orderno=323&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_323_content:
  string
  line `(1) After any commission issued under section 319 has been duly`
  line `executed, it shall be returned, together with the deposition of the witness examined thereunder, to the Court`
  line `or Magistrate issuing the commission; and the commission, the return thereto and the deposition shall be`
  line `open at all reasonable times to inspection of the parties, and may, subject to all just exceptions, be read in`
  line `evidence in the case by either party, and shall form part of the record.`
  line
  line `(2) Any deposition so taken, if it satisfies the conditions specified by section 27 of the Bharatiya`
  line `Sakshya Adhiniyam, 2023, may also be received in evidence at any subsequent stage of the case before`
  line `another Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_324:
  sectionId (91309)
  sectionNo (324)
  orderNo 324
  title `Adjournment of proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_324_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91309&sectionno=324&orderno=324&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_324_content:
  string
  line `In every case in which a commission is issued under section 319,`
  line `the inquiry, trial or other proceeding may be adjourned for a specified time reasonably sufficient for the`
  line `execution and return of the commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_325:
  sectionId (91310)
  sectionNo (325)
  orderNo 325
  title `Execution of foreign commissions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_325_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91310&sectionno=325&orderno=325&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_325_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of section 321 and so much of section`
  line `322 and section 323 as relate to the execution of a commission and its return shall apply in respect of`
  line `commissions issued by any of the Courts, Judges or Magistrates hereinafter mentioned as they apply to`
  line `commissions issued under section 319.`
  line
  line `(2) The Courts, Judges and Magistrates referred to in sub-section (1) are---`
  line
  line `(a) any such Court, Judge or Magistrate exercising jurisdiction within an area in India to which this`
  line `Sanhita does not extend, as the Central Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) any Court, Judge or Magistrate exercising jurisdiction in any such country or place outside`
  line `India, as the Central Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf, and having authority,`
  line `under the law in force in that country or place, to issue commissions for the examination of witnesses`
  line `in relation to criminal matters.`
obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_326:
  sectionId (91311)
  sectionNo (326)
  orderNo 326
  title `Deposition of medical witness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_326_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91311&sectionno=326&orderno=326&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_326_content:
  string
  line `(1) The deposition of a civil surgeon or other medical witness,`
  line `taken and attested by a Magistrate in the presence of the accused, or taken on commission under this`
  line `Chapter, may be given in evidence in any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita, although the`
  line `deponent is not called as a witness.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may, if it thinks fit, and shall, on the application of the prosecution or the accused,`
  line `summon and examine any such deponent as to the subject-matter of his deposition.`
obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_327:
  sectionId (91312)
  sectionNo (327)
  orderNo 327
  title `Identification report of Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_327_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91312&sectionno=327&orderno=327&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_327_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any document purporting to be a report of`
  line `identification under the hand of an Executive Magistrate in respect of a person or property may be used as`
  line `evidence in any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita, although such Magistrate is not called`
  line `as a witness:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such report contains a statement of any suspect or witness to which the provisions`
  line `of section 19, section 26, section 27, section 158 or section 160 of the Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam, 2023,`
  line `apply, such statement shall not be used under this sub-section except in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `those sections.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may, if it thinks fit, and shall, on the application of the prosecution or of the accused,`
  line `summon and examine such Magistrate as to the subject-matter of the said report.`
obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_328:
  sectionId (91313)
  sectionNo (328)
  orderNo 328
  title `Evidence of officers of Mint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_328_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91313&sectionno=328&orderno=328&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_328_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any document purporting to be a report under the hand of a`
  line `gazetted officer of any Mint or of any Note Printing Press or of any Security Printing Press (including the`
  line `officer of the Controller of Stamps and Stationery) or of any Forensic Department or Division of Forensic`
  line `Science Laboratory or any Government Examiner of Questioned Documents or any State Examiner of`
  line `Questioned Documents as the Central Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf, upon any`
  line `matter or thing duly submitted to him for examination and report in the course of any proceeding under this`
  line `Sanhita, may be used as evidence in any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita, although such`
  line `officer is not called as a witness.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may, if it thinks fit, summon and examine any such officer as to the subject-matter of his`
  line `report:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such officer shall be summoned to produce any records on which the report is based.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sections 129 and 130 of the Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam,`
  line `2023, no such officer shall, except with the permission of the General Manager or any officer in charge of`
  line `any Mint or of any Note Printing Press or of any Security Printing Press or of any Forensic Department or`
  line `any officer in charge of the Forensic Science Laboratory or of the Government Examiner of Questioned`
  line `Documents Organisation or of the State Examiner of Questioned Documents Organisation be permitted---`
  line
  line `(a) to give any evidence derived from any unpublished official records on which the report is based;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) to disclose the nature or particulars of any test applied by him in the course of the examination`
  line `of the matter or thing.`
obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_329:
  sectionId (91314)
  sectionNo (329)
  orderNo 329
  title `Reports of certain Government scientific experts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_329_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91314&sectionno=329&orderno=329&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_329_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any document purporting to be a report`
  line `under the hand of a Government scientific expert to whom this section applies, upon any matter or thing`
  line `duly submitted to him for examination or analysis and report in the course of any proceeding under this`
  line `Sanhita, may be used as evidence in any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may, if it thinks fit, summon and examine any such expert as to the subject-matter of his`
  line report.
  line
  line `(3) Where any such expert is summoned by a Court, and he is unable to attend personally, he may,`
  line `unless the Court has expressly directed him to appear personally, depute any responsible officer working`
  line `with him to attend the Court, if such officer is conversant with the facts of the case and can satisfactorily`
  line `depose in Court on his behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) This section applies to the following Government scientific experts, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) any Chemical Examiner or Assistant Chemical Examiner to Government;`
  line
  line `(b) the Chief Controller of Explosives;`
  line
  line `(c) the Director of the Finger Print Bureau;`
  line
  line `(d) the Director, Haffkeine Institute, Bombay;`
  line
  line `(e) the Director, Deputy Director or Assistant Director of a Central Forensic Science Laboratory`
  line `or a State Forensic Science Laboratory;`
  line
  line `(f) the Serologist to the Government;`
  line
  line `(g) any other scientific expert specified or certified, by notification, by the State Government or`
  line `the Central Government for this purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_330:
  sectionId (91315)
  sectionNo (330)
  orderNo 330
  title `No formal proof of certain documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_330_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91315&sectionno=330&orderno=330&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_330_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any document is filed before any Court by`
  line `the prosecution or the accused, the particulars of every such document shall be included in a list and the`
  line `prosecution or the accused or the advocate for the prosecution or the accused, if any, shall be called upon`
  line `to admit or deny the genuineness of each such document soon after supply of such documents and in no`
  line `case later than thirty days after such supply:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, in its discretion, relax the time limit with reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no expert shall be called to appear before the Court unless the report of such expert`
  line `is disputed by any of the parties to the trial.`
  line
  line `(2) The list of documents shall be in such form as the State Government may, by rules, provide.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the genuineness of any document is not disputed, such document may be read in evidence in`
  line `any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita without proof of the signature of the person by`
  line `whom it purports to be signed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, in its discretion, require such signature to be proved.`
obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_331:
  sectionId (91316)
  sectionNo (331)
  orderNo 331
  title `Affidavit in proof of conduct of public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_331_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91316&sectionno=331&orderno=331&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_331_content:
  string
  line `When any application is made to any Court`
  line `in the course of any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita, and allegations are made therein`
  line `respecting any public servant, the applicant may give evidence of the facts alleged in the application by`
  line `affidavit, and the Court may, if it thinks fit, order that evidence relating to such facts be so given.`
obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_332:
  sectionId (91317)
  sectionNo (332)
  orderNo 332
  title `Evidence of formal character on affidavit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_332_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91317&sectionno=332&orderno=332&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_332_content:
  string
  line `(1) The evidence of any person whose evidence is`
  line `of a formal character may be given by affidavit and may, subject to all just exceptions, be read in evidence`
  line `in any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may, if it thinks fit, and shall, on the application of the prosecution or the accused,`
  line `summon and examine any such person as to the facts contained in his affidavit.`
obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_333:
  sectionId (91318)
  sectionNo (333)
  orderNo 333
  title `Authorities before whom affidavits may be sworn.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_333_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91318&sectionno=333&orderno=333&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_333_content:
  string
  line `(1) Affidavits to be used before any Court`
  line `under this Sanhita may be sworn or affirmed before---`
  line
  line `(a) any Judge or Judicial or Executive Magistrate; or`
  line
  line `(b) any Commissioner of Oaths appointed by a High Court or Court of Session; or`
  line
  line `(c) any notary appointed under the Notaries Act, 1952 (53 of 1952).`
  line
  line `(2) Affidavits shall be confined to, and shall state separately, such facts as the deponent is able to prove`
  line `from his own knowledge and such facts as he has reasonable ground to believe to be true, and in the latter`
  line `case, the deponent shall clearly state the grounds of such belief.`
  line
  line `(3) The Court may order any scandalous and irrelevant matter in the affidavit to be struck out or`
  line amended.
obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_334:
  sectionId (91319)
  sectionNo (334)
  orderNo 334
  title `Previous conviction or acquittal how proved.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_334_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91319&sectionno=334&orderno=334&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_334_content:
  string
  line `In any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under`
  line `this Sanhita, a previous conviction or acquittal may be proved, in addition to any other mode provided by`
  line `any law for the time being in force,---`
  line
  line `(a) by an extract certified under the hand of the officer having the custody of the records of the`
  line `Court in which such conviction or acquittal was held, to be a copy of the sentence or order; or`
  line
  line `(b) in case of a conviction, either by a certificate signed by the officer in charge of the jail in which`
  line `the punishment or any part thereof was undergone, or by production of the warrant of commitment`
  line `under which the punishment was suffered, together with, in each of such cases, evidence as to the`
  line `identity of the accused person with the person so convicted or acquitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_335:
  sectionId (91320)
  sectionNo (335)
  orderNo 335
  title `Record of evidence in absence of accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_335_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91320&sectionno=335&orderno=335&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_335_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it is proved that an accused person has`
  line `absconded, and that there is no immediate prospect of arresting him, the Court competent to try, or commit`
  line `for trial, such person for the offence complained of may, in his absence, examine the witnesses (if any)`
  line `produced on behalf of the prosecution, and record their depositions and any such deposition may, on the`
  line `arrest of such person, be given in evidence against him on the inquiry into, or trial for, the offence with`
  line `which he is charged, if the deponent is dead or incapable of giving evidence or cannot be found or his`
  line `presence cannot be procured without an amount of delay, expense or inconvenience which, under the`
  line `circumstances of the case, would be unreasonable.`
  line
  line `(2) If it appears that an offence punishable with death or imprisonment for life has been committed by`
  line `some person or persons unknown, the High Court or the Sessions Judge may direct that any Magistrate of`
  line `the first class shall hold an inquiry and examine any witnesses who can give evidence concerning the`
  line `offence and any depositions so taken may be given in evidence against any person who is subsequently`
  line `accused of the offence, if the deponent is dead or incapable of giving evidence or beyond the limits of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_336:
  sectionId (91321)
  sectionNo (336)
  orderNo 336
  title `Evidence of public servants, experts, police officers in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_336_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91321&sectionno=336&orderno=336&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_336_content:
  string
  line `Where any document`
  line `or report prepared by a public servant, scientific expert or medical officer is purported to be used as evidence`
  line `in any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita, and---`
  line
  line `(i) such public servant, expert or officer is either transferred, retired, or died; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such public servant, expert or officer cannot be found or is incapable of giving deposition; or`
  line
  line `(iii) securing presence of such public servant, expert or officer is likely to cause delay in holding`
  line `the inquiry, trial or other proceeding, the Court shall secure presence of successor officer of such public`
  line `servant, expert, or officer who is holding that post at the time of such deposition to give deposition on`
  line `such document or report:`
  line
  line `Provided that no public servant, scientific expert or medical officer shall be called to appear before the`
  line `Court unless the report of such public servant, scientific expert or medical officer is disputed by any of the`
  line `parties of the trial or other proceedings:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the deposition of such successor public servant, expert or officer may be allowed`
  line `through audio-video electronic means.`
obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_337:
  sectionId (91322)
  sectionNo (337)
  orderNo 337
  title `Person once convicted or acquitted not to be tried for same offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_337_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91322&sectionno=337&orderno=337&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_337_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person who has`
  line `once been tried by a Court of competent jurisdiction for an offence and convicted or acquitted of such`
  line `offence shall, while such conviction or acquittal remains in force, not be liable to be tried again for the same`
  line `offence, nor on the same facts for any other offence for which a different charge from the one made against`
  line `him might have been made under sub-section (1) of section 244, or for which he might have been convicted`
  line `under sub-section (2) thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) A person acquitted or convicted of any offence may be afterwards tried, with the consent of the`
  line `State Government, for any distinct offence for which a separate charge might have been made against him`
  line `at the former trial under sub-section (1) of section 243.`
  line
  line `(3) A person convicted of any offence constituted by any act causing consequences which, together`
  line `with such act, constituted a different offence from that of which he was convicted, may be afterwards tried`
  line `for such last-mentioned offence, if the consequences had not happened, or were not known to the Court to`
  line `have happened, at the time when he was convicted.`
  line
  line `(4) A person acquitted or convicted of any offence constituted by any acts may, notwithstanding such`
  line `acquittal or conviction, be subsequently charged with, and tried for, any other offence constituted by the`
  line `same acts which he may have committed if the Court by which he was first tried was not competent to try`
  line `the offence with which he is subsequently charged.`
  line
  line `(5) A person discharged under section 281 shall not be tried again for the same offence except with the`
  line `consent of the Court by which he was discharged or of any other Court to which the first-mentioned Court`
  line `is subordinate.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in this section shall affect the provisions of section 26 of the General Clauses Act, 1897`
  line `(10 of 1897) or of section 208 of this Sanhita.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The dismissal of a complaint, or the discharge of the accused, is not an acquittal for the`
  line `purposes of this section.`
  line
  line Illustrations.
  line
  line `(a) A is tried upon a charge of theft as a servant and acquitted. He cannot afterwards, while the acquittal`
  line `remains in force, be charged with theft as a servant, or, upon the same facts, with theft simply, or with`
  line `criminal breach of trust.`
  line
  line `(b) A is tried for causing grievous hurt and convicted. The person injured afterwards dies. A may be`
  line `tried again for culpable homicide.`
  line
  line `(c) A is charged before the Court of Session and convicted of the culpable homicide of B. A may not`
  line `afterwards be tried on the same facts for the murder of B.`
  line
  line `(d) A is charged by a Magistrate of the first class with, and convicted by him of, voluntarily causing`
  line `hurt to B. A may not afterwards be tried for voluntarily causing grievous hurt to B on the same facts, unless`
  line `the case comes within sub-section (3) of this section.`
  line
  line `(e) A is charged by a Magistrate of the second class with, and convicted by him of, theft of property`
  line `from the person of B. A may subsequently be charged with, and tried for, robbery on the same facts.`
  line
  line `(f) A, B and C are charged by a Magistrate of the first class with, and convicted by him of, robbing D.`
  line `A, B and C may afterwards be charged with, and tried for, dacoity on the same facts.`
obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_338:
  sectionId (91323)
  sectionNo (338)
  orderNo 338
  title `Appearance by Public Prosecutors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_338_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91323&sectionno=338&orderno=338&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_338_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Public Prosecutor or Assistant Public Prosecutor`
  line `in charge of a case may appear and plead without any written authority before any Court in which that case`
  line `is under inquiry, trial or appeal.`
  line
  line `(2) If in any such case any private person instructs his advocate to prosecute any person in any Court,`
  line `the Public Prosecutor or Assistant Public Prosecutor in charge of the case shall conduct the prosecution,`
  line `and the advocate so instructed shall act therein under the directions of the Public Prosecutor or Assistant`
  line `Public Prosecutor, and may, with the permission of the Court, submit written arguments after the evidence`
  line `is closed in the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_339:
  sectionId (91324)
  sectionNo (339)
  orderNo 339
  title `Permission to conduct prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_339_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91324&sectionno=339&orderno=339&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_339_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Magistrate inquiring into or trying a case may`
  line `permit the prosecution to be conducted by any person other than a police officer below the rank of inspector;`
  line `but no person, other than the Advocate-General or Government Advocate or a Public Prosecutor or`
  line `Assistant Public Prosecutor, shall be entitled to do so without such permission:`
  line
  line `Provided that no police officer shall be permitted to conduct the prosecution if he has taken part in the`
  line `investigation into the offence with respect to which the accused is being prosecuted.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person conducting the prosecution may do so personally or by an advocate.`
obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_340:
  sectionId (91325)
  sectionNo (340)
  orderNo 340
  title `Right of person against whom proceedings are instituted to be defended.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_340_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91325&sectionno=340&orderno=340&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_340_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `accused of an offence before a Criminal Court, or against whom proceedings are instituted under this`
  line `Sanhita, may of right be defended by an advocate of his choice.`
obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_341:
  sectionId (91326)
  sectionNo (341)
  orderNo 341
  title `Legal aid to accused at State expense in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_341_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91326&sectionno=341&orderno=341&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_341_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in a trial or appeal before a`
  line `Court, the accused is not represented by an advocate, and where it appears to the Court that the accused has`
  line `not sufficient means to engage an advocate, the Court shall assign an advocate for his defence at the expense`
  line `of the State.`
  line
  line `(2)The High Court may, with the previous approval of the State Government, make rules providing`
  line for---
  line
  line `(a) the mode of selecting advocates for defence under sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) the facilities to be allowed to such advocates by the Courts;`
  line
  line `(c) the fees payable to such advocates by the Government, and generally, for carrying out the`
  line `purposes of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, by notification, direct that, as from such date as may be specified in`
  line `the notification, the provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) shall apply in relation to any class of trials before`
  line `other Courts in the State as they apply in relation to trials before Courts of Session.`
obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_342:
  sectionId (91327)
  sectionNo (342)
  orderNo 342
  title `Procedure when corporation or registered society is an accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_342_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91327&sectionno=342&orderno=342&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_342_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this`
  line `section, "corporation" means an incorporated company or other body corporate, and includes a society`
  line `registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(2) Where a corporation is the accused person or one of the accused persons in an inquiry or trial, it`
  line `may appoint a representative for the purpose of the inquiry or trial and such appointment need not be under`
  line `the seal of the corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a representative of a corporation appears, any requirement of this Sanhita that anything shall`
  line `be done in the presence of the accused or shall be read or stated or explained to the accused, shall be`
  line `construed as a requirement that that thing shall be done in the presence of the representative or read or`
  line `stated or explained to the representative, and any requirement that the accused shall be examined shall be`
  line `construed as a requirement that the representative shall be examined.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a representative of a corporation does not appear, any such requirement as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) shall not apply.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a statement in writing purporting to be signed by the managing director of the corporation`
  line `or by any person duly authorised by him (by whatever name called) having, or being one of the persons`
  line `having the management of the affairs of the corporation to the effect that the person named in the statement`
  line `has been appointed as the representative of the corporation for the purposes of this section, is filed, the`
  line `Court shall, unless the contrary is proved, presume that such person has been so appointed.`
  line
  line `(6) If a question arises as to whether any person, appearing as the representative of a corporation in an`
  line `inquiry or trial before a Court is or is not such representative, the question shall be determined by the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_343:
  sectionId (91328)
  sectionNo (343)
  orderNo 343
  title `Tender of pardon to accomplice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_343_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91328&sectionno=343&orderno=343&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_343_content:
  string
  line `(1) With a view to obtaining the evidence of any person`
  line `supposed to have been directly or indirectly concerned in or privy to an offence to which this section applies,`
  line `the Chief Judicial Magistrate at any stage of the investigation or inquiry into, or the trial of, the offence,`
  line `and the Magistrate of the first class inquiring into or trying the offence, at any stage of the inquiry or trial,`
  line `may tender a pardon to such person on condition of his making a full and true disclosure of the whole of`
  line `the circumstances within his knowledge relative to the offence and to every other person concerned,`
  line `whether as principal or abettor, in the commission thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) This section applies to---`
  line
  line `(a) any offence triable exclusively by the Court of Session or by the Court of a Special Judge`
  line `appointed under any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) any offence punishable with imprisonment which may extend to seven years or with a more`
  line `severe sentence.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Magistrate who tenders a pardon under sub-section (1) shall record—`
  line
  line `(a) his reasons for so doing;`
  line
  line `(b) whether the tender was or was not accepted by the person to whom it was made, and shall, on`
  line `application made by the accused, furnish him with a copy of such record free of cost.`
  line
  line `(4) Every person accepting a tender of pardon made under sub-section (1)---`
  line
  line `(a) shall be examined as a witness in the Court of the Magistrate taking cognizance of the offence`
  line `and in the subsequent trial, if any;`
  line
  line `(b) shall, unless he is already on bail, be detained in custody until the termination of the trial.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a person has accepted a tender of pardon made under sub-section (1) and has been examined`
  line `under sub-section (4), the Magistrate taking cognizance of the offence shall, without making any further`
  line `inquiry in the case---`
  line
  line `(a) commit it for trial---`
  line
  line `(i) to the Court of Session if the offence is triable exclusively by that Court or if the Magistrate`
  line `taking cognizance is the Chief Judicial Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(ii) to a Court of Special Judge appointed under any other law for the time being in force, if the`
  line `offence is triable exclusively by that Court;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, make over the case to the Chief Judicial Magistrate who shall try the case`
  line himself.
obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_344:
  sectionId (91329)
  sectionNo (344)
  orderNo 344
  title `Power to direct tender of pardon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_344_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91329&sectionno=344&orderno=344&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_344_content:
  string
  line `At any time after commitment of a case but before judgment`
  line `is passed, the Court to which the commitment is made may, with a view to obtaining at the trial the evidence`
  line `of any person supposed to have been directly or indirectly concerned in, or privy to, any such offence,`
  line `tender a pardon on the same condition to such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_345:
  sectionId (91330)
  sectionNo (345)
  orderNo 345
  title `Trial of person not complying with conditions of pardon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_345_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91330&sectionno=345&orderno=345&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_345_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in regard to a person`
  line `who has accepted a tender of pardon made under section 343 or section 344, the Public Prosecutor certifies`
  line `that in his opinion such person has, either by wilfully concealing anything essential or by giving false`
  line `evidence, not complied with the condition on which the tender was made, such person may be tried for the`
  line `offence in respect of which the pardon was so tendered or for any other offence of which he appears to have`
  line `been guilty in connection with the same matter, and also for the offence of giving false evidence:`
  line
  line `Provided that such person shall not be tried jointly with any of the other accused:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such person shall not be tried for the offence of giving false evidence except with`
  line `the sanction of the High Court, and nothing contained in section 215 or section 379 shall apply to that`
  line offence.
  line
  line `(2) Any statement made by such person accepting the tender of pardon and recorded by a Magistrate`
  line `under section 183 or by a Court under sub-section (4) of section 343 may be given in evidence against him`
  line `at such trial.`
  line
  line `(3) At such trial, the accused shall be entitled to plead that he has complied with the condition upon`
  line `which such tender was made; in which case it shall be for the prosecution to prove that the condition has`
  line `not been complied with.`
  line
  line `(4) At such trial, the Court shall---`
  line
  line `(a) if it is a Court of Session, before the charge is read out and explained to the accused;`
  line
  line `(b) if it is the Court of a Magistrate, before the evidence of the witnesses for the prosecution is`
  line taken,
  line
  line `ask the accused whether he pleads that he has complied with the conditions on which the tender of pardon`
  line `was made.`
  line
  line `(5) If the accused does so plead, the Court shall record the plea and proceed with the trial and it shall,`
  line `before passing judgment in the case, find whether or not the accused has complied with the conditions of`
  line `the pardon, and, if it finds that he has so complied, it shall, notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Sanhita, pass judgment of acquittal.`
obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_346:
  sectionId (91331)
  sectionNo (346)
  orderNo 346
  title `Power to postpone or adjourn proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_346_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91331&sectionno=346&orderno=346&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_346_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every inquiry or trial the proceedings shall`
  line `be continued from day-to-day basis until all the witnesses in attendance have been examined, unless the`
  line `Court finds the adjournment of the same beyond the following day to be necessary for reasons to be`
  line `recorded:`
  line
  line `Provided that when the inquiry or trial relates to an offence under section 64, section 65, section 66,`
  line `section 67, section 68, section 70 or section 71 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) the`
  line `inquiry or trial shall be completed within a period of two months from the date of filing of the chargesheet.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Court, after taking cognizance of an offence, or commencement of trial, finds it necessary or`
  line `advisable to postpone the commencement of, or adjourn, any inquiry or trial, it may, from time to time, for`
  line `reasons to be recorded, postpone or adjourn the same on such terms as it thinks fit, for such time as it`
  line `considers reasonable, and may by a warrant remand the accused if in custody:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Court shall remand an accused person to custody under this section for a term`
  line `exceeding fifteen days at a time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that when witnesses are in attendance, no adjournment or postponement shall be`
  line `granted, without examining them, except for special reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no adjournment shall be granted for the purpose only of enabling the accused person`
  line `to show cause against the sentence proposed to be imposed on him:`
  line
  line `Provided also that---`
  line
  line `(a) no adjournment shall be granted at the request of a party, except where the circumstances are`
  line `beyond the control of that party;`
  line
  line `(b) where the circumstances are beyond the control of a party, not more than two adjournments`
  line `may be granted by the Court after hearing the objections of the other party and for the reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing;`
  line
  line `(c) the fact that the advocate of a party is engaged in another Court, shall not be a ground for`
  line adjournment;
  line
  line `(d) where a witness is present in Court but a party or his advocate is not present or the party or his`
  line `advocate though present in Court, is not ready to examine or cross-examine the witness, the Court may,`
  line `if thinks fit, record the statement of the witness and pass such orders as it thinks fit dispensing with the`
  line `examination-in-chief or cross-examination of the witness, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—If sufficient evidence has been obtained to raise a suspicion that the accused may have`
  line `committed an offence, and it appears likely that further evidence may be obtained by a remand, this is a`
  line `reasonable cause for a remand.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—The terms on which an adjournment or postponement may be granted include, in`
  line `appropriate cases, the payment of costs by the prosecution or the accused.`
obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_347:
  sectionId (91332)
  sectionNo (347)
  orderNo 347
  title `Local inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91332&sectionno=347&orderno=347&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_347_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Judge or Magistrate may, at any stage of any inquiry, trial or other`
  line `proceeding, after due notice to the parties, visit and inspect any place in which an offence is alleged to have`
  line `been committed, or any other place which it is in his opinion necessary to view for the purpose of properly`
  line `appreciating the evidence given at such inquiry or trial, and shall without unnecessary delay record a`
  line `memorandum of any relevant facts observed at such inspection.`
  line
  line `(2) Such memorandum shall form part of the record of the case and if the prosecutor, complainant or`
  line `accused or any other party to the case, so desires, a copy of the memorandum shall be furnished to him free`
  line `of cost.`
obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_348:
  sectionId (91333)
  sectionNo (348)
  orderNo 348
  title `Power to summon material witness, or examine person present.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_348_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91333&sectionno=348&orderno=348&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_348_content:
  string
  line `Any Court may, at any stage`
  line `of any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under this Sanhita, summon any person as a witness, or examine`
  line `any person in attendance, though not summoned as a witness, or re-call and re-examine any person already`
  line `examined; and the Court shall summon and examine or re-call and re-examine any such person if his`
  line `evidence appears to it to be essential to the just decision of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_349:
  sectionId (91334)
  sectionNo (349)
  orderNo 349
  title `Power of Magistrate to order person to give specimen signatures or handwriting, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_349_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91334&sectionno=349&orderno=349&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_349_content:
  string
  line `If a`
  line `Magistrate of the first class is satisfied that, for the purposes of any investigation or proceeding under this`
  line `Sanhita, it is expedient to direct any person, including an accused person, to give specimen signatures or`
  line `finger impressions or handwriting or voice sample, he may make an order to that effect and in that case the`
  line `person to whom the order relates shall be produced or shall attend at the time and place specified in such`
  line `order and shall give his specimen signatures or finger impressions or handwriting or voice sample:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section unless the person has at some time been arrested`
  line `in connection with such investigation or proceeding:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Magistrate may, for the reasons to be recorded in writing, order any person to`
  line `give such specimen or sample without him being arrested.`
obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_350:
  sectionId (91335)
  sectionNo (350)
  orderNo 350
  title `Expenses of complainants and witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_350_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91335&sectionno=350&orderno=350&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_350_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made by the State Government,`
  line `any Criminal Court may, if it thinks fit, order payment, on the part of the Government, of the reasonable`
  line `expenses of any complainant or witness attending for the purposes of any inquiry, trial or other proceeding`
  line `before such Court under this Sanhita.`
obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_351:
  sectionId (91336)
  sectionNo (351)
  orderNo 351
  title `Power to examine accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_351_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91336&sectionno=351&orderno=351&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_351_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every inquiry or trial, for the purpose of enabling the accused`
  line `personally to explain any circumstances appearing in the evidence against him, the Court----`
  line
  line `(a) may at any stage, without previously warning the accused put such questions to him as the`
  line `Court considers necessary;`
  line
  line `(b) shall, after the witnesses for the prosecution have been examined and before he is called on`
  line `for his defence, question him generally on the case:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a summons case, where the Court has dispensed with the personal attendance of`
  line `the accused, it may also dispense with his examination under clause (b).`
  line
  line `(2) No oath shall be administered to the accused when he is examined under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The accused shall not render himself liable to punishment by refusing to answer such questions, or`
  line `by giving false answers to them.`
  line
  line `(4) The answers given by the accused may be taken into consideration in such inquiry or trial, and put`
  line `in evidence for or against him in any other inquiry into, or trial for, any other offence which such answers`
  line `may tend to show he has committed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Court may take help of Prosecutor and Defence Counsel in preparing relevant questions which`
  line `are to be put to the accused and the Court may permit filing of written statement by the accused as sufficient`
  line `compliance of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_352:
  sectionId (91337)
  sectionNo (352)
  orderNo 352
  title `Oral arguments and memorandum of arguments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_352_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91337&sectionno=352&orderno=352&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_352_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any party to a proceeding may, as soon`
  line `as may be, after the close of his evidence, address concise oral arguments, and may, before he concludes`
  line `the oral arguments, if any, submit a memorandum to the Court setting forth concisely and under distinct`
  line `headings, the arguments in support of his case and every such memorandum shall form part of the record.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every such memorandum shall be simultaneously furnished to the opposite party.`
  line
  line `(3) No adjournment of the proceedings shall be granted for the purpose of filing the written arguments`
  line `unless the Court, for reasons to be recorded in writing, considers it necessary to grant such adjournment.`
  line
  line `(4) The Court may, if it is of opinion that the oral arguments are not concise or relevant, regulate such`
  line arguments.
obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_353:
  sectionId (91338)
  sectionNo (353)
  orderNo 353
  title `Accused person to be competent witness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_353_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91338&sectionno=353&orderno=353&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_353_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person accused of an offence before a`
  line `Criminal Court shall be a competent witness for the defence and may give evidence on oath in disproof of`
  line `the charges made against him or any person charged together with him at the same trial:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) he shall not be called as a witness except on his own request in writing;`
  line
  line `(b) his failure to give evidence shall not be made the subject of any comment by any of the parties`
  line `or the Court or give rise to any presumption against himself or any person charged together with him`
  line `at the same trial.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person against whom proceedings are instituted in any Criminal Court under section 101, or`
  line `section 126, or section 127, or section 128, or section 129, or under Chapter X or under Part B, Part C or`
  line `Part D of Chapter XI, may offer himself as a witness in such proceedings:`
  line
  line `Provided that in proceedings under section 127, section 128, or section 129, the failure of such person`
  line `to give evidence shall not be made the subject of any comment by any of the parties or the Court or give`
  line `rise to any presumption against him or any other person proceeded against together with him at the same`
  line inquiry.
obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_354:
  sectionId (91339)
  sectionNo (354)
  orderNo 354
  title `No influence to be used to induce disclosure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_354_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91339&sectionno=354&orderno=354&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_354_content:
  string
  line `Except as provided in sections 343 and 344, no`
  line `influence, by means of any promise or threat or otherwise, shall be used to an accused person to induce`
  line `him to disclose or withhold any matter within his knowledge.`
obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_355:
  sectionId (91340)
  sectionNo (355)
  orderNo 355
  title `Provision for inquiries and trial being held in absence of accused in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_355_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91340&sectionno=355&orderno=355&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_355_content:
  string
  line `(1) At`
  line `any stage of an inquiry or trial under this Sanhita, if the Judge or Magistrate is satisfied, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded, that the personal attendance of the accused before the Court is not necessary in the interests of`
  line `justice, or that the accused persistently disturbs the proceedings in Court, the Judge or Magistrate may, if`
  line `the accused is represented by an advocate, dispense with his attendance and proceed with such inquiry or`
  line `trial in his absence, and may, at any subsequent stage of the proceedings, direct the personal attendance of`
  line `such accused.`
  line
  line `(2) If the accused in any such case is not represented by an advocate, or if the Judge or Magistrate`
  line `considers his personal attendance necessary, he may, if he thinks fit and for reasons to be recorded by him,`
  line `either adjourn such inquiry or trial, or order that the case of such accused be taken up or tried separately.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this section, personal attendance of the accused includes attendance`
  line `through audio-video electronic means.`
obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_356:
  sectionId (91341)
  sectionNo (356)
  orderNo 356
  title `Inquiry, trial or judgment in absentia of proclaimed offender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_356_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91341&sectionno=356&orderno=356&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_356_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Sanhita or in any other law for the time being in force, when a person declared as a`
  line `proclaimed offender, whether or not charged jointly, has absconded to evade trial and there is no immediate`
  line `prospect of arresting him, it shall be deemed to operate as a waiver of the right of such person to be present`
  line `and tried in person, and the Court shall, after recording reasons in writing, in the interest of justice, proceed`
  line `with the trial in the like manner and with like effect as if he was present, under this Sanhita and pronounce`
  line `the judgment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court shall not commence the trial unless a period of ninety days has lapsed from the`
  line `date of framing of the charge.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court shall ensure that the following procedure has been complied with before proceeding`
  line `under sub-section (1), namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) issuance of two consecutive warrants of arrest within the interval of at least thirty days;`
  line
  line `(ii) publish in a national or local daily newspaper circulating in the place of his last known address`
  line `of residence, requiring the proclaimed offender to appear before the Court for trial and informing him`
  line `that in case he fails to appear within thirty days from the date of such publication, the trial shall`
  line `commence in his absence;`
  line
  line `(iii) inform his relative or friend, if any, about the commencement of the trial; and`
  line
  line `(iv) affix information about the commencement of the trial on some conspicuous part of the house`
  line `or homestead in which such person ordinarily resides and display in the police station of the district of`
  line `his last known address of residence.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the proclaimed offender is not represented by any advocate, he shall be provided with an`
  line `advocate for his defence at the expense of the State.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Court, competent to try the case or commit for trial, has examined any witnesses for`
  line `prosecution and recorded their depositions, such depositions shall be given in evidence against such`
  line `proclaimed offender on the inquiry into, or in trial for, the offence with which he is charged:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the proclaimed offender is arrested and produced or appears before the Court during`
  line `such trial, the Court may, in the interest of justice, allow him to examine any evidence which may have`
  line `been taken in his absence.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a trial is related to a person under this section, the deposition and examination of the witness,`
  line `may, as far as practicable, be recorded by audio-video electronic means preferably mobile phone and such`
  line `recording shall be kept in such manner as the Court may direct.`
  line
  line `(6) In prosecution for offences under this Sanhita, voluntary absence of accused after the trial has`
  line `commenced under sub-section (1) shall not prevent continuing the trial including the pronouncement of the`
  line `judgment even if he is arrested and produced or appears at the conclusion of such trial.`
  line
  line `(7) No appeal shall lie against the judgment under this section unless the proclaimed offender presents`
  line `himself before the Court of appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appeal against conviction shall lie after the expiry of three years from the date of the`
  line judgment.
  line
  line `(8) The State may, by notification, extend the provisions of this section to any absconder mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 84.`
obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_357:
  sectionId (91342)
  sectionNo (357)
  orderNo 357
  title `Procedure where accused does not understand proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_357_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91342&sectionno=357&orderno=357&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_357_content:
  string
  line `If the accused, though not a`
  line `person of unsound mind, cannot be made to understand the proceedings, the Court may proceed with the`
  line `inquiry or trial; and, in the case of a Court other than a High Court, if such proceedings result in a conviction,`
  line `the proceedings shall be forwarded to the High Court with a report of the circumstances of the case, and the`
  line `High Court shall pass thereon such order as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_358:
  sectionId (91343)
  sectionNo (358)
  orderNo 358
  title `Power to proceed against other persons appearing to be guilty of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_358_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91343&sectionno=358&orderno=358&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_358_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in the`
  line `course of any inquiry into, or trial of, an offence, it appears from the evidence that any person not being the`
  line `accused has committed any offence for which such person could be tried together with the accused, the`
  line `Court may proceed against such person for the offence which he appears to have committed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such person is not attending the Court, he may be arrested or summoned, as the circumstances`
  line `of the case may require, for the purpose aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person attending the Court, although not under arrest or upon a summons, may be detained by`
  line `such Court for the purpose of the inquiry into, or trial of, the offence which he appears to have committed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Court proceeds against any person under sub-section (1), then---`
  line
  line `(a) the proceedings in respect of such person shall be commenced afresh, and the witnesses reheard;`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the provisions of clause (a), the case may proceed as if such person had been an`
  line `accused person when the Court took cognizance of the offence upon which the inquiry or trial was`
  line commenced.
obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_359:
  sectionId (91344)
  sectionNo (359)
  orderNo 359
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_359_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91344&sectionno=359&orderno=359&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_359_content:
  string
  line `(1) The offences punishable under the sections of the Bharatiya`
  line `Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) specified in the first two columns of the Table next following may be`
  line `compounded by the persons mentioned in the third column of that Table: ---`
  line
  line TABLE
  line
  line `OffenceSection of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 applicablePerson by whom offencemay be compounded`
  line
  line `1 23`
  line
  line `Enticing or taking away or detaining with criminal intent a married woman.Voluntarily causing hurt.84The husband of the woman and the woman.`
  line
  line `Voluntarily causing hurt. 115(2) The person to whom the hurt`
  line `is caused`
  line
  line `Voluntarily causing hurt on`
  line provocation.
  line `122(1) The person to whom the hurt`
  line `is caused.`
  line
  line `Voluntarily causing grievous hurt`
  line `on grave and sudden provocation.`
  line `122(2) The person to whom the hurt`
  line `is caused.`
  line
  line `Wrongfully restraining or`
  line `confining any person.`
  line `126(2), 127(2) The person restrained or`
  line confined.
  line
  line `Wrongfully confining a person for`
  line `three days or more.`
  line `127(3) The person confined.`
  line
  line `Wrongfully confining a person for`
  line `ten days or more.`
  line `127(4) The person confined.`
  line
  line `Wrongfully confining a person in`
  line secret.
  line `127(6) The person confined.`
  line
  line `Assault or use of criminal force. 131,133,136`
  line `The person assaulted or to`
  line `whom criminal force is used.`
  line
  line `Uttering words, etc., with`
  line `deliberate intent to wound the`
  line `religious feelings of any person.`
  line `302 The person whose religious`
  line `feelings are intended to be`
  line wounded.
  line
  line `Theft. 303(2) The owner of the property`
  line stolen.
  line
  line `Dishonest misappropriation of`
  line property.
  line `314 The owner of the property`
  line misappropriated.
  line
  line `Criminal breach of trust by a`
  line `carrier, wharfinger, etc.`
  line `316(3) The owner of the property in`
  line `respect of which the breach`
  line `of trust has been committed.`
  line
  line `Dishonestly receiving stolen property knowing it to`
  line `be stolen.`
  line `317(2) The owner of the property stolen.`
  line
  line `Assisting in the concealment or disposal of stolen`
  line `property, knowing it to be stolen.`
  line `317(5) The owner of the property stolen.`
  line
  line `Cheating. 318(2) The person cheated.`
  line
  line `Cheating by personation. 319(2) The person cheated.`
  line
  line `Fraudulent removal or concealment of property,`
  line `etc., to prevent distribution among creditors..`
  line `320 The creditors who are affected`
  line thereby.
  line
  line `Fraudulently preventing from being made available`
  line `for his creditors a debt or demand due to the`
  line offender.
  line `321 The creditors who are affected`
  line thereby.
  line
  line `Fraudulent execution of deed of transfer containing`
  line `false statement of consideration.`
  line `322 The person affected thereby.`
  line
  line `Fraudulent removal or concealment of property. 323 The person affected thereby.`
  line
  line `Mischief, when the only loss or damage caused is`
  line `loss or damage to a private person..`
  line `324(2), 324(4) The person to whom the loss or`
  line `damage is caused.`
  line
  line `Mischief by killing or maiming animal. .325 The owner of the animal.`
  line
  line `Mischief by injury to works of irrigation by`
  line `wrongfully diverting water when the only loss or`
  line `damage caused is loss or damage to private person.`
  line `326(a) The person to whom the loss or`
  line `damage is caused.`
  line
  line `Criminal trespass.329(3) The person in possession of the`
  line `property trespassed upon.`
  line
  line `House-trespass. 329(4) The person in possession of the`
  line `property trespassed upon.`
  line
  line `House-trespass to commit an offence (other than`
  line `theft) punishable with imprisonment.`
  line `332(c) The person in possession of the`
  line `house trespassed upon.`
  line
  line `Using a false trade or property mark. 345(3) The person to whom loss or injury is`
  line `caused by such use.`
  line
  line `Counterfeiting a property mark used by another. 347(1) The person to whom loss or injury is`
  line `caused by such use.`
  line
  line `Selling goods marked with a counterfeit property`
  line mark.
  line `349 The person to whom loss or injury is`
  line `caused by such use.`
  line
  line `Criminal intimidation. 351(2), 351(3) The person intimidated.`
  line
  line `Insult intended to provoke a breach of peace. 352 The person insulted.`
  line
  line `Inducing person to believe himself an object of`
  line `divine displeasure.`
  line `354 The person induced.`
  line
  line `Defamation, except such cases as are specified`
  line `against section 356(2) of the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023, (45 of 2023) column 1 of the Table`
  line `under sub-section (2).`
  line `356(2) The person defamed.`
  line
  line `Printing or engraving matter, knowing it to be`
  line defamatory.
  line `356(3) The person defamed.`
  line
  line `Sale of printed or engraved substance containing`
  line `defamatory matter, knowing it to contain such`
  line matter.
  line `356(4) The person defamed.`
  line
  line `Criminal breach of contract of service. 357 The person with whom the offender`
  line `has contracted.`
  line
  line `(2) The offences punishable under the sections of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023)`
  line `specified in the first two columns of the Table next following may, with the permission of the Court before`
  line `which any prosecution for such offence is pending, be compounded by the persons mentioned in the third`
  line `column of that Table:.---`
  line
  line TABLE
  line
  line `OffenceSection of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, applicablePerson by whom offencemay be compounded`
  line
  line `1 23`
  line
  line `Word, gesture or act intended to insult the`
  line `modesty of a woman.`
  line `79 The woman whom it was`
  line `intended to insult or whose`
  line `privacy was intruded upon.`
  line
  line `Marrying again during the life-time of a`
  line `husband or wife.`
  line `82(1) The husband or wife of the`
  line `person so marrying.`
  line
  line `Causing miscarriage. 88 The woman to whom`
  line `miscarriage is caused.`
  line
  line `Voluntarily causing grievous hurt. 117(2) The person to whom hurt is`
  line caused.
  line
  line `Causing hurt by doing an act so rashly and`
  line `negligently as to endanger human life or`
  line `the personal safety of others.`
  line `125(a) The person to whom hurt is`
  line caused.
  line
  line `Causing grievous hurt by doing an act so`
  line `rashly and negligently as to endanger`
  line `human life or the personal safety of others.`
  line `125(b) The person to whom hurt is`
  line caused.
  line
  line `Assault or criminal force in attempting`
  line `wrongfully to confine a person.`
  line `135 The person assaulted or to`
  line `whom the force was used.`
  line
  line `Theft, by clerk or servant of property in`
  line `possession of master.`
  line `306 The owner of the property`
  line stolen.
  line
  line `Criminal breach of trust. 316(2) The owner of the property in`
  line `respect of which breach of`
  line `trust has been committed.`
  line
  line `Criminal breach of trust by a clerk or`
  line servant.
  line `316(4) The owner of the property in`
  line `respect of which the breach of`
  line `trust has been committed.`
  line
  line `Cheating a person whose interest the`
  line `offender was bound, either by law or by`
  line `legal contract, to protect.`
  line `318(3) The person cheated.`
  line
  line `Cheating and dishonestly inducing delivery`
  line `of property or the making, alteration or`
  line `destruction of a valuable security.`
  line `318(4) The person cheated.`
  line
  line `Defamation against the President or the`
  line `Vice-President or the Governor of the State`
  line `or the Administrator of the Union territory`
  line `or a Minister in respect of his public`
  line `functions when instituted upon a complaint`
  line `made by the public prosecutor.`
  line `356(2) The person defamed.`
  line
  line `(3) When an offence is compoundable under this section, the abetment of such offence or an attempt to`
  line `commit such offence (when such attempt is itself an offence) or where the accused is liable under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 3 or section 190 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023), may be`
  line `compounded in like manner.`
  line
  line `(4)(a) When the person who would otherwise be competent to compound an offence under this`
  line `section is a child or of unsound mind, any person competent to contract on his behalf may, with the`
  line `permission of the Court, compound such offence;`
  line
  line `(b) When the person who would otherwise be competent to compound an offence under this section is`
  line `dead, the legal representative, as defined in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) of such person`
  line `may, with the consent of the Court, compound such offence.`
  line
  line `(5) When the accused has been committed for trial or when he has been convicted and an appeal is`
  line `pending, no composition for the offence shall be allowed without the leave of the Court to which he is`
  line `committed, or, as the case may be, before which the appeal is to be heard.`
  line
  line `(6) A High Court or Court of Session acting in the exercise of its powers of revision under section 442`
  line `may allow any person to compound any offence which such person is competent to compound under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(7) No offence shall be compounded if the accused is, by reason of a previous conviction, liable either`
  line `to enhanced punishment or to a punishment of a different kind for such offence.`
  line
  line `(8) The composition of an offence under this section shall have the effect of an acquittal of the accused`
  line `with whom the offence has been compounded.`
  line
  line `(9) No offence shall be compounded except as provided by this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_360:
  sectionId (91345)
  sectionNo (360)
  orderNo 360
  title `Withdrawal from prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_360_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91345&sectionno=360&orderno=360&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_360_content:
  string
  line `The Public Prosecutor or Assistant Public Prosecutor in charge`
  line `of a case may, with the consent of the Court, at any time before the judgment is pronounced, withdraw from`
  line `the prosecution of any person either generally or in respect of any one or more of the offences for which he`
  line `is tried; and, upon such withdrawal,---`
  line
  line `(a) if it is made before a charge has been framed, the accused shall be discharged in respect of such`
  line `offence or offences;`
  line
  line `(b) if it is made after a charge has been framed, or when under this Sanhita no charge is required,`
  line
  line `he shall be acquitted in respect of such offence or offences:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such offence---`
  line
  line `(i) was against any law relating to a matter to which the executive power of the Union extends; or`
  line
  line `(ii) was investigated under any Central Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) involved the misappropriation or destruction of, or damage to, any property belonging to the`
  line `Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(iv) was committed by a person in the service of the Central Government while acting or purporting`
  line `to act in the discharge of his official duty,`
  line
  line `and the Prosecutor in charge of the case has not been appointed by the Central Government, he shall not,`
  line `unless he has been permitted by the Central Government to do so, move the Court for its consent to`
  line `withdraw from the prosecution and the Court shall, before according consent, direct the Prosecutor to`
  line `produce before it the permission granted by the Central Government to withdraw from the prosecution:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no Court shall allow such withdrawal without giving an opportunity of being`
  line `heard to the victim in the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_361:
  sectionId (91346)
  sectionNo (361)
  orderNo 361
  title `Procedure in cases which Magistrate cannot dispose of.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_361_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91346&sectionno=361&orderno=361&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_361_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the course of any inquiry`
  line `into an offence or a trial before a Magistrate in any district, the evidence appears to him to warrant a`
  line presumption---
  line
  line `(a) that he has no jurisdiction to try the case or commit it for trial; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the case is one which should be tried or committed for trial by some other Magistrate in the`
  line `district; or`
  line
  line `(c) that the case should be tried by the Chief Judicial Magistrate,`
  line
  line `he shall stay the proceedings and submit the case, with a brief report explaining its nature, to the Chief`
  line `Judicial Magistrate or to such other Magistrate, having jurisdiction, as the Chief Judicial Magistrate directs.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate to whom the case is submitted may, if so empowered, either try the case himself, or`
  line `refer it to any Magistrate subordinate to him having jurisdiction, or commit the accused for trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_362:
  sectionId (91562)
  sectionNo (362)
  orderNo 362
  title `Procedure when after commencement of inquiry or trial, Magistrate finds case should be committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_362_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91562&sectionno=362&orderno=362&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_362_content:
  string
  line `If, in any inquiry into an offence or a trial before a Magistrate, it appears to him at any stage`
  line `of the proceedings before signing the judgment that the case is one which ought to be tried by the Court of`
  line `Session, he shall commit it to that Court under the provisions hereinbefore contained and thereupon the`
  line `provisions of Chapter XIX shall apply to the commitment so made.`
obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_363:
  sectionId (91348)
  sectionNo (363)
  orderNo 363
  title `Trial of persons previously convicted of offences against coinage, stamp-law or property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_363_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_363_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91348&sectionno=363&orderno=363&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_363_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person, having been convicted of an offence punishable under Chapter X or`
  line `Chapter XVII of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023), with imprisonment for a term of three`
  line `years or upwards, is again accused of any offence punishable under either of those Chapters with`
  line `imprisonment for a term of three years or upwards, and the Magistrate before whom the case is pending is`
  line `satisfied that there is ground for presuming that such person has committed the offence, he shall be sent for`
  line `trial to the Chief Judicial Magistrate or committed to the Court of Session, unless the Magistrate is`
  line `competent to try the case and is of opinion that he can himself pass an adequate sentence if the accused is`
  line convicted.
  line
  line `(2) When any person is sent for trial to the Chief Judicial Magistrate or committed to the Court of`
  line `Session under sub-section (1), any other person accused jointly with him in the same inquiry or trial shall`
  line `be similarly sent or committed, unless the Magistrate discharges such other person under section 262 or`
  line `section 268, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_363_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_364:
  sectionId (91349)
  sectionNo (364)
  orderNo 364
  title `Procedure when Magistrate cannot pass sentence sufficiently severe.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_364_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_364_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91349&sectionno=364&orderno=364&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_364_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever a`
  line `Magistrate is of opinion, after hearing the evidence for the prosecution and the accused, that the accused is`
  line `guilty, and that he ought to receive a punishment different in kind from, or more severe than, that which`
  line `such Magistrate is empowered to inflict, or, being a Magistrate of the second class, is of opinion that the`
  line `accused ought to be required to execute a bond or bail bond under section 125, he may record the opinion`
  line `and submit his proceedings, and forward the accused, to the Chief Judicial Magistrate to whom he is`
  line subordinate.
  line
  line `(2) When more accused persons than one are being tried together, and the Magistrate considers it`
  line `necessary to proceed under sub-section (1), in regard to any of such accused, he shall forward all the`
  line `accused, who are in his opinion guilty, to the Chief Judicial Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Judicial Magistrate to whom the proceedings are submitted may, if he thinks fit, examine`
  line `the parties and recall and examine any witness who has already given evidence in the case and may call for`
  line `and take any further evidence and shall pass such judgment, sentence or order in the case as he thinks fit,`
  line `and is according to law.`
obj_root_law_sections_364_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_365:
  sectionId (91350)
  sectionNo (365)
  orderNo 365
  title `Conviction or commitment on evidence partly recorded by one Magistrate and partly by another.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_365_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_365_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91350&sectionno=365&orderno=365&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_365_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any Judge or Magistrate, after having heard and recorded the whole or any part`
  line `of the evidence in any inquiry or a trial, ceases to exercise jurisdiction therein and is succeeded by another`
  line `Judge or Magistrate who has and who exercises such jurisdiction, the Judge or Magistrate so succeeding`
  line `may act on the evidence so recorded by his predecessor, or partly recorded by his predecessor and partly`
  line `recorded by himself:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the succeeding Judge or Magistrate is of the opinion that further examination of any of`
  line `the witnesses whose evidence has already been recorded is necessary in the interests of justice, he may resummon any such witness, and after such further examination, cross-examination and re-examination, if`
  line `any, as he may permit, the witness shall be discharged.`
  line
  line `(2) When a case is transferred under the provisions of this Sanhita from one Judge to another Judge or`
  line `from one Magistrate to another Magistrate, the former shall be deemed to cease to exercise jurisdiction`
  line `therein, and to be succeeded by the latter, within the meaning of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section applies to summary trials or to cases in which proceedings have been stayed`
  line `under section 361 or in which proceedings have been submitted to a superior Magistrate under section 364.`
obj_root_law_sections_365_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_366:
  sectionId (91351)
  sectionNo (366)
  orderNo 366
  title `Court to be open.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_366_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_366_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91351&sectionno=366&orderno=366&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_366_content:
  string
  line `(1) The place in which any Criminal Court is held for the purpose of inquiring`
  line `into or trying any offence shall be deemed to be an open Court, to which the public generally may have`
  line `access, so far as the same can conveniently contain them:`
  line
  line `Provided that the presiding Judge or Magistrate may, if he thinks fit, order at any stage of any inquiry`
  line `into, or trial of, any particular case, that the public generally, or any particular person, shall not have access`
  line `to, or be or remain in, the room or building used by the Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the inquiry into and trial of rape or an`
  line `offence under section 64, section 65, section 66, section 67, section 68, section 70 or section 71 of the`
  line `Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) or under sections 4, 6, 8 or section 10 of the Protection of`
  line `Children from Sexual Offences Act, 2012 (32 of 2012) shall be conducted in camera:`
  line
  line `Provided that the presiding Judge may, if he thinks fit, or on an application made by either of the parties,`
  line `allow any particular person to have access to, or be or remain in, the room or building used by the Court:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in camera trial shall be conducted as far as practicable by a woman Judge or`
  line Magistrate.
  line
  line `(3) Where any proceedings are held under sub-section (2), it shall not be lawful for any person to print`
  line `or publish any matter in relation to any such proceedings except with the previous permission of the Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ban on printing or publication of trial proceedings in relation to an offence of rape`
  line `may be lifted, subject to maintaining confidentiality of name and address of the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_366_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_367:
  sectionId (91352)
  sectionNo (367)
  orderNo 367
  title `Procedure in case of accused being person of unsound mind.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_367_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_367_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91352&sectionno=367&orderno=367&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_367_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a Magistrate holding`
  line `an inquiry has reason to believe that the person against whom the inquiry is being held is a person of`
  line `unsound mind and consequently incapable of making his defence, the Magistrate shall inquire into the fact`
  line `of such unsoundness of mind, and shall cause such person to be examined by the civil surgeon of the district`
  line `or such other medical officer as the State Government may direct, and thereupon shall examine such`
  line `surgeon or other medical officer as a witness, and shall reduce the examination to writing.`
  line
  line `(2) If the civil surgeon finds the accused to be a person of unsound mind, he shall refer such person to`
  line `a psychiatrist or clinical psychologist of Government hospital or Government medical college for care,`
  line `treatment and prognosis of the condition and the psychiatrist or clinical psychologist, as the case may be,`
  line `shall inform the Magistrate whether the accused is suffering from unsoundness of mind or intellectual`
  line `disability:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the accused is aggrieved by the information given by the psychiatric or clinical`
  line `psychologist, as the case may be, to the Magistrate, he may prefer an appeal before the Medical Board`
  line `which shall consist of---`
  line
  line `(a) head of psychiatry unit in the nearest Government hospital; and`
  line
  line `(b) a faculty member in psychiatry in the nearest Government medical college.`
  line
  line `(3) Pending such examination and inquiry, the Magistrate may deal with such person in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of section 369.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Magistrate is informed that the person referred to in sub-section (2) is a person of unsound`
  line `mind, the Magistrate shall further determine whether the unsoundness of mind renders the accused`
  line `incapable of entering defence and if the accused is found so incapable, the Magistrate shall record a finding`
  line `to that effect, and shall examine the record of evidence produced by the prosecution and after hearing the`
  line `advocate of the accused but without questioning the accused, if he finds that no prima facie case is made`
  line `out against the accused, he shall, instead of postponing the enquiry, discharge the accused and deal with`
  line `him in the manner provided under section 369:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Magistrate finds that a prima facie case is made out against the accused in respect`
  line `of whom a finding of unsoundness of mind is arrived at, he shall postpone the proceeding for such period,`
  line `as in the opinion of the psychiatrist or clinical psychologist, is required for the treatment of the accused,`
  line `and order the accused to be dealt with as provided under section 369.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Magistrate is informed that the person referred to in sub-section (2) is a person with intellectual`
  line `disability, the Magistrate shall further determine whether the intellectual disability renders the accused`
  line `incapable of entering defence, and if the accused is found so incapable, the Magistrate shall order closure`
  line `of the inquiry and deal with the accused in the manner provided under section 369.`
obj_root_law_sections_367_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_368:
  sectionId (91353)
  sectionNo (368)
  orderNo 368
  title `Procedure in case of person of unsound mind tried before Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_368_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_368_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91353&sectionno=368&orderno=368&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_368_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at the trial of any`
  line `person before a Magistrate or Court of Session, it appears to the Magistrate or Court that such person is of`
  line `unsound mind and consequently incapable of making his defence, the Magistrate or Court shall, in the first`
  line `instance, try the fact of such unsoundness of mind and incapacity, and if the Magistrate or Court, after`
  line `considering such medical and other evidence as may be produced before him or it, is satisfied of the fact,`
  line `he or it shall record a finding to that effect and shall postpone further proceedings in the case.`
  line
  line `(2) If during trial, the Magistrate or Court of Session finds the accused to be of unsound mind, he or it`
  line `shall refer such person to a psychiatrist or clinical psychologist for care and treatment, and the psychiatrist`
  line `or clinical psychologist, as the case may be, shall report to the Magistrate or Court whether the accused is`
  line `suffering from unsoundness of mind:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the accused is aggrieved by the information given by the psychiatrist or clinical`
  line `psychologist, as the case may be, to the Magistrate, he may prefer an appeal before the Medical Board`
  line `which shall consist of`
  line
  line `(a) head of psychiatry unit in the nearest Government hospital; and`
  line
  line `(b) a faculty member in psychiatry in the nearest Government medical college.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Magistrate or Court is informed that the person referred to in sub-section (2) is a person of`
  line `unsound mind, the Magistrate or Court shall further determine whether the unsoundness of mind renders`
  line `the accused incapable of entering defence and if the accused is found so incapable, the Magistrate or Court`
  line `shall record a finding to that effect and shall examine the record of evidence produced by the prosecution`
  line `and after hearing the advocate of the accused but without questioning the accused, if the Magistrate or Court`
  line `finds that no prima facie case is made out against the accused, he or it shall, instead of postponing the trial,`
  line `discharge the accused and deal with him in the manner provided under section 369:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Magistrate or Court finds that a prima facie case is made out against the accused in`
  line `respect of whom a finding of unsoundness of mind is arrived at, he shall postpone the trial for such period,`
  line `as in the opinion of the psychiatrist or clinical psychologist, is required for the treatment of the accused.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Magistrate or Court finds that a prima facie case is made out against the accused and he is`
  line `incapable of entering defence by reason of intellectual disability, he or it shall not hold the trial and order`
  line `the accused to be dealt with in accordance with section 369.`
obj_root_law_sections_368_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_369:
  sectionId (91354)
  sectionNo (369)
  orderNo 369
  title `Release of person of unsound mind pending investigation or trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_369_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_369_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91354&sectionno=369&orderno=369&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_369_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever a person if`
  line `found under section 367 or section 368 to be incapable of entering defence by reason of unsoundness of`
  line `mind or intellectual disability, the Magistrate or Court, as the case may be, shall, whether the case is one in`
  line `which bail may be taken or not, order release of such person on bail:`
  line
  line `Provided that the accused is suffering from unsoundness of mind or intellectual disability which does`
  line `not mandate in-patient treatment and a friend or relative undertakes to obtain regular out-patient psychiatric`
  line `treatment from the nearest medical facility and to prevent from doing injury to himself or to any other`
  line person.
  line
  line `(2) If the case is one in which, in the opinion of the Magistrate or Court, as the case may be, bail cannot`
  line `be granted or if an appropriate undertaking is not given, he or it shall order the accused to be kept in such`
  line `a place where regular psychiatric treatment can be provided, and shall report the action taken to the State`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order for the detention of the accused in a public mental health establishment shall be`
  line `made otherwise than in accordance with such rules as the State Government may have made under the`
  line `Mental Healthcare Act, 2017 (10 of 2017).`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever a person is found under section 367 or section 368 to be incapable of entering defence`
  line `by reason of unsoundness of mind or intellectual disability, the Magistrate or Court, as the case may be,`
  line `shall keeping in view the nature of the act committed and the extent of unsoundness of mind or intellectual`
  line `disability, further determine if the release of the accused can be ordered:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) if on the basis of medical opinion or opinion of a specialist, the Magistrate or Court, as the case`
  line `may be, decide to order discharge of the accused, as provided under section 367 or section 368, such`
  line `release may be ordered, if sufficient security is given that the accused shall be prevented from doing`
  line `injury to himself or to any other person;`
  line
  line `(b) if the Magistrate or Court, as the case may be, is of the opinion that discharge of the accused`
  line `cannot be ordered, the transfer of the accused to a residential facility for persons with unsoundness of`
  line `mind or intellectual disability may be ordered wherein the accused may be provided care and`
  line `appropriate education and training.`
obj_root_law_sections_369_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_370:
  sectionId (91355)
  sectionNo (370)
  orderNo 370
  title `Resumption of inquiry or trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_370_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_370_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91355&sectionno=370&orderno=370&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_370_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever an inquiry or a trial is postponed under`
  line `section 367 or section 368, the Magistrate or Court, as the case may be, may at any time after the person`
  line `concerned has ceased to be of unsound mind, resume the inquiry or trial and require the accused to appear`
  line `or be brought before such Magistrate or Court.`
  line
  line `(2) When the accused has been released under section 369, and the sureties for his appearance produce`
  line `him to the officer whom the Magistrate or Court appoints in this behalf, the certificate of such officer that`
  line `the accused is capable of making his defence shall be receivable in evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_370_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_371:
  sectionId (91356)
  sectionNo (371)
  orderNo 371
  title `Procedure on accused appearing before Magistrate or Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_371_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_371_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91356&sectionno=371&orderno=371&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_371_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, when the accused`
  line `appears or is again brought before the Magistrate or Court, as the case may be, the Magistrate or Court`
  line `considers him capable of making his defence, the inquiry or trial shall proceed.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Magistrate or Court considers the accused to be still incapable of making his defence, the`
  line `Magistrate or Court shall act according to the provisions of section 367 or section 368, as the case may be,`
  line `and if the accused is found to be of unsound mind and consequently incapable of making his defence, shall`
  line `deal with such accused in accordance with the provisions of section 369.`
obj_root_law_sections_371_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_372:
  sectionId (91357)
  sectionNo (372)
  orderNo 372
  title `When accused appears to have been of sound mind.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_372_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_372_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91357&sectionno=372&orderno=372&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_372_content:
  string
  line `When the accused appears to be of sound`
  line `mind at the time of inquiry or trial, and the Magistrate is satisfied from the evidence given before him that`
  line `there is reason to believe that the accused committed an act, which, if he had been of sound mind, would`
  line `have been an offence, and that he was, at the time when the act was committed, by reason of unsoundness`
  line `of mind, incapable of knowing the nature of the act or that it was wrong or contrary to law, the Magistrate`
  line `shall proceed with the case, and, if the accused ought to be tried by the Court of Session, commit him for`
  line `trial before the Court of Session.`
obj_root_law_sections_372_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_373:
  sectionId (91358)
  sectionNo (373)
  orderNo 373
  title `Judgment of acquittal on ground of unsoundness of mind.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_373_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_373_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91358&sectionno=373&orderno=373&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_373_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person is acquitted`
  line `upon the ground that, at the time at which he is alleged to have committed an offence, he was, by reason of`
  line `unsoundness of mind, incapable of knowing the nature of the act alleged as constituting the offence, or that`
  line `it was wrong or contrary to law, the finding shall state specifically whether he committed the act or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_373_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_374:
  sectionId (91359)
  sectionNo (374)
  orderNo 374
  title `Person acquitted on ground of unsoundness of mind to be detained in safe custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_374_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_374_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91359&sectionno=374&orderno=374&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_374_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Whenever the finding states that the accused person committed the act alleged, the Magistrate or Court`
  line `before whom or which the trial has been held, shall, if such act would, but for the incapacity found, have`
  line `constituted an offence,---`
  line
  line `(a) order such person to be detained in safe custody in such place and manner as the Magistrate or`
  line `Court thinks fit; or`
  line
  line `(b) order such person to be delivered to any relative or friend of such person.`
  line
  line `(2) No order for the detention of the accused in a public mental health establishment shall be made`
  line `under clause (a) of sub-section (1) otherwise than in accordance with such rules as the State Government`
  line `may have made under the Mental Healthcare Act, 2017 (10 of 2017).`
  line
  line `(3) No order for the delivery of the accused to a relative or friend shall be made under clause (b) of subsection (1) except upon the application of such relative or friend and on his giving security to the satisfaction`
  line `of the Magistrate or Court that the person delivered shall---`
  line
  line `(a) be properly taken care of and prevented from doing injury to himself or to any other person;`
  line
  line `(b) be produced for the inspection of such officer, and at such times and places, as the State`
  line `Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(4) The Magistrate or Court shall report to the State Government the action taken under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_374_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_375:
  sectionId (91360)
  sectionNo (375)
  orderNo 375
  title `Power of State Government to empower officer in charge to discharge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_375_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_375_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91360&sectionno=375&orderno=375&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_375_content:
  string
  line `The State`
  line `Government may empower the officer in charge of the jail in which a person is confined under the`
  line `provisions of section 369 or section 374 to discharge all or any of the functions of the Inspector-General of`
  line `Prisons under section 376 or section 377.`
obj_root_law_sections_375_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_376:
  sectionId (91361)
  sectionNo (376)
  orderNo 376
  title `Procedure where prisoner of unsound mind is reported capable of making his defence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_376_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_376_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91361&sectionno=376&orderno=376&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_376_content:
  string
  line If
  line `a person is detained under the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 369, and in the case of a person`
  line `detained in a jail, the Inspector-General of Prisons, or, in the case of a person detained in a public mental`
  line `health establishment, the Mental Health Review Board constituted under the Mental Healthcare Act, 2017`
  line `(10 of 2017), shall certify that, in his or their opinion, such person is capable of making his defence, he`
  line `shall be taken before the Magistrate or Court, as the case may be, at such time as the Magistrate or Court`
  line `appoints, and the Magistrate or Court shall deal with such person under the provisions of section 371; and`
  line `the certificate of such Inspector-General or visitors as aforesaid shall be receivable as evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_376_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_377:
  sectionId (91362)
  sectionNo (377)
  orderNo 377
  title `Procedure where person of unsound mind detained is declared fit to be released.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_377_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91362&sectionno=377&orderno=377&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_377_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a`
  line `person is detained under the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 369, or section 374, and such InspectorGeneral or visitors shall certify that, in his or their judgment, he may be released without danger of his`
  line `doing injury to himself or to any other person, the State Government may thereupon order him to be`
  line `released, or to be detained in custody, or to be transferred to a public mental health establishment if he has`
  line `not been already sent to such establishment; and, in case it orders him to be transferred to a public mental`
  line `health establishment, may appoint a Commission, consisting of a Judicial and two medical officers.`
  line
  line `(2) Such Commission shall make a formal inquiry into the state of mind of such person, take such`
  line `evidence as is necessary, and shall report to the State Government, which may order his release or detention`
  line `as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_378:
  sectionId (91363)
  sectionNo (378)
  orderNo 378
  title `Delivery of person of unsound mind to care of relative or friend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_378_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91363&sectionno=378&orderno=378&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_378_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any relative`
  line `or friend of any person detained under the provisions of section 369 or section 374 desires that he shall be`
  line `delivered to his care and custody, the State Government may, upon the application of such relative or friend`
  line `and on his giving security to the satisfaction of such State Government, that the person delivered shall---`
  line
  line `(a) be properly taken care of and prevented from doing injury to himself or to any other person;`
  line
  line `(b) be produced for the inspection of such officer, and at such times and places, as the State`
  line `Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a person detained under sub-section (2) of section 369, be produced when required`
  line `before such Magistrate or Court,`
  line
  line `order such person to be delivered to such relative or friend.`
  line
  line `(2) If the person so delivered is accused of any offence, the trial of which has been postponed by reason`
  line `of his being of unsound mind and incapable of making his defence, and the inspecting officer referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1), certifies at any time to the Magistrate or Court that such person is capable of`
  line `making his defence, such Magistrate or Court shall call upon the relative or friend to whom such accused`
  line `was delivered to produce him before the Magistrate or Court; and, upon such production the Magistrate or`
  line `Court shall proceed in accordance with the provisions of section 371, and the certificate of the inspecting`
  line `officer shall be receivable as evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_378_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_379:
  sectionId (91364)
  sectionNo (379)
  orderNo 379
  title `Procedure in cases mentioned in section 215.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_379_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_379_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91364&sectionno=379&orderno=379&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_379_content:
  string
  line `(1) When, upon an application made to it in this`
  line `behalf or otherwise, any Court is of opinion that it is expedient in the interests of justice that an inquiry`
  line `should be made into any offence referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 215, which appears`
  line `to have been committed in or in relation to a proceeding in that Court or, as the case may be, in respect of`
  line `a document produced or given in evidence in a proceeding in that Court, such Court may, after such`
  line `preliminary inquiry, if any, as it thinks necessary,---`
  line
  line `(a) record a finding to that effect;`
  line
  line `(b) make a complaint thereof in writing;`
  line
  line `(c) send it to a Magistrate of the first class having jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(d) take sufficient security for the appearance of the accused before such Magistrate, or if the`
  line `alleged offence is non-bailable and the Court thinks it necessary so to do, send the accused in custody`
  line `to such Magistrate; and`
  line
  line `(e) bind over any person to appear and give evidence before such Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) The power conferred on a Court by sub-section (1) in respect of an offence may, in any case where`
  line `that Court has neither made a complaint under sub-section (1) in respect of that offence nor rejected an`
  line `application for the making of such complaint, be exercised by the Court to which such former Court is`
  line `subordinate within the meaning of sub-section (4) of section 215.`
  line
  line `(3) A complaint made under this section shall be signed,---`
  line
  line `(a) where the Court making the complaint is a High Court, by such officer of the Court as the Court`
  line `may appoint;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, by the presiding officer of the Court or by such officer of the Court as the`
  line `Court may authorise in writing in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) In this section, "Court" has the same meaning as in section 215.`
obj_root_law_sections_379_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_380:
  sectionId (91365)
  sectionNo (380)
  orderNo 380
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_380_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91365&sectionno=380&orderno=380&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_380_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person on whose application any Court other than a High Court has refused to`
  line `make a complaint under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 379, or against whom such a complaint`
  line `has been made by such Court, may appeal to the Court to which such former Court is subordinate within`
  line `the meaning of sub-section (4) of section 215, and the superior Court may thereupon, after notice to the`
  line `parties concerned, direct the withdrawal of the complaint, or, as the case may be, making of the complaint`
  line `which such former Court might have made under section 379, and, if it makes such complaint, the`
  line `provisions of that section shall apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) An order under this section, and subject to any such order, an order under section 379, shall be final,`
  line `and shall not be subject to revision.`
obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_381:
  sectionId (91366)
  sectionNo (381)
  orderNo 381
  title `Power to order costs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_381_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91366&sectionno=381&orderno=381&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_381_content:
  string
  line `Any Court dealing with an application made to it for filing a complaint`
  line `under section 379 or an appeal under section 380, shall have power to make such order as to costs as may`
  line `be just.`
obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_382:
  sectionId (91367)
  sectionNo (382)
  orderNo 382
  title `Procedure of Magistrate taking cognizance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_382_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_382_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91367&sectionno=382&orderno=382&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_382_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Magistrate to whom a complaint is made`
  line `under section 379 or section 380 shall, notwithstanding anything contained in Chapter XVI, proceed, as far`
  line `as may be, to deal with the case as if it were instituted on a police report.`
  line
  line `(2) Where it is brought to the notice of such Magistrate, or of any other Magistrate to whom the case`
  line `may have been transferred, that an appeal is pending against the decision arrived at in the judicial`
  line `proceeding out of which the matter has arisen, he may, if he thinks fit, at any stage, adjourn the hearing of`
  line `the case until such appeal is decided.`
obj_root_law_sections_382_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_383:
  sectionId (91368)
  sectionNo (383)
  orderNo 383
  title `Summary procedure for trial for giving false evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_383_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91368&sectionno=383&orderno=383&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_383_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, at the time of delivery of any`
  line `judgment or final order disposing of any judicial proceeding, a Court of Session or Magistrate of the first`
  line `class expresses an opinion to the effect that any witness appearing in such proceeding had knowingly or`
  line `wilfully given false evidence or had fabricated false evidence with the intention that such evidence should`
  line `be used in such proceeding, it or he may, if satisfied that it is necessary and expedient in the interest of`
  line `justice that the witness should be tried summarily for giving or fabricating, as the case may be, false`
  line `evidence, take cognizance of the offence and may, after giving the offender a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `showing cause why he should not be punished for such offence, try such offender summarily and sentence`
  line `him to imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or to fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) In every such case the Court shall follow, as nearly as may be practicable, the procedure prescribed`
  line `for summary trials.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall affect the power of the Court to make a complaint under section 379`
  line `for the offence, where it does not choose to proceed under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) Where, after any action is initiated under sub-section (1), it is made to appear to the Court of Session`
  line `or Magistrate of the first class that an appeal or an application for revision has been preferred or filed against`
  line `the judgment or order in which the opinion referred to in that sub-section has been expressed, it or he shall`
  line `stay further proceedings of the trial until the disposal of the appeal or the application for revision, as the`
  line `case may be, and thereupon the further proceedings of the trial shall abide by the results of the appeal or`
  line `application for revision.`
obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_384:
  sectionId (91369)
  sectionNo (384)
  orderNo 384
  title `Procedure in certain cases of contempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_384_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_384_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91369&sectionno=384&orderno=384&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_384_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any such offence as is described`
  line `in section 210, section 213, section 214, section 215 or section 267 of the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) is committed in the view or presence of any Civil, Criminal, or Revenue Court,`
  line `the Court may cause the offender to be detained in custody, and may, at any time before the rising of the`
  line `Court on the same day, take cognizance of the offence and, after giving the offender a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of showing cause why he should not be punished under this section, sentence the offender to`
  line `fine not exceeding one thousand rupees, and, in default of payment of fine, to simple imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to one month, unless such fine be sooner paid.`
  line
  line `(2) In every such case the Court shall record the fact constituting the offence, with the statement (if`
  line `any) made by the offender, as well as the finding and sentence.`
  line
  line `(3) If the offence is under section 267 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023), the record`
  line `shall show the nature and stage of the judicial proceeding in which the Court interrupted or insulted was`
  line `sitting, and the nature of the interruption or insult.`
obj_root_law_sections_384_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_385:
  sectionId (91370)
  sectionNo (385)
  orderNo 385
  title `Procedure where Court considers that case should not be dealt with under section 384.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_385_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_385_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91370&sectionno=385&orderno=385&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_385_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Court in any case considers that a person accused of any of the offences referred`
  line `to in section 384 and committed in its view or presence should be imprisoned otherwise than in default of`
  line `payment of fine, or that a fine exceeding two hundred rupees should be imposed upon him, or such Court`
  line `is for any other reason of opinion that the case should not be disposed of under section 384, such Court,`
  line `after recording the facts constituting the offence and the statement of the accused as hereinbefore provided,`
  line `may forward the case to a Magistrate having jurisdiction to try the same, and may require security to be`
  line `given for the appearance of such person before such Magistrate, or if sufficient security is not given, shall`
  line `forward such person in custody to such Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate to whom any case is forwarded under this section shall proceed to deal with, as far`
  line `as may be, as if it were instituted on a police report.`
obj_root_law_sections_385_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_386:
  sectionId (91371)
  sectionNo (386)
  orderNo 386
  title `When Registrar or Sub-Registrar to be deemed a Civil Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_386_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_386_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91371&sectionno=386&orderno=386&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_386_content:
  string
  line `When the State Government`
  line `so directs, any Registrar or any Sub-Registrar appointed under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908),`
  line `shall be deemed to be a Civil Court within the meaning of sections 384 and 385.`
obj_root_law_sections_386_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_387:
  sectionId (91372)
  sectionNo (387)
  orderNo 387
  title `Discharge of offender on submission of apology.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_387_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_387_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91372&sectionno=387&orderno=387&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_387_content:
  string
  line `When any Court has under section 384`
  line `adjudged an offender to punishment, or has under section 385 forwarded him to a Magistrate for trial, for`
  line `refusing or omitting to do anything which he was lawfully required to do or for any intentional insult or`
  line `interruption, the Court may, in its discretion, discharge the offender or remit the punishment on his`
  line `submission to the order or requisition of such Court, or on apology being made to its satisfaction.`
obj_root_law_sections_387_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_388:
  sectionId (91373)
  sectionNo (388)
  orderNo 388
  title `Imprisonment or committal of person refusing to answer or produce document.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_388_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91373&sectionno=388&orderno=388&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_388_content:
  string
  line `If any`
  line `witness or person called to produce a document or thing before a Criminal Court refuses to answer such`
  line `questions as are put to him or to produce any document or thing in his possession or power which the Court`
  line `requires him to produce, and does not, after a reasonable opportunity has been given to him so to do, offer`
  line `any reasonable excuse for such refusal, such Court may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, sentence him`
  line `to simple imprisonment, or by warrant under the hand of the Presiding Magistrate or Judge commit him to`
  line `the custody of an officer of the Court for any term not exceeding seven days, unless in the meantime, such`
  line `person consents to be examined and to answer, or to produce the document or thing and in the event of his`
  line `persisting in his refusal, he may be dealt with according to the provisions of section 384 or section 385.`
obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_389:
  sectionId (91374)
  sectionNo (389)
  orderNo 389
  title `Summary procedure for punishment for non-attendance by a witness in obedience to summons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_389_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91374&sectionno=389&orderno=389&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_389_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any witness being summoned to appear before a Criminal Court is legally bound to`
  line `appear at a certain place and time in obedience to the summons and without just excuse neglects or refuses`
  line `to attend at that place or time or departs from the place where he has to attend before the time at which it is`
  line `lawful for him to depart, and the Court before which the witness is to appear is satisfied that it is expedient`
  line `in the interests of justice that such a witness should be tried summarily, the Court may take cognizance of`
  line `the offence and after giving the offender an opportunity of showing cause why he should not be punished`
  line `under this section, sentence him to fine not exceeding five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) In every such case the Court shall follow, as nearly as may be practicable, the procedure prescribed`
  line `for summary trials.`
obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_390:
  sectionId (91375)
  sectionNo (390)
  orderNo 390
  title `Appeals from convictions under sections 383, 384, 388 and 389.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_390_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91375&sectionno=390&orderno=390&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_390_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person sentenced by`
  line `any Court other than a High Court under section 383, section 384, section 388, or section 389 may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this Sanhita appeal to the Court to which decrees or orders made in`
  line `such Court are ordinarily appealable.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of Chapter XXXI shall, so far as they are applicable, apply to appeals under this`
  line `section, and the Appellate Court may alter or reverse the finding, or reduce or reverse the sentence appealed`
  line against.
  line
  line `(3) An appeal from such conviction by a Court of Small Causes shall lie to the Court of Session for the`
  line `sessions division within which such Court is situate.`
  line
  line `(4) An appeal from such conviction by any Registrar or Sub-Registrar deemed to be a Civil Court by`
  line `virtue of a direction issued under section 386 shall lie to the Court of Session for the sessions division`
  line `within which the office of such Registrar or Sub-Registrar is situate.`
obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_391:
  sectionId (91376)
  sectionNo (391)
  orderNo 391
  title `Certain Judges and Magistrates not to try certain offences when committed before themselves.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_391_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_391_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91376&sectionno=391&orderno=391&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_391_content:
  string
  line `Except as provided in sections 383, 384, 388 and 389, no Judge of a Criminal Court (other`
  line `than a Judge of a High Court) or Magistrate shall try any person for any offence referred to in section 215,`
  line `when such offence is committed before himself or in contempt of his authority, or is brought under his`
  line `notice as such Judge or Magistrate in the course of a judicial proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_391_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_392:
  sectionId (91377)
  sectionNo (392)
  orderNo 392
  title Judgment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_392_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_392_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91377&sectionno=392&orderno=392&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_392_content:
  string
  line `(1) The judgment in every trial in any Criminal Court of original jurisdiction shall`
  line `be pronounced in open Court by the presiding officer immediately after the termination of the trial or at`
  line `some subsequent time not later than forty-five days of which notice shall be given to the parties or their`
  line advocates,---
  line
  line `(a) by delivering the whole of the judgment; or`
  line
  line `(b) by reading out the whole of the judgment; or`
  line
  line `(c) by reading out the operative part of the judgment and explaining the substance of the judgment`
  line `in a language which is understood by the accused or his advocate.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the judgment is delivered under clause (a) of sub-section (1), the presiding officer shall cause`
  line `it to be taken down in short-hand, sign the transcript and every page thereof as soon as it is made ready, and`
  line `write on it the date of the delivery of the judgment in open Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the judgment or the operative part thereof is read out under clause (b) or clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1), as the case may be, it shall be dated and signed by the presiding officer in open Court, and`
  line `if it is not written with his own hand, every page of the judgment shall be signed by him.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the judgment is pronounced in the manner specified in clause (c) of sub-section (1), the`
  line `whole judgment or a copy thereof shall be immediately made available for the perusal of the parties or their`
  line `advocates free of cost:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court shall, as far as practicable, upload the copy of the judgment on its portal within`
  line `a period of seven days from the date of judgment.`
  line
  line `(5) If the accused is in custody, he shall be brought up to hear the judgment pronounced either in person`
  line `or through audio-video electronic means.`
  line
  line `(6) If the accused is not in custody, he shall be required by the Court to attend to hear the judgment`
  line `pronounced, except where his personal attendance during the trial has been dispensed with and the sentence`
  line `is one of fine only or he is acquitted:`
  line
  line `Provided that where there are more accused persons than one, and one or more of them do not attend`
  line `the Court on the date on which the judgment is to be pronounced, the presiding officer may, in order to`
  line `avoid undue delay in the disposal of the case, pronounce the judgment notwithstanding their absence.`
  line
  line `(7) No judgment delivered by any Criminal Court shall be deemed to be invalid by reason only of the`
  line `absence of any party or his advocate on the day or from the place notified for the delivery thereof, or of any`
  line `omission to serve, or defect in serving, on the parties or their advocates, or any of them, the notice of such`
  line `day and place.`
  line
  line `(8) Nothing in this section shall be construed to limit in any way the extent of the provisions of`
  line `section 511.`
obj_root_law_sections_392_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_393:
  sectionId (91378)
  sectionNo (393)
  orderNo 393
  title `Language and contents of judgment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_393_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_393_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91378&sectionno=393&orderno=393&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_393_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as otherwise expressly provided by this`
  line `Sanhita, every judgment referred to in section 392,---`
  line
  line `(a) shall be written in the language of the Court;`
  line
  line `(b) shall contain the point or points for determination, the decision thereon and the reasons for the`
  line decision;
  line
  line `(c) shall specify the offence (if any) of which, and the section of the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) or other law under which, the accused is convicted, and the punishment to`
  line `which he is sentenced;`
  line
  line `(d) if it be a judgment of acquittal, shall state the offence of which the accused is acquitted and`
  line `direct that he be set at liberty.`
  line
  line `(2) When the conviction is under the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) and it is doubtful`
  line `under which of two sections, or under which of two parts of the same section, of that Sanhita the offence`
  line `falls, the Court shall distinctly express the same, and pass judgment in the alternative.`
  line
  line `(3) When the conviction is for an offence punishable with death or, in the alternative, with`
  line `imprisonment for life or imprisonment for a term of years, the judgment shall state the reasons for the`
  line `sentence awarded, and, in the case of sentence of death, the special reasons for such sentence.`
  line
  line `(4) When the conviction is for an offence punishable with imprisonment for a term of one year or more,`
  line `but the Court imposes a sentence of imprisonment for a term of less than three months, it shall record its`
  line `reasons for awarding such sentence, unless the sentence is one of imprisonment till the rising of the Court`
  line `or unless the case was tried summarily under the provisions of this Sanhita.`
  line
  line `(5) When any person is sentenced to death, the sentence shall direct that he be hanged by the neck till`
  line `he is dead.`
  line
  line `(6) Every order under section 136 or sub-section (2) of section 157 and every final order made under`
  line `section 144, section 164 or section 166 shall contain the point or points for determination, the decision`
  line `thereon and the reasons for the decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_393_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_394:
  sectionId (91379)
  sectionNo (394)
  orderNo 394
  title `Order for notifying address of previously convicted offender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_394_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_394_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91379&sectionno=394&orderno=394&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_394_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person, having`
  line `been convicted by a Court in India of an offence punishable with imprisonment for a term of three years,`
  line `or upwards, is again convicted of any offence punishable with imprisonment for a term of three years or`
  line `upwards by any Court other than that of a Magistrate of the second class, such Court may, if it thinks fit, at`
  line `the time of passing a sentence of imprisonment on such person, also order that his residence and any change`
  line `of, or absence from, such residence after release be notified as hereinafter provided for a term not exceeding`
  line `five years from the date of the expiration of such sentence.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall also apply to criminal conspiracies to commit such offences`
  line `and to the abetment of such offences and attempts to commit them.`
  line
  line `(3) If such conviction is set aside on appeal or otherwise, such order shall become void.`
  line
  line `(4) An order under this section may also be made by an Appellate Court or by the High Court or Court`
  line `of Session when exercising its powers of revision.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Government may, by notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this section`
  line `relating to the notification of residence or change of, or absence from, residence by released convicts.`
  line
  line `(6) Such rules may provide for punishment for the breach thereof and any person charged with a breach`
  line `of any such rule may be tried by a Magistrate of competent jurisdiction in the district in which the place`
  line `last notified by him as his place of residence is situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_394_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_395:
  sectionId (91380)
  sectionNo (395)
  orderNo 395
  title `Order to pay compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_395_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_395_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91380&sectionno=395&orderno=395&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_395_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a Court imposes a sentence of fine or a sentence`
  line `(including a sentence of death) of which fine forms a part, the Court may, when passing judgment, order`
  line `the whole or any part of the fine recovered to be applied---`
  line
  line `(a) in defraying the expenses properly incurred in the prosecution;`
  line
  line `(b) in the payment to any person of compensation for any loss or injury caused by the offence,`
  line `when compensation is, in the opinion of the Court, recoverable by such person in a Civil Court;`
  line
  line `(c) when any person is convicted of any offence for having caused the death of another person or`
  line `of having abetted the commission of such an offence, in paying compensation to the persons who are,`
  line `under the Fatal Accidents Act, 1855 (13 of 1855), entitled to recover damages from the person`
  line `sentenced for the loss resulting to them from such death;`
  line
  line `(d) when any person is convicted of any offence which includes theft, criminal misappropriation,`
  line `criminal breach of trust, or cheating, or of having dishonestly received or retained, or of having`
  line `voluntarily assisted in disposing of, stolen property knowing or having reason to believe the same to be`
  line `stolen, in compensating any bona fide purchaser of such property for the loss of the same if such`
  line `property is restored to the possession of the person entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) If the fine is imposed in a case which is subject to appeal, no such payment shall be made before`
  line `the period allowed for presenting the appeal has elapsed, or, if an appeal be presented, before the decision`
  line `of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(3) When a Court imposes a sentence, of which fine does not form a part, the Court may, when passing`
  line `judgment, order the accused person to pay, by way of compensation, such amount as may be specified in`
  line `the order to the person who has suffered any loss or injury by reason of the act for which the accused person`
  line `has been so sentenced.`
  line
  line `(4) An order under this section may also be made by an Appellate Court or by the High Court or Court`
  line `of Session when exercising its powers of revision.`
  line
  line `(5) At the time of awarding compensation in any subsequent civil suit relating to the same matter, the`
  line `Court shall take into account any sum paid or recovered as compensation under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_395_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_396:
  sectionId (91381)
  sectionNo (396)
  orderNo 396
  title `Victim compensation scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_396_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_396_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91381&sectionno=396&orderno=396&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_396_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government in co-ordination with the Central`
  line `Government shall prepare a scheme for providing funds for the purpose of compensation to the victim or`
  line `his dependents who have suffered loss or injury as a result of the crime and who require rehabilitation.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever a recommendation is made by the Court for compensation, the District Legal Service`
  line `Authority or the State Legal Service Authority, as the case may be, shall decide the quantum of`
  line `compensation to be awarded under the scheme referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) If the trial Court, at the conclusion of the trial, is satisfied, that the compensation awarded under`
  line `section 395 is not adequate for such rehabilitation, or where the cases end in acquittal or discharge and the`
  line `victim has to be rehabilitated, it may make recommendation for compensation.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the offender is not traced or identified, but the victim is identified, and where no trial takes`
  line `place, the victim or his dependents may make an application to the State or the District Legal Services`
  line `Authority for award of compensation.`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of such recommendations or on the application under sub-section (4), the State or the`
  line `District Legal Services Authority shall, after due enquiry award adequate compensation by completing the`
  line `enquiry within two months.`
  line
  line `(6) The State or the District Legal Services Authority, as the case may be, to alleviate the suffering of`
  line `the victim, may order for immediate first-aid facility or medical benefits to be made available free of cost`
  line `on the certificate of the police officer not below the rank of the officer in charge of the police station or a`
  line `Magistrate of the area concerned, or any other interim relief as the appropriate authority deems fit.`
  line
  line `(7) The compensation payable by the State Government under this section shall be in addition to the`
  line `payment of fine to the victim under section 65, section 70 and sub-section (1) of section 124 of the`
  line `Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_396_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_397:
  sectionId (91382)
  sectionNo (397)
  orderNo 397
  title `Treatment of victims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_397_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_397_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91382&sectionno=397&orderno=397&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_397_content:
  string
  line `All hospitals, public or private, whether run by the Central Government,`
  line `the State Government, local bodies or any other person, shall immediately, provide the first-aid or medical`
  line `treatment, free of cost, to the victims of any offence covered under section 64, section 65, section`
  line `66, section 67, section 68, section 70, section 71 or sub-section (1) of section 124 of the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) or under sections 4, 6, 8 or section 10 of the Protection of Children from Sexual`
  line `Offences Act, 2012 (32 of 2012), and shall immediately inform the police of such incident.`
obj_root_law_sections_397_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_398:
  sectionId (91383)
  sectionNo (398)
  orderNo 398
  title `Witness protection scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_398_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_398_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91383&sectionno=398&orderno=398&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_398_content:
  string
  line `Every State Government shall prepare and notify a Witness`
  line `Protection Scheme for the State with a view to ensure protection of the witnesses.`
obj_root_law_sections_398_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_399:
  sectionId (91384)
  sectionNo (399)
  orderNo 399
  title `Compensation to persons groundlessly arrested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_399_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_399_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91384&sectionno=399&orderno=399&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_399_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any person causes a police`
  line `officer to arrest another person, if it appears to the Magistrate by whom the case is heard that there was no`
  line `sufficient ground for causing such arrest, the Magistrate may award such compensation, not exceeding one`
  line `thousand rupees, to be paid by the person so causing the arrest to the person so arrested, for his loss of time`
  line `and expenses in the matter, as the Magistrate thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) In such cases, if more persons than one are arrested, the Magistrate may, in like manner, award to`
  line `each of them such compensation, not exceeding one thousand rupees, as such Magistrate thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(3) All compensation awarded under this section may be recovered as if it were a fine, and, if it cannot`
  line `be so recovered, the person by whom it is payable shall be sentenced to simple imprisonment for such term`
  line `not exceeding thirty days as the Magistrate directs, unless such sum is sooner paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_399_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_400:
  sectionId (91385)
  sectionNo (400)
  orderNo 400
  title `Order to pay costs in non-cognizable cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_400_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_400_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91385&sectionno=400&orderno=400&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_400_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any complaint of a non-cognizable`
  line `offence is made to a Court, the Court, if it convicts the accused, may, in addition to the penalty imposed`
  line `upon him, order him to pay to the complainant, in whole or in part, the cost incurred by him in the`
  line `prosecution, and may further order that in default of payment, the accused shall suffer simple imprisonment`
  line `for a period not exceeding thirty days and such costs may include any expenses incurred in respect of`
  line `process-fees, witnesses and advocate's fees which the Court may consider reasonable.`
  line
  line `(2) An order under this section may also be made by an Appellate Court or by the High Court or Court`
  line `of Session when exercising its powers of revision.`
obj_root_law_sections_400_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_401:
  sectionId (91386)
  sectionNo (401)
  orderNo 401
  title `Order to release on probation of good conduct or after admonition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_401_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_401_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91386&sectionno=401&orderno=401&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_401_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person`
  line `not under twenty-one years of age is convicted of an offence punishable with fine only or with imprisonment`
  line `for a term of seven years or less, or when any person under twenty-one years of age or any woman is`
  line `convicted of an offence not punishable with death or imprisonment for life, and no previous conviction is`
  line `proved against the offender, if it appears to the Court before which he is convicted, regard being had to the`
  line `age, character or antecedents of the offender, and to the circumstances in which the offence was committed,`
  line `that it is expedient that the offender should be released on probation of good conduct, the Court may, instead`
  line `of sentencing him at once to any punishment, direct that he be released on his entering into a bond or bail`
  line `bond to appear and receive sentence when called upon during such period (not exceeding three years) as`
  line `the Court may direct, and in the meantime to keep the peace and be of good behavior:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any first offender is convicted by a Magistrate of the second class not specially`
  line `empowered by the High Court, and the Magistrate is of opinion that the powers conferred by this section`
  line `should be exercised, he shall record his opinion to that effect, and submit the proceedings to a Magistrate`
  line `of the first class, forwarding the accused to, or taking bail for his appearance before, such Magistrate, who`
  line `shall dispose of the case in the manner provided by sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) Where proceedings are submitted to a Magistrate of the first class as provided by sub-section (1) ,`
  line `such Magistrate may thereupon pass such sentence or make such order as he might have passed or made if`
  line `the case had originally been heard by him, and, if he thinks further inquiry or additional evidence on any`
  line `point to be necessary, he may make such inquiry or take such evidence himself or direct such inquiry or`
  line `evidence to be made or taken.`
  line
  line `(3) In any case in which a person is convicted of theft, theft in a building, dishonest misappropriation,`
  line `cheating or any offence under the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, punishable with not more than two years’`
  line `imprisonment or any offence punishable with fine only and no previous conviction is proved against him,`
  line `the Court before which he is so convicted may, if it thinks fit, having regard to the age, character,`
  line `antecedents or physical or mental condition of the offender and to the trivial nature of the offence or any`
  line `extenuating circumstances under which the offence was committed, instead of sentencing him to any`
  line `punishment, release him after due admonition.`
  line
  line `(4) An order under this section may be made by any Appellate Court or by the High Court or Court of`
  line `Session when exercising its powers of revision.`
  line
  line `(5) When an order has been made under this section in respect of any offender, the High Court or Court`
  line `of Session may, on appeal when there is a right of appeal to such Court, or when exercising its powers of`
  line `revision, set aside such order, and in lieu thereof pass sentence on such offender according to law:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court or Court of Session shall not under this sub-section inflict a greater`
  line `punishment than might have been inflicted by the Court by which the offender was convicted.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of sections 140, 143 and 414 shall, so far as may be, apply in the case of sureties`
  line `offered in pursuance of the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(7) The Court, before directing the release of an offender under sub-section (1), shall be satisfied that`
  line `an offender or his surety (if any) has a fixed place of abode or regular occupation in the place for which the`
  line `Court acts or in which the offender is likely to live during the period named for the observance of the`
  line conditions.
  line
  line `(8) If the Court which convicted the offender, or a Court which could have dealt with the offender in`
  line `respect of his original offence, is satisfied that the offender has failed to observe any of the conditions of`
  line `his recognizance, it may issue a warrant for his apprehension.`
  line
  line `(9) An offender, when apprehended on any such warrant, shall be brought forthwith before the Court`
  line `issuing the warrant, and such Court may either remand him in custody until the case is heard or admit him`
  line `to bail with a sufficient surety conditioned on his appearing for sentence and such Court may, after hearing`
  line `the case, pass sentence.`
  line
  line `(10) Nothing in this section shall affect the provisions of the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958`
  line `(20 of 1958), or the Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2015 (2 of 2016) or any other`
  line `law for the time being in force for the treatment, training or rehabilitation of youthful offenders.`
obj_root_law_sections_401_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_402:
  sectionId (91387)
  sectionNo (402)
  orderNo 402
  title `Special reasons to be recorded in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_402_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_402_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91387&sectionno=402&orderno=402&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_402_content:
  string
  line `Where in any case the Court could have dealt`
  line with,---
  line
  line `(a) an accused person under section 401 or under the provisions of the Probation of Offenders Act,`
  line `1958 (20 of 1958); or`
  line
  line `(b) a youthful offender under the Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2015`
  line `(2 of 2016) or any other law for the time being in force for the treatment, training or rehabilitation of`
  line `youthful offenders,`
  line
  line `but has not done so, it shall record in its judgment the special reasons for not having done so.`
obj_root_law_sections_402_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_403:
  sectionId (91388)
  sectionNo (403)
  orderNo 403
  title `Court not to alter judgment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_403_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_403_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91388&sectionno=403&orderno=403&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_403_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided by this Sanhita or by any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, no Court, when it has signed its judgment or final order disposing of a case,`
  line `shall alter or review the same except to correct a clerical or arithmetical error.`
obj_root_law_sections_403_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_404:
  sectionId (91389)
  sectionNo (404)
  orderNo 404
  title `Copy of judgment to be given to accused and other persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_404_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_404_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91389&sectionno=404&orderno=404&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_404_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the accused is`
  line `sentenced to imprisonment, a copy of the judgment shall, immediately after the pronouncement of the`
  line `judgment, be given to him free of cost.`
  line
  line `(2) On the application of the accused, a certified copy of the judgment, or when he so desires, a`
  line `translation in his own language if practicable or in the language of the Court, shall be given to him without`
  line `delay, and such copy shall, in every case where the judgment is appealable by the accused, be given free of`
  line `cost:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a sentence of death is passed or confirmed by the High Court, a certified copy of`
  line `the judgment shall be immediately given to the accused free of cost whether or not he applies for the same.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (2) shall apply in relation to an order under section 136 as they apply`
  line `in relation to a judgment which is appealable by the accused.`
  line
  line `(4) When the accused is sentenced to death by any Court and an appeal lies from such judgment as of`
  line `right, the Court shall inform him of the period within which, if he wishes to appeal, his appeal should be`
  line preferred.
  line
  line `(5) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (2), any person affected by a judgment or order passed`
  line `by a Criminal Court shall, on an application made in this behalf and on payment of the prescribed charges,`
  line `be given a copy of such judgment or order or of any deposition or other part of the record:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may, if it thinks fit for some special reason, give it to him free of cost:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Court may, on an application made in this behalf by the Prosecuting Officer,`
  line `provide to the Government, free of cost, a certified copy of such judgment, order, deposition or record.`
  line
  line `(6) The High Court may, by rules, provide for the grant of copies of any judgment or order of a Criminal`
  line `Court to any person who is not affected by a judgment or order, on payment, by such person, of such fees,`
  line `and subject to such conditions, as the High Court may, by such rules, provide.`
obj_root_law_sections_404_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_405:
  sectionId (91390)
  sectionNo (405)
  orderNo 405
  title `Judgment when to be translated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_405_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_405_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91390&sectionno=405&orderno=405&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_405_content:
  string
  line `The original judgment shall be filed with the record of the`
  line `proceedings and where the original is recorded in a language different from that of the Court, and if either`
  line `party so requires, a translation thereof into the language of the Court shall be added to such record.`
obj_root_law_sections_405_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_406:
  sectionId (91391)
  sectionNo (406)
  orderNo 406
  title `Court of Session to send copy of finding and sentence to District Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_406_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_406_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91391&sectionno=406&orderno=406&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_406_content:
  string
  line `In cases tried`
  line `by the Court of Session or a Chief Judicial Magistrate, the Court or such Magistrate, as the case may be,`
  line `shall forward a copy of its or his finding and sentence (if any) to the District Magistrate within whose local`
  line `jurisdiction the trial was held.`
obj_root_law_sections_406_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_407:
  sectionId (91392)
  sectionNo (407)
  orderNo 407
  title `Sentence of death to be submitted by Court of Session for confirmation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_407_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_407_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91392&sectionno=407&orderno=407&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_407_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the Court`
  line `of Session passes a sentence of death, the proceedings shall forthwith be submitted to the High Court, and`
  line `the sentence shall not be executed unless it is confirmed by the High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court passing the sentence shall commit the convicted person to jail custody under a warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_407_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_408:
  sectionId (91393)
  sectionNo (408)
  orderNo 408
  title `Power to direct further inquiry to be made or additional evidence to be taken.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_408_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_408_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91393&sectionno=408&orderno=408&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_408_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, when`
  line `such proceedings are submitted, the High Court thinks that a further inquiry should be made into, or`
  line `additional evidence taken upon, any point bearing upon the guilt or innocence of the convicted person, it`
  line `may make such inquiry or take such evidence itself, or direct it to be made or taken by the Court of Session.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless the High Court otherwise directs, the presence of the convicted person may be dispensed`
  line `with when such inquiry is made or such evidence is taken.`
  line
  line `(3) When the inquiry or evidence (if any) is not made or taken by the High Court, the result of such`
  line `inquiry or evidence shall be certified to such Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_408_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_409:
  sectionId (91394)
  sectionNo (409)
  orderNo 409
  title `Power of High Court to confirm sentence or annul conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_409_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_409_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91394&sectionno=409&orderno=409&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_409_content:
  string
  line `In any case submitted under`
  line `section 407, the High Court---`
  line
  line `(a) may confirm the sentence, or pass any other sentence warranted by law; or`
  line
  line `(b) may annul the conviction, and convict the accused of any offence of which the Court of Session`
  line `might have convicted him, or order a new trial on the same or an amended charge; or`
  line
  line `(c) may acquit the accused person:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of confirmation shall be made under this section until the period allowed for`
  line `preferring an appeal has expired, or, if an appeal is presented within such period, until such appeal is`
  line `disposed of.`
obj_root_law_sections_409_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_410:
  sectionId (91395)
  sectionNo (410)
  orderNo 410
  title `Confirmation or new sentence to be signed by two Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_410_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_410_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91395&sectionno=410&orderno=410&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_410_content:
  string
  line `In every case so submitted, the`
  line `confirmation of the sentence, or any new sentence or order passed by the High Court, shall, when such`
  line `Court consists of two or more Judges, be made, passed and signed by at least two of them.`
obj_root_law_sections_410_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_411:
  sectionId (91396)
  sectionNo (411)
  orderNo 411
  title `Procedure in case of difference of opinion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_411_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_411_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91396&sectionno=411&orderno=411&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_411_content:
  string
  line `Where any such case is heard before a Bench of`
  line `Judges and such Judges are equally divided in opinion, the case shall be decided in the manner provided by`
  line `section 433.`
obj_root_law_sections_411_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_412:
  sectionId (91397)
  sectionNo (412)
  orderNo 412
  title `Procedure in cases submitted to High Court for confirmation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_412_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_412_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91397&sectionno=412&orderno=412&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_412_content:
  string
  line `In cases submitted by the`
  line `Court of Session to the High Court for the confirmation of a sentence of death, the proper officer of the`
  line `High Court shall, without delay, after the order of confirmation or other order has been made by the High`
  line `Court, send either physically, or through electronic means, a copy of the order, under the seal of the High`
  line `Court and attested with his official signature, to the Court of Session.`
obj_root_law_sections_412_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_413:
  sectionId (91398)
  sectionNo (413)
  orderNo 413
  title `No appeal to lie unless otherwise provided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_413_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_413_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91398&sectionno=413&orderno=413&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_413_content:
  string
  line `No appeal shall lie from any judgment or order of`
  line `a Criminal Court except as provided for by this Sanhita or by any other law for the time being in force:`
  line `Provided that the victim shall have a right to prefer an appeal against any order passed by the Court`
  line `acquitting the accused or convicting for a lesser offence or imposing inadequate compensation, and such`
  line `appeal shall lie to the Court to which an appeal ordinarily lies against the order of conviction of such Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_413_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_414:
  sectionId (91563)
  sectionNo (414)
  orderNo 414
  title `Appeal from orders requiring security or refusal to accept or rejecting surety for keeping peace or good behavior.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_414_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_414_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91563&sectionno=414&orderno=414&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_414_content:
  string
  line `Any person, ---`
  line
  line `(i) who has been ordered under section 136 to give security for keeping the peace or for good`
  line `behaviour; or`
  line
  line `(ii) who is aggrieved by any order refusing to accept or rejecting a surety under section 140,`
  line
  line `may appeal against such order to the Court of Session:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to persons the proceedings against whom are laid before`
  line `a Sessions Judge in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) or sub-section (4) of section 141.`
obj_root_law_sections_414_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_415:
  sectionId (91400)
  sectionNo (415)
  orderNo 415
  title `Appeals from convictions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_415_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_415_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91400&sectionno=415&orderno=415&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_415_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person convicted on a trial held by a High Court in its`
  line `extraordinary original criminal jurisdiction may appeal to the Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person convicted on a trial held by a Sessions Judge or an Additional Sessions Judge or on a`
  line `trial held by any other Court in which a sentence of imprisonment for more than seven years has been`
  line `passed against him or against any other person convicted at the same trial, may appeal to the High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (2), any person,---`
  line
  line `(a) convicted on a trial held by Magistrate of the first class, or of the second class; or`
  line
  line `(b) sentenced under section 364; or`
  line
  line `(c) in respect of whom an order has been made or a sentence has been passed under section 401 by`
  line `any Magistrate,`
  line
  line `may appeal to the Court of Session.`
  line
  line `(4) When an appeal has been filed against a sentence passed under section 64, section 65,`
  line `section 66, section 67, section 68, section 70 or section 71 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, the appeal`
  line `shall be disposed of within a period of six months from the date of filing of such appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_415_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_416:
  sectionId (91401)
  sectionNo (416)
  orderNo 416
  title `No appeal in certain cases when accused pleads guilty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_416_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_416_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91401&sectionno=416&orderno=416&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_416_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in section`
  line `415, where an accused person has pleaded guilty and has been convicted on such plea, there shall be no`
  line appeal,---
  line
  line `(i) if the conviction is by a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if the conviction is by a Court of Session or Magistrate of the first or second class, except as to`
  line `the extent or legality of the sentence.`
obj_root_law_sections_416_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_417:
  sectionId (91402)
  sectionNo (417)
  orderNo 417
  title `No appeal in petty cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_417_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_417_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91402&sectionno=417&orderno=417&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_417_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in section 415, there shall be no appeal by`
  line `a convicted person in any of the following cases, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) where a High Court passes only a sentence of imprisonment for a term not exceeding three`
  line `months or of fine not exceeding one thousand rupees, or of both such imprisonment and fine;`
  line
  line `(b) where a Court of Session passes only a sentence of imprisonment for a term not exceeding three`
  line `months or of fine not exceeding two hundred rupees, or of both such imprisonment and fine;`
  line
  line `(c) where a Magistrate of the first class passes only a sentence of fine not exceeding one hundred`
  line `rupees; or`
  line
  line `(d) where, in a case tried summarily, a Magistrate empowered to act under section 283 passes only`
  line `a sentence of fine not exceeding two hundred rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be brought against any such sentence if any other punishment is combined`
  line `with it, but such sentence shall not be appealable merely on the ground---`
  line
  line `(i) that the person convicted is ordered to furnish security to keep the peace; or`
  line
  line `(ii) that a direction for imprisonment in default of payment of fine is included in the sentence; or`
  line
  line `(iii) that more than one sentence of fine is passed in the case, if the total amount of fine imposed`
  line `does not exceed the amount hereinbefore specified in respect of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_417_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_418:
  sectionId (91403)
  sectionNo (418)
  orderNo 418
  title `Appeal by State Government against sentence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_418_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_418_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91403&sectionno=418&orderno=418&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_418_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in`
  line `sub-section (2), the State Government may, in any case of conviction on a trial held by any Court other than`
  line `a High Court, direct the Public Prosecutor to present an appeal against the sentence on the ground of its`
  line inadequacy---
  line
  line `(a) to the Court of Session, if the sentence is passed by the Magistrate; and`
  line
  line `(b) to the High Court, if the sentence is passed by any other Court.`
  line
  line `(2) If such conviction is in a case in which the offence has been investigated by any agency empowered`
  line `to make investigation into an offence under any Central Act other than this Sanhita, the Central Government`
  line `may also direct the Public Prosecutor to present an appeal against the sentence on the ground of its`
  line inadequacy---
  line
  line `(a) to the Court of Session, if the sentence is passed by the Magistrate; and`
  line
  line `(b) to the High Court, if the sentence is passed by any other Court.`
  line
  line `(3) When an appeal has been filed against the sentence on the ground of its inadequacy, the Court of`
  line `Session or, as the case may be, the High Court shall not enhance the sentence except after giving to the`
  line `accused a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such enhancement and while showing cause,`
  line `the accused may plead for his acquittal or for the reduction of the sentence.`
  line
  line `(4) When an appeal has been filed against a sentence passed under section 64, section 65,`
  line `section 66, section 67, section 68, section 70 or section 71 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, the appeal`
  line `shall be disposed of within a period of six months from the date of filing of such appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_418_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_419:
  sectionId (91404)
  sectionNo (419)
  orderNo 419
  title `Appeal in case of acquittal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_419_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_419_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91404&sectionno=419&orderno=419&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_419_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (2), and subject`
  line `to the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (5),---`
  line
  line `(a) the District Magistrate may, in any case, direct the Public Prosecutor to present an appeal to the`
  line `Court of Session from an order of acquittal passed by a Magistrate in respect of a cognizable and nonbailable offence;`
  line
  line `(b) the State Government may, in any case, direct the Public Prosecutor to present an appeal to the`
  line `High Court from an original or appellate order of acquittal passed by any Court other than a High Court`
  line `not being an order under clause (a) or an order of acquittal passed by the Court of Session in revision.`
  line
  line `(2) If such an order of acquittal is passed in a case in which the offence has been investigated by any`
  line `agency empowered to make investigation into an offence under any Central Act other than this Sanhita, the`
  line `Central Government may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), also direct the Public Prosecutor to`
  line `present an appeal---`
  line
  line `(a) to the Court of Session, from an order of acquittal passed by a Magistrate in respect of a`
  line `cognizable and non-bailable offence;`
  line
  line `(b) to the High Court from an original or appellate order of an acquittal passed by any Court other`
  line `than a High Court not being an order under clause (a) or an order of acquittal passed by the Court of`
  line `Session in revision.`
  line
  line `(3) No appeal to the High Court under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be entertained except`
  line `with the leave of the High Court.`
  line
  line `(4) If such an order of acquittal is passed in any case instituted upon complaint and the High Court, on`
  line `an application made to it by the complainant in this behalf, grants special leave to appeal from the order of`
  line `acquittal, the complainant may present such an appeal to the High Court.`
  line
  line `(5) No application under sub-section (4) for the grant of special leave to appeal from an order of`
  line `acquittal shall be entertained by the High Court after the expiry of six months, where the complainant is a`
  line `public servant, and sixty days in every other case, computed from the date of that order of acquittal.`
  line
  line `(6) If, in any case, the application under sub-section (4) for the grant of special leave to appeal from an`
  line `order of acquittal is refused, no appeal from that order of acquittal shall lie under sub-section (1) or under`
  line `sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_419_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_420:
  sectionId (91405)
  sectionNo (420)
  orderNo 420
  title `Appeal against conviction by High Court in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_420_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_420_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91405&sectionno=420&orderno=420&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_420_content:
  string
  line `Where the High Court has, on`
  line `appeal, reversed an order of acquittal of an accused person and convicted him and sentenced him to death`
  line `or to imprisonment for life or to imprisonment for a term of ten years or more, he may appeal to the Supreme`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_420_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_421:
  sectionId (91406)
  sectionNo (421)
  orderNo 421
  title `Special right of appeal in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_421_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_421_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91406&sectionno=421&orderno=421&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_421_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in this Chapter, when more`
  line `persons than one are convicted in one trial, and an appealable judgment or order has been passed in respect`
  line `of any of such persons, all or any of the persons convicted at such trial shall have a right of appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_421_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_422:
  sectionId (91407)
  sectionNo (422)
  orderNo 422
  title `Appeal to Court of Session how heard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_422_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_422_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91407&sectionno=422&orderno=422&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_422_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), an`
  line `appeal to the Court of Session or Sessions Judge shall be heard by the Sessions Judge or by an Additional`
  line `Sessions Judge:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal against a conviction on a trial held by a Magistrate of the second class may be`
  line `heard and disposed of by the Chief Judicial Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) An Additional Sessions Judge or a Chief Judicial Magistrate shall hear only such appeals as the`
  line `Sessions Judge of the division may, by general or special order, make over to him or as the High Court`
  line `may, by special order, direct him to hear.`
obj_root_law_sections_422_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_423:
  sectionId (91408)
  sectionNo (423)
  orderNo 423
  title `Petition of appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_423_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_423_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91408&sectionno=423&orderno=423&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_423_content:
  string
  line `Every appeal shall be made in the form of a petition in writing presented by`
  line `the appellant or his advocate, and every such petition shall (unless the Court to which it is presented`
  line `otherwise directs) be accompanied by a copy of the judgment or order appealed against.`
obj_root_law_sections_423_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_424:
  sectionId (91409)
  sectionNo (424)
  orderNo 424
  title `Procedure when appellant in jail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_424_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_424_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91409&sectionno=424&orderno=424&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_424_content:
  string
  line `If the appellant is in jail, he may present his petition of`
  line `appeal and the copies accompanying the same to the officer in charge of the jail, who shall thereupon`
  line `forward such petition and copies to the proper Appellate Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_424_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_425:
  sectionId (91410)
  sectionNo (425)
  orderNo 425
  title `Summary dismissal of appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_425_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_425_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91410&sectionno=425&orderno=425&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_425_content:
  string
  line `(1) If upon examining the petition of appeal and copy of the`
  line `judgment received under section 423 or section 424, the Appellate Court considers that there is no sufficient`
  line `ground for interfering, it may dismiss the appeal summarily:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) no appeal presented under section 423 shall be dismissed unless the appellant or his advocate`
  line `has had a reasonable opportunity of being heard in support of the same;`
  line
  line `(b) no appeal presented under section 424 shall be dismissed except after giving the appellant a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in support of the same, unless the Appellate Court considers that`
  line `the appeal is frivolous or that the production of the accused in custody before the Court would involve`
  line `such inconvenience as would be disproportionate in the circumstances of the case;`
  line
  line `(c) no appeal presented under section 424 shall be dismissed summarily until the period allowed`
  line `for preferring such appeal has expired.`
  line
  line `(2) Before dismissing an appeal under this section, the Court may call for the record of the case.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Appellate Court dismissing an appeal under this section is a Court of Session or of the`
  line `Chief Judicial Magistrate, it shall record its reasons for doing so.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an appeal presented under section 424 has been dismissed summarily under this section and`
  line `the Appellate Court finds that another petition of appeal duly presented under section 423 on behalf of the`
  line `same appellant has not been considered by it, that Court may, notwithstanding anything contained in section`
  line `434, if satisfied that it is necessary in the interests of justice so to do, hear and dispose of such appeal in`
  line `accordance with law.`
obj_root_law_sections_425_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_426:
  sectionId (91411)
  sectionNo (426)
  orderNo 426
  title `Procedure for hearing appeals not dismissed summarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_426_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_426_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91411&sectionno=426&orderno=426&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_426_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Appellate Court does not`
  line `dismiss the appeal summarily, it shall cause notice of the time and place at which such appeal will be heard`
  line `to be given---`
  line
  line `(i) to the appellant or his advocate;`
  line
  line `(ii) to such officer as the State Government may appoint in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(iii) if the appeal is from a judgment of conviction in a case instituted upon complaint, to the`
  line complainant;
  line
  line `(iv) if the appeal is under section 418 or section 419, to the accused, and shall also furnish such`
  line `officer, complainant and accused with a copy of the grounds of appeal.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Court shall then send for the record of the case, if such record is not already available`
  line `in that Court, and hear the parties:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the appeal is only as to the extent or the legality of the sentence, the Court may dispose`
  line `of the appeal without sending for the record.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the only ground for appeal from a conviction is the alleged severity of the sentence, the`
  line `appellant shall not, except with the leave of the Court, urge or be heard in support of any other ground.`
obj_root_law_sections_426_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_427:
  sectionId (91412)
  sectionNo (427)
  orderNo 427
  title `Powers of Appellate Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_427_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_427_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91412&sectionno=427&orderno=427&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_427_content:
  string
  line `After perusing such record and hearing the appellant or his`
  line `advocate, if he appears, and the Public Prosecutor if he appears, and in case of an appeal under section 418`
  line `or section 419, the accused, if he appears, the Appellate Court may, if it considers that there is no sufficient`
  line `ground for interfering, dismiss the appeal, or may---`
  line
  line `(a) in an appeal from an order of acquittal, reverse such order and direct that further inquiry be`
  line `made, or that the accused be re-tried or committed for trial, as the case may be, or find him guilty and`
  line `pass sentence on him according to law;`
  line
  line `(b) in an appeal from a conviction---`
  line
  line `(i) reverse the finding and sentence and acquit or discharge the accused, or order him to be`
  line `re-tried by a Court of competent jurisdiction subordinate to such Appellate Court or committed for`
  line `trial; or`
  line
  line `(ii) alter the finding, maintaining the sentence; or`
  line
  line `(iii) with or without altering the finding, alter the nature or the extent, or the nature and extent,`
  line `of the sentence, but not so as to enhance the same;`
  line
  line `(c) in an appeal for enhancement of sentence---`
  line
  line `(i) reverse the finding and sentence and acquit or discharge the accused or order him to be`
  line `re-tried by a Court competent to try the offence; or`
  line
  line `(ii) alter the finding maintaining the sentence; or`
  line
  line `(iii) with or without altering the finding, alter the nature or the extent, or, the nature and extent,`
  line `of the sentence, so as to enhance or reduce the same;`
  line
  line `(d) in an appeal from any other order, alter or reverse such order;`
  line
  line `(e) make any amendment or any consequential or incidental order that may be just or proper:`
  line
  line `Provided that the sentence shall not be enhanced unless the accused has had an opportunity of showing`
  line `cause against such enhancement:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Appellate Court shall not inflict greater punishment for the offence which in`
  line `its opinion the accused has committed, than might have been inflicted for that offence by the Court passing`
  line `the order or sentence under appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_427_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_428:
  sectionId (91413)
  sectionNo (428)
  orderNo 428
  title `Judgments of subordinate Appellate Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_428_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_428_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91413&sectionno=428&orderno=428&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_428_content:
  string
  line `The rules contained in Chapter XXIX as to the`
  line `judgment of a Criminal Court of original jurisdiction shall apply, so far as may be practicable, to the`
  line `judgment in appeal of a Court of Session or Chief Judicial Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that, unless the Appellate Court otherwise directs, the accused shall not be brought up, or`
  line `required to attend, to hear judgment delivered.`
obj_root_law_sections_428_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_429:
  sectionId (91414)
  sectionNo (429)
  orderNo 429
  title `Order of High Court on appeal to be certified to lower Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_429_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_429_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91414&sectionno=429&orderno=429&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_429_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever a case is decided`
  line `on appeal by the High Court under this Chapter, it shall certify its judgment or order to the Court by which`
  line `the finding, sentence or order appealed against was recorded or passed and if such Court is that of a Judicial`
  line `Magistrate other than the Chief Judicial Magistrate, the High Court's judgment or order shall be sent through`
  line `the Chief Judicial Magistrate, and if such Court is that of an Executive Magistrate, the High Court's`
  line `judgment or order shall be sent through the District Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court to which the High Court certifies its judgment or order shall thereupon make such orders`
  line `as are conformable to the judgment or order of the High Court; and if necessary, the record shall be amended`
  line `in accordance therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_429_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_430:
  sectionId (91415)
  sectionNo (430)
  orderNo 430
  title `Suspension of sentence pending appeal; release of appellant on bail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_430_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_430_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91415&sectionno=430&orderno=430&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_430_content:
  string
  line `(1) Pending any appeal`
  line `by a convicted person, the Appellate Court may, for reasons to be recorded by it in writing, order that the`
  line `execution of the sentence or order appealed against be suspended and, also, if he is in confinement, that he`
  line `be released on bail, or on his own bond or bail bond:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Court shall, before releasing on his own bond or bail bond a convicted`
  line `person who is convicted of an offence punishable with death or imprisonment for life or imprisonment for`
  line `a term of not less than ten years, shall give opportunity to the Public Prosecutor for showing cause in writing`
  line `against such release:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in cases where a convicted person is released on bail it shall be open to the Public`
  line `Prosecutor to file an application for the cancellation of the bail.`
  line
  line `(2) The power conferred by this section on an Appellate Court may be exercised also by the High Court`
  line `in the case of an appeal by a convicted person to a Court subordinate thereto.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the convicted person satisfies the Court by which he is convicted that he intends to present`
  line `an appeal, the Court shall,---`
  line
  line `(i) where such person, being on bail, is sentenced to imprisonment for a term not exceeding three`
  line `years; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where the offence of which such person has been convicted is a bailable one, and he is on bail,`
  line
  line `order that the convicted person be released on bail, unless there are special reasons for refusing bail, for`
  line `such period as will afford sufficient time to present the appeal and obtain the orders of the Appellate Court`
  line `under sub-section (1); and the sentence of imprisonment shall, so long as he is so released on bail, be`
  line `deemed to be suspended.`
  line
  line `(4) When the appellant is ultimately sentenced to imprisonment for a term or to imprisonment for life,`
  line `the time during which he is so released shall be excluded in computing the term for which he is so sentenced.`
obj_root_law_sections_430_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_431:
  sectionId (91416)
  sectionNo (431)
  orderNo 431
  title `Arrest of accused in appeal from acquittal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_431_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_431_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91416&sectionno=431&orderno=431&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_431_content:
  string
  line `When an appeal is presented under section 419,`
  line `the High Court may issue a warrant directing that the accused be arrested and brought before it or any`
  line `subordinate Court, and the Court before which he is brought may commit him to prison pending the disposal`
  line `of the appeal or admit him to bail.`
obj_root_law_sections_431_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_432:
  sectionId (91417)
  sectionNo (432)
  orderNo 432
  title `Appellate Court may take further evidence or direct it to be taken.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_432_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_432_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91417&sectionno=432&orderno=432&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_432_content:
  string
  line `(1) In dealing with any`
  line `appeal under this Chapter, the Appellate Court, if it thinks additional evidence to be necessary, shall record`
  line `its reasons and may either take such evidence itself, or direct it to be taken by a Magistrate or, when the`
  line `Appellate Court is a High Court, by a Court of Session or a Magistrate.`
  line
  line `(2) When the additional evidence is taken by the Court of Session or the Magistrate, it or he shall certify`
  line `such evidence to the Appellate Court, and such Court shall thereupon proceed to dispose of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(3) The accused or his advocate shall have the right to be present when the additional evidence is taken.`
  line
  line `(4) The taking of evidence under this section shall be subject to the provisions of Chapter XXV, as if it`
  line `were an inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_432_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_433:
  sectionId (91418)
  sectionNo (433)
  orderNo 433
  title `Procedure where Judges of Court of appeal are equally divided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_433_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_433_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91418&sectionno=433&orderno=433&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_433_content:
  string
  line `When an appeal under this`
  line `Chapter is heard by a High Court before a Bench of Judges and they are divided in opinion, the appeal, with`
  line `their opinions, shall be laid before another Judge of that Court, and that Judge, after such hearing as he`
  line `thinks fit, shall deliver his opinion, and the judgment or order shall follow that opinion:`
  line
  line `Provided that if one of the Judges constituting the Bench, or, where the appeal is laid before another`
  line `Judge under this section, that Judge, so requires, the appeal shall be re-heard and decided by a larger Bench`
  line `of Judges.`
obj_root_law_sections_433_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_434:
  sectionId (91419)
  sectionNo (434)
  orderNo 434
  title `Finality of judgments and orders on appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_434_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_434_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91419&sectionno=434&orderno=434&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_434_content:
  string
  line `Judgments and orders passed by an Appellate`
  line `Court upon an appeal shall be final, except in the cases provided for in section 418, section 419,`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 425 or Chapter XXXII:`
  line
  line `Provided that notwithstanding the final disposal of an appeal against conviction in any case, the`
  line
  line `Appellate Court may hear and dispose of, on the merits,---`
  line
  line `(a) an appeal against acquittal under section 419, arising out of the same case; or`
  line
  line `(b) an appeal for the enhancement of sentence under section 418, arising out of the same case.`
obj_root_law_sections_434_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_435:
  sectionId (91420)
  sectionNo (435)
  orderNo 435
  title `Abatement of appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_435_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_435_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91420&sectionno=435&orderno=435&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_435_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every appeal under section 418 or section 419 shall finally abate on`
  line `the death of the accused.`
  line
  line `(2) Every other appeal under this Chapter (except an appeal from a sentence of fine) shall finally abate`
  line `on the death of the appellant:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the appeal is against a conviction and sentence of death or of imprisonment, and`
  line `the appellant dies during the pendency of the appeal, any of his near relatives may, within thirty days of the`
  line `death of the appellant, apply to the Appellate Court for leave to continue the appeal; and if leave is granted,`
  line `the appeal shall not abate.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, "near relative" means a parent, spouse, lineal descendant, brother or`
  line sister.
obj_root_law_sections_435_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_436:
  sectionId (91421)
  sectionNo (436)
  orderNo 436
  title `Reference to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_436_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_436_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91421&sectionno=436&orderno=436&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_436_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any Court is satisfied that a case pending before it involves`
  line `a question as to the validity of any Act, Ordinance or Regulation or of any provision contained in an Act,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation, the determination of which is necessary for the disposal of the case, and is of`
  line `opinion that such Act, Ordinance, Regulation or provision is invalid or inoperative, but has not been so`
  line `declared by the High Court to which that Court is subordinate or by the Supreme Court, the Court shall`
  line `state a case setting out its opinion and the reasons therefor, and refer the same for the decision of the High`
  line Court.
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, "Regulation" means any Regulation as defined in the General Clauses`
  line `Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), or in the General Clauses Act of a State.`
  line
  line `(2) A Court of Session may, if it thinks fit in any case pending before it to which the provisions of subsection (1) do not apply, refer for the decision of the High Court any question of law arising in the hearing`
  line `of such case.`
  line
  line `(3) Any Court making a reference to the High Court under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) may,`
  line `pending the decision of the High Court thereon, either commit the accused to jail or release him on bail to`
  line `appear when called upon.`
obj_root_law_sections_436_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_437:
  sectionId (91422)
  sectionNo (437)
  orderNo 437
  title `Disposal of case according to decision of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_437_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_437_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91422&sectionno=437&orderno=437&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_437_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a question has been so`
  line `referred, the High Court shall pass such order thereon as it thinks fit, and shall cause a copy of such order`
  line `to be sent to the Court by which the reference was made, which shall dispose of the case conformably to`
  line `the said order.`
  line
  line `(2) The High Court may direct by whom the costs of such reference shall be paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_437_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_438:
  sectionId (91423)
  sectionNo (438)
  orderNo 438
  title `Calling for records to exercise powers of revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_438_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_438_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91423&sectionno=438&orderno=438&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_438_content:
  string
  line `(1) The High Court or any Sessions Judge`
  line `may call for and examine the record of any proceeding before any inferior Criminal Court situate within its`
  line `or his local jurisdiction for the purpose of satisfying itself or himself as to the correctness, legality or`
  line `propriety of any finding, sentence or order, recorded or passed, and as to the regularity of any proceedings`
  line `of such inferior Court, and may, when calling, for such record, direct that the execution of any sentence or`
  line `order be suspended, and if the accused is in confinement that he be released on his own bond or bail bond`
  line `pending the examination of the record.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—All Magistrates, whether Executive or Judicial, and whether exercising original or`
  line `appellate jurisdiction, shall be deemed to be inferior to the Sessions Judge for the purposes of this subsection and of section 439.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers of revision conferred by sub-section (1) shall not be exercised in relation to any`
  line `interlocutory order passed in any appeal, inquiry, trial or other proceeding.`
  line
  line `(3) If an application under this section has been made by any person either to the High Court or to the`
  line `Sessions Judge, no further application by the same person shall be entertained by the other of them.`
obj_root_law_sections_438_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_439:
  sectionId (91424)
  sectionNo (439)
  orderNo 439
  title `Power to order inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_439_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_439_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91424&sectionno=439&orderno=439&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_439_content:
  string
  line `On examining any record under section 438 or otherwise, the High`
  line `Court or the Sessions Judge may direct the Chief Judicial Magistrate by himself or by any of the Magistrates`
  line `subordinate to him to make, and the Chief Judicial Magistrate may himself make or direct any subordinate`
  line `Magistrate to make, further inquiry into any complaint which has been dismissed under section 226 or subsection (4) of section 227, or into the case of any person accused of an offence who has been discharged:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Court shall make any direction under this section for inquiry into the case of any`
  line `person who has been discharged unless such person has had an opportunity of showing cause why such`
  line `direction should not be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_439_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_440:
  sectionId (91425)
  sectionNo (440)
  orderNo 440
  title `Sessions Judge's powers of revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_440_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_440_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91425&sectionno=440&orderno=440&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_440_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of any proceeding the record of which has`
  line `been called for by himself, the Sessions Judge may exercise all or any of the powers which may be exercised`
  line `by the High Court under sub-section (1) of section 442.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any proceeding by way of revision is commenced before a Sessions Judge under`
  line `sub-section (1), the provisions of sub-sections (2), (3), (4) and (5) of section 442 shall, so far as may be,`
  line `apply to such proceeding and references in the said sub-sections to the High Court shall be construed as`
  line `references to the Sessions Judge.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any application for revision is made by or on behalf of any person before the Sessions Judge,`
  line `the decision of the Sessions Judge thereon in relation to such person shall be final and no further proceeding`
  line `by way of revision at the instance of such person shall be entertained by the High Court or any other Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_440_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_441:
  sectionId (91426)
  sectionNo (441)
  orderNo 441
  title `Power of Additional Sessions Judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_441_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_441_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91426&sectionno=441&orderno=441&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_441_content:
  string
  line `An Additional Sessions Judge shall have and may`
  line `exercise all the powers of a Sessions Judge under this Chapter in respect of any case which may be`
  line `transferred to him by or under any general or special order of the Sessions Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_441_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_442:
  sectionId (91427)
  sectionNo (442)
  orderNo 442
  title `High Court's powers of revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_442_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_442_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91427&sectionno=442&orderno=442&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_442_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the case of any proceeding the record of which has`
  line `been called for by itself or which otherwise comes to its knowledge, the High Court may, in its discretion,`
  line `exercise any of the powers conferred on a Court of Appeal by sections 427, 430, 431 and 432 or on a Court`
  line `of Session by section 344, and, when the Judges composing the Court of revision are equally divided in`
  line `opinion, the case shall be disposed of in the manner provided by section 433.`
  line
  line `(2) No order under this section shall be made to the prejudice of the accused or other person unless he`
  line `has had an opportunity of being heard either personally or by advocate in his own defence.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to authorise a High Court to convert a finding of acquittal`
  line `into one of conviction.`
  line
  line `(4) Where under this Sanhita an appeal lies and no appeal is brought, no proceeding by way of revision`
  line `shall be entertained at the instance of the party who could have appealed.`
  line
  line `(5) Where under this Sanhita an appeal lies but an application for revision has been made to the High`
  line `Court by any person and the High Court is satisfied that such application was made under the erroneous`
  line `belief that no appeal lies thereto and that it is necessary in the interests of justice so to do, the High Court`
  line `may treat the application for revision as a petition of appeal and deal with the same accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_442_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_443:
  sectionId (91428)
  sectionNo (443)
  orderNo 443
  title `Power of High Court to withdraw or transfer revision cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_443_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_443_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91428&sectionno=443&orderno=443&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_443_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever one or more`
  line `persons convicted at the same trial makes or make application to a High Court for revision and any other`
  line `person convicted at the same trial makes an application to the Sessions Judge for revision, the High Court`
  line `shall decide, having regard to the general convenience of the parties and the importance of the questions`
  line `involved, which of the two Courts should finally dispose of the applications for revision and when the High`
  line `Court decides that all the applications for revision should be disposed of by itself, the High Court shall`
  line `direct that the applications for revision pending before the Sessions Judge be transferred to itself and where`
  line `the High Court decides that it is not necessary for it to dispose of the applications for revision, it shall direct`
  line `that the applications for revision made to it be transferred to the Sessions Judge.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any application for revision is transferred to the High Court, that Court shall deal with`
  line `the same as if it were an application duly made before itself.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever any application for revision is transferred to the Sessions Judge, that Judge shall deal`
  line `with the same as if it were an application duly made before himself.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an application for revision is transferred by the High Court to the Sessions Judge, no further`
  line `application for revision shall lie to the High Court or to any other Court at the instance of the person or`
  line `persons whose applications for revision have been disposed of by the Sessions Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_443_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_444:
  sectionId (91429)
  sectionNo (444)
  orderNo 444
  title `Option of Court to hear parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_444_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_444_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91429&sectionno=444&orderno=444&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_444_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided by this Sanhita, no party`
  line `has any right to be heard either personally or by an advocate before any Court exercising its powers of`
  line `revision; but the Court may, if it thinks fit, when exercising such powers, hear any party either personally`
  line `or by an advocate.`
obj_root_law_sections_444_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_445:
  sectionId (91430)
  sectionNo (445)
  orderNo 445
  title `High Court's order to be certified to lower Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_445_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_445_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91430&sectionno=445&orderno=445&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_445_content:
  string
  line `When a case is revised under this Chapter`
  line `by the High Court or a Sessions Judge, it or he shall, in the manner provided by section 429, certify its`
  line `decision or order to the Court by which the finding, sentence or order revised was recorded or passed, and`
  line `the Court to which the decision or order is so certified shall thereupon make such orders as are conformable`
  line `to the decision so certified, and, if necessary, the record shall be amended in accordance therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_445_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_446:
  sectionId (91431)
  sectionNo (446)
  orderNo 446
  title `Power of Supreme Court to transfer cases and appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_446_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_446_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91431&sectionno=446&orderno=446&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_446_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it is made to appear to`
  line `the Supreme Court that an order under this section is expedient for the ends of justice, it may direct that any`
  line `particular case or appeal be transferred from one High Court to another High Court or from a Criminal`
  line `Court subordinate to one High Court to another Criminal Court of equal or superior jurisdiction subordinate`
  line `to another High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The Supreme Court may act under this section only on the application of the Attorney-General of`
  line `India or of a party interested, and every such application shall be made by motion, which shall, except when`
  line `the applicant is the Attorney-General of India or the Advocate-General of the State, be supported by`
  line `affidavit or affirmation.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any application for the exercise of the powers conferred by this section is dismissed, the`
  line `Supreme Court may, if it is of opinion that the application was frivolous or vexatious, order the applicant`
  line `to pay by way of compensation to any person who has opposed the application such sum as it may consider`
  line `appropriate in the circumstances of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_446_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_447:
  sectionId (91432)
  sectionNo (447)
  orderNo 447
  title `Power of High Court to transfer cases and appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_447_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_447_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91432&sectionno=447&orderno=447&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_447_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it is made to appear to the`
  line `High Court---`
  line
  line `(a) that a fair and impartial inquiry or trial cannot be had in any Criminal Court subordinate thereto;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) that some question of law of unusual difficulty is likely to arise; or`
  line
  line `(c) that an order under this section is required by any provision of this Sanhita, or will tend to the`
  line `general convenience of the parties or witnesses, or is expedient for the ends of justice,`
  line
  line `it may order---`
  line
  line `(i) that any offence be inquired into or tried by any Court not qualified under sections 197 to 205`
  line `(both inclusive), but in other respects competent to inquire into or try such offence;`
  line
  line `(ii) that any particular case or appeal, or class of cases or appeals, be transferred from a Criminal`
  line `Court subordinate to its authority to any other such Criminal Court of equal or superior jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(iii) that any particular case be committed for trial to a Court of Session; or`
  line
  line `(iv) that any particular case or appeal be transferred to and tried before itself.`
  line
  line `(2) The High Court may act either on the report of the lower Court, or on the application of a party`
  line `interested, or on its own initiative:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application shall lie to the High Court for transferring a case from one Criminal Court`
  line `to another Criminal Court in the same sessions division, unless an application for such transfer has been`
  line `made to the Sessions Judge and rejected by him.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application for an order under sub-section (1) shall be made by motion, which shall, except`
  line `when the applicant is the Advocate-General of the State, be supported by affidavit or affirmation.`
  line
  line `(4) When such application is made by an accused person, the High Court may direct him to execute a`
  line `bond or bail bond for the payment of any compensation which the High Court may award under`
  line `sub-section (7).`
  line
  line `(5) Every accused person making such application shall give to the Public Prosecutor notice in writing`
  line `of the application, together with a copy of the grounds on which it is made; and no order shall be made on`
  line `the merits of the application unless at least twenty-four hours have elapsed between the giving of such`
  line `notice and the hearing of the application.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the application is for the transfer of a case or appeal from any subordinate Court, the High`
  line `Court may, if it is satisfied that it is necessary so to do in the interest of justice, order that, pending the`
  line `disposal of the application the proceedings in the subordinate Court shall be stayed, on such terms as the`
  line `High Court may think fit to impose:`
  line
  line `Provided that such stay shall not affect the subordinate Court's power of remand under section 346.`
  line
  line `(7) Where an application for an order under sub-section (1) is dismissed, the High Court may, if it is of`
  line `opinion that the application was frivolous or vexatious, order the applicant to pay by way of compensation`
  line `to any person who has opposed the application such sum as it may consider proper in the circumstances of`
  line `the case.`
  line
  line `(8) When the High Court orders under sub-section (1) that a case be transferred from any Court for trial`
  line `before itself, it shall observe in such trial the same procedure which that Court would have observed if the`
  line `case had not been so transferred.`
  line
  line `(9) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect any order of the Government under section 218.`
obj_root_law_sections_447_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_448:
  sectionId (91433)
  sectionNo (448)
  orderNo 448
  title `Power of Sessions Judge to transfer cases and appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_448_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_448_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91433&sectionno=448&orderno=448&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_448_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it is made to appear to`
  line `a Sessions Judge that an order under this sub-section is expedient for the ends of justice, he may order that`
  line `any particular case be transferred from one Criminal Court to another Criminal Court in his sessions`
  line division.
  line
  line `(2) The Sessions Judge may act either on the report of the lower Court, or on the application of a party`
  line `interested, or on his own initiative.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-sections (3), (4), (5), (6), (7) and (9) of section 447 shall apply in relation to`
  line `an application to the Sessions Judge for an order under sub-section (1) as they apply in relation to an`
  line `application to the High Court for an order under sub-section (1) of section 447, except that sub-section (7)`
  line `of that section shall so apply as if for the word "sum" occurring therein, the words "sum not exceeding ten`
  line `thousand rupees" were substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_448_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_449:
  sectionId (91434)
  sectionNo (449)
  orderNo 449
  title `Withdrawal of cases and appeals by Sessions Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_449_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_449_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91434&sectionno=449&orderno=449&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_449_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Sessions Judge may withdraw`
  line `any case or appeal from, or recall any case or appeal which he has made over to a Chief Judicial Magistrate`
  line `subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(2) At any time before the trial of the case or the hearing of the appeal has commenced before the`
  line `Additional Sessions Judge, a Sessions Judge may recall any case or appeal which he has made over to any`
  line `Additional Sessions Judge.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a Sessions Judge withdraws or recalls case or appeal under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2), he may either try the case in his own Court or hear the appeal himself, or make it over in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Sanhita to another Court for trial or hearing, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_449_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_450:
  sectionId (91435)
  sectionNo (450)
  orderNo 450
  title `Withdrawal of cases by Judicial Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_450_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_450_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91435&sectionno=450&orderno=450&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_450_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Chief Judicial Magistrate may`
  line `withdraw any case from, or recall any case which he has made over to, any Magistrate subordinate to him,`
  line `and may inquire into or try such case himself, or refer it for inquiry or trial to any other such Magistrate`
  line `competent to inquire into or try the same.`
  line
  line `(2) Any Judicial Magistrate may recall any case made over by him under sub-section (2) of section 212`
  line `to any other Magistrate and may inquire into or try such cases himself.`
obj_root_law_sections_450_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_451:
  sectionId (91436)
  sectionNo (451)
  orderNo 451
  title `Making over or withdrawal of cases by Executive Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_451_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_451_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91436&sectionno=451&orderno=451&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_451_content:
  string
  line `Any District Magistrate or`
  line `Sub-divisional Magistrate may---`
  line
  line `(a) make over, for disposal, any proceeding which has been started before him, to any Magistrate`
  line `subordinate to him;`
  line
  line `(b) withdraw any case from, or recall any case which he has made over to, any Magistrate subordinate`
  line `to him, and dispose of such proceeding himself or refer it for disposal to any other Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_451_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_452:
  sectionId (91437)
  sectionNo (452)
  orderNo 452
  title `Reasons to be recorded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_452_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_452_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91437&sectionno=452&orderno=452&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_452_content:
  string
  line `A Sessions Judge or Magistrate making an order under section 448,`
  line `section 449, section 450 or section 451 shall record his reasons for making it.`
obj_root_law_sections_452_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_453:
  sectionId (91564)
  sectionNo (453)
  orderNo 453
  title `Execution of order passed under section 409.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_453_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_453_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91564&sectionno=453&orderno=453&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_453_content:
  string
  line `When in a case submitted to the High Court for`
  line `the confirmation of a sentence of death, the Court of Session receives the order of confirmation or other`
  line `order of the High Court thereon, it shall cause such order to be carried into effect by issuing a warrant or`
  line `taking such other steps as may be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_453_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_454:
  sectionId (91439)
  sectionNo (454)
  orderNo 454
  title `Execution of sentence of death passed by High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_454_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_454_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91439&sectionno=454&orderno=454&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_454_content:
  string
  line `When a sentence of death is passed by`
  line `the High Court in appeal or in revision, the Court of Session shall, on receiving the order of the High Court,`
  line `cause the sentence to be carried into effect by issuing a warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_454_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_455:
  sectionId (91440)
  sectionNo (455)
  orderNo 455
  title `Postponement of execution of sentence of death in case of appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_455_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_455_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91440&sectionno=455&orderno=455&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_455_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person is sentenced to death by the High Court and an appeal from its judgment lies`
  line `to the Supreme Court under sub-clause (a) or sub-clause (b) of clause (1) of article 134 of the Constitution,`
  line `the High Court shall order the execution of the sentence to be postponed until the period allowed for`
  line `preferring such appeal has expired, or if, an appeal is preferred within that period, until such appeal is`
  line `disposed of.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a sentence of death is passed or confirmed by the High Court, and the person sentenced`
  line `makes an application to the High Court for the grant of a certificate under article 132 or under sub-clause`
  line `(c) of clause (1) of article 134 of the Constitution, the High Court shall order the execution of the sentence`
  line `to be postponed until such application is disposed of by the High Court, or if a certificate is granted on such`
  line `application, until the period allowed for preferring an appeal to the Supreme Court on such certificate has`
  line expired.
  line
  line `(3) Where a sentence of death is passed or confirmed by the High Court, and the High Court is satisfied`
  line `that the person sentenced intends to present a petition to the Supreme Court for the grant of special leave`
  line `to appeal under article 136 of the Constitution, the High Court shall order the execution of the sentence to`
  line `be postponed for such period as it considers sufficient to enable him to present such petition.`
obj_root_law_sections_455_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_456:
  sectionId (91441)
  sectionNo (456)
  orderNo 456
  title `Commutation of sentence of death on pregnant woman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_456_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_456_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91441&sectionno=456&orderno=456&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_456_content:
  string
  line `If a woman sentenced to death is`
  line `found to be pregnant, the High Court shall commute the sentence to imprisonment for life.`
obj_root_law_sections_456_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_457:
  sectionId (91565)
  sectionNo (457)
  orderNo 457
  title `Power to appoint place of imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_457_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_457_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91565&sectionno=457&orderno=457&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_457_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except when otherwise provided by any law for`
  line `the time being in force, the State Government may direct in what place any person liable to be imprisoned`
  line `or committed to custody under this Sanhita shall be confined.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person liable to be imprisoned or committed to custody under this Sanhita is in confinement`
  line `in a civil jail, the Court or Magistrate ordering the imprisonment or committal may direct that the person`
  line `be removed to a criminal jail.`
  line
  line `(3) When a person is removed to a criminal jail under sub-section (2), he shall, on being released`
  line `therefrom, be sent back to the civil jail, unless either---`
  line
  line `(a) three years have elapsed since he was removed to the criminal jail, in which case he shall be`
  line `deemed to have been released from the civil jail under section 58 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908); or`
  line
  line `(b) the Court which ordered his imprisonment in the civil jail has certified to the officer in charge`
  line `of the criminal jail that he is entitled to be released under section 58 of the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_457_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_458:
  sectionId (91443)
  sectionNo (458)
  orderNo 458
  title `Execution of sentence of imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_458_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_458_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91443&sectionno=458&orderno=458&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_458_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the accused is sentenced to imprisonment`
  line `for life or to imprisonment for a term in cases other than those provided for by section 453, the Court`
  line `passing the sentence shall forthwith forward a warrant to the jail or other place in which he is, or is to be,`
  line `confined, and, unless the accused is already confined in such jail or other place, shall forward him to such`
  line `jail or other place, with the warrant:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the accused is sentenced to imprisonment till the rising of the Court, it shall not be`
  line `necessary to prepare or forward a warrant to a jail, and the accused may be confined in such place as the`
  line `Court may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the accused is not present in Court when he is sentenced to such imprisonment as is`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (1), the Court shall issue a warrant for his arrest for the purpose of forwarding`
  line `him to the jail or other place in which he is to be confined; and in such case, the sentence shall commence`
  line `on the date of his arrest.`
obj_root_law_sections_458_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_459:
  sectionId (91444)
  sectionNo (459)
  orderNo 459
  title `Direction of warrant for execution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_459_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_459_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91444&sectionno=459&orderno=459&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_459_content:
  string
  line `Every warrant for the execution of a sentence of`
  line `imprisonment shall be directed to the officer in charge of the jail or other place in which the prisoner is, or`
  line `is to be, confined.`
obj_root_law_sections_459_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_460:
  sectionId (91445)
  sectionNo (460)
  orderNo 460
  title `Warrant with whom to be lodged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_460_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_460_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91445&sectionno=460&orderno=460&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_460_content:
  string
  line `When the prisoner is to be confined in a jail, the warrant`
  line `shall be lodged with the jailor.`
obj_root_law_sections_460_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_461:
  sectionId (91566)
  sectionNo (461)
  orderNo 461
  title `Warrant for levy of fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_461_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_461_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91566&sectionno=461&orderno=461&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_461_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an offender has been sentenced to pay a fine, but no such`
  line `payment has been made, the Court passing the sentence may take action for the recovery of the fine in either`
  line `or both of the following ways, that is to say, it may---`
  line
  line `(a) issue a warrant for the levy of the amount by attachment and sale of any movable property`
  line `belonging to the offender;`
  line
  line `(b) issue a warrant to the Collector of the district, authorising him to realise the amount as arrears`
  line `of land revenue from the movable or immovable property, or both, of the defaulter:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the sentence directs that in default of payment of the fine, the offender shall be imprisoned,`
  line `and if such offender has undergone the whole of such imprisonment in default, no Court shall issue such warrant`
  line `unless, for special reasons to be recorded in writing, it considers it necessary so to do, or unless it has made an`
  line `order for the payment of expenses or compensation out of the fine under section 395.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may make rules regulating the manner in which warrants under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) are to be executed, and for the summary determination of any claims made by any person`
  line `other than the offender in respect of any property attached in execution of such warrant.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Court issues a warrant to the Collector under clause (b) of sub-section (1), the Collector`
  line `shall realise the amount in accordance with the law relating to recovery of arrears of land revenue, as if`
  line `such warrant were a certificate issued under such law:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such warrant shall be executed by the arrest or detention in prison of the offender.`
obj_root_law_sections_461_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_462:
  sectionId (91447)
  sectionNo (462)
  orderNo 462
  title `Effect of such warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_462_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_462_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91447&sectionno=462&orderno=462&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_462_content:
  string
  line `A warrant issued under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 461 by`
  line `any Court may be executed within the local jurisdiction of such Court, and it shall authorise the attachment`
  line `and sale of any such property outside such jurisdiction, when it is endorsed by the District Magistrate within`
  line `whose local jurisdiction such property is found.`
obj_root_law_sections_462_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_463:
  sectionId (91448)
  sectionNo (463)
  orderNo 463
  title `Warrant for levy of fine issued by a Court in any territory to which this Sanhita does not extend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_463_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_463_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91448&sectionno=463&orderno=463&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_463_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in this Sanhita or in any other law for the time being in force, when an`
  line `offender has been sentenced to pay a fine by a Criminal Court in any territory to which this Sanhita does`
  line `not extend and the Court passing the sentence issues a warrant to the Collector of a district in the territories`
  line `to which this Sanhita extends, authorising him to realise the amount as if it were an arrear of land revenue,`
  line `such warrant shall be deemed to be a warrant issued under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 461 by a`
  line `Court in the territories to which this Sanhita extends, and the provisions of sub-section (3) of the said section`
  line `as to the execution of such warrant shall apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_463_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_464:
  sectionId (91449)
  sectionNo (464)
  orderNo 464
  title `Suspension of execution of sentence of imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_464_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_464_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91449&sectionno=464&orderno=464&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_464_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an offender has been`
  line `sentenced to fine only and to imprisonment in default of payment of the fine, and the fine is not paid`
  line `forthwith, the Court may---`
  line
  line `(a) order that the fine shall be payable either in full on or before a date not more than thirty days`
  line `from the date of the order, or in two or three installments, of which the first shall be payable on or`
  line `before a date not more than thirty days from the date of the order and the other or others at an interval`
  line `or at intervals, as the case may be, of not more than thirty days;`
  line
  line `(b) suspend the execution of the sentence of imprisonment and release the offender, on the`
  line `execution by the offender of a bond or bail bond, as the Court thinks fit, conditioned for his appearance`
  line `before the Court on the date or dates on or before which payment of the fine or the installments thereof,`
  line `as the case may be, is to be made; and if the amount of the fine or of any installment, as the case may`
  line `be, is not realised on or before the latest date on which it is payable under the order, the Court may`
  line `direct the sentence of imprisonment to be carried into execution at once.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall be applicable also in any case in which an order for the`
  line `payment of money has been made on non-recovery of which imprisonment may be awarded and the money`
  line `is not paid forthwith; and, if the person against whom the order has been made, on being required to enter`
  line `into a bond such as is referred to in that sub-section, fails to do so, the Court may at once pass sentence of`
  line imprisonment.
obj_root_law_sections_464_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_465:
  sectionId (91567)
  sectionNo (465)
  orderNo 465
  title `Who may issue warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_465_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_465_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91567&sectionno=465&orderno=465&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_465_content:
  string
  line `Every warrant for the execution of a sentence may be issued either by`
  line `the Judge or Magistrate who passed the sentence, or by his successor-in-office.`
obj_root_law_sections_465_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_466:
  sectionId (91451)
  sectionNo (466)
  orderNo 466
  title `Sentence on escaped convict when to take effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_466_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_466_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91451&sectionno=466&orderno=466&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_466_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a sentence of death, imprisonment`
  line `for life or fine is passed under this Sanhita on an escaped convict, such sentence shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions hereinbefore contained, take effect immediately.`
  line
  line `(2) When a sentence of imprisonment for a term is passed under this Sanhita on an escaped`
  line convict,---
  line
  line `(a) if such sentence is severer in kind than the sentence which such convict was undergoing when`
  line `he escaped, the new sentence shall take effect immediately;`
  line
  line `(b) if such sentence is not severer in kind than the sentence which such convict was undergoing`
  line `when he escaped, the new sentence shall take effect after he has suffered imprisonment for a further`
  line `period equal to that which, at the time of his escape, remained unexpired of his former sentence.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of sub-section (2), a sentence of rigorous imprisonment shall be deemed to be`
  line `severer in kind than a sentence of simple imprisonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_466_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_467:
  sectionId (91452)
  sectionNo (467)
  orderNo 467
  title `Sentence on offender already sentenced for another offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_467_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_467_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91452&sectionno=467&orderno=467&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_467_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a person already`
  line `undergoing a sentence of imprisonment is sentenced on a subsequent conviction to imprisonment or`
  line `imprisonment for life, such imprisonment or imprisonment for life shall commence at the expiration of the`
  line `imprisonment to which he has been previously sentenced, unless the Court directs that the subsequent`
  line `sentence shall run concurrently with such previous sentence:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a person who has been sentenced to imprisonment by an order under section 141`
  line `in default of furnishing security is, whilst undergoing such sentence, sentenced to imprisonment for an`
  line `offence committed prior to the making of such order, the latter sentence shall commence immediately.`
  line
  line `(2) When a person already undergoing a sentence of imprisonment for life is sentenced on a subsequent`
  line `conviction to imprisonment for a term or imprisonment for life, the subsequent sentence shall run`
  line `concurrently with such previous sentence.`
obj_root_law_sections_467_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_468:
  sectionId (91453)
  sectionNo (468)
  orderNo 468
  title `Period of detention undergone by accused to be set off against sentence of imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_468_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_468_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91453&sectionno=468&orderno=468&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_468_content:
  string
  line `Where an accused person has, on conviction, been sentenced to imprisonment for a term, not being`
  line `imprisonment in default of payment of fine, the period of detention, if any, undergone by him during the`
  line `investigation, inquiry or trial of the same case and before the date of such conviction, shall be set off against`
  line `the term of imprisonment imposed on him on such conviction, and the liability of such person to undergo`
  line `imprisonment on such conviction shall be restricted to the remainder, if any, of the term of imprisonment`
  line `imposed on him:`
  line
  line `Provided that in cases referred to in section 475, such period of detention shall be set off against the`
  line `period of fourteen years referred to in that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_468_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_469:
  sectionId (91454)
  sectionNo (469)
  orderNo 469
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_469_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_469_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91454&sectionno=469&orderno=469&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_469_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in section 466 or section 467 shall be held to excuse any person from any`
  line `part of the punishment to which he is liable upon his former or subsequent conviction.`
  line
  line `(2) When an award of imprisonment in default of payment of a fine is annexed to a substantive sentence`
  line `of imprisonment and the person undergoing the sentence is after its execution to undergo a further`
  line `substantive sentence or further substantive sentences of imprisonment, effect shall not be given to the award`
  line `of imprisonment in default of payment of the fine until the person has undergone the further sentence or`
  line sentences.
obj_root_law_sections_469_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_470:
  sectionId (91455)
  sectionNo (470)
  orderNo 470
  title `Return of warrant on execution of sentence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_470_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_470_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91455&sectionno=470&orderno=470&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_470_content:
  string
  line `When a sentence has been fully executed, the`
  line `officer executing it shall return the warrant to the Court from which it is issued, with an endorsement under`
  line `his hand certifying the manner in which the sentence has been executed.`
obj_root_law_sections_470_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_471:
  sectionId (91456)
  sectionNo (471)
  orderNo 471
  title `Money ordered to be paid recoverable as a fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_471_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_471_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91456&sectionno=471&orderno=471&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_471_content:
  string
  line `Any money (other than a fine) payable by`
  line `virtue of any order made under this Sanhita, and the method of recovery of which is not otherwise expressly`
  line `provided for, shall be recoverable as if it were a fine:`
  line
  line `Provided that section 461 shall, in its application to an order under section 400, by virtue of this section,`
  line `be construed as if in the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 461, after the words and figures "under section`
  line `395", the words and figures "or an order for payment of costs under section 400" had been inserted.`
obj_root_law_sections_471_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_472:
  sectionId (91568)
  sectionNo (472)
  orderNo 472
  title `Mercy petition in death sentence cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_472_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_472_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91568&sectionno=472&orderno=472&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_472_content:
  string
  line `(1) A convict under the sentence of death or his legal`
  line `heir or any other relative may, if he has not already submitted a petition for mercy, file a mercy petition`
  line `before the President of India under article 72 or the Governor of the State under article 161 of the`
  line `Constitution within a period of thirty days from the date on which the Superintendent of the jail, ---`
  line
  line `(i) informs him about the dismissal of the appeal, review or special leave to appeal by the Supreme`
  line `Court; or`
  line
  line `(ii) informs him about the date of confirmation of the sentence of death by the High Court and the`
  line `time allowed to file an appeal or special leave in the Supreme Court has expired.`
  line
  line `(2) The petition under sub-section (1) may, initially be made to the Governor and on its rejection or`
  line `disposal by the Governor, the petition shall be made to the President within a period of sixty days from the`
  line `date of rejection or disposal of such petition.`
  line
  line `(3) The Superintendent of the jail or officer in charge of the jail shall ensure, that every convict, in case`
  line `there are more than one convict in a case, also files the mercy petition within a period of sixty days and on`
  line `non-receipt of such petition from the other convicts, Superintendent of the jail shall send the names,`
  line `addresses, copy of the record of the case and all other details of the case to the Central Government or the`
  line `State Government for consideration along with the said mercy petition.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall, on receipt of the mercy petition seek the comments of the State`
  line `Government and consider the petition along with the records of the case and make recommendations to the`
  line `President in this behalf, as expeditiously as possible, within a period of sixty days from the date of receipt`
  line `of comments of the State Government and records from Superintendent of the Jail.`
  line
  line `(5) The President may, consider, decide and dispose of the mercy petition and, in case there are more`
  line `than one convict in a case, the petitions shall be decided by the President together in the interests of justice.`
  line
  line `(6) Upon receipt of the order of the President on the mercy petition, the Central Government shall`
  line `within forty-eight hours, communicate the same to the Home Department of the State Government and the`
  line `Superintendent of the jail or officer in charge of the jail.`
  line
  line `(7) No appeal shall lie in any Court against the order of the President or of the Governor made`
  line `under article 72 or article 161 of the Constitution and it shall be final, and any question as to the arriving of`
  line `the decision by the President or the Governor shall not be inquired into in any Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_472_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_473:
  sectionId (91458)
  sectionNo (473)
  orderNo 473
  title `Power to suspend or remit sentences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_473_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_473_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91458&sectionno=473&orderno=473&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_473_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person has been sentenced to punishment`
  line `for an offence, the appropriate Government may, at any time, without conditions or upon any conditions`
  line `which the person sentenced accepts, suspend the execution of his sentence or remit the whole or any part`
  line `of the punishment to which he has been sentenced.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever an application is made to the appropriate Government for the suspension or remission of`
  line `a sentence, the appropriate Government may require the presiding Judge of the Court before or by which`
  line `the conviction was had or confirmed, to state his opinion as to whether the application should be granted or`
  line `refused, together with his reasons for such opinion and also to forward with the statement of such opinion`
  line `a certified copy of the record of the trial or of such record thereof as exists.`
  line
  line `(3) If any condition on which a sentence has been suspended or remitted is, in the opinion of the`
  line `appropriate Government, not fulfilled, the appropriate Government may cancel the suspension or remission,`
  line `and thereupon the person in whose favour the sentence has been suspended or remitted may, if at large, be`
  line `arrested by any police officer, without warrant and remanded to undergo the unexpired portion of the`
  line sentence.
  line
  line `(4) The condition on which a sentence is suspended or remitted under this section may be one to be`
  line `fulfilled by the person in whose favour the sentence is suspended or remitted, or one independent of his`
  line will.
  line
  line `(5) The appropriate Government may, by general rules or special orders, give directions as to the`
  line `suspension of sentences and the conditions on which petitions should be presented and dealt with:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any sentence (other than a sentence of fine) passed on a person above the`
  line `age of eighteen years, no such petition by the person sentenced or by any other person on his behalf shall`
  line `be entertained, unless the person sentenced is in jail, and---`
  line
  line `(a) where such petition is made by the person sentenced, it is presented through the officer in charge`
  line `of the jail; or`
  line
  line `(b) where such petition is made by any other person, it contains a declaration that the person`
  line `sentenced is in jail.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of the above sub-sections shall also apply to any order passed by a Criminal Court`
  line `under any section of this Sanhita or of any other law, which restricts the liberty of any person or imposes`
  line `any liability upon him or his property.`
  line
  line `(7) In this section and in section 474, the expression "appropriate Government" means,---`
  line
  line `(a) in cases where the sentence is for an offence against, or the order referred to in sub-section (6)`
  line `is passed under, any law relating to a matter to which the executive power of the Union extends, the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) in other cases, the Government of the State within which the offender is sentenced or the said`
  line `order is passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_473_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_474:
  sectionId (91459)
  sectionNo (474)
  orderNo 474
  title `Power to commute sentence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_474_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_474_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91459&sectionno=474&orderno=474&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_474_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, without the consent of the`
  line `person sentenced, commute---`
  line
  line `(a) a sentence of death, for imprisonment for life;`
  line
  line `(b) a sentence of imprisonment for life, for imprisonment for a term not less than seven years;`
  line
  line `(c) a sentence of imprisonment for seven years or more, for imprisonment for a term not less than`
  line `three years;`
  line
  line `(d) a sentence of imprisonment for less than seven years, for fine;`
  line
  line `(e) a sentence of rigorous imprisonment, for simple imprisonment for any term to which that person`
  line `might have been sentenced.`
obj_root_law_sections_474_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_475:
  sectionId (91460)
  sectionNo (475)
  orderNo 475
  title `Restriction on powers of remission or commutation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_475_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_475_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91460&sectionno=475&orderno=475&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_475_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in section 473, where a sentence of imprisonment for life is imposed on conviction of a`
  line `person for an offence for which death is one of the punishments provided by law, or where a sentence of`
  line `death imposed on a person has been commuted under section 474 into one of imprisonment for life, such`
  line `person shall not be released from prison unless he had served at least fourteen years of imprisonment.`
obj_root_law_sections_475_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_476:
  sectionId (91461)
  sectionNo (476)
  orderNo 476
  title `Concurrent power of Central Government in case of death sentences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_476_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_476_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91461&sectionno=476&orderno=476&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_476_content:
  string
  line `The powers conferred`
  line `by sections 473 and 474 upon the State Government may, in the case of sentences of death, also be exercised`
  line `by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_476_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_477:
  sectionId (91462)
  sectionNo (477)
  orderNo 477
  title `State Government to act after concurrence with Central Government in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_477_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_477_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91462&sectionno=477&orderno=477&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_477_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The powers conferred by sections 473 and 474 upon the State Government to remit or commute a sentence,`
  line `in any case where the sentence is for an offence---`
  line
  line `(a) which was investigated by any agency empowered to make investigation into an offence under`
  line `any Central Act other than this Sanhita; or`
  line
  line `(b) which involved the misappropriation or destruction of, or damage to, any property belonging to`
  line `the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(c) which was committed by a person in the service of the Central Government while acting or`
  line `purporting to act in the discharge of his official duty,`
  line
  line `shall not be exercised by the State Government except after concurrence with the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) No order of suspension, remission or commutation of sentences passed by the State Government in`
  line `relation to a person, who has been convicted of offences, some of which relate to matters to which the`
  line `executive power of the Union extends, and who has been sentenced to separate terms of imprisonment`
  line `which are to run concurrently, shall have effect unless an order for the suspension, remission or`
  line `commutation, as the case may be, of such sentences has also been made by the Central Government in`
  line `relation to the offences committed by such person with regard to matters to which the executive power of`
  line `the Union extends.`
obj_root_law_sections_477_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_478:
  sectionId (91463)
  sectionNo (478)
  orderNo 478
  title `In what cases bail to be taken.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_478_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_478_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91463&sectionno=478&orderno=478&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_478_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person other than a person accused of a nonbailable offence is arrested or detained without warrant by an officer in charge of a police station, or appears`
  line `or is brought before a Court, and is prepared at any time while in the custody of such officer or at any stage`
  line `of the proceeding before such Court to give bail, such person shall be released on bail:`
  line
  line `Provided that such officer or Court, if he or it thinks fit, may, and shall, if such person is indigent and`
  line `is unable to furnish surety, instead of taking bail bond from such person, discharge him on his executing a`
  line `bond for his appearance as hereinafter provided.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Where a person is unable to give bail bond within a week of the date of his arrest, it`
  line `shall be a sufficient ground for the officer or the Court to presume that he is an indigent person for the`
  line `purposes of this proviso:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the provisions of sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 135 or section 492.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (1), where a person has failed to comply with the`
  line `conditions of the bond or bail bond as regards the time and place of attendance, the Court may refuse to`
  line `release him on bail, when on a subsequent occasion in the same case he appears before the Court or is`
  line `brought in custody and any such refusal shall be without prejudice to the powers of the Court to call upon`
  line `any person bound by such bond or bail bond to pay the penalty thereof under section 491.`
obj_root_law_sections_478_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_479:
  sectionId (91464)
  sectionNo (479)
  orderNo 479
  title `Maximum period for which under-trial prisoner can be detained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_479_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_479_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91464&sectionno=479&orderno=479&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_479_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person has,`
  line `during the period of investigation, inquiry or trial under this Sanhita of an offence under any law (not being`
  line `an offence for which the punishment of death or life imprisonment has been specified as one of the`
  line `punishments under that law) undergone detention for a period extending up to one-half of the maximum`
  line `period of imprisonment specified for that offence under that law, he shall be released by the Court on bail:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person is a first-time offender (who has never been convicted of any offence`
  line `in the past) he shall be released on bond by the Court, if he has undergone detention for the period extending`
  line `up to one-third of the maximum period of imprisonment specified for such offence under that law:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Court may, after hearing the Public Prosecutor and for reasons to be recorded`
  line `by it in writing, order the continued detention of such person for a period longer than one-half of the said`
  line `period or release him on bail bond instead of his bond:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no such person shall in any case be detained during the period of investigation,`
  line `inquiry or trial for more than the maximum period of imprisonment provided for the said offence under that`
  line law.
  line
  line `Explanation.—In computing the period of detention under this section for granting bail, the period of`
  line `detention passed due to delay in proceeding caused by the accused shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (1), and subject to the third proviso thereof, where an`
  line `investigation, inquiry or trial in more than one offence or in multiple cases are pending against a person, he`
  line `shall not be released on bail by the Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The Superintendent of jail, where the accused person is detained, on completion of one-half or onethird of the period mentioned in sub-section (1), as the case may be, shall forthwith make an application in`
  line `writing to the Court to proceed under sub-section (1) for the release of such person on bail.`
obj_root_law_sections_479_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_480:
  sectionId (91465)
  sectionNo (480)
  orderNo 480
  title `When bail may be taken in case of non-bailable offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_480_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_480_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91465&sectionno=480&orderno=480&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_480_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person accused of, or`
  line `suspected of, the commission of any non-bailable offence is arrested or detained without warrant by an`
  line `officer in charge of a police station or appears or is brought before a Court other than the High Court or`
  line `Court of Session, he may be released on bail, but---`
  line
  line `(i) such person shall not be so released if there appear reasonable grounds for believing that he has`
  line `been guilty of an offence punishable with death or imprisonment for life;`
  line
  line `(ii) such person shall not be so released if such offence is a cognizable offence and he had been`
  line `previously convicted of an offence punishable with death, imprisonment for life or imprisonment for`
  line `seven years or more, or he had been previously convicted on two or more occasions of a cognizable`
  line `offence punishable with imprisonment for three years or more but less than seven years:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may direct that a person referred to in clause (i) or clause (ii) be released on`
  line `bail if such person is a child or is a woman or is sick or infirm:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Court may also direct that a person referred to in clause (ii) be released on bail`
  line `if it is satisfied that it is just and proper so to do for any other special reason:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the mere fact that an accused person may be required for being identified by`
  line `witnesses during investigation or for police custody beyond the first fifteen days shall not be sufficient`
  line `ground for refusing to grant bail if he is otherwise entitled to be released on bail and gives an undertaking`
  line `that he shall comply with such directions as may be given by the Court:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no person shall, if the offence alleged to have been committed by him is punishable`
  line `with death, imprisonment for life, or imprisonment for seven years or more, be released on bail by the Court`
  line `under this sub-section without giving an opportunity of hearing to the Public Prosecutor.`
  line
  line `(2) If it appears to such officer or Court at any stage of the investigation, inquiry or trial, as the case`
  line `may be, that there are not reasonable grounds for believing that the accused has committed a non-bailable`
  line `offence, but that there are sufficient grounds for further inquiry into his guilt, the accused shall, subject to`
  line `the provisions of section 492 and pending such inquiry, be released on bail, or, at the discretion of such`
  line `officer or Court, on the execution by him of a bond for his appearance as hereinafter provided.`
  line
  line `(3) When a person accused or suspected of the commission of an offence punishable with imprisonment`
  line `which may extend to seven years or more or of an offence under Chapter VI, Chapter VII or Chapter XVII`
  line `of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 or abetment of, or conspiracy or attempt to commit, any such offence,`
  line `is released on bail under sub-section (1), the Court shall impose the conditions,---`
  line
  line `(a) that such person shall attend in accordance with the conditions of the bond executed under this`
  line Chapter;
  line
  line `(b) that such person shall not commit an offence similar to the offence of which he is accused, or`
  line `suspected, of the commission of which he is suspected; and`
  line
  line `(c) that such person shall not directly or indirectly make any inducement, threat or promise to any`
  line `person acquainted with the facts of the case so as to dissuade him from disclosing such facts to the`
  line `Court or to any police officer or tamper with the evidence,`
  line
  line `and may also impose, in the interests of justice, such other conditions as it considers necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) An officer or a Court releasing any person on bail under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), shall`
  line `record in writing his or its reasons or special reasons for so doing.`
  line
  line `(5) Any Court which has released a person on bail under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), may, if it`
  line `considers it necessary so to do, direct that such person be arrested and commit him to custody.`
  line
  line `(6) If, in any case triable by a Magistrate, the trial of a person accused of any non-bailable offence is`
  line `not concluded within a period of sixty days from the first date fixed for taking evidence in the case, such`
  line `person shall, if he is in custody during the whole of the said period, be released on bail to the satisfaction`
  line `of the Magistrate, unless for reasons to be recorded in writing, the Magistrate otherwise directs.`
  line
  line `(7) If, at any time, after the conclusion of the trial of a person accused of a non-bailable offence and`
  line `before judgment is delivered, the Court is of opinion that there are reasonable grounds for believing that`
  line `the accused is not guilty of any such offence, it shall release the accused, if he is in custody, on the execution`
  line `by him of a bond for his appearance to hear judgment delivered.`
obj_root_law_sections_480_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_481:
  sectionId (91569)
  sectionNo (481)
  orderNo 481
  title `Bail to require accused to appear before next Appellate Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_481_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_481_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91569&sectionno=481&orderno=481&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_481_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before conclusion of the`
  line `trial and before disposal of the appeal, the Court trying the offence or the Appellate Court, as the case may`
  line `be, shall require the accused to execute a bond or bail bond, to appear before the higher Court as and when`
  line `such Court issues notice in respect of any appeal or petition filed against the judgment of the respective`
  line `Court and such bond shall be in force for six months.`
  line
  line `(2) If such accused fails to appear, the bond stand forfeited and the procedure under section 491 shall`
  line apply.
obj_root_law_sections_481_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_482:
  sectionId (91570)
  sectionNo (482)
  orderNo 482
  title `Direction for grant of bail to person apprehending arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_482_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_482_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91570&sectionno=482&orderno=482&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_482_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person has reason`
  line `to believe that he may be arrested on an accusation of having committed a non-bailable offence, he may`
  line `apply to the High Court or the Court of Session for a direction under this section; and that Court may, if it`
  line `thinks fit, direct that in the event of such arrest, he shall be released on bail.`
  line
  line `(2) When the High Court or the Court of Session makes a direction under sub-section (1), it may include`
  line `such conditions in such directions in the light of the facts of the particular case, as it may think fit,`
  line including---
  line
  line `(i) a condition that the person shall make himself available for interrogation by a police officer as`
  line `and when required;`
  line
  line `(ii) a condition that the person shall not, directly or indirectly, make any inducement, threat or`
  line `promise to any person acquainted with the facts of the case so as to dissuade him from disclosing such`
  line `facts to the Court or to any police officer;`
  line
  line `(iii) a condition that the person shall not leave India without the previous permission of the Court;`
  line
  line `(iv) such other condition as may be imposed under sub-section (3) of section 480, as if the bail were`
  line `granted under that section.`
  line
  line `(3) If such person is thereafter arrested without warrant by an officer in charge of a police station on`
  line `such accusation, and is prepared either at the time of arrest or at any time while in the custody of such`
  line `officer to give bail, he shall be released on bail; and if a Magistrate taking cognizance of such offence`
  line `decides that a warrant should be issued in the first instance against that person, he shall issue a bailable`
  line `warrant in conformity with the direction of the Court under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall apply to any case involving the arrest of any person on accusation of`
  line `having committed an offence under section 65 and sub-section (2) of section 70 of the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023.`
obj_root_law_sections_482_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_483:
  sectionId (91467)
  sectionNo (483)
  orderNo 483
  title `Special powers of High Court or Court of Session regarding bail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_483_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_483_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91467&sectionno=483&orderno=483&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_483_content:
  string
  line `(1) A High Court or Court`
  line `of Session may direct,---`
  line
  line `(a) that any person accused of an offence and in custody be released on bail, and if the offence is of the`
  line `nature specified in sub-section (3) of section 480, may impose any condition which it considers necessary`
  line `for the purposes mentioned in that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(b) that any condition imposed by a Magistrate when releasing any person on bail be set aside or`
  line `modified:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court or the Court of Session shall, before granting bail to a person who is`
  line `accused of an offence which is triable exclusively by the Court of Session or which, though not so triable,`
  line `is punishable with imprisonment for life, give notice of the application for bail to the Public Prosecutor`
  line `unless it is, for reasons to be recorded in writing, of opinion that it is not practicable to give such notice:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the High Court or the Court of Session shall, before granting bail to a person who`
  line `is accused of an offence triable under section 65 or sub-section (2) of section 70 of the Bharatiya Nyaya`
  line `Sanhita, 2023, give notice of the application for bail to the Public Prosecutor within a period of fifteen days`
  line `from the date of receipt of the notice of such application.`
  line
  line `(2) The presence of the informant or any person authorised by him shall be obligatory at the time of`
  line `hearing of the application for bail to the person under section 65 or sub-section (2) of section 70 of the`
  line `Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023.`
  line
  line `(3) A High Court or Court of Session may direct that any person who has been released on bail under`
  line `this Chapter be arrested and commit him to custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_483_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_484:
  sectionId (91468)
  sectionNo (484)
  orderNo 484
  title `Amount of bond and reduction thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_484_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_484_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91468&sectionno=484&orderno=484&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_484_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount of every bond executed under this`
  line `Chapter shall be fixed with due regard to the circumstances of the case and shall not be excessive.`
  line
  line `(2) The High Court or the Court of Session may direct that the bail required by a police officer or`
  line `Magistrate be reduced.`
obj_root_law_sections_484_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_485:
  sectionId (91469)
  sectionNo (485)
  orderNo 485
  title `Bond of accused and sureties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_485_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_485_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91469&sectionno=485&orderno=485&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_485_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before any person is released on bond or bail bond, a bond`
  line `for such sum of money as the police officer or Court, as the case may be, thinks sufficient shall be executed`
  line `by such person, and, when he is released on bond or bail bond, by one or more sufficient sureties conditioned`
  line `that such person shall attend at the time and place mentioned in the bond, and shall continue so to attend`
  line `until otherwise directed by the police officer or Court, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any condition is imposed for the release of any person on bail, the bond or bail bond shall`
  line `also contain that condition.`
  line
  line `(3) If the case so requires, the bond or bail bond shall also bind the person released on bail to appear`
  line `when called upon at the High Court, Court of Session or other Court to answer the charge.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of determining whether the sureties are fit or sufficient, the Court may accept`
  line `affidavits in proof of the facts contained therein relating to the sufficiency or fitness of the sureties, or, if it`
  line `considers necessary, may either hold an enquiry itself or cause an inquiry to be made by a Magistrate`
  line `subordinate to the Court, as to such sufficiency or fitness.`
obj_root_law_sections_485_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_486:
  sectionId (91470)
  sectionNo (486)
  orderNo 486
  title `Declaration by sureties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_486_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_486_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91470&sectionno=486&orderno=486&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_486_content:
  string
  line `Every person standing surety to an accused person for his release on`
  line `bail, shall make a declaration before the Court as to the number of persons to whom he has stood surety`
  line `including the accused, giving therein all the relevant particulars.`
obj_root_law_sections_486_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_487:
  sectionId (91471)
  sectionNo (487)
  orderNo 487
  title `Discharge from custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_487_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_487_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91471&sectionno=487&orderno=487&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_487_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as the bond or bail bond has been executed, the person`
  line `for whose appearance it has been executed shall be released; and, when he is in jail, the court admitting him`
  line `to bail shall issue an order of release to the officer in charge of the jail, and such officer on receipt of the`
  line `orders shall release him.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section, section 478 or section 480, shall be deemed to require the release of any`
  line `person liable to be detained for some matter other than that in respect of which the bond or bail bond was`
  line executed.
obj_root_law_sections_487_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_488:
  sectionId (91472)
  sectionNo (488)
  orderNo 488
  title `Power to order sufficient bail when that first taken is insufficient.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_488_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_488_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91472&sectionno=488&orderno=488&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_488_content:
  string
  line `If, through mistake,`
  line `fraud or otherwise, insufficient sureties have been accepted, or if they afterwards become insufficient, the`
  line `Court may issue a warrant of arrest directing that the person released on bail be brought before it and may`
  line `order him to find sufficient sureties, and, on his failing so to do, may commit him to jail.`
obj_root_law_sections_488_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_489:
  sectionId (91473)
  sectionNo (489)
  orderNo 489
  title `Discharge of sureties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_489_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_489_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91473&sectionno=489&orderno=489&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_489_content:
  string
  line `(1) All or any sureties for the attendance and appearance of a person`
  line `released on bail may at any time apply to a Magistrate to discharge the bond, either wholly or so far as`
  line `relates to the applicants.`
  line
  line `(2) On such application being made, the Magistrate shall issue his warrant of arrest directing that the`
  line `person so released be brought before him.`
  line
  line `(3) On the appearance of such person pursuant to the warrant, or on his voluntary surrender, the`
  line `Magistrate shall direct the bond to be discharged either wholly or so far as relates to the applicants, and`
  line `shall call upon such person to find other sufficient sureties, and, if he fails to do so, may commit him to jail.`
obj_root_law_sections_489_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_490:
  sectionId (91474)
  sectionNo (490)
  orderNo 490
  title `Deposit instead of recognizance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_490_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_490_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91474&sectionno=490&orderno=490&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_490_content:
  string
  line `When any person is required by any Court or officer to`
  line `execute a bond or bail bond, such Court or officer may, except in the case of a bond for good behaviour,`
  line `permit him to deposit a sum of money or Government promissory notes to such amount as the Court or`
  line `officer may fix in lieu of executing such bond.`
obj_root_law_sections_490_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_491:
  sectionId (91475)
  sectionNo (491)
  orderNo 491
  title `Procedure when bond has been forfeited.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_491_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_491_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91475&sectionno=491&orderno=491&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_491_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where,---`
  line
  line `(a) a bond under this Sanhita is for appearance, or for production of property, before a Court and it`
  line `is proved to the satisfaction of that Court, or of any Court to which the case has subsequently been`
  line `transferred, that the bond has been forfeited; or`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of any other bond under this Sanhita, it is proved to the satisfaction of the Court by`
  line `which the bond was taken, or of any Court to which the case has subsequently been transferred, or of`
  line `the Court of any Magistrate of the first class, that the bond has been forfeited,`
  line
  line `the Court shall record the grounds of such proof, and may call upon any person bound by such bond to pay`
  line `the penalty thereof or to show cause why it should not be paid.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—A condition in a bond for appearance, or for production of property, before a Court shall`
  line `be construed as including a condition for appearance, or as the case may be, for production of property,`
  line `before any Court to which the case may subsequently be transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) If sufficient cause is not shown and the penalty is not paid, the Court may proceed to recover the`
  line `same as if such penalty were a fine imposed by it under this Sanhita:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such penalty is not paid and cannot be recovered in the manner aforesaid, the`
  line `person so bound as surety shall be liable, by order of the Court ordering the recovery of the penalty, to`
  line `imprisonment in civil jail for a term which may extend to six months.`
  line
  line `(3) The Court may, after recording its reasons for doing so, remit any portion of the penalty mentioned`
  line `and enforce payment in part only.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a surety to a bond dies before the bond is forfeited, his estate shall be discharged from all`
  line `liability in respect of the bond.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any person who has furnished security under section 125 or section 136 or section 401 is`
  line `convicted of an offence the commission of which constitutes a breach of the conditions of his bond, or of a`
  line `bond executed in lieu of his bond under section 494, a certified copy of the judgment of the Court by which`
  line `he was convicted of such offence may be used as evidence in proceedings under this section against his`
  line `surety or sureties, and, if such certified copy is so used, the Court shall presume that such offence was`
  line `committed by him unless the contrary is proved.`
obj_root_law_sections_491_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_492:
  sectionId (91571)
  sectionNo (492)
  orderNo 492
  title `Cancellation of bond and bail bond.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_492_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_492_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91571&sectionno=492&orderno=492&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_492_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of section 491, where`
  line `a bond or bail bond under this Sanhita is for appearance of a person in a case and it is forfeited for breach`
  line `of a condition,---`
  line
  line `(a) the bond executed by such person as well as the bond, if any, executed by one or more of his`
  line `sureties in that case shall stand cancelled; and`
  line
  line `(b) thereafter no such person shall be released only on his own bond in that case, if the police officer`
  line `or the Court, as the case may be, for appearance before whom the bond was executed, is satisfied that`
  line `there was no sufficient cause for the failure of the person bound by the bond to comply with its`
  line `condition:`
  line
  line `Provided that subject to any other provisions of this Sanhita he may be released in that case upon the`
  line `execution of a fresh personal bond for such sum of money and bond by one or more of such sureties as the`
  line `police officer or the Court, as the case may be, thinks sufficient.`
obj_root_law_sections_492_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_493:
  sectionId (91572)
  sectionNo (493)
  orderNo 493
  title `Procedure in case of insolvency or death of surety or when a bond is forfeited.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_493_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_493_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91572&sectionno=493&orderno=493&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_493_content:
  string
  line `When any`
  line `surety to a bail bond under this Sanhita becomes insolvent or dies, or when any bond is forfeited under the`
  line `provisions of section 491, the Court by whose order such bond was taken, or a Magistrate of the first class`
  line `may order the person from whom such security was demanded to furnish fresh security in accordance with`
  line `the directions of the original order, and if such security is not furnished, such Court or Magistrate may`
  line `proceed as if there had been a default in complying with such original order.`
obj_root_law_sections_493_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_494:
  sectionId (91477)
  sectionNo (494)
  orderNo 494
  title `Bond required from child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_494_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_494_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91477&sectionno=494&orderno=494&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_494_content:
  string
  line `When the person required by any Court, or officer to execute a bond`
  line `is a child, such Court or officer may accept, in lieu thereof, a bond executed by a surety or sureties only.`
obj_root_law_sections_494_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_495:
  sectionId (91478)
  sectionNo (495)
  orderNo 495
  title `Appeal from orders under section 491.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_495_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_495_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91478&sectionno=495&orderno=495&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_495_content:
  string
  line `All orders passed under section 491 shall be`
  line appealable,---
  line
  line `(i) in the case of an order made by a Magistrate, to the Sessions Judge;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of an order made by a Court of Session, to the Court to which an appeal lies from an`
  line `order made by such Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_495_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_496:
  sectionId (91479)
  sectionNo (496)
  orderNo 496
  title `Power to direct levy of amount due on certain recognizances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_496_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_496_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91479&sectionno=496&orderno=496&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_496_content:
  string
  line `The High Court or Court of`
  line `Session may direct any Magistrate to levy the amount due on a bond for appearance or attendance at such`
  line `High Court or Court of Session.`
obj_root_law_sections_496_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_497:
  sectionId (91480)
  sectionNo (497)
  orderNo 497
  title `Order for custody and disposal of property pending trial in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_497_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_497_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91480&sectionno=497&orderno=497&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_497_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any`
  line `property is produced before any Criminal Court or the Magistrate empowered to take cognizance or commit`
  line `the case for trial during any investigation, inquiry or trial, the Court or the Magistrate may make such order`
  line `as it thinks fit for the proper custody of such property pending the conclusion of the investigation, inquiry`
  line `or trial, and, if the property is subject to speedy and natural decay, or if it is otherwise expedient so to do,`
  line `the Court or the Magistrate may, after recording such evidence as it thinks necessary, order it to be sold or`
  line `otherwise disposed of.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section, "property" includes---`
  line
  line `(a) property of any kind or document which is produced before the Court or which is in its custody;`
  line
  line `(b) any property regarding which an offence appears to have been committed or which appears to`
  line `have been used for the commission of any offence.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court or the Magistrate shall, within a period of fourteen days from the production of the`
  line `property referred to in sub-section (1) before it, prepare a statement of such property containing its`
  line `description in such form and manner as the State Government may, by rules, provide.`
  line
  line `(3) The Court or the Magistrate shall cause to be taken the photograph and if necessary, videograph on`
  line `mobile phone or any electronic media, of the property referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The statement prepared under sub-section (2) and the photograph or the videography taken under`
  line `sub-section (3) shall be used as evidence in any inquiry, trial or other proceeding under the Sanhita.`
  line
  line `(5) The Court or the Magistrate shall, within a period of thirty days after the statement has been prepared`
  line `under sub-section (2) and the photograph or the videography has been taken under sub-section (3), order`
  line `the disposal, destruction, confiscation or delivery of the property in the manner specified hereinafter.`
obj_root_law_sections_497_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_498:
  sectionId (91481)
  sectionNo (498)
  orderNo 498
  title `Order for disposal of property at conclusion of trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_498_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_498_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91481&sectionno=498&orderno=498&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_498_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an investigation, inquiry or`
  line `trial in any criminal case is concluded, the Court or the Magistrate may make such order as it thinks fit for`
  line `the disposal, by destruction, confiscation or delivery to any person claiming to be entitled to possession`
  line `thereof or otherwise, of any property or document produced before it or in its custody, or regarding which`
  line `any offence appears to have been committed, or which has been used for the commission of any offence.`
  line
  line `(2) An order may be made under sub-section (1) for the delivery of any property to any person claiming`
  line `to be entitled to the possession thereof, without any condition or on condition that he executes a bond, with`
  line `or without securities, to the satisfaction of the Court or the Magistrate, engaging to restore such property to`
  line `the Court if the order made under sub-section (1) is modified or set aside on appeal or revision.`
  line
  line `(3) A Court of Session may, instead of itself making an order under sub-section (1), direct the property`
  line `to be delivered to the Chief Judicial Magistrate, who shall thereupon deal with it in the manner provided in`
  line `sections 503, 504 and 505.`
  line
  line `(4) Except where the property is livestock or is subject to speedy and natural decay, or where a bond`
  line `has been executed in pursuance of sub-section (2), an order made under sub-section (1) shall not be carried`
  line `out for two months, or when an appeal is presented, until such appeal has been disposed of.`
  line
  line `(5) In this section, the term "property" includes, in the case of property regarding which an offence`
  line `appears to have been committed, not only such property as has been originally in the possession or under`
  line `the control of any party, but also any property into or for which the same may have been converted or`
  line `exchanged, and anything acquired by such conversion or exchange, whether immediately or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_498_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_499:
  sectionId (91482)
  sectionNo (499)
  orderNo 499
  title `Payment to innocent purchaser of money found on accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_499_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_499_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91482&sectionno=499&orderno=499&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_499_content:
  string
  line `When any person is convicted`
  line `of any offence which includes, or amounts to, theft or receiving stolen property, and it is proved that any`
  line `other person bought the stolen property from him without knowing or having reason to believe that the`
  line `same was stolen, and that any money has on his arrest been taken out of the possession of the convicted`
  line `person, the Court may, on the application of such purchaser and on the restitution of the stolen property to`
  line `the person entitled to the possession thereof, order that out of such money a sum not exceeding the price`
  line `paid by such purchaser be delivered to him within six months from the date of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_499_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_500:
  sectionId (91483)
  sectionNo (500)
  orderNo 500
  title `Appeal against orders under section 498 or section 499.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_500_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_500_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91483&sectionno=500&orderno=500&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_500_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order`
  line `made by a Court or Magistrate under section 498 or section 499, may appeal against it to the Court to which`
  line `appeals ordinarily lie from convictions by the former Court.`
  line
  line `(2) On such appeal, the Appellate Court may direct the order to be stayed pending disposal of the`
  line `appeal, or may modify, alter or annul the order and make any further orders that may be just.`
  line
  line `(3) The powers referred to in sub-section (2) may also be exercised by a Court of appeal, confirmation`
  line `or revision while dealing with the case in which the order referred to in sub-section (1) was made.`
obj_root_law_sections_500_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_501:
  sectionId (91484)
  sectionNo (501)
  orderNo 501
  title `Destruction of libellous and other matter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_501_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_501_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91484&sectionno=501&orderno=501&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_501_content:
  string
  line `(1) On a conviction under section 294, section 295,`
  line `or sub-sections (3) and (4) of section 356 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, the Court may order the`
  line `destruction of all the copies of the thing in respect of which the conviction was had, and which are in the`
  line `custody of the Court or remain in the possession or power of the person convicted.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may, in like manner, on a conviction under section 274, section 275, section 276`
  line `or section 277 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023, order the food, drink, drug or medical preparation in`
  line `respect of which the conviction was had, to be destroyed.`
obj_root_law_sections_501_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_502:
  sectionId (91485)
  sectionNo (502)
  orderNo 502
  title `Power to restore possession of immovable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_502_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_502_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91485&sectionno=502&orderno=502&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_502_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a person is convicted of an`
  line `offence by use of criminal force or show of force or by criminal intimidation, and it appears to the Court`
  line `that, by such use of force or show of force or intimidation, any person has been dispossessed of any`
  line `immovable property, the Court may, if it thinks fit, order that possession of the same be restored to that`
  line `person after evicting by force, if necessary, any other person who may be in possession of the property:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made by the Court more than one month after the date of the`
  line conviction.
  line
  line `(2) Where the Court trying the offence has not made an order under sub-section (1), the Court of appeal,`
  line `confirmation or revision may, if it thinks fit, make such order while disposing of the appeal, reference or`
  line `revision, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an order has been made under sub-section (1), the provisions of section 500 shall apply in`
  line `relation thereto as they apply in relation to an order under section 499.`
  line
  line `(4) No order made under this section shall prejudice any right or interest to or in such immovable`
  line `property which any person may be able to establish in a civil suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_502_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_503:
  sectionId (91486)
  sectionNo (503)
  orderNo 503
  title `Procedure by police upon seizure of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_503_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_503_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91486&sectionno=503&orderno=503&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_503_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the seizure of property by any`
  line `police officer is reported to a Magistrate under the provisions of this Sanhita, and such property is not`
  line `produced before a Criminal Court during an inquiry or trial, the Magistrate may make such order as he`
  line `thinks fit respecting the disposal of such property or the delivery of such property to the person entitled to`
  line `the possession thereof, or if such person cannot be ascertained, respecting the custody and production of`
  line `such property.`
  line
  line `(2) If the person so entitled is known, the Magistrate may order the property to be delivered to him on`
  line `such conditions (if any) as the Magistrate thinks fit and if such person is unknown, the Magistrate may`
  line `detain it and shall, in such case, issue a proclamation specifying the articles of which such property consists,`
  line `and requiring any person who may have a claim thereto, to appear before him and establish his claim within`
  line `six months from the date of such proclamation.`
obj_root_law_sections_503_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_504:
  sectionId (91487)
  sectionNo (504)
  orderNo 504
  title `Procedure where no claimant appears within six months.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_504_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_504_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91487&sectionno=504&orderno=504&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_504_content:
  string
  line `(1) If no person within such period`
  line `establishes his claim to such property, and if the person in whose possession such property was found is`
  line `unable to show that it was legally acquired by him, the Magistrate may by order direct that such property`
  line `shall be at the disposal of the State Government and may be sold by that Government and the proceeds of`
  line `such sale shall be dealt with in such manner as the State Government may, by rules, provide.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal shall lie against any such order to the Court to which appeals ordinarily lie from`
  line `convictions by the Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_504_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_505:
  sectionId (91488)
  sectionNo (505)
  orderNo 505
  title `Power to sell perishable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_505_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_505_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91488&sectionno=505&orderno=505&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_505_content:
  string
  line `If the person entitled to the possession of such property is`
  line `unknown or absent and the property is subject to speedy and natural decay, or if the Magistrate to whom its`
  line `seizure is reported is of opinion that its sale would be for the benefit of the owner, or that the value of such`
  line `property is less than ten thousand rupees, the Magistrate may at any time direct it to be sold; and the`
  line `provisions of sections 503 and 504 shall, as nearly as may be practicable, apply to the net proceeds of such`
  line sale.
obj_root_law_sections_505_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_506:
  sectionId (91489)
  sectionNo (506)
  orderNo 506
  title `Irregularities which do not vitiate proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_506_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_506_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91489&sectionno=506&orderno=506&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_506_content:
  string
  line `If any Magistrate not empowered by law to`
  line `do any of the following things, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) to issue a search-warrant under section 97;`
  line
  line `(b) to order, under section 174, the police to investigate an offence;`
  line
  line `(c) to hold an inquest under section 196;`
  line
  line `(d) to issue process under section 207, for the apprehension of a person within his local jurisdiction`
  line `who has committed an offence outside the limits of such jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(e) to take cognizance of an offence under clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 210;`
  line
  line `(f) to make over a case under sub-section (2) of section 212;`
  line
  line `(g) to tender a pardon under section 343;`
  line
  line `(h) to recall a case and try it himself under section 450; or`
  line
  line `(i) to sell property under section 504 or section 505, erroneously in good faith does that thing, his`
  line `proceedings shall not be set aside merely on the ground of his not being so empowered.`
obj_root_law_sections_506_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_507:
  sectionId (91490)
  sectionNo (507)
  orderNo 507
  title `Irregularities which vitiate proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_507_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_507_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91490&sectionno=507&orderno=507&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_507_content:
  string
  line `If any Magistrate, not being empowered by law in`
  line `this behalf, does any of the following things, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) attaches and sells property under section 85;`
  line
  line `(b) issues a search-warrant for a document, parcel or other things in the custody of a postal`
  line authority;
  line
  line `(c) demands security to keep the peace;`
  line
  line `(d) demands security for good behaviour;`
  line
  line `(e) discharges a person lawfully bound to be of good behaviour;`
  line
  line `(f) cancels a bond to keep the peace;`
  line
  line `(g) makes an order for maintenance;`
  line
  line `(h) makes an order under section 152 as to a local nuisance;`
  line
  line `(i) prohibits, under section 162, the repetition or continuance of a public nuisance;`
  line
  line `(j) makes an order under Part C or Part D of Chapter XI;`
  line
  line `(k) takes cognizance of an offence under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 210;`
  line
  line `(l) tries an offender;`
  line
  line `(m) tries an offender summarily;`
  line
  line `(n) passes a sentence, under section 364, on proceedings recorded by another Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(o) decides an appeal;`
  line
  line `(p) calls, under section 438, for proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(q) revises an order passed under section 491,`
  line
  line `his proceedings shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_507_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_508:
  sectionId (91491)
  sectionNo (508)
  orderNo 508
  title `Proceedings in wrong place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_508_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_508_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91491&sectionno=508&orderno=508&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_508_content:
  string
  line `No finding, sentence or order of any Criminal Court shall be set`
  line `aside merely on the ground that the inquiry, trial or other proceedings in the course of which it was arrived`
  line `at or passed, took place in a wrong sessions division, district, sub-division or other local area, unless it`
  line `appears that such error has in fact occasioned a failure of justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_508_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_509:
  sectionId (91492)
  sectionNo (509)
  orderNo 509
  title `Non-compliance with provisions of section 183 or section 316.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_509_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_509_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91492&sectionno=509&orderno=509&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_509_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any Court before which`
  line `a confession or other statement of an accused person recorded, or purporting to be recorded under section`
  line `183 or section 316, is tendered, or has been received, in evidence finds that any of the provisions of either`
  line `of such sections have not been complied with by the Magistrate recording the statement, it may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in section 94 of the Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam, 2023, take evidence`
  line `in regard to such non-compliance, and may, if satisfied that such non-compliance has not injured the`
  line `accused in his defence on the merits and that he duly made the statement recorded, admit such statement.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section apply to Courts of appeal, reference and revision.`
obj_root_law_sections_509_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_510:
  sectionId (91493)
  sectionNo (510)
  orderNo 510
  title `Effect of omission to frame, or absence of, or error in, charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_510_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_510_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91493&sectionno=510&orderno=510&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_510_content:
  string
  line `(1) No finding, sentence or`
  line `order by a Court of competent jurisdiction shall be deemed invalid merely on the ground that no charge was`
  line `framed or on the ground of any error, omission or irregularity in the charge including any misjoinder of`
  line `charges, unless, in the opinion of the Court of appeal, confirmation or revision, a failure of justice has in`
  line `fact been occasioned thereby.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Court of appeal, confirmation or revision, is of opinion that a failure of justice has in fact been`
  line `occasioned, it may,---`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an omission to frame a charge, order that a charge be framed, and that the trial be`
  line `recommenced from the point immediately after the framing of the charge;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an error, omission or irregularity in the charge, direct a new trial to be had upon`
  line `a charge framed in whatever manner it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Court is of opinion that the facts of the case are such that no valid charge could`
  line `be preferred against the accused in respect of the facts proved, it shall quash the conviction.`
obj_root_law_sections_510_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_511:
  sectionId (91494)
  sectionNo (511)
  orderNo 511
  title `Finding or sentence when reversible by reason of error, omission or irregularity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_511_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_511_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91494&sectionno=511&orderno=511&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_511_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject`
  line `to the provisions hereinbefore contained, no finding, sentence or order passed by a Court of competent`
  line `jurisdiction shall be reversed or altered by a Court of appeal, confirmation of revision on account of any`
  line `error, omission or irregularity in the complaint, summons, warrant, proclamation, order, judgment or other`
  line `proceedings before or during trial or in any inquiry or other proceedings under this Sanhita, or any error, or`
  line `irregularity in any sanction for the prosecution, unless in the opinion of that Court, a failure of justice has`
  line `in fact been occasioned thereby.`
  line
  line `(2) In determining whether any error, omission or irregularity in any proceeding under this Sanhita, or`
  line `any error, or irregularity in any sanction for the prosecution has occasioned a failure of justice, the Court`
  line `shall have regard to the fact whether the objection could and should have been raised at an earlier stage in`
  line `the proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_511_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_512:
  sectionId (91495)
  sectionNo (512)
  orderNo 512
  title `Defect or error not to make attachment unlawful.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_512_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_512_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91495&sectionno=512&orderno=512&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_512_content:
  string
  line `No attachment made under this Sanhita`
  line `shall be deemed unlawful, nor shall any person making the same be deemed a trespasser, on account of any`
  line `defect or want of form in the summons, conviction, writ of attachment or other proceedings relating thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_512_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_513:
  sectionId (91496)
  sectionNo (513)
  orderNo 513
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_513_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_513_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91496&sectionno=513&orderno=513&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_513_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, "period of`
  line `limitation" means the period specified in section 514 for taking cognizance of an offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_513_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_514:
  sectionId (91497)
  sectionNo (514)
  orderNo 514
  title `Bar to taking cognizance after lapse of period of limitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_514_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_514_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91497&sectionno=514&orderno=514&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_514_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as otherwise provided`
  line `in this Sanhita, no Court shall take cognizance of an offence of the category specified in sub-section (2),`
  line `after the expiry of the period of limitation.`
  line
  line `(2) The period of limitation shall be---`
  line
  line `(a) six months, if the offence is punishable with fine only;`
  line
  line `(b) one year, if the offence is punishable with imprisonment for a term not exceeding one year;`
  line
  line `(c) three years, if the offence is punishable with imprisonment for a term exceeding one year but`
  line `not exceeding three years.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, the period of limitation, in relation to offences which may be tried`
  line `together, shall be determined with reference to the offence which is punishable with the more severe`
  line `punishment or, as the case may be, the most severe punishment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of computing the period of limitation, the relevant date shall be the date`
  line `of filing complaint under section 223 or the date of recording of information under section 173.`
obj_root_law_sections_514_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_515:
  sectionId (91498)
  sectionNo (515)
  orderNo 515
  title `Commencement of period of limitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_515_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_515_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91498&sectionno=515&orderno=515&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_515_content:
  string
  line `(1) The period of limitation, in relation to an offender,`
  line `shall commence,---`
  line
  line `(a) on the date of the offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the commission of the offence was not known to the person aggrieved by the offence or`
  line `to any police officer, the first day on which such offence comes to the knowledge of such person or to`
  line `any police officer, whichever is earlier; or`
  line
  line `(c) where it is not known by whom the offence was committed, the first day on which the identity`
  line `of the offender is known to the person aggrieved by the offence or to the police officer making`
  line `investigation into the offence, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the said period, the day from which such period is to be computed shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_515_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_516:
  sectionId (91499)
  sectionNo (516)
  orderNo 516
  title `Exclusion of time in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_516_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_516_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91499&sectionno=516&orderno=516&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_516_content:
  string
  line `(1) In computing the period of limitation, the time during`
  line `which any person has been prosecuting with due diligence another prosecution, whether in a Court of first`
  line `instance or in a Court of appeal or revision, against the offender, shall be excluded:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such exclusion shall be made unless the prosecution relates to the same facts and is`
  line `prosecuted in good faith in a Court which from defect of jurisdiction or other cause of a like nature, is`
  line `unable to entertain it.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the institution of the prosecution in respect of an offence has been stayed by an injunction`
  line `or order, then, in computing the period of limitation, the period of the continuance of the injunction or order,`
  line `the day on which it was issued or made, and the day on which it was withdrawn, shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(3) Where notice of prosecution for an offence has been given, or where, under any law for the time`
  line `being in force, the previous consent or sanction of the Government or any other authority is required for`
  line `the institution of any prosecution for an offence, then, in computing the period of limitation, the period of`
  line `such notice or, as the case may be, the time required for obtaining such consent or sanction shall be`
  line excluded.
  line
  line `Explanation.---In computing the time required for obtaining the consent or sanction of the Government`
  line `or any other authority, the date on which the application was made for obtaining the consent or sanction`
  line `and the date of receipt of the order of the Government or other authority shall both be excluded.`
  line
  line `(4) In computing the period of limitation, the time during which the offender---`
  line
  line `(a) has been absent from India or from any territory outside India which is under the administration`
  line `of the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) has avoided arrest by absconding or concealing himself,`
  line
  line `shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_516_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_517:
  sectionId (91500)
  sectionNo (517)
  orderNo 517
  title `Exclusion of date on which Court is closed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_517_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_517_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91500&sectionno=517&orderno=517&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_517_content:
  string
  line `Where the period of limitation expires on a day`
  line `when the Court is closed, the Court may take cognizance on the day on which the Court reopens.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---A Court shall be deemed to be closed on any day within the meaning of this section, if,`
  line `during its normal working hours, it remains closed on that day.`
obj_root_law_sections_517_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_518:
  sectionId (91501)
  sectionNo (518)
  orderNo 518
  title `Continuing offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_518_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_518_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91501&sectionno=518&orderno=518&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_518_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a continuing offence, a fresh period of limitation shall begin`
  line `to run at every moment of the time during which the offence continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_518_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_519:
  sectionId (91502)
  sectionNo (519)
  orderNo 519
  title `Extension of period of limitation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_519_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_519_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91502&sectionno=519&orderno=519&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_519_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Chapter, any Court may take cognizance of an offence after the expiry of the`
  line `period of limitation, if it is satisfied on the facts and in the circumstances of the case that the delay has been`
  line `properly explained or that it is necessary so to do in the interests of justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_519_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_520:
  sectionId (91503)
  sectionNo (520)
  orderNo 520
  title `Trials before High Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_520_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_520_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91503&sectionno=520&orderno=520&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_520_content:
  string
  line `When an offence is tried by the High Court otherwise than under`
  line `section 447, it shall, in the trial of the offence, observe the same procedure as a Court of Sessions would`
  line `observe if it were trying the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_520_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_521:
  sectionId (91504)
  sectionNo (521)
  orderNo 521
  title `Delivery to commanding officers of persons liable to be tried by Court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_521_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_521_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91504&sectionno=521&orderno=521&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_521_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government may make rules consistent with this Sanhita and the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950),`
  line `the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950), the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957), and any other law, relating to the Armed`
  line `Forces of the Union, for the time being in force, as to cases in which persons subject to army, naval or airforce law, or such other law, shall be tried by a Court to which this Sanhita applies, or by a Court-martial;`
  line `and when any person is brought before a Magistrate and charged with an offence for which he is liable to`
  line `be tried either by a Court to which this Sanhita applies or by a Court-martial, such Magistrate shall have`
  line `regard to such rules, and shall in proper cases deliver him, together with a statement of the offence of which`
  line `he is accused, to the commanding officer of the unit to which he belongs, or to the commanding officer of`
  line `the nearest army, naval or air-force station, as the case may be, for the purpose of being tried by a Courtmartial.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---In this section---`
  line
  line `(a) "unit" includes a regiment, corps, ship, detachment, group, battalion or company;`
  line
  line `(b) "Court-martial" includes any Tribunal with the powers similar to those of a Court-martial`
  line `constituted under the relevant law applicable to the Armed Forces of the Union.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Magistrate shall, on receiving a written application for that purpose by the commanding`
  line `officer of any unit or body of soldiers, sailors or airmen stationed or employed at any such place, use his`
  line `utmost endeavours to apprehend and secure any person accused of such offence.`
  line
  line `(3) A High Court may, if it thinks fit, direct that a prisoner detained in any jail situate within the State`
  line `be brought before a Court-martial for trial or to be examined touching any matter pending before the Courtmartial.`
obj_root_law_sections_521_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_522:
  sectionId (91505)
  sectionNo (522)
  orderNo 522
  title Forms.
  content obj_root_law_sections_522_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_522_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91505&sectionno=522&orderno=522&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_522_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the power conferred by article 227 of the Constitution, the forms set forth in`
  line `the Second Schedule, with such variations as the circumstances of each case require, may be used for the`
  line `respective purposes therein mentioned, and if used shall be sufficient.`
obj_root_law_sections_522_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_523:
  sectionId (91506)
  sectionNo (523)
  orderNo 523
  title `Power of High Court to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_523_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_523_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91506&sectionno=523&orderno=523&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_523_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every High Court may, with the previous approval of`
  line `the State Government, make rules---`
  line
  line `(a) as to the persons who may be permitted to act as petition-writers in the Criminal Courts`
  line `subordinate to it;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the issue of licences to such persons, the conduct of business by them, and the scale`
  line `of fees to be charged by them;`
  line
  line `(c) providing a penalty for a contravention of any of the rules so made and determining the authority`
  line `by which such contravention may be investigated and the penalties imposed;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, provided by rules made by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) All rules made under this section shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_523_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_524:
  sectionId (91507)
  sectionNo (524)
  orderNo 524
  title `Power to alter functions allocated to Executive Magistrate in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_524_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_524_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91507&sectionno=524&orderno=524&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_524_content:
  string
  line `If the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of a State by a resolution so permits, the State Government may, after consultation with the High`
  line `Court, by notification, direct that references in sections 127, 128, 129, 164 and 166 to an Executive`
  line `Magistrate shall be construed as references to a Judicial Magistrate of the first class.`
obj_root_law_sections_524_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_525:
  sectionId (91508)
  sectionNo (525)
  orderNo 525
  title `Cases in which Judge or Magistrate is personally interested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_525_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_525_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91508&sectionno=525&orderno=525&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_525_content:
  string
  line `No Judge or Magistrate shall,`
  line `except with the permission of the Court to which an appeal lies from his Court, try or commit for trial any`
  line `case to or in which he is a party, or personally interested, and no Judge or Magistrate shall hear an appeal`
  line `from any judgment or order passed or made by himself.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---A Judge or Magistrate shall not be deemed to be a party to, or personally interested in,`
  line `any case by reason only that he is concerned therein in a public capacity, or by reason only that he has`
  line `viewed the place in which an offence is alleged to have been committed, or any other place in which any`
  line `other transaction material to the case is alleged to have occurred, and made an inquiry in connection with`
  line `the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_525_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_526:
  sectionId (91509)
  sectionNo (526)
  orderNo 526
  title `Practising advocate not to sit as Magistrate in certain Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_526_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_526_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91509&sectionno=526&orderno=526&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_526_content:
  string
  line `No advocate who practices in`
  line `the Court of any Magistrate shall sit as a Magistrate in that Court or in any Court within the local jurisdiction`
  line `of that Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_526_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_527:
  sectionId (91510)
  sectionNo (527)
  orderNo 527
  title `Public servant concerned in sale not to purchase or bid for property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_527_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_527_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91510&sectionno=527&orderno=527&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_527_content:
  string
  line `A public servant having`
  line `any duty to perform in connection with the sale of any property under this Sanhita shall not purchase or bid`
  line `for the property.`
obj_root_law_sections_527_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_528:
  sectionId (91511)
  sectionNo (528)
  orderNo 528
  title `Saving of inherent powers of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_528_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_528_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91511&sectionno=528&orderno=528&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_528_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Sanhita shall be deemed to limit or`
  line `affect the inherent powers of the High Court to make such orders as may be necessary to give effect to any`
  line `order under this Sanhita, or to prevent abuse of the process of any Court or otherwise to secure the ends of`
  line justice.
obj_root_law_sections_528_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_529:
  sectionId (91512)
  sectionNo (529)
  orderNo 529
  title `Duty of High Court to exercise continuous superintendence over Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_529_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_529_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91512&sectionno=529&orderno=529&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_529_content:
  string
  line `Every High Court`
  line `shall so exercise its superintendence over the Courts of Session and Courts of Judicial Magistrates`
  line `subordinate to it as to ensure that there is an expeditious and proper disposal of cases by the Judges and`
  line Magistrates.
obj_root_law_sections_529_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_530:
  sectionId (91513)
  sectionNo (530)
  orderNo 530
  title `Trial and proceedings to be held in electronic mode.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_530_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_530_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91513&sectionno=530&orderno=530&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_530_content:
  string
  line `All trials, inquires and proceedings under`
  line `this Sanhita, including---`
  line
  line `(i) issuance, service and execution of summons and warrant;`
  line
  line `(ii) examination of complainant and witnesses;`
  line
  line `(iii) recording of evidence in inquiries and trials; and`
  line
  line `(iv) all appellate proceedings or any other proceeding,`
  line
  line `may be held in electronic mode, by use of electronic communication or use of audio-video electronic means.`
obj_root_law_sections_530_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_531:
  sectionId (91514)
  sectionNo (531)
  orderNo 531
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_531_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_531_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687&sectionId=91514&sectionno=531&orderno=531&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00049_202346_1719552320687
obj_root_law_sections_531_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal---`
  line
  line `(a) if, immediately before the date on which this Sanhita comes into force, there is any appeal,`
  line `application, trial, inquiry or investigation pending, then, such appeal, application, trial, inquiry or`
  line `investigation shall be disposed of, continued, held or made, as the case may be, in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), as in force immediately before such`
  line `commencement (hereinafter referred to as the said Code), as if this Sanhita had not come into force;`
  line
  line `(b) all notifications published, proclamations issued, powers conferred, forms provided by rules,`
  line `local jurisdictions defined, sentences passed and orders, rules and appointments, not being`
  line `appointments as Special Magistrates, made under the said Code and which are in force immediately`
  line `before the commencement of this Sanhita, shall be deemed, respectively, to have been published,`
  line `issued, conferred, specified, defined, passed or made under the corresponding provisions of this`
  line Sanhita;
  line
  line `(c) any sanction accorded or consent given under the said Code in pursuance of which no`
  line `proceeding was commenced under that Code, shall be deemed to have been accorded or given under`
  line `the corresponding provisions of this Sanhita and proceedings may be commenced under this Sanhita in`
  line `pursuance of such sanction or consent.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the period specified for an application or other proceeding under the said Code had expired`
  line `on or before the commencement of this Sanhita, nothing in this Sanhita shall be construed as enabling any`
  line `such application to be made or proceeding to be commenced under this Sanhita by reason only of the fact`
  line `that a longer period therefor is specified by this Sanhita or provisions are made in this Sanhita for the`
  line `extension of time.`
obj_root_law_sections_531_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
